site:groundtemperature:undisturbed:kusud.name: Site:GroundTemperature:Undisturbed:KusudaAchenbach
site:groundtemperature:undisturbed:kusud.memo: Undisturbed ground temperature object using the Kusuda-Achenbach 1965 correlation.

fields.name: Average Soil Surface Temperature
fields.memo: Annual average surface temperature If left blank the Site:GroundTemperature:Shallow object must be included in the input The soil temperature, amplitude, and phase shift must all be included or omitted together

fields.name: Average Amplitude of Surface Temperature
fields.memo: Annual average surface temperature variation from average. If left blank the Site:GroundTemperature:Shallow object must be included in the input The soil temperature, amplitude, and phase shift must all be included or omitted together

fields.name: Phase Shift of Minimum Surface Temperature
fields.memo: The phase shift of minimum surface temperature, or the day of the year when the minimum surface temperature occurs. If left blank the Site:GroundTemperature:Shallow object must be included in the input The soil temperature, amplitude, and phase shift must all be included or omitted together

groundheattransfer:basement:manualgrid.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:ManualGrid
groundheattransfer:basement:manualgrid.memo: Manual Grid only necessary using manual gridding (not recommended)

fields.name: NX: Number of cells in the X direction: 20]
NY: Number of cells in the Y direction: 20]
NZAG: Number of cells in the Z direction. above grade: 4 Always]
NZBG: Number of cells in Z direction. below grade: 10-35]
IBASE: X direction cell indicator of slab edge: 5-20]
JBASE: Y direction cell indicator of slab edge: 5-20]
KBASE: Z direction cell indicator of the top of the floor slab: 5-20]

zonecontrol:thermostat.name: ZoneControl:Thermostat
zonecontrol:thermostat.memo: Define the Thermostat settings for a zone or list of zones. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Control Type Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains appropriate control types for thermostat. Control types are integers: 0 - Uncontrolled (floating, no thermostat), 1 = ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeating, 2 = ThermostatSetpoint:SingleCooling, 3 = ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeatingOrCooling, 4 = ThermostatSetpoint:DualSetpoint

fields.name: Control 1 Name
fields.memo: Control names are names of individual control objects (e.g. ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeating) Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Control 2 Name
fields.memo: Control names are names of individual control objects (e.g. ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeating) Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Control 3 Name
fields.memo: Control names are names of individual control objects (e.g. ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeating) Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Control 4 Name
fields.memo: Control names are names of individual control objects (e.g. ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeating) Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Temperature Difference Between Cutout And Setpoint
fields.memo: This optional choice field provides a temperature difference between cut-out temperature and setpoint. The difference is used to adjust to heating or cooling setpoint based on control types.

hvactemplate:plant:boiler.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:Boiler
hvactemplate:plant:boiler.memo: This object adds a boiler to an HVACTemplate:Plant:HotWaterLoop or MixedWaterLoop.

fields.name: Efficiency
fields.memo: Not applicable  if Boiler Type is DistrictHotWater

fields.name: Fuel Type
fields.memo: Not applicable  if Boiler Type is DistrictHotWater

fields.name: Priority
fields.memo: If Hot Water Plant Operation Scheme Type=Default in HVACTemplate:Plant:HotWaterLoop, then equipment operates in priority order, 1, 2, 3, etc.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Template Plant Loop Type
fields.memo: Specifies if this boiler serves a template hot water loop or mixed water loop If left blank, will serve a hot water loop if present, or a mixed water loop (if no hot water loop is present).

faultmodel:fouling:coolingtower.name: FaultModel:Fouling:CoolingTower
faultmodel:fouling:coolingtower.memo: This object describes the fault of fouling cooling towers

fields.name: Cooling Tower Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of the cooling tower affected

fields.name: Cooling Tower Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the cooling tower affected

fields.name: Reference UA Reduction Factor
fields.memo: Factor describing the tower UA reduction due to fouling It is the ratio between the UA value at fouling case and that at fault free case It is applicable to both the Design UA and Free Convection UA of the tower

schedule:file.name: Schedule:File
schedule:file.memo: A Schedule:File points to a text computer file that has 8760-8784 hours of data.

fields.name: Number of Hours of Data
fields.memo: 8760 hours does not account for leap years, 8784 does. should be either 8760 or 8784

fields.name: Interpolate to Timestep
fields.memo: when the interval does not match the user specified timestep a "Yes" choice will average between the intervals request (to timestep resolution.  a "No" choice will use the interval value at the simulation timestep without regard to if it matches the boundary or not.

fields.name: Minutes per Item
fields.memo: Must be evenly divisible into 60

electricloadcenter:inverter:lookuptable.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Inverter:LookUpTable
electricloadcenter:inverter:lookuptable.memo: California Energy Commission tests and publishes data on inverters This inverter model interpolates using CEC test data Input data are at http://www.gosolarcalifornia.org/equipment/inverter_tests/summaries

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter name of zone to receive inverter losses as heat if blank then inverter is assumed to be outdoors

fields.name: Efficiency at 10% Power and Nominal Voltage
Efficiency at 20% Power and Nominal Voltage
Efficiency at 30% Power and Nominal Voltage
Efficiency at 50% Power and Nominal Voltage
Efficiency at 75% Power and Nominal Voltage
Efficiency at 100% Power and Nominal Voltage

curve:quadraticlinear.name: Curve:QuadraticLinear
curve:quadraticlinear.memo: Quadratic-linear curve with two independent variables. Input consists of the curve name, the six coefficients, and min and max values for each of the independent variables. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = (C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2) + (C4 + C5*x + C6*x**2)*y

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitExport:From:Variable
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.memo: This object declares an FMU input variable

fan:variablevolume.name: Fan:VariableVolume
fan:variablevolume.memo: Variable air volume fan where the electric power input varies according to a performance curve as a function of flow fraction.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Fan Power Minimum Flow Rate Input Method
Fan Power Minimum Air Flow Rate
Motor In Airstream Fraction
fields.memo: 0.0 means fan motor outside of air stream, 1.0 means motor inside of air stream

fields.name: Fan Power Coefficient 1
fields.memo: all Fan Power Coefficients should not be 0.0 or no fan power will be consumed. Fan Power Coefficents are specified as function of full flow rate/power Equation:

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

setpointmanager:scheduled:dualsetpoint.name: SetpointManager:Scheduled:DualSetpoint
setpointmanager:scheduled:dualsetpoint.memo: This setpoint manager places a high and low schedule value on one or more nodes.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which temperature will be set

pipe:outdoor.name: Pipe:Outdoor
pipe:outdoor.memo: Pipe model with transport delay and heat transfer to the environment.

fields.name: Ambient Temperature Outdoor Air Node Name

energymanagementsystem:internalvariable.name: EnergyManagementSystem:InternalVariable
energymanagementsystem:internalvariable.memo: Declares EMS variable as an internal data variable

availabilitymanager:optimumstart.name: AvailabilityManager:OptimumStart
availabilitymanager:optimumstart.memo: Determines the optimal start of HVAC systems before occupancy.

fields.name: Maximum Value for Optimum Start Time
fields.memo: this is the maximum number of hours that a system can start before occupancy

fields.name: Constant Start Time
fields.memo: this is the number of hours before occupancy for a system

fields.name: Number of Previous Days
fields.memo: this is the number of days that their actual temperature gradients will be used in the AdaptiveTemperatureGradient method

gasequipment.name: GasEquipment
gasequipment.memo: Sets internal gains and contaminant rates for gas equipment in the zone. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone name field then this definition applies to all those zones.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in Schedule should be fraction applied to design level of gas equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Design Level Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of gas equipment for this set of attributes Choices: EquipmentLevel => Design Level -- simply enter power input of equipment Watts/Area or Power/Area => Power per Zone Floor Area -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Floor Area = Equipment Level Watts/Person or Power/Person => Power per Person -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Occupants = Equipment Level

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Generation Rate
fields.memo: CO2 generation rate per unit of power input The default value assumes the equipment is fully vented. For unvented equipment, a suggested value is 3.45E-8 m3/s-W. This value is converted from a natural gas CO2 emission rate of 117 lbs CO2 per million Btu. The maximum value assumes to be 10 times of the recommended value.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

exterior:fuelequipment.name: Exterior:FuelEquipment
exterior:fuelequipment.memo: only used for Meter type reporting, does not affect building loads

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in schedule should be fraction applied to capacity of the exterior fuel equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

roomair:temperaturepattern:userdefined.name: RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:UserDefined
roomair:temperaturepattern:userdefined.memo: Used to explicitly define temperature patterns that are to be applied to the mean air temperature within a thermal zone.  Used with RoomAirModelType = UserDefined.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this model. Schedule value > 0 means the model is active. Schedule value = 0 means the model is inactive and the zone will be modeled as fully mixed (Mixing). If this field is blank, the model is always active.

fields.name: Pattern Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule should contain integer values that correspond to unique Control Integer fields in one of the RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:* objects.

wateruse:raincollector.name: WaterUse:RainCollector
wateruse:raincollector.memo: Used for harvesting rainwater falling on building surfaces. The rainwater is sent to a WaterUse:Storage object. In order to use this object it is necessary to also include a Site:Precipitation object to describe the rates of rainfall.

fields.name: Collection Loss Factor
fields.memo: this is the portion of rain that is lost in the process of collecting it the rain collected is one minus this factor

fields.name: Maximum Collection Rate
fields.memo: Defaults to unlimited flow.

airterminal:dualduct:constantvolume.name: AirTerminal:DualDuct:ConstantVolume
airterminal:dualduct:constantvolume.memo: Central air system terminal unit, dual duct, constant volume.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The outlet node of the terminal unit. This is also the zone inlet node.

zonehvac:unitheater.name: ZoneHVAC:UnitHeater
zonehvac:unitheater.memo: Unit heater. Forced-convection heating-only unit with supply fan, heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam) and fixed-position outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Allowable fan types are Fan:ConstantVolume, Fan:OnOff, Fan:VariableVolume and Fan:SystemModel

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule name values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with the heating coil). Schedule values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this input field is left blank.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operation During No Heating
fields.memo: This choice field allows the user to define how the unit heater will operate under "no heating load" or cooling conditions. If the "No" is selected, then the fan will not run unless there is a heating load. If the fan does not run, this effectively shuts the unit heater system off when there is no heating load. If the "Yes" is selected, the unit heater is available and has a ConstantVolume fan, or has an OnOff fan with "Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule" value greater than zero, then the fan will always run regardless of the zone load.

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when heating coil is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when heating coil is gas or electric

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

fields.name: Reference Coefficient of Performance
fields.memo: This optional field is used to autosize Reference Heating Power Consumption COP = Reference Heating Capacity / Reference Heating Power Consumption

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

ceiling:adiabatic.name: Ceiling:Adiabatic
ceiling:adiabatic.memo: Allows for simplified entry of interior ceilings.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of Ceiling

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Ceilings are usually tilted 0 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: If not Flat, Starting coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Ceiling

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: Along X Axis

fields.name: Width
fields.memo: Along Y Axis

thermostatsetpoint:dualsetpoint.name: ThermostatSetpoint:DualSetpoint
thermostatsetpoint:dualsetpoint.memo: Used for a heating and cooling thermostat with dual setpoints. The setpoints can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation for both heating and cooling.

glazeddoor:interzone.name: GlazedDoor:Interzone
glazeddoor:interzone.memo: Allows for simplified entry of interzone (glass interior) doors (adjacent to other zones).

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Building Surface Name
fields.memo: Name of Surface (Wall, usually) the Door is on (i.e., Base Surface) Door assumes the azimuth and tilt angles of the surface it is on.

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Specify a surface name in an adjacent zone for known interior doors. Specify a zone name of an adjacent zone to automatically generate the interior door in the adjacent zone. a blank field will set up a Window in an adjacent zone (same zone as adjacent to base surface)

fields.name: Multiplier
fields.memo: Used only for Surface Type = WINDOW, GLASSDOOR or DOOR Non-integer values will be truncated to integer

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Door starting coordinate is specified relative to the Base Surface origin.

fields.name: Starting Z Coordinate
fields.memo: How far up the wall the Door starts. (in 2-d, this would be a Y Coordinate)

refrigeration:transferloadlist.name: Refrigeration:TransferLoadList
refrigeration:transferloadlist.memo: A refrigeration system may provide cooling to other, secondary, systems through either a secondary loop or a cascade condenser. If multiple transfer loads are served by a single primary system, use this list to group them together for reference by the primary system (see the field "Refrigeration Transfer Load or TransferLoad List Name" in the Refrigeration:System object).

plantequipmentoperation:outdoorwetbulbdi.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorWetBulbDifference
plantequipmentoperation:outdoorwetbulbdi.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor wet-bulb temperature difference operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive ranges based the difference between a reference node temperature and the outdoor wet-bulb temperature.

fields.name: Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 1 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 1 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 2 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 2 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 3 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 3 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 4 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 4 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 5 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 5 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 6 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 6 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 7 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 7 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 8 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 8 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 9 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 9 Upper Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 10 Lower Limit
Wet-Bulb Temperature Difference Range 10 Upper Limit

coil:cooling:dx:singlespeed.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:SingleSpeed
coil:cooling:dx:singlespeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and condensing unit (includes electric compressor and condenser fan), single-speed. Optional inputs for moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total cooling capacity, Rated SHR and Rated COP should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total cooling capacity

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Fan Power Per Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the evaporator fan power per air volume flow rate at the rated test conditions. The test conditions vary external static pressure based on total cooling capacity. This value is only used to calculate Seasonal Energy Efficiency Ratio (SEER), Energy Efficiency Ratio (EER), Integrated Energy Efficiency Ratio (IEER), and the Standard Rating (Net) Cooling Capacity which will be outputs in the EnergyPlus eio file.  This value is not used for modeling the evaporator fan during simulations.

fields.name: Total Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Total Cooling Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = Fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = Fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Nominal Time for Condensate Removal to Begin
fields.memo: The nominal time for condensate to begin leaving the coil's condensate drain line at the coil's rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Nominal time is equal to the ratio of the energy of the coil's maximum condensate holding capacity (J) to the coil's steady state latent capacity (W). Suggested value is 1000; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Ratio of Initial Moisture Evaporation Rate and Steady State Latent Capacity
fields.memo: Ratio of the initial moisture evaporation rate from the cooling coil (when the compressor first turns off) and the coil's steady state latent capacity at rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Suggested value is 1.5; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: The maximum on-off cycling Rate for the compressor, which occurs at 50% run time fraction. Suggested value is 3; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Latent Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: Time constant for the cooling coil's latent capacity to reach steady state after startup. Suggested value is 45; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*wb*db wb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) db = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) entering temperature can be outside air or pretreated air.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Report ASHRAE Standard 127 Performance Ratings
fields.memo: when this input field is specified as Yes then the program calculates the net cooling capacity and total electric power input of DX cooling coils per ANSI/ASHRAE 127.

fields.name: Zone Name for Condenser Placement
fields.memo: This input field is name of a conditioned or unconditioned zone where the secondary coil (condenser) of DX system or a heat pump is to be placed.  This is an optional input field specified only when user desires to reject the condenser heat into a zone. The heat rejected is modelled as internal sensible heat gain of the zone.

simulationcontrol.name: SimulationControl
simulationcontrol.memo: Note that the following 3 fields are related to the Sizing:Zone, Sizing:System, and Sizing:Plant objects.  Having these fields set to Yes but no corresponding Sizing object will not cause the sizing to be done. However, having any of these fields set to No, the corresponding Sizing object is ignored. Note also, if you want to do system sizing, you must also do zone sizing in the same run or an error will result.

fields.name: Do Zone Sizing Calculation
fields.memo: If Yes, Zone sizing is accomplished from corresponding Sizing:Zone objects and autosize fields.

fields.name: Do System Sizing Calculation
fields.memo: If Yes, System sizing is accomplished from corresponding Sizing:System objects and autosize fields. If Yes, Zone sizing (previous field) must also be Yes.

fields.name: Do Plant Sizing Calculation
fields.memo: If Yes, Plant sizing is accomplished from corresponding Sizing:Plant objects and autosize fields.

fields.name: Run Simulation for Sizing Periods
fields.memo: If Yes, SizingPeriod:* objects are executed and results from those may be displayed..

fields.name: Run Simulation for Weather File Run Periods
fields.memo: If Yes, RunPeriod:* objects are executed and results from those may be displayed..

fields.name: Do HVAC Sizing Simulation for Sizing Periods
fields.memo: If Yes, SizingPeriod:* objects are exectuted additional times for advanced sizing. Currently limited to use with coincident plant sizing, see Sizing:Plant object

fields.name: Maximum Number of HVAC Sizing Simulation Passes
fields.memo: the entire set of SizingPeriod:* objects may be repeated to fine tune size results this input sets a limit on the number of passes that the sizing algorithms can repeate the set

site:groundtemperature:undisturbed:finit.name: Site:GroundTemperature:Undisturbed:FiniteDifference
site:groundtemperature:undisturbed:finit.memo: Undisturbed ground temperature object using a detailed finite difference 1-D model

fields.name: Soil Moisture Content Volume Fraction at Saturation
Evapotranspiration Ground Cover Parameter
fields.memo: This specifies the ground cover effects during evapotranspiration calculations.  The value roughly represents the following cases: = 0   : concrete or other solid, non-permeable ground surface material = 0.5 : short grass, much like a manicured lawn = 1   : standard reference state (12 cm grass) = 1.5 : wild growth

chiller:enginedriven.name: Chiller:EngineDriven
chiller:enginedriven.memo: This chiller model is the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Chiller performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to third order polynomial equations.  Three sets of coefficients are required.

fields.name: Nominal COP
fields.memo: Nominal Refrigeration Cycle COP

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the maximum flow and for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is not used for Condenser Type = AirCooled or EvaporativelyCooled

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 2 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 3 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Chilled Water Outlet Temperature Lower Limit
fields.memo: Special EngineDriven Chiller Parameters Below

fields.name: Fuel Use Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve is a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of evaporator heat transfer rate to nominal capacity

fields.name: Jacket Heat Recovery Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve is a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of evaporator heat transfer rate to nominal capacity

fields.name: Lube Heat Recovery Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve is a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of evaporator heat transfer rate to nominal capacity

fields.name: Total Exhaust Energy Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve is a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of evaporator heat transfer rate to nominal capacity

fields.name: Exhaust Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve is a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of evaporator heat transfer rate to nominal capacity

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: curve = C1 * (nominal capacity)**C2

fields.name: Coefficient 2 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: curve = C1 * (nominal capacity)**C2 typical value .9

fields.name: Maximum Exhaust Flow per Unit of Power Output
Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered.

fields.name: Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Maximum Temperature for Heat Recovery at Heat Recovery Outlet Node
Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the chiller is not operating.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Condenser Heat Recovery Relative Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This optional field is the fraction of total rejected heat that can be recovered at full load. Also used to autosize Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate as a fraction of Design Condenser Water Flow Rate.

construction:windowequivalentlayer.name: Construction:WindowEquivalentLayer
construction:windowequivalentlayer.memo: Start with outside layer and work your way to the inside Layer Up to 11 layers total. Up to six solid layers and up to five gaps. Enter the material name for each layer

fan:systemmodel.name: Fan:SystemModel
fan:systemmodel.memo: Versatile simple fan that can be used in variable air volume, constant volume, on-off cycling, two-speed or multi-speed applications. Performance at different flow rates, or speed levels, is determined using separate performance curve or table or prescribed power fractions at discrete speed levels for two-speed or multi-speed fans.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this fan. Schedule value > 0 means the fan is available. If this field is blank, the fan is always available.

fields.name: Electric Power Minimum Flow Rate Fraction
Motor In Air Stream Fraction
fields.memo: 0.0 means fan motor outside of air stream, 1.0 means motor inside of air stream

fields.name: Design Electric Power Consumption
fields.memo: Fan power consumption at maximum air flow rate. If autosized the method used to scale power is chosen in the following field

fields.name: Electric Power Per Unit Flow Rate
Electric Power Per Unit Flow Rate Per Unit Pressure
Electric Power Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: independent variable is normalized flow rate, current flow divided by Design Maximum Air Flow Rate. dependent variable is modification factor multiplied by Design Power Consumption. This field is required if Speed Control Method is set to Continuous or if the Number of Speeds is greater than 1 and Speed Electric Power Fraction fields are not used.

fields.name: Night Ventilation Mode Pressure Rise
fields.memo: Total system fan pressure rise at the fan when in night mode using AvailabilityManager:NightVentilation

fields.name: Night Ventilation Mode Flow Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of Design Maximum Air Flow Rate to use when in night mode using AvailabilityManager:NightVentilation

fields.name: Motor Loss Zone Name
fields.memo: optional, if used fan motor heat losses that not added to air stream are transferred to zone as internal gains

fields.name: Motor Loss Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: optional. If zone identified in previous field then this determines the split between convection and radiation for the fan motor's skin losses

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Number of Speeds
fields.memo: number of different speed levels available when Speed Control Method is set to Discrete Speed need to be arranged in increasing order in remaining field sets. If set to 1, or omitted, and Speed Control Method is Discrete then constant fan speed is the design maximum.

refrigeration:walkin.name: Refrigeration:WalkIn
refrigeration:walkin.memo: Works in conjunction with a compressor rack, a refrigeration system, or a refrigeration secondary system to simulate the performance of a walk-in cooler. The walk-in cooler model uses information at rated conditions along with input descriptions for heat transfer surfaces facing multiple zones to determine performance.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Rated Cooling Source Temperature
fields.memo: If DXEvaporator, use evaporating temperature (saturated suction temperature) If BrineCoil, use Brine entering temperature used to set minimum suction pressure for DX systems and minimum brine temp for secondary systems

fields.name: Rated Total Heating Power
fields.memo: Include total for all anti-sweat, door, drip-pan, and floor heater power Do not include defrost heater power

fields.name: Heating Power Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values will be used to multiply the total heating power Values in the schedule should be between 0.0 and 1.0 For example, this could be used if display door antisweat heaters are turned off at night Defaults to always on if schedule name left blank.

fields.name: Rated Total Lighting Power
fields.memo: Enter the total (display + task) installed lighting power.

fields.name: Lighting Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule should contain values between 0 and 1 Defaults to always on if schedule name left blank.

fields.name: Defrost Type
fields.memo: HotFluid includes either hot gas defrost for a DX system or Hot Brine defrost if this walk in is cooled by brine from a secondary chiller

fields.name: Defrost Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule values should be 0 (off) or 1 (on)

fields.name: Defrost Drip-Down Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule values should be 0 (off) or 1 (on) The start time for each defrost period in this drip-down schedule should coincide with the start time for each defrost period in the defrost schedule (previous input field).The length of each defrost drip-down period must be greater than or equal to the corresponding defrost period specified in the defrost schedule. This extra time allows the melted frost to drip from the coil before refrigeration is restarted.

fields.name: Defrost Power
fields.memo: needed for all defrost types except none and offcycle

fields.name: Temperature Termination Defrost Fraction to Ice
fields.memo: This is the portion of the defrost energy that is available to melt frost Needed only for defrost control type TemperatureTermination defaults to 0.7 for electric defrost and to 0.3 for hot fluid defrost

fields.name: Restocking Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be in units of Watts Leave this field blank if no restocking is to be modeled

fields.name: Average Refrigerant Charge Inventory
fields.memo: This value is only used if the Cooling Source Type is DXEvaporator

fields.name: Insulated Floor Surface Area
fields.memo: floor area of walk-in cooler

fields.name: Insulated Floor U-Value
fields.memo: The default value corresponds to R18 [ft2-F-hr/Btu] To convert other IP R-values to U, divide 5.678 by the R-value Some examples: R15 is U 0.3785 W/m2-K R5 is U 1.136 W/m2-K

site:location.name: Site:Location
site:location.memo: Specifies the building's location. Only one location is allowed. Weather data file location, if it exists, will override this object.

fields.name: Latitude
fields.memo: + is North, - is South, degree minutes represented in decimal (i.e. 30 minutes is .5)

fields.name: Longitude
fields.memo: - is West, + is East, degree minutes represented in decimal (i.e. 30 minutes is .5)

fields.name: Time Zone
fields.memo: basic these limits on the WorldTimeZone Map (2003) Time relative to GMT. Decimal hours.

generator:internalcombustionengine.name: Generator:InternalCombustionEngine
generator:internalcombustionengine.memo: This generator model is the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Engine performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to second order polynomial equations.  Three sets of coefficients are required.

fields.name: Shaft Power Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output

fields.name: Jacket Heat Recovery Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output

fields.name: Lube Heat Recovery Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output

fields.name: Total Exhaust Energy Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output

fields.name: Exhaust Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: curve = C1 * Generator Rated Power Output**C2

fields.name: Coefficient 2 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: curve = C1 * Generator Rated Power Output**C2 typical value .9

fields.name: Maximum Exhaust Flow per Unit of Power Output
Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: if non-zero, then inlet, outlet nodes must be entered.

site:solarandvisiblespectrum.name: Site:SolarAndVisibleSpectrum
site:solarandvisiblespectrum.memo: If this object is omitted, the default solar and visible spectrum data will be used.

fields.name: Spectrum Data Method
fields.memo: The method specifies which of the solar and visible spectrum data to use in the calculations. Choices: Default - existing hard-wired spectrum data in EnergyPlus. UserDefined - user specified spectrum data referenced by the next two fields

foundation:kiva.name: Foundation:Kiva
foundation:kiva.memo: Refined definition of the foundation surface construction used to inform two-dimensional heat transfer calculated using the Kiva ground heat transfer methodology.

fields.name: Interior Horizontal Insulation Depth
fields.memo: Distance from the slab bottom to the top of interior horizontal insulation

fields.name: Interior Horizontal Insulation Width
fields.memo: Extent of insulation as measured from the wall interior

fields.name: Interior Vertical Insulation Depth
fields.memo: Extent of insulation as measured from the wall top to the bottom edge of the interior vertical insulation

fields.name: Exterior Horizontal Insulation Depth
fields.memo: Distance from the exterior grade to the top of exterior horizontal insulation

fields.name: Exterior Horizontal Insulation Width
fields.memo: Extent of insulation as measured from the wall exterior

fields.name: Exterior Vertical Insulation Depth
fields.memo: Extent of insulation as measured from the wall top to the bottom edge of the exterior vertical insulation

fields.name: Wall Height Above Grade
fields.memo: Distance from the exterior grade to the wall top

fields.name: Wall Depth Below Slab
fields.memo: Distance from the slab bottom to the bottom of the foundation wall

fields.name: Footing Wall Construction Name
fields.memo: Defines the below-grade surface construction for slabs. Required if foundation wall is not exposed to the zone.

fields.name: Footing Depth
fields.memo: Top-to-bottom dimension of the footing (not to be confused with its depth in the ground). The width of the footing is defined by the material's thickness.

fanperformance:nightventilation.name: FanPerformance:NightVentilation
fanperformance:nightventilation.memo: Specifies an alternate set of performance parameters for a fan. These alternate parameters are used when a system manager (such as AvailabilityManager:NightVentilation) sets a specified flow rate.  May be used with any type of fan except not with Fan:ComponentModel. If the fan model senses that a fixed flow rate has been set, it will use these alternate performance parameters. It is assumed that the fan will run at a fixed speed in the alternate mode.

fields.name: Motor in Airstream Fraction
fields.memo: 0.0 means fan motor outside of airstream 1.0 means fan motor inside of airstream

material:nomass.name: Material:NoMass
material:nomass.memo: Regular materials properties described whose principal description is R (Thermal Resistance)

generator:fuelcell.name: Generator:FuelCell
generator:fuelcell.memo: This generator model is the FC model from IEA Annex 42

fields.name: Power Module Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:PowerModule object.

fields.name: Air Supply Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:AirSupply object.

fields.name: Fuel Supply Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelSupply object.

fields.name: Water Supply Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:WaterSupply object.

fields.name: Auxiliary Heater Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:AuxiliaryHeater object.

fields.name: Heat Exchanger Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:ExhaustGasToWaterHeatExchanger object.

fields.name: Electrical Storage Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:ElectricalStorage object.

fields.name: Inverter Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:Inverter object.

fields.name: Stack Cooler Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelCell:StackCooler object. optional, used for PEMFC

surfaceproperty:othersideconditionsmodel.name: SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel
surfaceproperty:othersideconditionsmodel.memo: This object sets up modifying the other side conditions for a surface from other model results.

fields.name: Type of Modeling
fields.memo: GapConvectionRadiation provides boundary conditions for convection and linearized thermal radiation across a gap or cavity on the other side of the surface that are modeled separately. UndergroundPipingSystemSurface provides boundary conditions for surfaces in contact with PipingSystem:Underground domains GroundCoupledSurface provides boundary conditions for surfaces in contact with GroundDomain objects ConvectiveUnderwater provides a connection between a surface and an underwater boundary condition defined using a SurfaceProperty:Underwater object

setpointmanager:warmest.name: SetpointManager:Warmest
setpointmanager:warmest.memo: This SetpointManager resets the cooling supply air temperature of a central forced air HVAC system according to the cooling demand of the warmest zone.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

airflownetwork:distribution:component:fa.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:Fan
airflownetwork:distribution:component:fa.memo: This object defines the name of the supply Air Fan used in an Air loop.

fields.name: Fan Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the fan in the primary air loop.

parametric:logic.name: Parametric:Logic
parametric:logic.memo: This object allows some types of objects to be included for some parametric cases and not for others. For example, you might want an overhang on a window in some parametric runs and not others. A single Parametric:Logic object is allowed per file. Consult the Input Output Reference for available commands and syntax.

generator:photovoltaic.name: Generator:Photovoltaic
generator:photovoltaic.memo: Describes an array of photovoltaic (PV) modules.  A series of different PV arrays can be connected to a single electric load center (and inverter) by listing them all in an ElectricLoadCenter:Generator object. PV performance is taken from the referenced PhotovoltaicPerformance:* object. Array tilt, azimuth, and gross area are taken from the referenced building surface or shading surface. The array surface participates normally in all shading calculations.

fields.name: Module Performance Name
fields.memo: PV array modeling details

fields.name: Number of Series Strings in Parallel
fields.memo: number of series-wired strings of PV modules that are in parallel

fields.name: Number of Modules in Series
fields.memo: Number of PV modules wired in series for each string.

thermostatsetpoint:singleheating.name: ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeating
thermostatsetpoint:singleheating.memo: Used for a heating only thermostat. The setpoint can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation but only heating is allowed with this control type.

availabilitymanager:lowtemperatureturnon.name: AvailabilityManager:LowTemperatureTurnOn
availabilitymanager:lowtemperatureturnon.memo: Overrides fan/pump schedules depending on temperature at sensor node.

roomair:node:airflownetwork.name: RoomAir:Node:AirflowNetwork
roomair:node:airflownetwork.memo: define an air node for some types of nodal air models

zonethermalchimney.name: ZoneThermalChimney
zonethermalchimney.memo: A thermal chimney is a vertical shaft utilizing solar radiation to enhance natural ventilation. It consists of an absorber wall, air gap and glass cover with high solar transmissivity.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of zone that is the thermal chimney

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Cross Sectional Area of Air Channel Outlet
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 1
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 1
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 1
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 2
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 2
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 2
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 3
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 3
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 3
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 4
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 4
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 4
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 5
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 5
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 5
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 6

Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 6
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 7

Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 7

Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 8
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 9
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 9
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 9
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 10
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 10
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 10
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 11
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 11
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 11
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 12
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 12
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 12
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 13
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 13
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 13
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 14
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 14
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 14
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 15
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 15
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 15
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 16
Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 16
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 16
Distance from Top of Thermal Chimney to Inlet 17

Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 18

Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 19

Relative Ratios of Air Flow Rates Passing through Zone 20
Cross Sectional Areas of Air Channel Inlet 20

airterminal:singleduct:userdefined.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:UserDefined
airterminal:singleduct:userdefined.memo: Defines a generic single duct air terminal unit for custom modeling using Energy Management System or External Interface

fields.name: Overall Model Simulation Program Calling Manager Name
Model Setup and Sizing Program Calling Manager Name
Primary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air inlet node for the unit must be a zone splitter outlet.

fields.name: Primary Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air outlet node for the unit must be a zone air inlet node.

fields.name: Secondary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Inlet air used for heat rejection or air source

fields.name: Secondary Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Outlet air used for heat rejection or air source

fields.name: Supply Inlet Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: Water use storage tank for alternate source of water consumed by device

fields.name: Collection Outlet Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: Water use storage tank for collection of condensate by device

fields.name: Ambient Zone Name
fields.memo: Used for modeling device losses to surrounding zone

airloophvac:unitaryheatcool.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatCool
airloophvac:unitaryheatcool.memo: Unitary system, heating and cooling with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling), direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam), and optional reheat coil for dehumidification control. Identical to AirLoopHVAC:Unitary:Furnace:HeatCool.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Unitary System Air Inlet Node Name
Unitary System Air Outlet Node Name
Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: A fan operating mode schedule value of 0 indicates cycling fan mode (supply air fan cycles on and off in tandem with the cooling or heating coil). Any other schedule value indicates continuous fan mode (supply air fan operates continuously regardless of cooling or heating coil operation). Provide a schedule with non-zero values when high humidity control is specified. Leaving this schedule name blank will default to cycling fan mode for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate. Only used when fan operating mode is continuous (disregarded for cycling fan mode). This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required (i.e., the DX coil compressor and heating coil are off). If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Supply Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works with continuous fan operating mode (i.e. supply air fan operating mode schedule values not equal to 0).

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with DX cooling coil types or Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableSpeed.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load.  Valid only with cooling coil type CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted. This control mode allows the heat exchanger to be turned on and off based on the zone dehumidification requirements. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required. CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint. as required to meet the humidity setpoint.  Valid with all cooling coil types. When a heat exchanger assisted Cooling coil is used, the heat exchanger is locked on at all times. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required.

fields.name: Reheat Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only required if dehumidification control type is "CoolReheat" works with gas, electric, desuperheating, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Reheat Coil Name
fields.memo: Only required if dehumidification control type is "CoolReheat"

shading:zone:detailed.name: Shading:Zone:Detailed
shading:zone:detailed.memo: used For fins, overhangs, elements that shade the building, are attached to the building but are not part of the heat transfer calculations

fields.name: Transmittance Schedule Name
fields.memo: Transmittance schedule for the shading device, defaults to zero (always opaque)

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 6 vertex coordinates -- extensible object vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- if relative, all surface coordinates are "relative" to the Zone Origin.  if world, then building and zone origins are used for some internal calculations, but all coordinates are given in an "absolute" system.

airflownetwork:distribution:node.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Node
airflownetwork:distribution:node.memo: This object represents an air distribution node in the AirflowNetwork model.

fields.name: Component Name or Node Name
fields.memo: Designates node names defined in another object. The node name may occur in air branches. Enter a node name to represent a node already defined in an air loop. Leave this field blank if the Node or Object Type field below is entered as AirLoopHVAC:ZoneMixer, AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter, AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem, or Other.

fields.name: Component Object Type or Node Type
fields.memo: Designates Node type for the Node or Component Name defined in the field above. AirLoopHVAC:ZoneMixer -- Represents a AirLoopHVAC:ZoneMixer object. AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter -- Represents a AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter object. AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem -- Represents an AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem object. OAMixerOutdoorAirStreamNode -- Represents an external node used in the OutdoorAir:Mixer OutdoorAir:NodeList -- Represents an external node when a heat exchanger is used before the OutdoorAir:Mixer OutdoorAir:Node -- Represents an external node when a heat exchanger is used before the OutdoorAir:Mixer Other -- none of the above, the Node name already defined in the previous field is part of an air loop.

fields.name: Node Height
fields.memo: Enter the reference height used to calculate the relative pressure.

airflownetwork:occupantventilationcontro.name: AirflowNetwork:OccupantVentilationControl
airflownetwork:occupantventilationcontro.memo: This object is used to provide advanced thermal comfort control of window opening and closing for both exterior and interior windows.

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Low Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents thermal comfort temperature as a function of outdoor dry-bulb temperature. Up to two curves are allowed if the performance cannot be represented by a single curve. The following two fields are used if two curves are required.

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Temperature Boundary Point
fields.memo: This point is used to allow separate low and high thermal comfort temperature curves. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Thermal Comfort High Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents thermal comfort temperature as a function of outdoor dry-bulb temperature. Up to two curves are allowed if the performance cannot be represented by a single curve. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Maximum Threshold for Persons Dissatisfied PPD
Occupancy Check
fields.memo: If Yes, occupancy check will be performed as part of the opening probability check.

fields.name: Opening Probability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the opening probability check is bypassed and opening is true.

fields.name: Closing Probability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the closing probability check is bypassed and closing is true.

output:table:monthly.name: Output:Table:Monthly
output:table:monthly.memo: Provides a generic method of setting up tables of monthly results. The report has multiple columns that are each defined using a repeated group of fields for any number of columns. A single Output:Table:Monthly object often produces multiple tables in the output. A table is produced for every instance of a particular output variable. For example, a table defined with zone variables will be produced once for every zone.

hvactemplate:thermostat.name: HVACTemplate:Thermostat
hvactemplate:thermostat.memo: Zone thermostat control.  Referenced schedules must be defined elsewhere in the idf.  Thermostat control type is dual setpoint with deadband.  It is not necessary to create a thermostat object for every zone, only for each unique set of setpoint schedules.  For example, an office building may have two thermostat objects, one for "Office" and one for "Storage".

fields.name: Heating Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint specified below, must enter schedule or constant setpoint

fields.name: Constant Heating Setpoint
fields.memo: Ignored if schedule specified above, must enter schedule or constant setpoint

fields.name: Cooling Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint specified below, must enter schedule or constant setpoint

fields.name: Constant Cooling Setpoint
fields.memo: Ignored if schedule specified above, must enter schedule or constant setpoint

version.name: Version
version.memo: Specifies the EnergyPlus version of the IDF file.

materialproperty:moisturepenetrationdept.name: MaterialProperty:MoisturePenetrationDepth:Settings
materialproperty:moisturepenetrationdept.memo: Additional properties for moisture using EMPD procedure HeatBalanceAlgorithm choice=MoisturePenetrationDepthConductionTransferFunction only Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms

fields.name: Water Vapor Diffusion Resistance Factor
fields.memo: Ratio of water vapor permeability of stagnant air to water vapor permeability of material

fields.name: Coating Layer Water Vapor Diffusion Resistance Factor
fields.memo: The coating's resistance to water vapor diffusion relative to the resistance to water vapor diffusion in stagnant air (see Water Vapor Diffusion Resistance Factor above).

hvactemplate:plant:hotwaterloop.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:HotWaterLoop
hvactemplate:plant:hotwaterloop.memo: Plant loop to serve all HVACTemplate hot water coils and boilers.

fields.name: Pump Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Hot Water Plant Operation Scheme Type
fields.memo: Default operation type makes all equipment available at all times operating in order of Priority specified in HVACTemplate:Plant:Boiler objects.

fields.name: Hot Water Plant Equipment Operation Schemes Name
fields.memo: Name of a PlantEquipmentOperationSchemes object Ignored if Plant Operation Scheme Type = Default

fields.name: Hot Water Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Hot Water Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Hot Water Pump Configuration
fields.memo: VariableFlow - variable flow to boilers and coils, excess bypassed ConstantFlow - constant flow to boilers and coils, excess bypassed

fields.name: Hot Water Pump Rated Head
fields.memo: Default head is 60 feet H2O

fields.name: Hot Water Setpoint Reset Type
fields.memo: Overrides Hot Water Setpoint Schedule Name

fields.name: Hot Water Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Hot Water Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Hot Water Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Hot Water Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Hot Water Pump Type
fields.memo: Describes the type of pump configuration used for the hot water loop.

fields.name: Supply Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a supply side bypass pipe is present in the hot water loop.

fields.name: Demand Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a demand side bypass pipe is present in the hot water loop.

fields.name: Loop Design Delta Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature difference used in sizing the loop flow rate.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: The maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature that the hot water loops operate. Leave blank for no limit.

roofirrigation.name: RoofIrrigation
roofirrigation.memo: Used to describe the amount of irrigation on the ecoroof surface over the course of the simulation runperiod.

fields.name: Irrigation Model Type
fields.memo: SmartSchedule will not allow irrigation when soil is already moist. Current threshold set at 30% of saturation.

fields.name: Irrigation Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values in meters of water per hour values should be non-negative

fields.name: Irrigation Maximum Saturation Threshold
fields.memo: Used with SmartSchedule to set the saturation level at which no irrigation is allowed.

heatexchanger:desiccant:balancedflow.name: HeatExchanger:Desiccant:BalancedFlow
heatexchanger:desiccant:balancedflow.memo: This object models a balanced desiccant heat exchanger. The heat exchanger transfers both sensible and latent energy between the process and regeneration air streams. The air flow rate and face velocity are assumed to be the same on both the process and regeneration sides of the heat exchanger.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Economizer Lockout
fields.memo: Yes means that the heat exchanger will be locked out (off) when the economizer is operating or high humidity control is active

airflownetwork:distribution:linkage.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Linkage
airflownetwork:distribution:linkage.memo: This object defines the connection between two nodes and a component.

fields.name: Node 1 Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of zone or AirflowNetwork Node.

fields.name: Node 2 Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of zone or AirflowNetwork Node.

fields.name: Component Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirflowNetwork component. A component is one of the following AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component objects: Leak, LeakageRatio, Duct, ConstantVolumeFan, Coil, TerminalUnit, ConstantPressureDrop, or HeatExchanger.

fields.name: Thermal Zone Name
fields.memo: Only used if component = AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:Duct The zone name is where AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:Duct is exposed. Leave this field blank if the duct conduction loss is ignored.

fields.name: FMU Timeout
fields.memo: in milli-seconds

windowmaterial:blind:equivalentlayer.name: WindowMaterial:Blind:EquivalentLayer
windowmaterial:blind:equivalentlayer.memo: Window equivalent layer blind slat optical and thermal properties. The model assumes that slats are thin and flat, applies correction empirical correlation to account for curvature effect. Slats are assumed to transmit and reflect diffusely.

fields.name: Slat Separation
fields.memo: Distance between adjacent slat faces

fields.name: Slat Crown
fields.memo: Perpendicular length between the cord and the curve. Slat is assumed to be rectangular in cross section and flat. Crown=0.0625x"Slat width"

fields.name: Slat Angle
fields.memo: Slat angle is +ve if the tip of the slat front face is tilted upward, else the slat angle is -ve if the tip of the slat front face is tilted downward. The slat angle varies between -90 to +90. The default value is 45 degrees.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar transmittance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar transmittance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar reflectance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar reflectance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse visible transmittance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse visible transmittance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse visible reflectance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Beam-Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse visible reflectance of the slat at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Slat Diffuse-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse solar transmittance of the slat averaged over the entire solar spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Diffuse-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar reflectance of the slat averaged over the entire solar spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Diffuse-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar reflectance of the slat averaged over the entire solar spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Slat Diffuse-Diffuse Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse visible transmittance of the slat averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Diffuse-Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse visible reflectance of the slat averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Diffuse-Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse visible reflectance of the slat averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation.

fields.name: Slat Infrared Transmittance
fields.memo: Long-wave hemispherical transmittance of the slat material. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the slat.

fields.name: Front Side Slat Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: Front side long-wave hemispherical emissivity of the slat material.

fields.name: Back Side Slat Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: Back side long-wave hemispherical emissivity of the slat material.

fields.name: Slat Angle Control
fields.memo: Used only if slat angle control is desired to either maximize solar gain (MaximizeSolar), maximize visibility while eliminating beam solar radiation (BlockBeamSolar), or fixed slate angle (FixedSlatAngle). If FixedSlatAngle is selected, the slat angle entered above is used.

coil:cooling:watertoairheatpump:paramete.name: Coil:Cooling:WaterToAirHeatPump:ParameterEstimation
coil:cooling:watertoairheatpump:paramete.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil for water-to-air heat pump (includes electric compressor), single-speed, parameter estimation model. Optional inputs for moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation. Parameter estimation model is a deterministic model that requires a consistent set of parameters to describe the operating conditions of the heat pump components.

fields.name: Compressor Type
fields.memo: Parameters 1-5 are as named below. Parameters 6-10 depend on the type of compressor and fluid. Refer to the InputOutputReference on the parameters required

fields.name: Nominal Time for Condensate Removal to Begin
fields.memo: The nominal time for condensate to begin leaving the coil's condensate drain line at the coil's rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Nominal time is equal to the ratio of the energy of the coil's maximum condensate holding capacity (J) to the coil's steady state latent capacity (W). Suggested value is 1000; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Ratio of Initial Moisture Evaporation Rate and Steady State Latent Capacity
fields.memo: Ratio of the initial moisture evaporation rate from the cooling coil (when the compressor first turns off) and the coil's steady state latent capacity at rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Suggested value is 1.5; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Load Side Total Heat Transfer Coefficient
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 1

fields.name: Load Side Outside Surface Heat Transfer Coefficient
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 2

fields.name: Superheat Temperature at the Evaporator Outlet
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 3

fields.name: Compressor Power Losses
fields.memo: Accounts for the loss of work due to mechanical and electrical losses in the compressor. Previously called Parameter 4

fields.name: Compressor Efficiency
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 5

fields.name: Compressor Piston Displacement
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Reciprocating or Rotary Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Scroll. Previously part of Parameter 6

fields.name: Compressor Suction/Discharge Pressure Drop
fields.memo: Used when Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Scroll. Previously part of Parameter 7

fields.name: Compressor Clearance Factor
fields.memo: Used when Compressor Type is Reciprocating. Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Scroll. Previously part of Parameter 8

fields.name: Refrigerant Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Scroll Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating. Previously part of Parameter 6

fields.name: Volume Ratio
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Scroll. Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating. Previously part of Parameter 7

fields.name: Leak Rate Coefficient
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Scroll. Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating. Previously part of Parameter 8

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Coefficient
fields.memo: Use when Source Side Fluid Name is Water Leave this field blank when Source Side Fluid Name is an antifreeze Previously part of Parameter 9

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Resistance1
fields.memo: Use when Source Side Fluid Name is an antifreeze Leave this field blank for Source Side Fluid is Water Previously part of Parameter 9

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Resistance2
fields.memo: Use when Source Side Fluid Name is an antifreeze Leave this field blank for Source Side Fluid is Water Previously part of Parameter 10

ceiling:interzone.name: Ceiling:Interzone
ceiling:interzone.memo: Allows for simplified entry of ceilings using adjacent zone (interzone) heat transfer - adjacent surface should be a floor

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone for the inside of the surface

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Specify a surface name in an adjacent zone for known interior floors Specify a zone name of an adjacent zone to automatically generate the interior floor in the adjacent zone.

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of wall (S=180,N=0,E=90,W=270)

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Ceilings are usually tilted 0 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: If not Flat, should be Lower Left Corner (from outside)

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: Along X Axis

fields.name: Width
fields.memo: Along Y Axis

electricequipment:ite:aircooled.name: ElectricEquipment:ITE:AirCooled
electricequipment:ite:aircooled.memo: This object describes air-cooled electric information technology equipment (ITE) which has variable power consumption as a function of loading and temperature.

fields.name: Air Flow Calculation Method
fields.memo: The specified method is used to calculate the IT inlet temperature and zone return air temperature. If FlowFromSystem is chosen, the zone is assumed to be well-mixed. If FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures is chosen, Supply and Return approach temperature should be defined to indicate the temperature difference due to the air distribution. When FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures is chosen, the inputs of Air Inlet Connection Type, Design Recirculation Fraction and Recirculation Function of Loading and Supply Temperature Curve Name are ignored. For multiple ITE objects defined for one zone, the same calculation method should apply. The FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures only applies to ITE zones with single duct VAV terminal unit. Other return air heat gains from window or lights are not allowed when FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures is chosen.

fields.name: Design Power Input Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to specify the design power input Watts/Unit => Watts per Unit -- Design Power = Watts per Unit * Number of Units Watts/Area => Watts per Zone Floor Area -- Design Power = Watts per Zone Floor Area * Floor Area

fields.name: Design Power Input Schedule Name
fields.memo: Operating schedule for this equipment, fraction applied to the design power input, generally (0.0 - 1.0) If this field is blank, the schedule is assumed to always be 1.0.

fields.name: CPU Loading  Schedule Name
fields.memo: CPU loading schedule for this equipment as a fraction from 0.0 (idle) to 1.0 (full load). If this field is blank, the schedule is assumed to always be 1.0.

fields.name: CPU Power Input Function of Loading and Air Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of a two-variable curve or table lookup object which modifies the CPU power input as a function of CPU loading (x) and air inlet node temperature (y). This curve (table) should equal 1.0 at design conditions (CPU loading = 1.0 and Design Entering Air Temperature).

fields.name: Design Fan Power Input Fraction
fields.memo: The fraction of the total power input at design conditions which is for the cooling fan(s)

fields.name: Design Fan Air Flow Rate per Power Input
fields.memo: The cooling fan air flow rate per total electric power input at design conditions
