fields.name: Air Flow Function of Loading and Air Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of a two-variable curve or table lookup object which modifies the cooling air flow rate as a function of CPU loading (x) and air inlet node temperature (y). This curve (table) should equal 1.0 at design conditions (CPU loading = 1.0 and Design Entering Air Temperature).

fields.name: Fan Power Input Function of Flow Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of a single-variable curve or table lookup object which modifies the cooling fan power as a function of flow fraction (x). This curve (table) should equal 1.0 at a flow fraction of 1.0.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Temperature
fields.memo: The entering air temperature at design conditions.

fields.name: Environmental Class
fields.memo: Specifies the allowable operating conditions for the air inlet conditions. Used for reporting time outside allowable conditions.

fields.name: Air Inlet Connection Type
fields.memo: Specifies the type of connection between the zone and the ITE air inlet node. AdjustedSupply = ITE inlet temperature will be the current Supply Air Node temperature adjusted by the current recirculation fraction. All heat output is added to the zone air heat balance as a convective gain. ZoneAirNode = ITE air inlet condition is  the average zone condition. All heat output is added to the zone air heat balance as a convective gain. RoomAirModel = ITE air inlet and outlet are connected to room air model nodes. This field is only used when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

fields.name: Air Inlet Room Air Model Node Name
fields.memo: Name of a RoomAir:Node object which is connected to the ITE air inlet.

fields.name: Air Outlet Room Air Model Node Name
fields.memo: Name of a RoomAir:Node object which is connected to the ITE air outlet.

fields.name: Supply Air Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the supply air inlet node serving this ITE. Required if the Air Node Connection Type = AdjustedSupply. Also required if Calculation Method = FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures. Also required if reporting of Supply Heat Index is desired.

fields.name: Design Recirculation Fraction
fields.memo: The recirculation fraction for this equipment at design conditions. This field is used only if the Air Node Connection Type = AdjustedSupply. The default is 0.0 (no recirculation). This field is only used when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

fields.name: Recirculation Function of Loading and Supply Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of a two-variable curve or table lookup object which modifies the recirculation fractionas a function of CPU loading (x) and supply air node temperature (y). This curve (table) should equal 1.0 at design conditions (CPU loading = 1.0 and Design Entering Air Temperature).This field is used only if the Air Node Connection Type = AdjustedSupply. If this curve is left blank, then the curve is assumed to always equal 1.0. This field is only used when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

fields.name: Design Electric Power Supply Efficiency
fields.memo: The efficiency of the power supply system serving this ITE

fields.name: Electric Power Supply Efficiency Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of a single-variable curve or table lookup object which modifies the electric power supply efficiency as a function of part-load ratio (x). This curve (table) should equal 1.0 at full load (PLR = 1.0). If this curve is left blank, then the curve is assumed to always equal 1.0.

fields.name: Fraction of Electric Power Supply Losses to Zone
fields.memo: Fraction of the electric power supply losses which are a heat gain to the zone If this field is <1.0, the remainder of the losses are assumed to be lost to the outdoors.

fields.name: CPU End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Fan End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Electric Power Supply End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Supply Temperature Difference
fields.memo: The difference of the IT inlet temperature from the AHU supply air temperature. Either Supply Temperature Difference or Supply Temperature Difference Schedule is required if Air Flow Calculation Method is set to FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures. This field is ignored when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

fields.name: Supply Temperature Difference Schedule
fields.memo: The difference schedule of the IT inlet temperature from the AHU supply air temperature. Either Supply Temperature Difference or Supply Temperature Difference Schedule is required if Air Flow Calculation Method is set to FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures. This field is ignored when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

fields.name: Return Temperature Difference
fields.memo: The difference of the return outlet temperature from the well mixed zone temperature. Either Return Temperature Difference or Return Temperature Difference Schedule is required if Air Flow Calculation Method is set to FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures. This field is ignored when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

fields.name: Return Temperature Difference Schedule
fields.memo: The difference schedule of the return outlet temperature from the well mixed zone temperature. Either Return Temperature Difference or Return Temperature Difference Schedule is required if Air Flow Calculation Method is set to FlowControlWithApproachTemperatures. This field is ignored when Air Flow Calculation Method is FlowFromSystem.

generator:fuelcell:powermodule.name: Generator:FuelCell:PowerModule
generator:fuelcell:powermodule.memo: Describe the core power module subsystem of a fuel cell power generator. This includes the fuel cell stack, fuel reformer, and whatever ancillary devices are included inside. If the model has multiple FC generators that are of the exact same type, then only one of these objects is needed and all the Generator:FuelCell objects can reference it.

fields.name: Nominal Efficiency
fields.memo: This field is not used.

fields.name: Nominal Electrical Power
fields.memo: This field is not used

fields.name: Number of Stops at Start of Simulation
fields.memo: this is Nstops in SOFC model specification

fields.name: Cycling Performance Degradation Coefficient
fields.memo: this is D in SOFC model specification

fields.name: Number of Run Hours at Beginning of Simulation
Accumulated Run Time Degradation Coefficient
fields.memo: this is L in SOFC model specification

fields.name: Run Time Degradation Initiation Time Threshold
Power Up Transient Limit
fields.memo: Maximum rate of change in electrical output [power increasing]

fields.name: Power Down Transient Limit
fields.memo: Maximum rate of change in electrical output [power decreasing] Enter positive value for rate of change

fields.name: Start Up Time
fields.memo: Time from start up to normal operation

fields.name: Skin Loss U-Factor Times Area Term
Skin Loss Quadratic Curve Name
fields.memo: curve is function of fuel use rate

fields.name: Stack Heat loss to Dilution Air

surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm:su.name: SurfaceProperty:HeatTransferAlgorithm:SurfaceList
surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm:su.memo: Determines which Heat Balance Algorithm will be used for a list of surfaces Allows selectively overriding the global setting in HeatBalanceAlgorithm CTF (Conduction Transfer Functions), EMPD (Effective Moisture Penetration Depth with Conduction Transfer Functions). Advanced/Research Usage: CondFD (Conduction Finite Difference) Advanced/Research Usage: HAMT (Combined Heat And Moisture Finite Element)

site:variablelocation.name: Site:VariableLocation
site:variablelocation.memo: Captures the scheduling of a moving/reorienting building, or more likely a vessel

fields.name: Building Location Latitude Schedule
fields.memo: The name of a schedule that defines the latitude of the building at any time. If not entered, the latitude defined in the Site:Location, or the default latitude, will be used for the entirety of the simulation

fields.name: Building Location Longitude Schedule
fields.memo: The name of a schedule that defines the longitude of the building at any time. If not entered, the longitude defined in the Site:Location, or the default longitude, will be used for the entirety of the simulation

fields.name: Building Location Orientation Schedule
fields.memo: The name of a schedule that defines the orientation of the building at any time. This orientation is based on a change from the original orientation. -- NEED TO REFINE THIS If not entered, the original orientation will be used for the entirety of the simulation

hvactemplate:zone:vav:fanpowered.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:VAV:FanPowered
hvactemplate:zone:vav:fanpowered.memo: Zone terminal unit, fan powered variable volume, reheat optional. Referenced schedules must be defined elsewhere in the idf.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone Name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template VAV System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:System:VAV or HVACTemplate:System:PackagedVAV object serving this zone.

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Primary Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Primary Supply Air Minimum Flow Fraction
Secondary Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Parallel Fan On Flow Fraction
fields.memo: The fraction of the primary air flow at which fan turns on Applicable only to Parallel Flow Type

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Reheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:VAV Cooling Coil Design Setpoint

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone PIU Fan Schedule Name
fields.memo: This is the operating schedule for the zone PIU fan. For a parallel PIU, the fan operates only when the primary air flow is below the Parallel Fan On Flow Fraction and the Zone PIU Fan Schedule is on, or it is activated by an availability manager. For a series PIU, the zone fan operates whenever the Zone PIU Fan Schedule is on, or it is activated by an availability manager. If this field is left blank, the System Availability Schedule for the HVACTemplate:System serving this zone will be used.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name

districtheating.name: DistrictHeating
districtheating.memo: Centralized source of hot water, such as a district heating system.

fields.name: Capacity Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are multiplied by Nominal Capacity for current capacity

refrigeration:case.name: Refrigeration:Case
refrigeration:case.memo: The Refrigeration Case object works in conjunction with a compressor rack, a refrigeration system, or a secondary loop to simulate the performance of a refrigerated case system. The object calculates the energy use for lights, fans and anti-sweat heaters and accounts for the sensible and latent heat exchange with the surrounding environment (termed "case credits") which impacts the temperature and humidity in the zone where the case is located.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: This must be a controlled zone and appear in a ZoneHVAC:EquipmentConnections object.

fields.name: Rated Total Cooling Capacity per Unit Length
Standard Case Fan Power per Unit Length
Operating Case Fan Power per Unit Length
Standard Case Lighting Power per Unit Length
Installed Case Lighting Power per Unit Length
fields.memo: default set equal to Standard Case Lighting Power per Unit Length

fields.name: Fraction of Lighting Energy to Case
Case Anti-Sweat Heater Power per Unit Length
Minimum Anti-Sweat Heater Power per Unit Length
fields.memo: This field is only applicable to the Linear, Dewpoint Method, and Heat Balance Method anti-sweat heater control types

fields.name: Humidity at Zero Anti-Sweat Heater Energy
fields.memo: This field is only applicable to Linear AS heater control type Zone relative humidity (%) where anti-sweat heater energy is zero

fields.name: Case Height
fields.memo: This field only applicable to Heat Balance Method AS heater control type Height must be greater than zero if Heat Balance Method AS heater control is selected

fields.name: Fraction of Anti-Sweat Heater Energy to Case
Case Defrost Power per Unit Length
fields.memo: Used to evaluate load on case as well as power or heat consumption

fields.name: Case Defrost Schedule Name
fields.memo: A case defrost schedule name is required unless case defrost type = None

fields.name: Case Defrost Drip-Down Schedule Name
fields.memo: If left blank, the defrost schedule will be used The start time for each defrost period in this drip-down schedule should coincide with the start time for each defrost period in the case defrost schedule (previous input field).The length of each defrost drip-down period must be greater than or equal to the corresponding defrost period specified in the case defrost schedule. This extra time allows the melted frost to drip from the coil before refrigeration is restarted.

fields.name: Defrost Energy Correction Curve Type
fields.memo: Case Temperature, Relative Humidity, and Dewpoint Method are applicable to case defrost types with temperature termination only.

fields.name: Defrost Energy Correction Curve Name
fields.memo: Defrost Energy Correction Curve Name is applicable to case defrost types with temperature termination only.

fields.name: Under Case HVAC Return Air Fraction
Refrigerated Case Restocking Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be in units of Watts per unit case length (W/m) Leave this field blank if no restocking is to be modeled

fields.name: Case Credit Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be from 0 to 1 Leave this field blank if no case credit fraction is to be applied

fields.name: Design Evaporator Temperature or Brine Inlet Temperature
fields.memo: Required for detailed refrigeration system, not for compressor rack For a DX system, enter the saturated temperature for refrigerant pressure leaving case For a brine-cooled cooled (secondary system) case, enter the brine inlet temperature Default is 5 C less than case operating temperature

fields.name: Under Case HVAC Return Air Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the return air node for this case. If left blank, defaults to the first return air node for this zone.

setpointmanager:outdoorairreset.name: SetpointManager:OutdoorAirReset
setpointmanager:outdoorairreset.memo: This Setpoint Manager is used to place a setpoint temperature on system node according to the outdoor air temperature using a reset rule. The outdoor air temperature is obtained from the weather information during the simulation.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which temperature will be set

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Optional input. Schedule allows scheduling of the outdoor air reset rule - a schedule value of 1 means use the first rule; a value of 2 means use the second rule.

fields.name: Setpoint at Outdoor Low Temperature 2
fields.memo: 2nd outdoor air temperature reset rule

fields.name: Outdoor Low Temperature 2
fields.memo: 2nd outdoor air temperature reset rule

fields.name: Setpoint at Outdoor High Temperature 2
fields.memo: 2nd outdoor air temperature reset rule

fields.name: Outdoor High Temperature 2
fields.memo: 2nd outdoor air temperature reset rule

coolingtower:twospeed.name: CoolingTower:TwoSpeed
coolingtower:twospeed.memo: This tower model is based on Merkel's theory, which is also the basis for the tower model in ASHRAE's HVAC1 Toolkit. The open wet cooling tower is modeled as a counter flow heat exchanger with a two-speed fan drawing air through the tower (induced-draft configuration). For a multi-cell tower, the capacity and air/water flow rate inputs are for the entire tower.

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower Water Inlet Node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower Water Outlet Node

fields.name: Design Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Leave field blank if Tower Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: High Fan Speed Air Flow Rate
High Fan Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at high speed

fields.name: High Fan Speed U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if Tower Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Low speed air flow rate must be less than high speed air flow rate Low speed air flow rate must be greater than free convection air flow rate

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Air Flow Rate Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at low speed

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Fan Power Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Low Fan Speed U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if tower Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity Low speed tower UA must be less than high speed tower UA Low speed tower UA must be greater than free convection tower UA

fields.name: Low Fan Speed U-Factor Times Area Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the Performance Input Method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate

fields.name: Free Convection Regime Air Flow Rate
Free Convection Regime Air Flow Rate Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Free Convection Regime U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if Tower Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Free Convection U-Factor Times Area Value Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the Performance Input Method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define tower thermal performance by specifying the tower UA, the Design Air Flow Rate and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the tower nominal capacity

fields.name: Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio
High Speed Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal tower capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature, with the tower fan operating at high speed. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt(3 gpm/ton). Nominal tower capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Low Speed Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal tower capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature, with the tower fan operating at low speed. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt of tower high-speed nominal capacity (3 gpm/ton). Nominal tower capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Low Speed Nominal Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: Free Convection Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Tower capacity in free convection regime with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt of tower high-speed nominal capacity (3 gpm/ton). Tower free convection capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25)  gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions

fields.name: Free Convection Nominal Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air dry-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air wet-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the approach temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design range temperature. Design approach temp = outlet water temperature minus inlet air wet-bulb temperature at design conditions. Autosized to 3.9 deltaC.

fields.name: Design Range Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the range temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design approach temperature. Design range = inlet water temperature minus outlet water temperature at design conditions. Autosized to 5.5 deltaC.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when water is not flowing through the tower.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Evaporation Loss Factor
fields.memo: Rate of water evaporated from the cooling tower and lost to the outdoor air [%/K] Evaporation loss is calculated as percentage of the circulating condenser water rate Value entered here is percent-per-degree K of temperature drop in the condenser water Typical values are from 0.15 to 0.27 [%/K].

fields.name: Drift Loss Percent
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a percentage of circulating condenser water flow rate Typical values are between 0.002 and 0.2% The default value is 0.008%

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the cooling tower. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the tower in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. Typical values for tower operation are 3 to 5.  The default value is 3.

fields.name: Blowdown Makeup Water Usage Schedule Name
fields.memo: Makeup water usage due to blowdown results from occasionally draining some amount of water in the tower basin to purge scale or other contaminants to reduce their concentration in order to maintain an acceptable level of water quality. Schedule values should reflect water usage in m3/s.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

fields.name: Cell Minimum  Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable minimal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Cell Maximum Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable maximal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

zonelist.name: ZoneList
zonelist.memo: Defines a list of thermal zones which can be referenced as a group. The ZoneList name may be used elsewhere in the input to apply a parameter to all zones in the list. ZoneLists can be used effectively with the following objects: People, Lights, ElectricEquipment, GasEquipment, HotWaterEquipment, ZoneInfiltration:DesignFlowRate, ZoneVentilation:DesignFlowRate, Sizing:Zone, ZoneControl:Thermostat, and others.

hvactemplate:zone:vav:heatandcool.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:VAV:HeatAndCool
hvactemplate:zone:vav:heatandcool.memo: VAV system with VAV for both heating and cooling and optional reheat coil. For heating, this unit increases airflow first, then activates reheat coil.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template VAV System Name
fields.memo: Name of a HVACTemplate:System:VAV or HVACTemplate:System:PackagedVAV object serving this zone

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Constant If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional. If a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the following field are entered, the larger result is used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Sizing
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification. Note that this field is used only for specifying the design outdoor air flow rate used for sizing. The field Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Control (see above) is used to actively control the VAV terminal air flow rate.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Reheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Maximum Reheat Air Temperature
fields.memo: Specifies the maximum allowable supply air temperature leaving the reheat coil. If left blank, there is no limit and no default. If unknown, 35C (95F) is recommended.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:VAV Cooling Coil Design Setpoint

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:VAV Heating Coil Design Setpoint TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

roomairmodeltype.name: RoomAirModelType
roomairmodeltype.memo: Selects the type of room air model to be used in a given zone. If no RoomAirModelType object is specified then the default Mixing model (all zone air at the same temperature) will be used.

fields.name: Room-Air Modeling Type
fields.memo: Mixing = Complete mixing air model UserDefined = UserDefined Room Air Temperature Patterns needs RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:UserDefined object referencing this Zone OneNodeDisplacementVentilation = Mundt roomair model for displacement ventilation with single floor air node needs RoomAirSettings:OneNodeDisplacementVentilation object referencing this Zone ThreeNodeDisplacementVentilation = RoomAir modeling using UCSD three-node displacement ventilation model needs RoomAirSettings:ThreeNodeDisplacementVentilation object referencing this Zone CrossVentilation = RoomAir modeling using UCSD two-zone cross ventilation model needs RoomAirSettings:CrossVentilation object referencing this Zone UnderFloorAirDistributionInterior = 2-Node UFAD model for interior zones needs RoomAirSettings:UnderFloorAirDistributionInterior object referencing this Zone UnderFloorAirDistributionExterior = RoomAir modeling using 2-Node UFAD model for exterior zones needs RoomAirSettings:UnderFloorAirDistributionExterior object referencing this Zone AirflowNetwork = RoomAir modeling using AirflowNetwork needs RoomAirSettings:AirflowNetwork object referencing this Zone

airloophvac:zonesplitter.name: AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter
airloophvac:zonesplitter.memo: Split one air stream into N outlet streams (currently 500 per air loop, but extensible).  Node names cannot be duplicated within a single zone splitter (AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter) list.

weatherproperty:skytemperature.name: WeatherProperty:SkyTemperature
weatherproperty:skytemperature.memo: This object is used to override internal sky temperature calculations.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: if name matches a SizingPeriod:DesignDay, put in a day schedule of this name if name is for a SizingPeriod:WeatherFileDays, SizingPeriod:WeatherFileConditionType or RunPeriod, put in a full year schedule that covers the appropriate days.

parametric:runcontrol.name: Parametric:RunControl
parametric:runcontrol.memo: Controls which parametric runs are simulated. This object is optional. If it is not included, then all parametric runs are performed.

faultmodel:fouling:boiler.name: FaultModel:Fouling:Boiler
faultmodel:fouling:boiler.memo: This object describes the fouling fault of boilers with water-based heat exchangers

fields.name: Boiler Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of a boiler object The fault applies to the hot-water boilers

fields.name: Boiler Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Boiler object

fields.name: Fouling Factor
fields.memo: The factor indicates the decrease of the nominal capacity of the boiler It is the ratio between the nominal capacity at fouling case and that at fault free case

controller:watercoil.name: Controller:WaterCoil
controller:watercoil.memo: Controller for a water coil which is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list. Controls the coil water flow to meet the specified leaving air setpoint(s). Used with Coil:Heating:Water, Coil:Cooling:Water, Coil:Cooling:Water:DetailedGeometry, and CoilSystem:Cooling:Water:HeatexchangerAssisted.

fields.name: Control Variable
fields.memo: keys HumidityRatio or TemperatureAndHumidityRatio requires a ZoneControl:Humidistat object along with SetpointManager:SingleZone:Humidity:Maximum, SetpointManager:MultiZone:MaximumHumidity:Average, or SetpointManager:Multizone:Humidity:Maximum object

fields.name: Action
fields.memo: Leave blank to have this automatically selected from coil type. Chilled water coils should be reverse action Hot water coils should be normal action

windowmaterial:glazing:equivalentlayer.name: WindowMaterial:Glazing:EquivalentLayer
windowmaterial:glazing:equivalentlayer.memo: Glass material properties for Windows or Glass Doors Transmittance/Reflectance input method.

fields.name: Optical Data Type
fields.memo: Spectral is not currently supported and SpectralAverage is the default.

fields.name: Window Glass Spectral Data Set Name
fields.memo: Spectral data is not currently supported. Used only when Optical Data Type = Spectral

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Beam Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Beam Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Beam Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Front Side is side closest to outdoor air

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Beam Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Back Side is side closest to zone air

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Beam Visible Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Beam Visible Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Beam Visible Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Front Side is side closest to outdoor air

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Beam Visible Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Back Side is side closest to zone air

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Front Side is side closest to outdoor air

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Back Side is side closest to zone air

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Diffuse Visible Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Diffuse Visible Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Front Side Beam-Diffuse Visible Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Front Side is side closest to outdoor air

fields.name: Back Side Beam-Diffuse Visible Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Back Side is side closest to zone air

fields.name: Diffuse-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage If this field is autocalculate, then the diffuse-diffuse solar transmittance is automatically estimated from other inputs and used in subsequent calculations. If this field is zero or positive, then the value entered here will be used.

fields.name: Front Side Diffuse-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage If this field is autocalculate, then the front diffuse-diffuse solar reflectance is automatically estimated from other inputs and used in subsequent calculations. If this field is zero or positive, then the value entered here will be used.  Front Side is side closest to outdoor air.

fields.name: Back Side Diffuse-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage If this field is autocalculate, then the back diffuse-diffuse solar reflectance is automatically estimated from other inputs and used in subsequent calculations. If this field is zero or positive, then the value entered here will be used.  Back side is side closest to indoor air.

fields.name: Diffuse-Diffuse Visible Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage This input field is not used currently.

fields.name: Front Side Diffuse-Diffuse Visible Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage This input field is not used currently.

fields.name: Back Side Diffuse-Diffuse Visible Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage This input field is not used currently.

fields.name: Infrared Transmittance (applies to front and back)
fields.memo: The long-wave hemispherical transmittance of the glazing. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the glazing.

fields.name: Front Side Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: The front side long-wave hemispherical emissivity of the glazing.

fields.name: Back Side Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: The back side long-wave hemispherical emissivity of the glazing.

airloophvac:returnpath.name: AirLoopHVAC:ReturnPath
airloophvac:returnpath.memo: A return air path can only contain one AirLoopHVAC:ZoneMixer and one or more AirLoopHVAC:ReturnPlenum objects.

fields.name: Return Air Path Outlet Node Name

zonehvac:unitventilator.name: ZoneHVAC:UnitVentilator
zonehvac:unitventilator.memo: Unit ventilator. Forced-convection ventilation unit with supply fan (constant-volume or variable-volume), optional chilled water cooling coil, optional heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam) and controllable outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: schedule values multiply the minimum outdoor air flow rate

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Fraction or Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: that this depends on the control type as to whether it is a fraction or temperature

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Inlet node name must be zone exhaust node name if there is no DOA Mixer, or if the unit ventilator is connected DOA, then the air inlet node name must be the mixer outlet air node name for InletSide mixer connection.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Outlet node name must be zone inlet node name if there is no DOA Mixer, or if the unit ventilator is connected DOA, then the air outlet node name must be the mixer secondary air inlet node name for SupplySide mixer connection.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: this field is left blank only if the Unit Ventilator is connected to a central dedicated outdoor air (DOA) via AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object

fields.name: Exhaust Air Node Name
fields.memo: this field is left blank only if the Unit Ventilator is connected to a central dedicated outdoor air (DOA) via AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object

fields.name: Mixed Air Node Name
fields.memo: inlet to coils this field is left blank only if the Unit Ventilator is connected to a central dedicated outdoor air (DOA) via AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Allowable fan types are Fan:ConstantVolume, Fan:OnOff, Fan:VariableVolume, and Fan:SystemModel

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule name values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling/heating coil). Schedule values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this input field is left blank.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

airconditioner:variablerefrigerantflow:f.name: AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl
airconditioner:variablerefrigerantflow:f.memo: This is a key object in the new physics based VRF model applicable for Fluid Temperature Control It describes the Variable Refrigerant Flow system excluding the performance of indoor units Indoor units are modeled separately, see ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow

fields.name: Heat Pump Name
fields.memo: Enter a unique name for this variable refrigerant flow heat pump

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that defines the availability of the unit Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off. All other values denote the unit is available If this field is left blank, the unit is available the entire simulation

fields.name: Zone Terminal Unit List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneTerminalUnitList. This list connects zone terminal units to this heat pump

fields.name: Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the total evaporative capacity in watts at rated conditions This is the capacity corresponding to the max compressor speed at rated conditions The actual evaporative capacity is obtained by multiplying the rated capacity with the modification factor calculated by Evaporative Capacity Multiplier Function of Temperature Curve

fields.name: Rated Compressor Power Per Unit of Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the rated compressor power per Watt of rated evaporative capacity [W/W] Rated compressor power corresponds to the max compressor speed at rated conditions The actual compressor power is obtained by multiplying the rated power with the modification factor calculated by Compressor Power Multiplier Function of Temperature Curve

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation Cooling is disabled below this temperature

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation Cooling is disabled above this temperature

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation Heating is disabled below this temperature

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation Heating is disabled below this temperature

fields.name: Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm for Indoor Unit
Reference Evaporating Temperature for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is ConstantTemp Evaporating temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Reference Condensing Temperature for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is ConstantTemp Condensing temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Evaporating Temperature Minimum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Evaporating temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Evaporating Temperature Maximum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Evaporating temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Condensing Temperature Minimum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Condensing temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Condensing Temperature Maximum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Condensing temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Fan Power Per Unit of Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor unit fan power per Watt of rated evaporative capacity [W/W]

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Fan Flow Rate Per Unit of Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous is set to autocalculate and performance input method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Evaporating Temperature Function of Superheating Curve Name
Outdoor Unit Condensing Temperature Function of Subcooling Curve Name
Diameter of Main Pipe Connecting Outdoor Unit to the First Branch Joint
fields.memo: used to calculate the piping loss

fields.name: Length of Main Pipe Connecting Outdoor Unit to the First Branch Joint
fields.memo: used to calculate the heat loss of the main pipe

fields.name: Equivalent Length of Main Pipe Connecting Outdoor Unit to the First Branch Joint
fields.memo: used to calculate the refrigerant pressure drop of the main pipe

fields.name: Height Difference Between Outdoor Unit and Indoor Units
fields.memo: Difference between outdoor unit height and indoor unit height Positive means outdoor unit is higher than indoor unit Negative means outdoor unit is lower than indoor unit

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Power per Compressor
fields.memo: Enter the value of the resistive heater located in the compressor(s). This heater is used to warm the refrigerant and oil when the compressor is off

fields.name: Number of Compressors
fields.memo: Enter the total number of compressor. This input is used only for crankcase heater calculations.

fields.name: Ratio of Compressor Size to Total Compressor Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the ratio of the first stage compressor to total compressor capacity All other compressors are assumed to be equally sized. This inputs is used only for crankcase heater calculations

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which the crankcase heaters are disabled

fields.name: Defrost Strategy
fields.memo: Select a defrost strategy. Reverse cycle reverses the operating mode from heating to cooling to melt frost formation on the condenser coil The resistive strategy uses a resistive heater to melt the frost.

fields.name: Defrost Control
fields.memo: Choose a defrost control type Either use a fixed Timed defrost period or select OnDemand to defrost only when necessary

fields.name: Defrost Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: A valid performance curve must be used if ReverseCycle defrost strategy is selected

fields.name: Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode Only applicable if timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the size of the resistive defrost heating element Only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which the defrost operation is disabled

fields.name: Number of Compressor Loading Index Entries
fields.memo: First index represents minimal capacity operation Last index represents full capacity operation

designspecification:outdoorair.name: DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir
designspecification:outdoorair.memo: This object is used to describe general outdoor air requirements which are referenced by other objects.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person => Outdoor Air Flow per Person * Occupancy = Design Flow Rate, Flow/Area => Outdoor Air Flow per Zone Floor Area * Zone Floor Area = Design Flow Rate, Flow/Zone => Outdoor Air Flow per Zone = Design Flow Rate, AirChanges/Hour => Outdoor Air Flow Air Changes per Hour * Zone Volume adjusted for m3/s = Design Flow Rate

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow per Person
fields.memo: 0.00944 m3/s is equivalent to 20 cfm per person This input is only used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum For sizing, the design number of occupants is used. For outdoor air flow control, the use of design occupants or current occupants depends on the component and DCV options. AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:NoReheat, AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:Reheat use the DCV flag specified in Controller:MechanicalVentilation AirTerminal:DualDuct:VAV:OutdoorAir and ZoneHVAC:IdealLoadsAirSystem have their own DCV control input. ZoneHVAC:FourPipeFanCoil always uses current occupants.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is only used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow per Zone
fields.memo: This input is only used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Air Changes per Hour
fields.memo: This input is only used if the field Outdoor Air Method is AirChanges/Hour, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are multiplied by the Outdoor Air Flow rate calculated using the previous four inputs. Schedule values are limited to 0 to 1. If left blank, the schedule defaults to 1.0. This schedule is ignored during sizing.  All other components which reference this design specification use the current schedule value to calculate the current outdoor air requirement. This includes AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:NoReheat, AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:Reheat, AirTerminal:DualDuct:VAV:OutdoorAir, ZoneHVAC:FourPipeFanCoil, and ZoneHVAC:IdealLoadsAirSystem. This schedule will also be applied by Controller:MechanicalVentilation for all System Outdoor Air Methods.

fields.name: Proportional Control Minimum Outdoor Air Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: This input is only used to calculate the minimum outdoor air flow rate when the field System Outdoor Air Method = ProportionalControlBasedOnDesignOARate in Controller:MechanicalVentilation.

zoneairbalance:outdoorair.name: ZoneAirBalance:OutdoorAir
zoneairbalance:outdoorair.memo: Provide a combined zone outdoor air flow by including interactions between mechanical ventilation, infiltration and duct leakage. This object will combine outdoor flows from all ZoneInfiltration and ZoneVentilation objects in the same zone. Balanced flows will be summed, while unbalanced flows will be added in quadrature.

fields.name: Air Balance Method
fields.memo: None: Only perform simple calculations without using a combined zone outdoor air. Quadrature: A combined outdoor air is used in the quadrature sum.

fields.name: Induced Outdoor Air Due to Unbalanced Duct Leakage
Induced Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the fraction values applied to the Induced Outdoor Air given in the previous input field (0.0 - 1.0).

buildingsurface:detailed.name: BuildingSurface:Detailed
buildingsurface:detailed.memo: Allows for detailed entry of building heat transfer surfaces.  Does not include subsurfaces such as windows or doors.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Non-blank only if the field Outside Boundary Condition is Surface, Zone, OtherSideCoefficients or OtherSideConditionsModel If Surface, specify name of corresponding surface in adjacent zone or specify current surface name for internal partition separating like zones If Zone, specify the name of the corresponding zone and the program will generate the corresponding interzone surface If Foundation, specify the name of the corresponding Foundation object and the program will calculate the heat transfer appropriately If OtherSideCoefficients, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideCoefficients If OtherSideConditionsModel, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel

fields.name: View Factor to Ground
fields.memo: From the exterior of the surface Unused if one uses the "reflections" options in Solar Distribution in Building input unless a DaylightingDevice:Shelf or DaylightingDevice:Tubular object has been specified. autocalculate will automatically calculate this value from the tilt of the surface

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 120 vertex coordinates -- extensible object "extensible" -- duplicate last set of x,y,z coordinates (last 3 fields), remembering to remove ; from "inner" fields. for clarity in any error messages, renumber the fields as well. (and changing z terminator to a comma "," for all but last one which needs a semi-colon ";") vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- if relative, all surface coordinates are "relative" to the Zone Origin.  If world, then building and zone origins are used for some internal calculations, but all coordinates are given in an "absolute" system.

site:groundtemperature:undisturbed:xing.name: Site:GroundTemperature:Undisturbed:Xing
site:groundtemperature:undisturbed:xing.memo: Undisturbed ground temperature object using the Xing 2014 2 harmonic parameter model.

surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm:mu.name: SurfaceProperty:HeatTransferAlgorithm:MultipleSurface
surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm:mu.memo: Determines which Heat Balance Algorithm will be used for a group of surface types Allows selectively overriding the global setting in HeatBalanceAlgorithm CTF (Conduction Transfer Functions), EMPD (Effective Moisture Penetration Depth with Conduction Transfer Functions). Advanced/Research Usage: CondFD (Conduction Finite Difference) Advanced/Research Usage: HAMT (Combined Heat And Moisture Finite Element)

airloophvac:unitary:furnace:heatcool.name: AirLoopHVAC:Unitary:Furnace:HeatCool
airloophvac:unitary:furnace:heatcool.memo: Unitary system, heating and cooling with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling), direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam), and optional reheat coil for dehumidification control. Identical to AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatCool.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. A schedule value greater than zero (usually 1 is used) indicates that the unit is available to operate as needed. A value less than or equal to zero (usually zero is used) denotes that the unit must be off.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: A fan operating mode schedule value of 0 indicates cycling fan mode (supply air fan cycles on and off in tandem with the cooling or heating coil). Any other schedule value indicates continuous fan mode (supply air fan operates continuously regardless of cooling or heating coil operation). Provide a schedule with non-zero values when high humidity control is specified. Leaving this schedule name blank will default to cycling fan mode for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow fate.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate. Only used when fan operating mode is continuous (disregarded for cycling fan mode). This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required (i.e., the DX coil compressor and heating coil are off). If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Supply Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works with continuous fan operating mode (i.e. supply air fan operating mode schedule values not equal to 0).

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with DX cooling coil types

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load.  Valid only with cooling coil type CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted. This control mode allows the heat exchanger to be turned on and off based on the zone dehumidification requirements. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required. CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint. as required to meet the humidity setpoint.  Valid with all cooling coil types. When a heat exchanger assisted cooling coil is used, the heat exchanger is locked on at all times. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required.

fields.name: Reheat Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only required if dehumidification control type is "CoolReheat" works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Reheat Coil Name
fields.memo: Only required if dehumidification control type is "CoolReheat"

electricloadcenter:storage:simple.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Storage:Simple
electricloadcenter:storage:simple.memo: Used to model storage of electricity in an electric load center.  This is a simple model that does not attempt to represent any of the characteristics of a real storage device such as a battery.  The type of power, AC or DC, depends on the configuration chosen as the Electrical Buss Type in the ElectricLoadCenter:Distribution object.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter name of zone to receive storage losses as heat if blank then storage is assumed to be outdoors

fields.name: Radiative Fraction for Zone Heat Gains

curve:fanpressurerise.name: Curve:FanPressureRise
curve:fanpressurerise.memo: Special curve type with two independent variables. Input for the fan total pressure rise curve consists of the curve name, the four coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1*Qfan**2+C2*Qfan+C3*Qfan*(Psm-Po)**0.5+C4*(Psm-Po) Po assumed to be zero See InputOut Reference for curve details

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

airloophvac:zonemixer.name: AirLoopHVAC:ZoneMixer
airloophvac:zonemixer.memo: Mix N inlet air streams into one (currently 500 per air loop, but extensible).  Node names cannot be duplicated within a single zone mixer (AirLoopHVAC:ZoneMixer) list.

zonehvac:baseboard:radiantconvective:ste.name: ZoneHVAC:Baseboard:RadiantConvective:Steam
zonehvac:baseboard:radiantconvective:ste.memo: The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 100, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Fraction of Radiant Energy Incident on People

sizing:zone.name: Sizing:Zone
sizing:zone.memo: Specifies the data needed to perform a zone design air flow calculation. The calculation is done for every sizing period included in the input. The maximum cooling and heating load and cooling, heating, and ventilation air flows are then saved for system level and zone component design calculations.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Zone Heating Design Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: if blank or zero, global heating sizing factor from Sizing:Parameters is used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: if blank or zero, global cooling sizing factor from Sizing:Parameters is used.

fields.name: Cooling Design Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This input is used if Cooling Design Air Flow Method is Flow/Zone This value will be multiplied by the global or zone sizing factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Cooling Minimum Air Flow per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: default is .15 cfm/ft2 This input is used if Cooling Design Air Flow Method is DesignDayWithLimit

fields.name: Cooling Minimum Air Flow
fields.memo: This input is used if Cooling Design Air Flow Method is DesignDayWithLimit

fields.name: Cooling Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: fraction of the Cooling design Air Flow Rate This input is currently used in sizing the VAV air terminal unit and fan minimum flow rate It does not currently affect other component autosizing.

fields.name: Heating Design Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This input is used if Heating Design Air Flow Method is Flow/Zone. This value will be multiplied by the global or zone sizing factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Heating Maximum Air Flow per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: default is .40 cfm/ft2 This field is used to size the heating design flow rate when Heating Design Air Flow Method = Flow/Zone. This input is used for autosizing components when Heating Design Air Flow Method = DesignDayWithLimit.

fields.name: Heating Maximum Air Flow
fields.memo: default is 300 cfm This input is used for autosizing components when Heating Design Air Flow Method = DesignDayWithLimit.

fields.name: Heating Maximum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: fraction of the Heating Design Air Flow Rate This input is used for autosizing components when Heating Design Air Flow Method = DesignDayWithLimit.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
Account for Dedicated Outdoor Air System
fields.memo: account for effect of dedicated outdoor air system supplying air directly to the zone

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air System Control Strategy
fields.memo: 1)supply neutral ventilation air; 2)supply neutral dehumidified and reheated ventilation air; 3)supply cold ventilation air

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air Low Setpoint Temperature for Design
Dedicated Outdoor Air High Setpoint Temperature for Design

fluidcooler:twospeed.name: FluidCooler:TwoSpeed
fluidcooler:twospeed.memo: The fluid cooler is modeled as a cross flow heat exchanger (both streams unmixed) with two-speed fans (induced draft configuration).

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of fluid cooler water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of fluid cooler water outlet node

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define fluid cooler thermal performance by specifying the fluid cooler UA and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the fluid cooler nominal capacity

fields.name: High Fan Speed U-factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if fluid cooler Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Low Fan Speed U-factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if fluid cooler Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity Low speed fluid cooler UA must be less than high speed fluid cooler UA Low speed fluid cooler UA must be greater than free convection fluid cooler UA

fields.name: Low Fan Speed U-Factor Times Area Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the Performance Input Method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate

fields.name: High Speed Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal fluid cooler capacity at high fan speed

fields.name: Low Speed Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal fluid cooler capacity at low fan speed

fields.name: Low Speed Nominal Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Design Entering Water Temperature
fields.memo: Design Entering Water Temperature must be specified for both the performance input methods and its value must be greater than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Temperature
fields.memo: Design Entering Air Temperature must be specified for both the performance input methods and its value must be greater than Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature must be specified for both the performance input methods and its value must be less than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: High Fan Speed Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Air Flow Rate at High Fan Speed must be greater than Air Flow Rate at Low Fan Speed

fields.name: High Fan Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at high speed

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Air Flow Rate at Low Fan Speed must be less than Air Flow Rate at High Fan Speed

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Air Flow Rate Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at low speed

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Fan Power Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

availabilitymanager:differentialthermost.name: AvailabilityManager:DifferentialThermostat
availabilitymanager:differentialthermost.memo: Overrides fan/pump schedules depending on temperature difference between two nodes.

fields.name: Temperature Difference Off Limit
fields.memo: Defaults to Temperature Difference On Limit.

shadingproperty:reflectance.name: ShadingProperty:Reflectance
shadingproperty:reflectance.memo: If this object is not defined for a shading surface the default values listed in following fields will be used in the solar reflection calculation.

fields.name: Diffuse Solar Reflectance of Unglazed Part of Shading Surface
Diffuse Visible Reflectance of Unglazed Part of Shading Surface
Fraction of Shading Surface That Is Glazed
Glazing Construction Name
fields.memo: Required if Fraction of Shading Surface That Is Glazed > 0.0

otherequipment.name: OtherEquipment
otherequipment.memo: Sets internal gains or losses for "other" equipment in the zone.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in Schedule should be fraction applied to design level of other equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Design Level Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of other equipment. to set a loss, use a negative value in the following fields. for this set of attributes Choices: EquipmentLevel => Design Level -- simply enter power input of equipment Watts/Area or Power/Area => Power per Zone Floor Area -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Floor Area = Equipment Level Watts/Person or Power/Person => Power per Person -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Occupants = Equipment Level

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Generation Rate
fields.memo: CO2 generation rate per unit of power input The default value assumes the equipment is fully vented.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

airterminal:dualduct:vav.name: AirTerminal:DualDuct:VAV
airterminal:dualduct:vav.memo: Central air system terminal unit, dual duct, variable volume.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The outlet node of the terminal unit. This is also the zone inlet node.

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: fraction of maximum air flow

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will increase flow as needed to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow.

parametric:setvalueforrun.name: Parametric:SetValueForRun
parametric:setvalueforrun.memo: Parametric objects allow a set of multiple simulations to be defined in a single idf file. The parametric preprocessor scans the idf for Parametric:* objects then creates and runs multiple idf files, one for each defined simulation. The core parametric object is Parametric:SetValueForRun which defines the name of a parameters and sets the parameter to different values depending on which run is being simulated.

coil:cooling:dx:variablerefrigerantflow:.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl
coil:cooling:dx:variablerefrigerantflow:.memo: This is a key object in the new physics based VRF model applicable for Fluid Temperature Control. It describes the the indoor unit coil of the system at cooling mode. Used with ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow. Outdoor unit is modeled separately, see AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl or AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl:HR

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that defines the availability of the coil Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off. All other values denote the unit is available If this field is left blank, the unit is available the entire simulation

fields.name: Coil Air Inlet Node
fields.memo: the inlet node to the coil

fields.name: Coil Air Outlet Node
fields.memo: the outlet node to the coil

fields.name: Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Supply air fan heat is not included

fields.name: Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Supply air fan heat is not included

fields.name: Indoor Unit Evaporating Temperature Function of Superheating Curve Name
Name of Water Storage Tank for Condensate Collection

surfaceproperty:convectioncoefficients.name: SurfaceProperty:ConvectionCoefficients
surfaceproperty:convectioncoefficients.memo: Allow user settable interior and/or exterior convection coefficients. Note that some other factors may limit the lower bounds for these values, such as for windows, the interior convection coefficient must be >.28, for trombe wall algorithm selection (zone), the interior convection coefficient must be >.1 for TARP interior convection, the lower limit is also .1 Minimum and maximum limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Defaults in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object are [.1,1000].

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 1
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Value, min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 1 Schedule Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Schedule,  min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 1 User Curve Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type = UserCurve

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 2
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Value, min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 2 Schedule Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Schedule,  min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000
