fields.name: Convection Coefficient 2 User Curve Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type = UserCurve

heatbalancesettings:conductionfinitediff.name: HeatBalanceSettings:ConductionFiniteDifference
heatbalancesettings:conductionfinitediff.memo: Determines settings for the Conduction Finite Difference algorithm for surface heat transfer modeling.

fields.name: Space Discretization Constant
fields.memo: increase or decrease number of nodes

fields.name: Inside Face Surface Temperature Convergence Criteria

materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.name: MaterialProperty:HeatAndMoistureTransfer:ThermalConductivity
materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.memo: HeatBalanceAlgorithm = CombinedHeatAndMoistureFiniteElement solution algorithm only. Relationship between thermal conductivity and moisture content Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms

fields.name: Material Name
fields.memo: Moisture Material Name that the Thermal Conductivity will be added to.

fields.name: Number of Thermal Coordinates
fields.memo: number of data coordinates

energymanagementsystem:programcallingman.name: EnergyManagementSystem:ProgramCallingManager
energymanagementsystem:programcallingman.memo: Input EMS program. a program needs a name a description of when it should be called and then lines of program code for EMS Runtime language

site:groundtemperature:fcfactormethod.name: Site:GroundTemperature:FCfactorMethod
site:groundtemperature:fcfactormethod.memo: These temperatures are specifically for underground walls and ground floors defined with the C-factor and F-factor methods, and should be close to the monthly average outdoor air temperature delayed by 3 months for the location.

boiler:hotwater.name: Boiler:HotWater
boiler:hotwater.memo: This boiler model is an adaptation of the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Boiler performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to polynomial equations. A constant efficiency boiler may be modeled by leaving the normalized boiler efficiency curve name input blank.

fields.name: Nominal Thermal Efficiency
fields.memo: Based on the higher heating value of fuel.

fields.name: Normalized Boiler Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: Linear, Quadratic and Cubic efficiency curves are solely a function of PLR. All other efficiency curve types are a function of PLR and boiler water temperature. Linear = C1 + C2*PLR Quadratic = C1 + C2*PLR + C3*PLR^2 Cubic = C1 + C2*PLR + C3*PLR^2 + C4*PLR^3 Biquadratic = C1 + C2*PLR + C3*PLR^2 + C4*T + C5*T^2 + C6*PLR*T QuadraticLinear = C1 + C2*PLR + C3*PLR^2 + (C4 + C5*PLR + C6*PLR^2)*T BiCubic = C1+C2*PLR+C3*PLR^2+C4*T+C5*T^2+C6*PLR*T+C7*PLR^3+C8*T^3+C9*PLR^2*T+C10*PLR*T^2 TriQuadratic curves are not allowed. PLR = part-load ratio T = boiler water temperature (either entering or leaving).

fields.name: Boiler Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the boiler. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by boiler to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by boiler to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

pump:variablespeed:condensate.name: Pump:VariableSpeed:Condensate
pump:variablespeed:condensate.memo: This pump model is described in the ASHRAE secondary HVAC toolkit. Variable Speed Condensate pump for Steam Systems

fields.name: Design Steam Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: this is the volume of steam before condensation, the volume of condensate is much lower and calculated from steam density

fields.name: Design Pump Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet

fields.name: Design Power Consumption
fields.memo: When autosized the type of scaling factor is chosen in the input field Design Power Sizing Method

fields.name: Motor Efficiency
fields.memo: This is the motor efficiency only. When the Design Power Consumption is autosized using PowerPerFlowPerPressure, the Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used in addition to the motor efficiency.

fields.name: Fraction of Motor Inefficiencies to Fluid Stream
Coefficient 1 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 2 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 3 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 4 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Pump Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the rated flow rate of the pump on a time basis. Default is that the pump is on and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: optional, if used pump losses transfered to zone as internal gains

fields.name: Skin Loss Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: optional. If zone identified in previous field then this determines the split between convection and radiation for the skin losses

fields.name: Design Power Sizing Method
fields.memo: Used to indicate which sizing factor is used to calculate Design Power Consumption. PowerPerFlow indicates that Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * scaling factor PowerPerFlowPerPressure indicates that Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * Design Pump Head * scaling factor / Motor Efficiency

fields.name: Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate

fields.name: Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate for head and motor efficiency

site:groundtemperature:buildingsurface.name: Site:GroundTemperature:BuildingSurface
site:groundtemperature:buildingsurface.memo: These temperatures are specifically for those surfaces that have the outside environment of "Ground".  Documentation about what values these should be is located in the Auxiliary programs document (Ground Heat Transfer) as well as the InputOutput Reference. CAUTION - Do not use the "undisturbed" ground temperatures from the weather data. These values are too extreme for the soil under a conditioned building. For best results, use the Slab or Basement program to calculate custom monthly average ground temperatures (see Auxiliary Programs).  For typical commercial buildings in the USA, a reasonable default value is 2C less than the average indoor space temperature.

shading:site:detailed.name: Shading:Site:Detailed
shading:site:detailed.memo: used for shading elements such as trees these items are fixed in space and would not move with relative geometry

fields.name: Transmittance Schedule Name
fields.memo: Transmittance schedule for the shading device, defaults to zero (always opaque)

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 6 vertex coordinates -- extensible object Rules for vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- For this object all surface coordinates are in world coordinates.

roomair:temperaturepattern:constantgradi.name: RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:ConstantGradient
roomair:temperaturepattern:constantgradi.memo: Used to model room air with a fixed temperature gradient in the vertical direction. Used in combination with RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:UserDefined.

fields.name: Room Air Temperature Pattern Constant Gradient Name
Control Integer for Pattern Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: reference this entry in Schedule Name

fields.name: Thermostat Offset
fields.memo: = (Temp at thermostat- Mean Air Temp)

fields.name: Return Air Offset
fields.memo: = (Tleaving - Mean Air Temp )

fields.name: Exhaust Air Offset
fields.memo: = (Texhaust - Mean Air Temp) deg C

fields.name: Temperature Gradient
fields.memo: Slope of temperature change in vertical direction

zonehvac:idealloadsairsystem.name: ZoneHVAC:IdealLoadsAirSystem
zonehvac:idealloadsairsystem.memo: Ideal system used to calculate loads without modeling a full HVAC system. All that is required for the ideal system are zone controls, zone equipment configurations, and the ideal loads system component. This component can be thought of as an ideal unit that mixes zone air with the specified amount of outdoor air and then adds or removes heat and moisture at 100% efficiency in order to meet the specified controls. Energy use is reported as DistrictHeating and DistrictCooling.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Supply Air Node Name
fields.memo: Must match a zone air inlet node name.

fields.name: Zone Exhaust Air Node Name
fields.memo: Should match a zone air exhaust node name. This field is optional, but is required if this this object is used with other forced air equipment.

fields.name: System Inlet Air Node Name
fields.memo: This field is only required when the Ideal Loads Air System is connected to an AirloopHVAC:ZoneReturnPlenum, otherwise leave this field blank. When connected to a plenum the return plenum Outlet Node Name (or Induced Air Outlet Node Name when connecting multiple ideal loads air sytems) is entered here. The two ideal loads air system node name fields described above, the Zone Supply Air Node Name and the Zone Exhaust Air Node Name must also be entered. The Zone Supply Air Node Name must match a zone inlet air node name for the zone where this Ideal Loads Air System is connected. The Zone Exhaust Air Node Name must match an inlet air node name of an AirloopHVAC:ReturnAirPlenum object.

fields.name: Maximum Heating Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Minimum Cooling Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Maximum Heating Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Heating Limit = NoLimit If this field is blank, there is no limit.

fields.name: Maximum Sensible Heating Capacity
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Heating Limit = NoLimit If this field is blank, there is no limit.

fields.name: Maximum Cooling Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Cooling Limit = NoLimit This field is required if Outdoor Air Economizer Type is anything other than NoEconomizer.

fields.name: Maximum Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Cooling Limit = NoLimit

fields.name: Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, heating is always available.

fields.name: Cooling Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, cooling is always available.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: ConstantSensibleHeatRatio means that the ideal loads system will be controlled to meet the sensible cooling load, and the latent cooling rate will be computed using a constant sensible heat ratio (SHR) Humidistat means that there is a ZoneControl:Humidistat for this zone and the ideal loads system will attempt to satisfy the humidistat. None means that there is no dehumidification. ConstantSupplyHumidityRatio means that during cooling the supply air will always be at the Minimum Cooling Supply Humidity Ratio.

fields.name: Cooling Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: This field is applicable only when Dehumidification Control Type is ConstantSensibleHeatRatio

fields.name: Humidification Control Type
fields.memo: None means that there is no humidification. Humidistat means that there is a ZoneControl:Humidistat for this zone and the ideal loads system will attempt to satisfy the humidistat. ConstantSupplyHumidityRatio means that during heating the supply air will always be at the Maximum Heating Supply Humidity Ratio.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the minimum outdoor air flow rate will be computed using these specifications. The outdoor air flow rate will also be affected by the next two fields. If this field is blank, there will be no outdoor air and the remaining fields will be ignored.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: This field is required if the system provides outdoor air Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Demand Controlled Ventilation Type
fields.memo: This field controls how the minimum outdoor air flow rate is calculated. None means that design occupancy will be used to compute the minimum outdoor air flow rate OccupancySchedule means that current occupancy level will be used. CO2Setpoint means that the design occupancy will be used to compute the minimum outdoor air flow rate and the outdoor air flow rate may be increased if necessary to maintain the indoor air carbon dioxide setpoint defined in a ZoneControl:ContaminantController object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Economizer Type
fields.memo: DifferentialDryBulb and DifferentialEnthalpy will increase the outdoor air flow rate when there is a cooling load and the outdoor air temperature or enthalpy is below the zone exhaust air temperature or enthalpy.

fields.name: Latent Heat Recovery Effectiveness
fields.memo: Applicable only if Heat Recovery Type is Enthalpy.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

availabilitymanager:scheduled.name: AvailabilityManager:Scheduled
availabilitymanager:scheduled.memo: Determines the availability of a loop or system: whether it is on or off. Schedule overrides fan/pump schedule.

site:grounddomain:basement.name: Site:GroundDomain:Basement
site:grounddomain:basement.memo: Ground-coupled basement model for simulating basements or other underground zones.

fields.name: Ground Domain Depth
fields.memo: The depth from ground surface to the deep ground boundary of the domain.

fields.name: Aspect Ratio
fields.memo: This defines the height to width ratio of the basement zone.

fields.name: Perimeter Offset
fields.memo: The distance from the basement wall edge to the edge of the ground domain

fields.name: Soil Moisture Content Volume Fraction at Saturation
Evapotranspiration Ground Cover Parameter
fields.memo: This specifies the ground cover effects during evapotranspiration calculations.  The value roughly represents the following cases: = 0   : concrete or other solid, non-permeable ground surface material = 0.5 : short grass, much like a manicured lawn = 1   : standard reference state (12 cm grass) = 1.5 : wild growth

fields.name: Basement Floor Boundary Condition Model Name
Horizontal Insulation
fields.memo: This field specifies the presence of insulation beneath the basement floor.

fields.name: Horizontal Insulation Extents
fields.memo: This field specifies whether the horizontal insulation fully insulates the surface or is perimeter only insulation

fields.name: Perimeter Horizontal Insulation Width
fields.memo: Width of horizontal perimeter insulation measured from foundation wall inside surface.

fields.name: Basement Wall Depth
fields.memo: Depth measured from ground surface.

fields.name: Basement Wall Boundary Condition Model Name
Basement Wall Vertical Insulation Material Name
Vertical Insulation Depth
fields.memo: Depth measured from the ground surface.

fields.name: Simulation Timestep
fields.memo: This field specifies the basement domain simulation interval.

pipe:indoor.name: Pipe:Indoor
pipe:indoor.memo: Pipe model with transport delay and heat transfer to the environment.

zonecontrol:thermostat:temperatureandhum.name: ZoneControl:Thermostat:TemperatureAndHumidity
zonecontrol:thermostat:temperatureandhum.memo: This object modifies a ZoneControl:Thermostat object to effect temperature control based on zone air humidity conditions.

fields.name: Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneControl:Thermostat object whose operation is to be modified to effect temperature control based on zone air humidity conditions. If the ZoneControl: Thermostat object references a ZoneList, simply enter the name of the ZoneControl:Thermostat object and this temperature and humidity thermostat control will be applied to all zones in the ZoneList. If the ZoneControl:Thermostat object references a ZoneList but it is desired that only a single zone within the ZoneList be controlled based on temperature and humidity control, then the name to be put here is <Zone Name> <Thermostat Name> where the Thermostat Name is the the name of the ZoneControl:Thermostat object.

fields.name: Dehumidifying Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be in Relative Humidity (percent)

fields.name: Overcool Constant Range
fields.memo: Maximum Overcool temperature range for cooling setpoint reduction. Used with Dehumidification Control Type = Overcool. A value of 0.0 indicates no zone temperature overcooling will be provided to gain additional dehumidification.

fields.name: Overcool Range Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values of 0.0 indicates no zone temperature overcooling will be provided to gain additional dehumidification. Schedule values should be >= 0 and <= 3 (deltaC).

fields.name: Overcool Control Ratio
fields.memo: The value of this input field is used to adjust the cooling setpoint temperature (established by the associated ZoneControl:Thermostat object) downward based on the difference between the zone air relative humidity level and the dehumidifying relative humidity setpoint.

zonehvac:baseboard:convective:electric.name: ZoneHVAC:Baseboard:Convective:Electric
zonehvac:baseboard:convective:electric.memo: Electric baseboard heater, convection-only. Natural convection electric heating unit.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

setpointmanager:multizone:maximumhumidit.name: SetpointManager:MultiZone:MaximumHumidity:Average
setpointmanager:multizone:maximumhumidit.memo: This setpoint manager sets the average supply air maximum humidity ratio based on moisture load requirements of all controlled zones in an air loop served by a central air-conditioner.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the humidity ratio will be set

groundheattransfer:slab:materials.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:Materials
groundheattransfer:slab:materials.memo: Object gives an overall description of the slab ground heat transfer model.

fields.name: NMAT: Number of materials
fields.memo: This field specifies the number of different materials that will be used in the model. Typically only a ground material and a slab material are used. (2 materials)

fields.name: ALBEDO: Surface Albedo: No Snow
fields.memo: Two fields specify the albedo value of the surface: first for no snow coverage days; second for days with snow coverage. The albedo is the solar reflectivity of the surface, and can vary from 0.05 for blacktop to 0.95 for fresh snow. Typical values for North America reported by Bahnfleth range from 0.16 to 0.4.

fields.name: EPSLW: Surface Emissivity: No Snow
fields.memo: EPSLW (No Snow and Snow) specifies the long wavelength (thermal) emissivity of the ground surface. primarily important for nighttime radiation to sky. typical value .95

fields.name: Z0: Surface Roughness: No Snow
fields.memo: fields Z0 (No Snow and Snow) describe the height at which an experimentally velocity profile goes to zero. typical value= .75 cm

fields.name: Z0: Surface Roughness: Snow
fields.memo: typical value= .05 cm

fields.name: HIN: Indoor HConv: Downward Flow
fields.memo: These fields specify the combined convective and radiative heat transfer coefficient between the slab top inside surface and the room air for the cases where heat is flowing downward, and upward. The program toggles between the two if the direction of the heat flux changes. Typical values can be found in the ASHRAE Handbook of Fundamentals, but should be about 6 W/(m2-K) for downward heat flow and 9 W/(m2-K) for upward heat flow. typical value= 4-10

fields.name: HIN: Indoor HConv: Upward
fields.memo: typical value= 4-10

runperiodcontrol:daylightsavingtime.name: RunPeriodControl:DaylightSavingTime
runperiodcontrol:daylightsavingtime.memo: This object sets up the daylight saving time period for any RunPeriod. Ignores any daylight saving time period on the weather file and uses this definition. These are not used with SizingPeriod:DesignDay objects. Use with SizingPeriod:WeatherFileDays object can be controlled in that object.

fields.name: End Date
fields.memo: Dates can be several formats: <number>/<number>  (month/day) <number> <Month> <Month> <number> <Nth> <Weekday> in <Month) Last <WeekDay> in <Month> <Month> can be January, February, March, April, May, June, July, August, September, October, November, December Months can be the first 3 letters of the month <Weekday> can be Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday <Nth> can be 1 or 1st, 2 or 2nd, etc. up to 5(?)

chiller:combustionturbine.name: Chiller:CombustionTurbine
chiller:combustionturbine.memo: This chiller model is the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Chiller performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to third order polynomial equations.  Three sets of coefficients are required.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the max flow & for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is not used for Condenser Type = AirCooled or EvaporativelyCooled

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 2 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 3 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Chilled Water Outlet Temperature Lower Limit
fields.memo: Special Gas Turbine Chiller Parameters Below

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of Temperature Based Fuel Input Curve
Coefficient 2 of Temperature Based Fuel Input Curve
Coefficient 3 of Temperature Based Fuel Input Curve
Coefficient 1 of Exhaust Gas Temperature Curve
Coefficient 2 of Exhaust Gas Temperature Curve
Coefficient 3 of Exhaust Gas Temperature Curve
Coefficient 1 of Temperature Based Exhaust Gas Temperature Curve
Coefficient 2 of Temperature Based Exhaust Gas Temperature Curve
Coefficient 3 of Temperature Based Exhaust Gas Temperature Curve
Coefficient 1 of Recovery Lube Heat Curve
Coefficient 2 of Recovery Lube Heat Curve
Coefficient 3 of Recovery Lube Heat Curve
Coefficient 1 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
Coefficient 2 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: typical value .9

fields.name: Maximum Exhaust Flow per Unit of Power Output
Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered.

fields.name: Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, The heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the chiller is not operating.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Condenser Heat Recovery Relative Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This optional field is the fraction of total rejected heat that can be recovered at full load. Also used to autosize Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate as a fraction of Design Condenser Water Flow Rate.

fields.name: Turbine Engine Efficiency
fields.memo: This optional field is the nominal turbine engine efficiency and is used when Gas Turbine Engine Capacity is set to Autosize

externalinterface.name: ExternalInterface
externalinterface.memo: This object activates the external interface of EnergyPlus. If the object ExternalInterface is present, then all ExtnernalInterface:* objects will receive their values from the BCVTB interface or from FMUs at each zone time step. If this object is not present, then the values of these objects will be fixed at the value declared in the "initial value" field of the corresponding object, and a warning will be written to the EnergyPlus error file.

fields.name: Name of External Interface
fields.memo: Name of External Interface Currently, the only valid entries are PtolemyServer, FunctionalMockupUnitImport, and FunctionalMockupUnitExport.

airflownetwork:multizone:component:simpl.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:SimpleOpening
airflownetwork:multizone:component:simpl.memo: This object specifies the properties of air flow through windows and doors (window, door and glass door heat transfer subsurfaces) when they are closed or open.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient When Opening is Closed
fields.memo: Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference. Enter the coefficient used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when opening (window or door) is closed.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent When Opening is Closed
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when opening (window or door) is closed.

fields.name: Minimum Density Difference for Two-Way Flow
fields.memo: Enter the minimum density difference above which two-way flow may occur due to stack effect.

fields.name: Discharge Coefficient
fields.memo: The Discharge Coefficient indicates the fractional effectiveness for air flow through a window or door at that Opening Factor.

output:table:timebins.name: Output:Table:TimeBins
output:table:timebins.memo: Produces a bin report in the table output file which shows the amount of time in hours that occurs in different bins for a single specific output variable or meter. Two different types of binning are reported: by month and by hour of the day.

fields.name: Key Value
fields.memo: use '*' (without quotes) to apply this variable to all keys

fields.name: Interval Start
fields.memo: The lowest value for the intervals being binned into.

fields.name: Interval Size
fields.memo: The size of the bins starting with Interval start.

fields.name: Interval Count
fields.memo: The number of bins used. The number of hours below the start of the Lowest bin and above the value of the last bin are also shown.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Optional schedule name. Binning is performed for non-zero hours. Binning always performed if left blank.

fields.name: Variable Type
fields.memo: Optional input on the type of units for the variable used by other fields in the object.

materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.name: MaterialProperty:HeatAndMoistureTransfer:SorptionIsotherm

fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

zonehvac:coolingpanel:radiantconvective:.name: ZoneHVAC:CoolingPanel:RadiantConvective:Water
zonehvac:coolingpanel:radiantconvective:.memo: The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 100, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the cooling design capacity for scalable sizing. CoolingDesignCapacity => selected when the design cooling capacity value is specified or auto-sized. CapacityPerFloorArea => selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from user specified cooling capacity per floor area and total floor area of cooled zone served by the hydrolic unit. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity => is selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design cooling capacity of the system.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design cooling capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method CoolingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the cooling design capacity per total floor area of cooled zones served by the unit. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto-sized cooling design capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: Temperature on which unit is controlled

fields.name: Fraction of Radiant Energy Incident on People

loadprofile:plant.name: LoadProfile:Plant
loadprofile:plant.memo: Used to simulate a scheduled plant loop demand profile.  Load and flow rate are specified using schedules. Positive values are heating loads, and negative values are cooling loads. The actual load met is dependent on the performance of the supply loop components.

fields.name: Load Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are load in [W]

faultmodel:thermostatoffset.name: FaultModel:ThermostatOffset
faultmodel:thermostatoffset.memo: This object describes fault of thermostat offset

fields.name: Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneControl:Thermostat object.

coilsystem:cooling:dx:heatexchangerassis.name: CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted
coilsystem:cooling:dx:heatexchangerassis.memo: Virtual component consisting of a direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and an air-to-air heat exchanger. The air-to-air heat exchanger precools the air entering the cooling coil and reuses this energy to reheat the supply air leaving the cooling coil. This heat exchange process improves the latent removal performance of the cooling coil (lower sensible heat ratio).

lifecyclecost:parameters.name: LifeCycleCost:Parameters
lifecyclecost:parameters.memo: Provides inputs related to the overall life-cycle analysis. It establishes many of the assumptions used in computing the present value. It is important that when comparing the results of multiple simulations that the fields in the LifeCycleCost:Parameters objects are the same for all the simulations. When this object is present the tabular report file will contain the Life-Cycle Cost Report.

fields.name: Discounting Convention
fields.memo: The field specifies if the discounting of future costs should be computed as occurring at the end of each year or the middle of each year or the beginning of each year. The most common discounting convention uses the end of each year.

fields.name: Inflation Approach
fields.memo: This field is used to determine if the analysis should use constant dollars or current dollars which is related to how inflation is treated. If ConstantDollar is selected then the Real Discount Rate input is used and it excludes the rate of inflation. If CurrentDollar is selected then the Nominal Discount Rate input is used and it includes the rate of inflation.

fields.name: Real Discount Rate
fields.memo: Enter the real discount rate as a decimal. For a 3% rate enter the value 0.03. This input is used when the Inflation Approach is ConstantDollar. The real discount rate reflects the interest rates needed to make current and future expenditures have comparable equivalent values when general inflation is ignored. When Inflation Approach is set to CurrentDollar this input is ignored.

fields.name: Nominal Discount Rate
fields.memo: Enter the nominal discount rate as a decimal. For a 5% rate enter the value 0.05. This input is used when the Inflation Approach is CurrentDollar. The real discount rate reflects the interest rates needed to make current and future expenditures have comparable equivalent values when general inflation is included. When Inflation Approach is set to ConstantDollar this input is ignored.

fields.name: Inflation
fields.memo: Enter the rate of inflation for general goods and services as a decimal. For a 2% rate enter the value 0.02.

fields.name: Base Date Month
fields.memo: Enter the month that is the beginning of study period also known as the beginning of the base period.

fields.name: Base Date Year
fields.memo: Enter the four digit year that is the beginning of study period such as 2010. The study period is also known as the base period.

fields.name: Service Date Month
fields.memo: Enter the month that is the beginning of building occupancy. Energy costs computed by EnergyPlus are assumed to occur during the year following the service date. The service date must be the same or later than the Base Date. This field could also be referred to as part of beneficial occupancy date.

fields.name: Service Date Year
fields.memo: Enter the four digit year that is the beginning of occupancy such as 2010.

fields.name: Length of Study Period in Years
fields.memo: Enter the number of years of the study period. It is the number of years that the study continues based on the start at the base date. The default value is 25 years. Only integers may be used indicating whole years.

fields.name: Tax rate
fields.memo: Enter the overall marginal tax rate for the project costs. This does not include energy or water taxes. The tax rate entered should be based on the marginal tax rate for the entity and not the average tax rate. Enter the tax rate results in present value calculations after taxes. Most analyses do not factor in the impact of taxes and assume that all options under consideration have roughly the same tax impact. Due to this many times the tax rate can be left to default to zero and the present value results before taxes are used to make decisions. The value should be entered as a decimal value. For 15% enter 0.15. For an analysis that does not include tax impacts enter 0.0.

fields.name: Depreciation Method
fields.memo: For an analysis that includes income tax impacts this entry describes how capital costs are depreciated. Only one depreciation method may be used for an analysis and is applied to all capital expenditures.

hvacsystemrootfindingalgorithm.name: HVACSystemRootFindingAlgorithm
hvacsystemrootfindingalgorithm.memo: Specifies a HVAC system solver algorithm to find a root

fields.name: Number of Iterations Before Algorithm Switch
fields.memo: This field is used when RegulaFalsiThenBisection or BisectionThenRegulaFalsi is entered. When iteration number is greater than the value, algorithm switches.

zonehvac:outdoorairunit:equipmentlist.name: ZoneHVAC:OutdoorAirUnit:EquipmentList
zonehvac:outdoorairunit:equipmentlist.memo: Equipment list for components in a ZoneHVAC:OutdoorAirUnit. Components are simulated sequentially in the order given in the equipment list.

setpointmanager:singlezone:reheat.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:Reheat
setpointmanager:singlezone:reheat.memo: This setpoint manager detects the control zone load, zone inlet node flow rate, and zone node temperature and calculates a setpoint temperature for the supply air that will satisfy the zone load (heating or cooling) for the control zone. This setpoint manager is not limited to reheat applications.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

materialproperty:phasechange.name: MaterialProperty:PhaseChange
materialproperty:phasechange.memo: Additional properties for temperature dependent thermal conductivity and enthalpy for Phase Change Materials (PCM) HeatBalanceAlgorithm = CondFD(ConductionFiniteDifference) solution algorithm only. Constructions with this should use the detailed CondFD process. Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms

fields.name: Temperature Coefficient for Thermal Conductivity
fields.memo: The base temperature is 20C. This is the thermal conductivity change per degree excursion from 20C. This variable conductivity function is overridden by the VariableThermalConductivity object, if present.

fields.name: Temperature 1
fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function

fields.name: Enthalpy 1
fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 1

fields.name: Temperature 2
fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 2

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 3

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 5

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 8

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 1

fields.name: Temperature 10

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 2

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 3

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 14

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 15

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 16

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function

fields.memo: for Temperature-enthalpy function corresponding to temperature 16

shading:building.name: Shading:Building
shading:building.memo: used for shading elements such as trees, other buildings, parts of this building not being modeled these items are relative to the current building and would move with relative geometry

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of shading device (S=180,N=0,E=90,W=270)

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Starting coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Shade

coil:heating:dx:variablerefrigerantflow.name: Coil:Heating:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow
coil:heating:dx:variablerefrigerantflow.memo: Variable refrigerant flow (VRF) direct expansion (DX) heating coil (air-to-air heat pump). Used with ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow. Condensing unit is modeled separately, see AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow.

fields.name: Availability Schedule
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point outside dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outside wet-bulb temp 6.11 C rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wetbulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: volume flow rate corresponding to rated total capacity should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated heating capacity

fields.name: Heating Capacity Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
Heating Capacity Modifier Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

windowmaterial:screen:equivalentlayer.name: WindowMaterial:Screen:EquivalentLayer
windowmaterial:screen:equivalentlayer.memo: Equivalent layer window screen physical properties. Can only be located on the exterior side of a window construction.

fields.name: Screen Beam-Beam Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-beam transmittance of the screen material at normal incidence. This input field is the same as the material openness area fraction and can be autocalculated from the wire spacing and wire and diameter. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse solar transmittance of the screen material at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse solar reflectance of the screen material at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Beam-Beam Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-beam visible transmittance of the screen material at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Beam-Diffuse Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse visible transmittance of the screen material at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Beam-Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Beam-diffuse visible reflectance of the screen material at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Infrared Transmittance
fields.memo: The long-wave hemispherical transmittance of the screen material. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: The long-wave hemispherical emissivity of the screen material. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Screen Wire Spacing
fields.memo: Spacing assumed to be the same in both directions.

fields.name: Screen Wire Diameter
fields.memo: Diameter assumed to be the same in both directions.

utilitycost:tariff.name: UtilityCost:Tariff
utilitycost:tariff.memo: Defines the name of a utility cost tariff, the type of tariff, and other details about the overall tariff. Each other object that is part of the tariff model references the tariff name.  See UtilityCost:Charge:Simple, UtilityCost:Charge:Block, UtilityCost:Ratchet, UtilityCost:Qualify, UtilityCost:Variable and UtilityCost:Computation objects.

fields.name: Output Meter Name
fields.memo: The name of any standard meter or custom meter or but usually set to either Electricity:Facility or Gas:Facility

fields.name: Conversion Factor Choice
fields.memo: A choice that allows several different predefined conversion factors to be used; otherwise user defined conversion factors are used as defined in the next two fields. If left blank m3 is used for water meters and kWh are used for all other meters.

fields.name: Energy Conversion Factor
fields.memo: Is a multiplier used to convert energy into the units specified by the utility in their tariff. If left blank it defaults to 1 (no conversion). This field should will be used only if Conversion Factor Choice is set to UserDefined.  Within EnergyPlus energy always has units of J (joules).  For conversion from J to kWh use the value of 0.0000002778. This is also used for all objects that reference the UtilityCost:Tariff.

fields.name: Demand Conversion Factor
fields.memo: Is a multiplier used to convert demand into the units specified by the utility in their tariff. If left blank it defaults to 1 (no conversion).  This field should will be used only if Conversion Factor Choice is set to UserDefined.  Within EnergyPlus demand always has units of J/s (joules/sec) which equivalent to W (watts).  For conversion from W to kW use the value of 0.001. This is also used for all objects that reference the UtilityCost:Tariff.

fields.name: Time of Use Period Schedule Name
fields.memo: The name of the schedule that defines the time-of-use periods that occur each day. The values for the different variables are: 1 for Peak. 2 for Shoulder. 3 for OffPeak. 4 for MidPeak. The following variables are created automatically if these different periods are used in the schedule and include: TotalEnergy, TotalDemand, PeakEnergy, PeakDemand, ShoulderEnergy, ShoulderDemand, OffPeakEnergy, OffPeakDemand, MidPeakEnergy, MidPeakDemand Some special variables are created that include: PeakExceedsOffPeak, OffPeakExceedsPeak, PeakExceedsMidPeak, MidPeakExceedsPeak, PeakExceedsShoulder, ShoulderExceedsPeak, Others include: PeakAndShoulderEnergy, PeakAndShoulderDemand, PeakAndMidPeakEnergy, PeakAndMidPeakDemand, ShoulderAndOffPeakEnergy, ShoulderAndOffPeakDemand, PeakAndOffPeakEnergy, PeakAndOffPeakDemand, RealTimePriceCosts, AboveCustomerBaseCosts, BelowCustomerBaseCosts, AboveCustomerBaseEnergy, BelowCustomerBaseEnergy

fields.name: Season Schedule Name
fields.memo: The name of a schedule that defines the seasons.  The schedule values are: 1 for Winter. 2 for Spring. 3 for Summer. 4 for Autumn. Variables are automatically created if a season schedule is used. These variables are set to 1 within the season and 0 for the months that are not in the season. The variables are: IsWinter, IsNotWinter, IsSpring, IsNotSpring, IsSummer, IsNotSummer, IsAutumn, IsNotAutumn.

fields.name: Month Schedule Name
fields.memo: The name of the schedule that defines the billing periods of the year. Normally this entry is allowed to default and a schedule will be internally used that has the breaks between billing periods occurring at the same time as the breaks between months i.e. at midnight prior to the first day of the month. If other billing periods are used such as two month cycles or a single bill for an entire season such as some natural gas companies do in the summer then the month schedule may be used to redefine it. Make sure that the month schedule and season schedule are consistent otherwise an error will be issued.

fields.name: Demand Window Length
fields.memo: The determination of demand can vary by utility. Some utilities use the peak instantaneous demand measured but most use a fifteen minute average demand or a one hour average demand. Some gas utilities measure demand as the use during the peak day or peak week.

fields.name: Monthly Charge or Variable Name
fields.memo: The fixed monthly service charge that many utilities have.  The entry may be numeric and gets added to the ServiceCharges variable or if a variable name is entered here its values for each month are used.

fields.name: Minimum Monthly Charge or Variable Name
fields.memo: The minimum total charge for the tariff or if a variable name is entered here its values for each month are used.

fields.name: Real Time Pricing Charge Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used with real time pricing rates. The name of a schedule that contains the cost of energy for that particular time period of the year. Real time rates can be modeled using a charge schedule with the actual real time prices entered in the schedule.

fields.name: Customer Baseline Load Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used with real time pricing rates. The name of a schedule that contains the baseline energy use for the customer. Many real time rates apply the charges as a credit or debit only to the difference between the baseline use and the actual use.

fields.name: Group Name
fields.memo: The group name of the tariff such as distribution transmission supplier etc. If more than one tariff with the same group name is present and qualifies only the lowest cost tariff is used. Usually the group name field is left blank which results in all tariffs using the same meter variable being compared and the lowest cost one being selected.

fields.name: Buy Or Sell
fields.memo: Sets whether the tariff is used for buying selling or both to the utility.  This should be allowed to default to buyFromUtility unless a power generation system is included in the building that may generate more power than the building needs during the year

fan:componentmodel.name: Fan:ComponentModel
fan:componentmodel.memo: A detailed fan type for constant-air-volume (CAV) and variable-air-volume (VAV) systems. It includes inputs that describe the air-distribution system as well as the fan, drive belt (if used), motor, and variable-frequency-drive (if used).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Fan Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Applied to specified or autosized max fan airflow

fields.name: Fan Wheel Diameter
fields.memo: Diameter of wheel outer circumference

fields.name: Fan Outlet Area
fields.memo: Area at fan outlet plane for determining discharge velocity pressure

fields.name: Maximum Fan Static Efficiency
fields.memo: Maximum ratio between power delivered to air and fan shaft input power Determined from fan performance data

fields.name: Euler Number at Maximum Fan Static Efficiency
fields.memo: Euler number (Eu) determined from fan performance data

fields.name: Maximum Dimensionless Fan Airflow
fields.memo: Corresponds to maximum ratio between fan airflow and fan shaft rotational speed for specified fan wheel diameter Determined from fan performance data

fields.name: Motor Fan Pulley Ratio
fields.memo: Ratio of motor pulley diameter to fan pulley diameter

fields.name: Belt Maximum Torque
fields.memo: Maximum torque transmitted by belt

fields.name: Belt Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Applied to specified or autosized max torque transmitted by belt

fields.name: Belt Fractional Torque Transition
fields.memo: Region 1 to 2 curve transition for belt normalized efficiency

fields.name: Motor Maximum Speed
fields.memo: Maximum rotational speed of fan motor shaft

fields.name: Maximum Motor Output Power
fields.memo: Maximum power input to drive belt by motor

fields.name: Motor Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Applied to specified or autosized motor output power

fields.name: Motor In Airstream Fraction
fields.memo: 0.0 means motor outside air stream 1.0 means motor inside air stream

fields.name: VFD Efficiency Type
fields.memo: Efficiency depends on fraction of full-load motor speed Efficiency depends on  fraction of full-load motor input power If field blank, then assumes constant VFD efficiency (0.97)

fields.name: Maximum VFD Output Power
fields.memo: Maximum power input to motor by VFD

fields.name: VFD Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Applied to specified or autosized VFD output power

fields.name: Fan Pressure Rise Curve Name
fields.memo: Pressure rise depends on volumetric flow, system resistances, system leakage, and duct static pressure set point

fields.name: Duct Static Pressure Reset Curve Name
fields.memo: Function of fan volumetric flow Minimum and maximum fan airflows correspond respectively to minimum and maximum duct static pressure set points

fields.name: Normalized Fan Static Efficiency Curve Name-Non-Stall Region
fields.memo: xfan <= 0 Curve should have maximum of 1.0

fields.name: Normalized Fan Static Efficiency Curve Name-Stall Region
fields.memo: xfan > 0 Curve should have maximum of 1.0

fields.name: Normalized Dimensionless Airflow Curve Name-Non-Stall Region
fields.memo: xspd <= 0 Curve should have maximum of 1.0

fields.name: Normalized Dimensionless Airflow Curve Name-Stall Region
fields.memo: xspd > 0 Curve should have maximum of 1.0

fields.name: Maximum Belt Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: Determines maximum fan drive belt efficiency in log space as function of xbelt,max Curve should have minimum of -4.6 and maximum of 0.0 If field blank, assumes output of curve is always 1.0

fields.name: Normalized Belt Efficiency Curve Name - Region 1
fields.memo: Region 1 (0 <= xbelt < xbelt,trans) Curve should have minimum > 0.0 and maximum of 1.0 If field blank, assumes output of curve is always 1.0 in Region 1

fields.name: Normalized Belt Efficiency Curve Name - Region 2
fields.memo: Region 2 (xbelt,trans <= xbelt <= 1) Curve should have minimum > 0.0 and maximum of 1.0 If field blank, assumes output of curve is always 1.0 in Region 2

fields.name: Normalized Belt Efficiency Curve Name - Region 3
fields.memo: Determines normalized drive belt efficiency Region 3 (xbelt > 1) Curve should have minimum > 0.0 and maximum of 1.0 If field blank, assumes output of curve is always 1.0 in Region 3

fields.name: Maximum Motor Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve should have minimum > 0.0 and maximum of 1.0 If field blank, assumes output of curve is always 1.0

fields.name: Normalized Motor Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve should have minimum > 0.0 and maximum of 1.0 If field blank, assumes output of curve is always 1.0

fields.name: VFD Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: Determines VFD efficiency as function of motor load or speed fraction Curve should have minimum > 0.0 and maximum of 1.0 If field blank, assumes constant VFD efficiency (0.97)

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

zonehvac:energyrecoveryventilator.name: ZoneHVAC:EnergyRecoveryVentilator
zonehvac:energyrecoveryventilator.memo: This compound component models a stand-alone energy recovery ventilator (ERV) that conditions outdoor ventilation air and supplies that air directly to a zone. The ERV unit is modeled as a collection of components: air-to-air heat exchanger, supply air fan, exhaust air fan and an optional controller to avoid overheating of the supply air (economizer or free cooling operation).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Heat Exchanger Name
fields.memo: Heat exchanger type must be HeatExchanger:AirToAir:SensibleAndLatent

fields.name: Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This flow rate must match the supply fan's air flow rate.

fields.name: Exhaust Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This flow rate must match the supply fan air flow rate.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Fan type must be Fan:OnOff or Fan:SystemModel

fields.name: Exhaust Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Fan type must be Fan:OnOff or Fan:SystemModel

fields.name: Controller Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneHVAC:EnergyRecoveryVentilator:Controller object.

fields.name: Ventilation Rate per Unit Floor Area
fields.memo: 0.000508 m3/s-m2 corresponds to 0.1 ft3/min-ft2 Used only when supply and exhaust air flow rates are autosized.

fields.name: Ventilation Rate per Occupant
fields.memo: 0.00236 m3/s-person corresponds to 5 ft3/min-person Used only when supply and exhaust air flow rates are autosized.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

surfaceproperty:convectioncoefficients:m.name: SurfaceProperty:ConvectionCoefficients:MultipleSurface
surfaceproperty:convectioncoefficients:m.memo: Allow user settable interior and/or exterior convection coefficients. Note that some other factors may limit the lower bounds for these values, such as for windows, the interior convection coefficient must be >.28, for trombe wall algorithm selection (zone), the interior convection coefficient must be >.1 for TARP interior convection, the lower limit is also .1 Minimum and maximum limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Defaults in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object are [.1,1000].

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 1
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Value, min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 1 Schedule Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Schedule,  min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 1 User Curve Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type = UserCurve

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 2
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Value, min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 2 Schedule Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type=Schedule,  min and max limits are set in HeatBalanceAlgorithm object. Default limits are Minimum >= 0.1 and Maximum <= 1000

fields.name: Convection Coefficient 2 User Curve Name
fields.memo: used if Convection Type = UserCurve

zoneproperty:localenvironment.name: ZoneProperty:LocalEnvironment
zoneproperty:localenvironment.memo: This object defines the local environment properties of a zone object. A corresponding outdoor air node should be defined and linked to the zone object.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a zone object

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an OutdoorAir:Node object

energymanagementsystem:constructionindex.name: EnergyManagementSystem:ConstructionIndexVariable
energymanagementsystem:constructionindex.memo: Declares EMS variable that identifies a construction

evaporativefluidcooler:twospeed.name: EvaporativeFluidCooler:TwoSpeed
evaporativefluidcooler:twospeed.memo: This model is based on Merkel's theory, which is also the basis for the cooling tower model in EnergyPlus. The Evaporative fluid cooler is modeled as a counter flow heat exchanger.

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of fluid cooler water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of fluid cooler water outlet node

fields.name: High Fan Speed Air Flow Rate
High Fan Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at high speed

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Low speed air flow rate must be less than high speed air flow rate

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Air Flow Rate Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at low speed

fields.name: Low Fan Speed Fan Power Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define fluid cooler thermal performance by specifying the fluid cooler UA and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the fluid cooler Standard Design Capacity or by specifying Design Capacity for Non standard conditions.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

fields.name: Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio
High Speed Standard Design Capacity
fields.memo: Standard design capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt (3 gpm/ton). Standard design capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25) gives the actual fluid cooler heat rejection at these operating conditions. Only used for Performance Input Method = StandardDesignCapacity; for other input methods, this field is ignored. The standard conditions mentioned above for Standard design capacity are already specified in the EnergyPlus. So the input fields such as design entering water temp., design entering air wet-bulb and dry-bulb temp. and design water flow rate, if provided in the input, will be ignored for the StandardDesignCapacity performance input method. Also, the standard conditions are for water as a fluid type so this performance input method can only be used with water as a fluid type (as specified in CondenserLoop object).

fields.name: Low Speed Standard Design Capacity
fields.memo: Standard design capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt (3 gpm/ton). Standard design capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25) gives the actual fluid cooler heat rejection at these operating conditions. Only used for Performance Input Method = StandardDesignCapacity; for other input methods, this field is ignored. The standard conditions mentioned above for Standard design capacity are already specified in the EnergyPlus. So the input fields such as design entering water temp., design entering air wet-bulb and dry-bulb temp. and design water flow rate, if provided in the input, will be ignored for the StandardDesignCapacity performance input method. Also, the standard conditions are for water as a fluid type so this performance input method can only be used with water as a fluid type (as specified in CondenserLoop object).

fields.name: Low Speed Standard Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: High Fan Speed U-factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored.

fields.name: Low Fan Speed U-factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate; for other input methods, this field is ignored. Low speed fluid cooler UA must be less than high speed fluid cooler UA

fields.name: Low Fan Speed U-Factor Times Area Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the Performance Input Method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate

fields.name: Design Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Input value is ignored if fluid cooler Performance Input Method= StandardDesignCapacity

fields.name: High Speed User Specified Design Capacity
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored.

fields.name: Low Speed User Specified Design Capacity
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored.

fields.name: Low Speed User Specified Design Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: Design Entering Water Temperature
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored. Design Entering Water Temperature must be greater than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Temperature
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored. Design Entering Air Temperature must be greater than Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored. Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature must be less than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: High Speed Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Evaporation Loss Factor
fields.memo: Rate of water evaporation from the Fluid Cooler and lost to the outdoor air [%/K] Empirical correlation is used to calculate default loss factor if it not explicitly provided.

fields.name: Drift Loss Percent
fields.memo: Default value is under investigation. For now cooling tower's default value is taken.

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the Evaporative Fluid Cooler. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the Evaporative Fluid Cooler in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. Default value is under investigation. For now cooling tower's default value is taken.

fields.name: Blowdown Makeup Water Usage Schedule Name
fields.memo: Makeup water usage due to blowdown results from occasionally draining some amount of water in the Evaporative Fluid Cooler basin to purge scale or other contaminants to reduce their concentration in order to maintain an acceptable level of water quality. Schedule values should reflect water usage in m3/s.

groundheattransfer:basement:simparameter.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:SimParameters
groundheattransfer:basement:simparameter.memo: Specifies certain parameters that control the Basement preprocessor ground heat transfer simulation.

fields.name: F: Multiplier for the ADI solution
fields.memo: 0<F<1.0, typically 0.1 (0.3 for high k soil - saturated sand is about 2.6 w/m-K)

fields.name: IYRS: Maximum number of yearly iterations:
fields.memo: typically 15-30]

utilitycost:charge:block.name: UtilityCost:Charge:Block
utilitycost:charge:block.memo: Used to compute energy and demand charges (or any other charges) that are structured in blocks of charges. Multiple UtilityCost:Charge:Block objects may be defined for a single tariff and they will be added together.

fields.name: Utility Cost Charge Block Name
fields.memo: Charge Variable Name This is the name associated with the UtilityCost:Charge:Block object and will appear in the report. In addition the results of the UtilityCost:Charge:Block are stored in a variable with the same name. That way the results may be used for further calculation.

fields.name: Tariff Name
fields.memo: The name of the UtilityCost:Tariff that is associated with this UtilityCost:Charge:Block.

fields.name: Source Variable
fields.memo: The name of the source used by the UtilityCost:Charge:Block.  This is usually the name of the variable holding the energy or demand but may also be the name of any variable including the subtotal or basis if other charges are based on those. Typical values include totalEnergy totalDemand EnergyCharges DemandCharges ServiceCharges Basis Adjustments Surcharges Subtotal Taxes and Total. If it is a time-of-use rate then peakEnergy peakDemand shoulderEnergy shoulderDemand offPeakEnergy offPeakDemand midPeakEnergy and midPeakDemand. In addition see the Tariff Report to see other native variables that may be available. Also you can create additional user defined variables to model complex tariffs.

fields.name: Season
fields.memo: If this is set to annual the calculations are performed for the UtilityCost:Charge:Block for the entire year (all months) otherwise it is calculated only for those months in the season defined.

fields.name: Category Variable Name
fields.memo: This field shows where the charge should be added. The reason to enter this field appropriately is so that the charge gets reported in a reasonable category.  The charge automatically gets added to the variable that is the category.

fields.name: Remaining Into Variable
fields.memo: If the blocks do not use all of the energy or demand from the source some energy and demand remains then the remaining amount should be assigned to a variable. If no variable is assigned and some amount of energy or demand is not used in the block structure a warning will be issued.

fields.name: Block Size Multiplier Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: The sizes of the blocks are usually used directly but if a value or a variable is entered here the block sizes entered in the rest of the charge are first multiplied by the entered value prior to being used. This is common for rates that are kWh/kW rates and in that case the variable that holds the monthly total electric demand would be entered.  If no value is entered a default value of one is assumed so that the block sizes remain exactly as entered.  This field is unusual for the EnergyPlus syntax because it can be either a number or a name of a variable.

fields.name: Block Size 1 Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: The size of the block of the charges is entered here. For most rates that use multiple blocks this will be the value for the block size. Using remaining may be used when the remaining amount should be included in that block.  This field is unusual because it can be either a number or a name of a variable.

fields.name: Block 1 Cost per Unit Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: The cost of the block. This field is unusual for the EnergyPlus syntax because it can be either a number or a name of a variable.

fields.name: Block Size 2 Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: The size of the block of the charges is entered here. For most rates that use multiple blocks this will be the value for the block size. Using remaining may be used when the remaining amount should be included in that block.  This field is unusual because it can be either a number or a name of a variable.

designspecification:airterminal:sizing.name: DesignSpecification:AirTerminal:Sizing
designspecification:airterminal:sizing.memo: This object is used to scale the sizing of air terminal units.

fields.name: Fraction of Design Cooling Load
fields.memo: The fraction of the design sensible cooling load to be met by this terminal unit. This fraction is applied after the Zone Cooling Sizing Factor (see Sizing:Zone).

fields.name: Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference Ratio
fields.memo: This ratio adjusts the supply air temperature difference used to calculate the cooling design supply air flow rate for this terminal unit.

fields.name: Fraction of Design Heating Load
fields.memo: The fraction of the design sensible heating load to be met by this terminal unit. This fraction is applied after the Zone Heating Sizing Factor (see Sizing:Zone).

fields.name: Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference Ratio
fields.memo: This ratio adjusts the supply air temperature difference used to calculate the heating design supply air flow rate for this terminal unit.

fields.name: Fraction of Minimum Outdoor Air Flow
fields.memo: The fraction of the zone minimum outdoor air requirement to be met by this terminal unit.

groundheattransfer:slab:equivalentslab.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:EquivalentSlab
groundheattransfer:slab:equivalentslab.memo: Using an equivalent slab allows non-rectangular shapes to be modeled accurately. Object uses the area - perimeter (area/perimeter) ratio to determine the size of an equivalent rectangular slab. EnergyPlus users normally use this option.

fields.name: APRatio: The area to perimeter ratio for this slab
fields.memo: Equivalent square slab is simulated,  side is 4*APRatio.

fields.name: SLABDEPTH: Thickness of slab on grade
fields.memo: This field specifies the thickness of the slab. The slab top surface is level with the ground surface, so this is the depth into the ground. The slab depth has a significant effect on the temperature calculation, and it is also important for the auto-grid process. The finite difference grids are set in such a way that they use the slab thickness to determine the vertical grid spacing. Autogridding will fail if the slab thickness is specified larger than 0.25 meters.

fields.name: CLEARANCE: Distance from edge of slab to domain edge
fields.memo: This field specifies the distance from the slab to the edge of the area that will be modeled with the grid system. It is the basic size dimension that is used to set the horizontal extent of the domain. 15 meters is a reasonable value.

fields.name: ZCLEARANCE: Distance from bottom of slab to domain bottom
fields.memo: This field specifies the vertical distance from the slab to the bottom edge of the area that will be modeled with the grid system. 15 meters is a reasonable value.

zonehvac:baseboard:radiantconvective:ele.name: ZoneHVAC:Baseboard:RadiantConvective:Electric
zonehvac:baseboard:radiantconvective:ele.memo: The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 100, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Fraction of Radiant Energy Incident on People

setpointmanager:multizone:minimumhumidit.name: SetpointManager:MultiZone:MinimumHumidity:Average
setpointmanager:multizone:minimumhumidit.memo: This setpoint manager sets the average supply air minimum humidity ratio based on moisture load requirements of all controlled zones in an air loop served by a central air-conditioner.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the humidity ratio will be set

refrigeration:transcriticalsystem.name: Refrigeration:TranscriticalSystem
refrigeration:transcriticalsystem.memo: Detailed transcritical carbon dioxide (CO2) booster refrigeration systems used in supermarkets.  The object allows for modeling either a single stage system with medium-temperature loads or a two stage system with both medium- and low-temperature loads.

fields.name: Medium Temperature Refrigerated Case or Walkin or CaseAndWalkInList Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Refrigeration:Case or Refrigeration:WalkIn object. If there is more than one refrigerated case or walk-in served by this system, enter the name of a Refrigeration:CaseAndWalkInList object. Only medium temperature cases and walk-ins served directly by the system should be included in this list.

fields.name: Low Temperature Refrigerated Case or Walkin or CaseAndWalkInList Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Refrigeration:Case or Refrigeration:WalkIn object. If there is more than one refrigerated case or walk-in served by this system, enter the name of a Refrigeration:CaseAndWalkInList object. Only low temperature cases and walkins served directly by the system should be included in this list.

fields.name: High Pressure Compressor or CompressorList Name
Low Pressure Compressor or CompressorList Name
Refrigeration System Working Fluid Type
fields.memo: Fluid property data for the refrigerant must be entered. The fluid property data, including the objects: FluidProperties:Name, FluidProperties:Temperatures, FluidProperties:Saturated and FluidProperties:Superheated can be copied from the FluidPropertiesRefData.idf dataset

fields.name: Sum UA Suction Piping for Medium Temperature Loads
fields.memo: Use only if you want to include suction piping heat gain in refrigeration load

fields.name: Medium Temperature Suction Piping Zone Name
fields.memo: This will be used to determine the temperature used for distribution piping heat gain and the pipe heat gains as cooling credit for the zone. Required only if Sum UA Distribution Piping for Medium Temperature Loads > 0.0

fields.name: Sum UA Suction Piping for Low Temperature Loads
fields.memo: Use only if you want to include suction piping heat gain in refrigeration load

fields.name: Low Temperature Suction Piping Zone Name
fields.memo: This will be used to determine the temperature used for distribution piping heat gain and the pipe heat gains as cooling credit for the zone. Required only if Sum UA Distribution Piping for Low Temperature Loads > 0.0

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

zonerefrigerationdoormixing.name: ZoneRefrigerationDoorMixing
zonerefrigerationdoormixing.memo: Refrigeration Door Mixing is used for an opening between two zones that are at the same elevation but have different air temperatures.  In this case, the mixing air flow between the two zones is determined by the density difference between the two zones. This would typically be used between two zones in a refrigerated warehouse that are controlled at different temperatures.  It could also be used to model a door to a walk-in refrigerated space if that space were modeled as a zone instead of using the object Refrigeration:WalkIn.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule defines the fraction of the time the refrigeration door is open For example, if the warehouse is closed at night and there are no door openings between two zones, the value for that time period would be 0.
