If doors were propped open, the value  over that time period would be 1.0 If the doors were open about 20% of the time, the value over that period would be 0.2 Schedule values must lie between 0 and 1.0

fields.name: Door Protection Type
fields.memo: Door protection can reduce the air flow through a refrigeration door The default value is "None" Choices: "None", "AirCurtain", and "StripCurtain" A strip curtain reduces the air flow more than an air curtain

chiller:constantcop.name: Chiller:ConstantCOP
chiller:constantcop.memo: This constant COP chiller model provides a means of quickly specifying a Chiller where performance data is not available.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the maximum flow and for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is not used for Condenser Type = AirCooled or EvaporativelyCooled

fields.name: Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the chiller is not operating.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

sizingperiod:weatherfileconditiontype.name: SizingPeriod:WeatherFileConditionType
sizingperiod:weatherfileconditiontype.memo: Use a weather file period for design sizing calculations. EPW weather files are created with typical and extreme periods created heuristically from the weather file data.  For more details on these periods, see AuxiliaryPrograms document.

fields.name: Period Selection
fields.memo: Following is a list of all possible types of Extreme and Typical periods that might be identified in the Weather File. Not all possible types are available for all weather files.

fields.name: Day of Week for Start Day
fields.memo: =[|Sunday|Monday|Tuesday|Wednesday|Thursday|Friday|Saturday|SummerDesignDay|WinterDesignDay| |CustomDay1|CustomDay2]; if you use SummerDesignDay or WinterDesignDay or the CustomDays then this will apply to the whole period; other days (i.e., Monday) will signify a start day and normal sequence of subsequent days

fields.name: Use Weather File Daylight Saving Period
fields.memo: If yes or blank, use daylight saving period as specified on Weatherfile. If no, do not use the daylight saving period as specified on the Weatherfile.

fields.name: Use Weather File Rain and Snow Indicators

windowmaterial:shade.name: WindowMaterial:Shade
windowmaterial:shade.memo: Specifies the properties of window shade materials. Reflectance and emissivity properties are assumed to be the same on both sides of the shade. Shades are considered to be perfect diffusers (all transmitted and reflected radiation is hemispherically-diffuse) independent of angle of incidence.

fields.name: Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Assumed independent of incidence angle

fields.name: Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Assumed same for both sides Assumed independent of incidence angle

fields.name: Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: Assumed independent of incidence angle

fields.name: Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Assumed same for both sides Assumed independent of incidence angle

zonehvac:windowairconditioner.name: ZoneHVAC:WindowAirConditioner
zonehvac:windowairconditioner.memo: Window air conditioner. Forced-convection cooling-only unit with supply fan, direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, and fixed-position outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: currently only one OutdoorAir:Mixer object type is available.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works when continuous fan operation is used the entire simulation (all supply air fan operating mode schedule values are greater than 0). If any fan operating mode schedule values are 0 a Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff object must be used.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Fan type Fan:ConstantVolume is used with continuous fan and fan type Fan:OnOff is used with cycling Fan.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule Name values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling coil). Schedule values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this field is left blank.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

hvactemplate:system:packagedvav.name: HVACTemplate:System:PackagedVAV
hvactemplate:system:packagedvav.memo: Packaged Variable Air Volume (PVAV) air loop with optional heating coil and optional preheat.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on; PVAV System always on.  Schedule is used in availability manager and fan scheduling. Also see "Night Cycle Control" field.

fields.name: Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Supply Fan Minimum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is only used to set a minimum part load on the VAV fan power curve. Autosize or zero is recommended.

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Cooling Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross SHR

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electric power input

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Heating Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the Minimum Outdoor Air Flow Rate If blank, multiplier is always one

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for FixedDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Enthalpy
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor enthalpy limit for FixedEnthalpy economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Minimum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for economizer control. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Supply Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

fields.name: Night Cycle Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Applicable only if Night Cycle Control is Cycle On Control Zone.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Reset Type
fields.memo: Overrides Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name None = no reset, control to Cooling Coil Design Setpoint Temperature or Schedule Warmest = reset as warm as possible yet meet all zone cooling loads at max supply air flow rate OutdoorAirTemperatureReset = reset based on outdoor air temperature (18.0C at 15.6C ODB, to the Cooling Design Setpoint at 26.7C) WarmestTemperatureFirst = reset as warm as possible yet meet all zone cooling loads at min supply air flow rate

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Reset Type
fields.memo: Overrides Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name None = no reset, control to Heating Coil Design Setpoint Temperature or Schedule OutdoorAirTemperatureReset = reset based on outdoor air temperature (Heating Design Setpoint at -6.7C ODB to Heating Design Setpoint minus 5.2C at 10C ODB) min supply air flow rate

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Dehumidification Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Sizing Option
fields.memo: Select whether autosized system supply flow rate is the sum of Coincident or NonCoincident zone air flow rates.

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Return Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

connectorlist.name: ConnectorList
connectorlist.memo: only two connectors allowed per loop if two entered, one must be Connector:Splitter and one must be Connector:Mixer

surfaceproperty:exteriornaturalventedcav.name: SurfaceProperty:ExteriorNaturalVentedCavity
surfaceproperty:exteriornaturalventedcav.memo: Used to describe the decoupled layer, or baffle, and the characteristics of the cavity and openings for naturally ventilated exterior surfaces. This object is also used in conjunction with the OtherSideConditionsModel.

fields.name: Boundary Conditions Model Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel object

fields.name: Thermal Emissivity of Exterior Baffle Material
Effective Thickness of Cavity Behind Exterior Baffle
fields.memo: if corrugated, use average depth

fields.name: Ratio of Actual Surface Area to Projected Surface Area
fields.memo: this parameter is used to help account for corrugations in the collector

fields.name: Effectiveness for Perforations with Respect to Wind
Discharge Coefficient for Openings with Respect to Buoyancy Driven Flow

photovoltaicperformance:sandia.name: PhotovoltaicPerformance:Sandia
photovoltaicperformance:sandia.memo: Describes performance input data needed for specific makes and models of production PV panels using the empirical coefficients assembled by Sandia National Laboratory.

fields.name: Active Area
fields.memo: (m2, single module)

fields.name: Short Circuit Current
fields.memo: (Amps)

fields.name: Open Circuit Voltage
fields.memo: (Volts)

fields.name: Current at Maximum Power Point
fields.memo: (Amps)

fields.name: Voltage at Maximum Power Point
fields.memo: (Volts)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter aIsc
fields.memo: (1/degC)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter aImp
fields.memo: (1/degC)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter BVoc0
fields.memo: (Volts/degC)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter mBVoc
fields.memo: (Volts/degC)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter BVmp0
fields.memo: (Volts/degC)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter mBVmp
fields.memo: (Volts/degC)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter Delta(Tc)
fields.memo: (deg C)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter Ix0
fields.memo: (Amps)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter Ixx0
fields.memo: (Amps)

fields.name: Sandia Database Parameter c7
fields.memo: (non-dimensional)

airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:no.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:ConstantVolume:NoReheat
airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:no.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, constant volume, without reheat coil

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The air-inlet node name that connects the air splitter to the individual zone air distribution unit. This node should also be one of the outlet air node of an AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter or AirLoopHVAC:SupplyPlenum component.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is an air outlet node from the air distribution unit. This node name should be one of the supply air inlet node names of a zone served by this component.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used to modulate the terminal unit flow rate based on the specified outdoor air requirement. When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will adjust flow to meet this outdoor air requirement and no more. Load is still "Uncontrolled." If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on either the current or design occupancy as specified in the Per Person Ventilation Rate Mode field. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. The requested fl rate may not be fully met if the system is operating with cycling fan. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow. This field is optional.

fields.name: Per Person Ventilation Rate Mode
fields.memo: CurrentOccupancy uses current number of people in the zone which may vary DesignOccupancy uses the total number of people in the zone and is constant

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitImport:To:Schedule
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.memo: This objects contains only one value, which is used during the first call of EnergyPlus

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during the first call of EnergyPlus.

floor:groundcontact.name: Floor:GroundContact
floor:groundcontact.memo: Allows for simplified entry of exterior floors with ground contact. View Factors to Ground is automatically calculated.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file If the construction is type "Construction:FfactorGroundFloor", then the GroundFCfactorMethod will be used.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Floors are usually tilted 180 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: if not flat, should be lower left corner (from outside)

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: Along X Axis

fields.name: Width
fields.memo: Along Y Axis

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:DedicatedOutdoorAir object if this zone is served by a separate dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Leave field blank if no DOAS serves this zone.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

surfaceproperty:heatbalancesourceterm.name: SurfaceProperty:HeatBalanceSourceTerm
surfaceproperty:heatbalancesourceterm.memo: Allows an additional heat source term to be added to the inside or outside surface boundary. A heat source can be added to either or both the inside and outside of the same surface.

fields.name: Inside Face Heat Source Term Schedule Name
fields.memo: The value of this schedule is the source term value for the inside face of this surface If this field is left blank, no inside surface source term will be applied. The schedule values are heat rate per surface area (W/m2), when positive schedule values indicate heat gain and negative values indicates loss.

fields.name: Outside Face Heat Source Term Schedule Name
fields.memo: The value of this schedule is the source term value for the outside face of this surface If this field is left blank, no outside surface source term will be applied. The schedule values are heat rate per surface area (W/m2), when positive schedule values indicate heat gain and negative values indicates loss.

airconditioner:variablerefrigerantflow.name: AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow
airconditioner:variablerefrigerantflow.memo: Variable refrigerant flow (VRF) air-to-air heat pump condensing unit (includes one or more electric compressors and outdoor fan). Serves one or more VRF zone terminal units. See ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow and ZoneTerminalUnitList.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Enter the name of a schedule that defines the availability of the unit. Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off. All other values denote the unit is available. If this field is left blank, the unit is available the entire simulation.

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the total cooling capacity in watts at rated conditions or set to autosize. Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Enter the coefficient of performance at rated conditions or leave blank to use default. COP includes compressor and condenser fan electrical energy input COP does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electric power input

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation. Cooling is disabled below this temperature.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation. Cooling is disabled above this temperature.

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Ratio Modifier Function of Low Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents full load cooling capacity ratio as a function of outdoor dry-bulb temperature and indoor wet-bulb temperature. Up to two curves are allowed if the performance cannot be represented by a single curve. The following two fields are used if two curves are required.

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Ratio Boundary Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to allow separate low and high cooling capacity ratio performance curves. This curve represents a line passing through the points where performance changes. The curve calculates outdoor dry-bulb temperature given weighted average indoor wet-bulb temperature. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Ratio Modifier Function of High Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to describe the high outdoor temperature performance curve used to describe cooling capacity ratio. This curve is used when a single performance curve does not accurately describe cooling capacity ratio as a function of temperature. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Cooling Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Low Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents cooling energy ratio as a function of outdoor dry-bulb temperature and indoor wet-bulb temperature

fields.name: Cooling Energy Input Ratio Boundary Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to allow separate low and high cooling energy input ratio performance curves. This curve represents a line passing through the points where performance changes. The curve calculates outdoor dry-bulb temperature given weighted average indoor wet-bulb temperature. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Cooling Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of High Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to describe the high outdoor temperature performance curve used to describe cooling energy ratio. This curve is used when a single performance curve does not accurately describe cooling energy ratio as a function of temperature

fields.name: Cooling Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Low Part-Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents cooling energy ratio as a function of part-load ratio for part-load ratios less than or equal to 1. If this field is left blank, the model assumes energy is proportional to part-load ratio.

fields.name: Cooling Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of High Part-Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents cooling energy ratio as a function of part-load ratio for part-load ratios greater than 1. Part-load ratios can exceed 1 in variable speed compression systems. If this field is left blank, the model assumes energy is proportional to part-load ratio.

fields.name: Cooling Combination Ratio Correction Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve defines how rated capacity changes when the total indoor terminal unit cooling capacity is greater than the Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity defined in this object. If this field is left blank, the model assumes total indoor terminal unit cooling capacity is equal to the Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity defined above.

fields.name: Cooling Part-Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve defines the cycling losses when the heat pump compressor cycles on and off below the Minimum Heat Pump Part-Load Ratio specified in the field below.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the heating capacity in watts at rated conditions or set to autosize. Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Rated Heating Capacity Sizing Ratio
fields.memo: If the Gross Rated Heating Capacity is autosized, the heating capacity is sized to be equal to the cooling capacity multiplied by this sizing ratio. The zone terminal unit heating coils are also sized using this ratio unless the sizing ratio input in the ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow object is entered.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating COP
fields.memo: COP includes compressor and condenser fan electrical energy input COP does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Ratio Modifier Function of Low Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents full load heating capacity ratio as a function of outdoor wet-bulb temperature and indoor dry-bulb temperature. Outdoor dry-bulb temperature may be used if wet-bulb temperature data is unavailable. See Heating Performance Curve Outdoor Temperature Type input below to determine which outdoor temperature type to use. Up to two curves are allowed if the performance cannot be represented by a single curve. The following two fields are used if two curves are required.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Ratio Boundary Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to allow separate low and high heating capacity ratio performance curves. This curve represents a line passing through the points where performance changes. The curve calculates outdoor dry-bulb or wet-bulb temperature given weighted average indoor dry-bulb temperature. See Heating Performance Curve Outdoor Temperature Type input below to determine which outdoor temperature type to use. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Ratio Modifier Function of High Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to describe the high outdoor temperature performance curve used to describe heating capacity ratio. This curve is used when a single performance curve does not accurately describe heating capacity ratio as a function of temperature. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Heating Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Low Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter a curve name that represents heating energy ratio as a function of outdoor wet-bulb temperature and indoor dry-bulb temperature Outdoor dry-bulb temperature may be used if wet-bulb temperature data is unavailable. See Heating Performance Curve Outdoor Temperature Type input below to determine which outdoor temperature type to use.

fields.name: Heating Energy Input Ratio Boundary Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to allow separate low and high heating energy input ratio performance curves. This curve represents a line passing through the points where performance changes. The curve calculates outdoor dry-bulb or wet-bulb temperature given weighted average indoor dry-bulb temperature. See Heating Performance Curve Outdoor Temperature Type input below to determine which outdoor temperature type to use. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Heating Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of High Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve object is used to allow separate performance curves for heating energy. If a single performance curve is used, leave this field blank.

fields.name: Heating Performance Curve Outdoor Temperature Type
fields.memo: Determines temperature type for heating capacity curves and heating energy curves. This input determines whether the outdoor air dry-bulb or wet-bulb temperature is used to evaluate these curves.

fields.name: Heating Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Low Part-Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve represents the heating energy input ratio for part-load ratios less than 1.

fields.name: Heating Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of High Part-Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve represents the heating energy input ratio for part-load ratios greater than 1.

fields.name: Heating Combination Ratio Correction Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve defines how rated capacity changes when the total indoor terminal unit heating capacity is greater than the Gross Rated Heating Capacity defined in this object. If this field is left blank, the model assumes total indoor terminal unit heating capacity is equal to the Gross Rated Heating Capacity defined above.

fields.name: Heating Part-Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve defines the cycling losses when the heat pump compressor cycles on and off below the Minimum Heat Pump Part-Load Ratio specified in the following field.

fields.name: Minimum Heat Pump Part-Load Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the minimum heat pump part-load ratio (PLR). When the cooling or heating PLR is below this value, the heat pump compressor will cycle to meet the cooling or heating demand.

fields.name: Zone Name for Master Thermostat Location
fields.memo: Enter the name of the zone where the master thermostat is located.

fields.name: Master Thermostat Priority Control Type
fields.memo: Choose a thermostat control logic scheme. If these control types fail to control zone temperature within a reasonable limit, consider using multiple VRF systems

fields.name: Thermostat Priority Schedule Name
fields.memo: this field is required if Master Thermostat Priority Control Type is Scheduled. Schedule values of 0 denote cooling, 1 for heating, and all other values disable the system.

fields.name: Zone Terminal Unit List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneTerminalUnitList. This list connects zone terminal units to this heat pump.

fields.name: Heat Pump Waste Heat Recovery
fields.memo: This field enables heat recovery operation within this VRF outdoor unit.

fields.name: Equivalent Piping Length used for Piping Correction Factor in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the equivalent length of the farthest terminal unit from the condenser

fields.name: Vertical Height used for Piping Correction Factor
fields.memo: Enter the height difference between the highest and lowest terminal unit

fields.name: Piping Correction Factor for Length in Cooling Mode Curve Name
fields.memo: PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*L^3 + a4*H PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*CR + a4*CR^2 + a5*(L)(CR) where L = length and CR = combination ratio specifies coefficients for a0, a1, a2, and a3 in the PCF equation

fields.name: Piping Correction Factor for Height in Cooling Mode Coefficient
fields.memo: PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*L^3 + a4*H PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*CR + a4*CR^2 + a5*(L)(CR) + a6*H where L = length, H = height, and CR = combination ratio specifies coefficient a4 (or a6 for biquadratic) in the PCF equation

fields.name: Equivalent Piping Length used for Piping Correction Factor in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the equivalent length of the farthest terminal unit from the condenser

fields.name: Piping Correction Factor for Length in Heating Mode Curve Name
fields.memo: PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*L^3 + a4*H PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*CR + a4*CR^2 + a5*(L)(CR) + a6*H where L = length and CR = combination ratio specifies coefficients for a0, a1, a2, and a3 (or a0-a5 for biquadratic) in the PCF equation

fields.name: Piping Correction Factor for Height in Heating Mode Coefficient
fields.memo: PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*L^3 + a4*H PCF = a0 + a1*L + a2*L^2 + a3*CR + a4*CR^2 + a5*(L)(CR) + a6*H where L = length, H = height, and CR = combination ratio specifies coefficient a4 (or a6 for biquadratic) in the PCF equation

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Power per Compressor
fields.memo: Enter the value of the resistive heater located in the compressor(s). This heater is used to warm the refrigerant and oil when the compressor is off.

fields.name: Number of Compressors
fields.memo: Enter the total number of compressor. This input is used only for crankcase heater calculations.

fields.name: Ratio of Compressor Size to Total Compressor Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the ratio of the first stage compressor to total compressor capacity. All other compressors are assumed to be equally sized. This inputs is used only for crankcase heater calculations.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which the crankcase heaters are disabled.

fields.name: Defrost Strategy
fields.memo: Select a defrost strategy. Reverse cycle reverses the operating mode from heating to cooling to melt frost formation on the condenser coil. The resistive strategy uses a resistive heater to melt the frost.

fields.name: Defrost Control
fields.memo: Choose a defrost control type. Either use a fixed Timed defrost period or select OnDemand to defrost only when necessary.

fields.name: Defrost Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: A valid performance curve must be used if reversecycle defrost strategy is selected.

fields.name: Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode. Only applicable if timed defrost control is specified.

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the size of the resistive defrost heating element. Only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which defrost operation is disabled.

fields.name: Condenser Type
fields.memo: Select either an air-cooled, evaporatively-cooled or water-cooled condenser.

fields.name: Condenser Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Choose an outside air node name or leave this field blank to use weather data. If this field is blank, the Condenser Type is assumed to be AirCooled. This input must be specified if Condenser Type = WaterCooled.

fields.name: Condenser Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter a water outlet node name if Condenser Type = WaterCooled. Leave this field blank if Condenser Type = Air or EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Water Condenser Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when Condenser Type = WaterCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Effectiveness
fields.memo: Enter the effectiveness of the evaporatively cooled condenser. This field is only used when the Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use. This field is only used when the Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump. This field is only used when the Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Supply Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: A separate storage tank may be used to supply an evaporatively cooled condenser.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
fields.memo: The minimum outdoor temperature below which heat recovery mode will not operate.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
fields.memo: The maximum outdoor temperature above which heat recovery mode will not operate.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a performance curve which represents the change in cooling capacity when heat recovery is active A default constant of 0.9 is used if this input is blank

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: Enter the fractional capacity available at the start of heat recovery mode. The capacity exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Modifier and Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a performance curve which represents the change in cooling energy when heat recovery is active A default constant of 1.1 is used if this input is blank

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Fraction
fields.memo: Enter the fractional electric consumption rate at the start of heat recovery mode. The electric consumption rate exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Modifier and Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Time Constant
fields.memo: Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a performance curve which represents the change in heating capacity when heat recovery is active A default constant of 1.1 is used if this input is blank

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: Enter the fractional capacity available at the start of heat recovery mode. The capacity exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Modifier and Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Heat Recovery Heating Energy Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a performance curve which represents the change in heating electric consumption rate when heat recovery is active A default constant of 1.1 is used if this input is blank

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Heating Energy Fraction
fields.memo: Enter the fractional electric consumption rate at the start of heat recovery mode. The electric consumption rate exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Modifier and Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Heating Energy Time Constant
fields.memo: Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fan:onoff.name: Fan:OnOff
fan:onoff.memo: Constant volume fan that is intended to cycle on and off based on cooling/heating load or other control signals. This fan can also operate continuously like Fan:ConstantVolume.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Motor In Airstream Fraction
fields.memo: 0.0 means fan motor outside of air stream, 1.0 means motor inside of air stream

fields.name: Fan Power Ratio Function of Speed Ratio Curve Name
Fan Efficiency Ratio Function of Speed Ratio Curve Name
End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

schedule:year.name: Schedule:Year
schedule:year.memo: A Schedule:Year contains from 1 to 52 week schedules

fields.name: End Day 26
fields.memo: Schedule:Week for Weeks 27-53 are condensed

zonecontrol:humidistat.name: ZoneControl:Humidistat
zonecontrol:humidistat.memo: Specifies zone relative humidity setpoint schedules for humidifying and dehumidifying.

fields.name: Humidifying Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: hourly schedule values should be in Relative Humidity (percent)

fields.name: Dehumidifying Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: hourly schedule values should be in Relative Humidity (percent)

zonehvac:ventilatedslab:slabgroup.name: ZoneHVAC:VentilatedSlab:SlabGroup
zonehvac:ventilatedslab:slabgroup.memo: This is used to allow the coordinate control of several ventilated slab system surfaces. Note that the flow fractions must sum up to 1.0. The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 10, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

hvactemplate:zone:idealloadsairsystem.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:IdealLoadsAirSystem
hvactemplate:zone:idealloadsairsystem.memo: Zone with ideal air system that meets heating or cooling loads

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Maximum Heating Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Minimum Cooling Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Maximum Heating Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Heating Limit = NoLimit If this field is blank, there is no limit.

fields.name: Maximum Sensible Heating Capacity
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Heating Limit = NoLimit If this field is blank, there is no limit.

fields.name: Maximum Cooling Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Cooling Limit = NoLimit This field is required if Outdoor Air Economizer Type is anything other than NoEconomizer.

fields.name: Maximum Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: This field is ignored if Cooling Limit = NoLimit

fields.name: Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, heating is always available.

fields.name: Cooling Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, cooling is always available.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: ConstantSensibleHeatRatio means that the ideal loads system will be controlled to meet the sensible cooling load, and the latent cooling rate will be computed using a constant sensible heat ratio (SHR) Humidistat means that there is a ZoneControl:Humidistat for this zone and the ideal loads system will attempt to satisfy the humidistat. None means that there is no dehumidification. ConstantSupplyHumidityRatio means that during cooling the supply air will always be at the Minimum Cooling Supply Humidity Ratio.

fields.name: Cooling Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: This field is applicable only when Dehumidification Control Type is ConstantSensibleHeatRatio

fields.name: Dehumidification Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Humidification Control Type
fields.memo: None means that there is no humidification. Humidistat means that there is a ZoneControl:Humidistat for this zone and the ideal loads system will attempt to satisfy the humidistat. ConstantSupplyHumidityRatio means that during heating the supply air will always be at the Maximum Heating Supply Humidity Ratio.

fields.name: Humidification Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: None means there is no outdoor air and all related fields will be ignored Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the minimum outdoor air flow rate will be computed using these specifications. The outdoor air flow rate will also be affected by the next two fields. If this field is blank, there will be no outdoor air and the remaining fields will be ignored.

fields.name: Demand Controlled Ventilation Type
fields.memo: This field controls how the minimum outdoor air flow rate is calculated. None means that design occupancy will be used to compute the minimum outdoor air flow rate OccupancySchedule means that current occupancy level will be used. CO2Setpoint means that the design occupancy will be used to compute the minimum outdoor air flow rate and the outdoor air flow rate may be increased if necessary to maintain the indoor air carbon dioxide setpoint defined in a ZoneControl:ContaminantController object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Economizer Type
fields.memo: DifferentialDryBulb and DifferentialEnthalpy will increase the outdoor air flow rate when there is a cooling load and the outdoor air temperature or enthalpy is below the zone exhaust air temperature or enthalpy.

fields.name: Latent Heat Recovery Effectiveness
fields.memo: Applicable only if Heat Recovery Type is Enthalpy.

setpointmanager:singlezone:humidity:maxi.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:Humidity:Maximum
setpointmanager:singlezone:humidity:maxi.memo: The Single Zone Maximum Humidity Setpoint Manager allows the control of a single zone maximum humidity level. This setpoint manager can be used in conjunction with object ZoneControl:Humidistat to detect humidity levels.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which humidity ratio setpoint will be set

fields.name: Control Zone Air Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the zone air node for the humidity control zone

zonehvac:equipmentconnections.name: ZoneHVAC:EquipmentConnections
zonehvac:equipmentconnections.memo: Specifies the HVAC equipment connections for a zone. Node names are specified for the zone air node, air inlet nodes, air exhaust nodes, and the air return node. A zone equipment list is referenced which lists all HVAC equipment connected to the zone.

fields.name: Zone Conditioning Equipment List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneHVAC:EquipmentList object.

fields.name: Zone Air Inlet Node or NodeList Name
Zone Air Exhaust Node or NodeList Name
Zone Return Air Node or NodeList Name
Zone Return Air Node 1 Flow Rate Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule is multiplied times the base return air flow rate. If this field is left blank, the schedule defaults to 1.0 at all times.

fields.name: Zone Return Air Node 1 Flow Rate Basis Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: The optional basis node(s) used to calculate the base return air flow rate for the first return air node in this zone. The return air flow rate is the sum of the flow rates at the basis node(s) multiplied by the Zone Return Air Flow Rate Fraction Schedule. If this  field is blank, then the base return air flow rate is the total supply inlet flow rate to the zone less the total exhaust node flow rate from the zone.

waterheater:mixed.name: WaterHeater:Mixed
waterheater:mixed.memo: Water heater with well-mixed, single-node water tank. May be used to model a tankless water heater (small tank volume), a hot water storage tank (zero heater capacity), or a heat pump water heater (see WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser.)

fields.name: Heater Minimum Capacity
fields.memo: Only used when Heater Control Type is set to Modulate

fields.name: Heater Ignition Minimum Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Heater Ignition Delay
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Off Cycle Parasitic Fuel Consumption Rate
Off Cycle Parasitic Heat Fraction to Tank
On Cycle Parasitic Fuel Consumption Rate
On Cycle Parasitic Heat Fraction to Tank
Ambient Temperature Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: required for Ambient Temperature Indicator=Outdoors

fields.name: Off Cycle Loss Coefficient to Ambient Temperature
Off Cycle Loss Fraction to Zone
On Cycle Loss Coefficient to Ambient Temperature
On Cycle Loss Fraction to Zone
Peak Use Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used if Use Side Node connections are blank

fields.name: Use Flow Rate Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Only used if Use Side Node connections are blank

fields.name: Cold Water Supply Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Only used if Use Side Node connections are blank Defaults to water temperatures calculated by Site:WaterMainsTemperature object

fields.name: Indirect Water Heating Recovery Time
fields.memo: Parameter for autosizing design flow rates for indirectly heated water tanks Time required to raise temperature of entire tank from 14.4C to 57.2C

fields.name: Source Side Flow Control Mode
fields.memo: StorageTank mode always requests flow unless tank is at its Maximum Temperature Limit IndirectHeatPrimarySetpoint mode requests flow whenever primary setpoint calls for heat IndirectHeatAlternateSetpoint mode requests flow whenever alternate indirect setpoint calls for heat

fields.name: Indirect Alternate Setpoint Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous is set to IndirectHeatAlternateSetpoint

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

groundheattransfer:slab:zface.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:ZFACE
groundheattransfer:slab:zface.memo: This is only needed when using manual gridding (not recommended) ZFACE: Z Direction cell face coordinates: m

construction:ffactorgroundfloor.name: Construction:FfactorGroundFloor
construction:ffactorgroundfloor.memo: Alternate method of describing slab-on-grade or underground floor constructions

fields.name: Area
fields.memo: Enter area of the floor

fields.name: PerimeterExposed
fields.memo: Enter exposed perimeter of the floor

setpointmanager:singlezone:onestagecooli.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:OneStageCooling
setpointmanager:singlezone:onestagecooli.memo: This object can be used with CoilSystem:Cooling:DX to model on/off cycling control of single stage air systems. Setpoints are modulated to run coil full on or full off depending on zone conditions. Intended for use with ZoneControl:Thermostat:StagedDualSetpoint

fields.name: Cooling Stage On Supply Air Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This is the setpoint value applied when cooling device is to cycle ON

fields.name: Cooling Stage Off Supply Air Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This is the setpoint value applied when cooling device is to cycle OFF

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

coilsystem:cooling:water:heatexchangeras.name: CoilSystem:Cooling:Water:HeatExchangerAssisted
coilsystem:cooling:water:heatexchangeras.memo: Virtual component consisting of a chilled-water cooling coil and an air-to-air heat exchanger. The air-to-air heat exchanger precools the air entering the cooling coil and reuses this energy to reheat the supply air leaving the cooling coil. This heat exchange process improves the latent removal performance of the cooling coil (lower sensible heat ratio).

surfaceproperty:othersidecoefficients.name: SurfaceProperty:OtherSideCoefficients
surfaceproperty:othersidecoefficients.memo: This object sets the other side conditions for a surface in a variety of ways.

fields.name: Combined Convective/Radiative Film Coefficient
fields.memo: if>0, this field becomes the exterior convective/radiative film coefficient and the other fields are used to calculate the outdoor air temperature then exterior surface temperature based on outdoor air and specified coefficient if<=0, then remaining fields calculate the outside surface temperature The following fields are used in the equation: OtherSideTemp=N2*N3 + N4*OutdoorDry-bulb + N5*GroundTemp + N6*WindSpeed*OutdoorDry-bulb + N7*TempZone + N9*TempPrev

fields.name: Constant Temperature
fields.memo: This parameter will be overwritten by the values from the Constant Temperature Schedule Name (below) if one is present

fields.name: Constant Temperature Coefficient
fields.memo: This coefficient is used even with a Schedule.  It should normally be 1.0 in that case. This field is ignored if Sinusoidal Variation of Constant Temperature Coefficient = Yes.

fields.name: Constant Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Name of schedule for values of constant temperature. Schedule values replace any value specified in the field Constant Temperature.

fields.name: Sinusoidal Variation of Constant Temperature Coefficient
fields.memo: Optionally used to vary Constant Temperature Coefficient with unitary sine wave

fields.name: Period of Sinusoidal Variation
fields.memo: Use with sinusoidal variation to define the time period

fields.name: Previous Other Side Temperature Coefficient
fields.memo: This coefficient multiplies the other side temperature result from the previous zone timestep

fields.name: Minimum Other Side Temperature Limit
fields.memo: This field specifies a lower limit for the other side temperature result. Blank indicates no limit

fields.name: Maximum Other Side Temperature Limit
fields.memo: This field specifies an upper limit for the other side temperature result. Blank indicates no limit

setpointmanager:returntemperature:chille.name: SetpointManager:ReturnTemperature:ChilledWater
setpointmanager:returntemperature:chille.memo: This setpoint manager is used to place a temperature setpoint on a plant supply outlet node based on a target return water setpoint. The setpoint manager attempts to achieve the desired return water temperature by adjusting the supply temperature setpoint based on the plant conditions at each system time step.

fields.name: Plant Loop Supply Outlet Node
fields.memo: This is the name of the supply outlet node for the plant being controlled by this setpoint manager.  Typically this is where the setpoint will be actuated for supply equipment to control to, but not necessarily.  This setpoint manager will mine that information from the internal plant data structures.

fields.name: Plant Loop Supply Inlet Node
fields.memo: This is the name of the supply inlet node for the plant being controlled with this setpoint manager. The temperature on this node is controlled by actuating the supply setpoint.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: This is the minimum chilled water supply temperature setpoint.  This is also used as the default setpoint during no-load or negative-load conditions and during initialization.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: This is the maximum reset temperature for the chilled water supply.

fields.name: Return Temperature Setpoint Input Type
fields.memo: This defines whether the chilled water return temperature target is constant, scheduled, or specified on the supply inlet node by a separate setpoint manager.

fields.name: Return Temperature Setpoint Constant Value
fields.memo: This is the desired return temperature target, which is met by adjusting the supply temperature setpoint. This constant value is only used if the Design Chilled Water Return Temperature Input Type is Constant

fields.name: Return Temperature Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: This is the desired return temperature target, which is met by adjusting the supply temperature setpoint. This is a schedule name to allow the return temperature target value to be scheduled.  This field is only used if the Design Chilled Water Return Temperature Input Type is Scheduled

zonehvac:hybridunitaryhvac.name: ZoneHVAC:HybridUnitaryHVAC
zonehvac:hybridunitaryhvac.memo: Hybrid Unitary HVAC. A black box model for multi-mode packaged forced air equipment. Independent variables include outdoor air conditions and indoor air conditions. Controlled inputs include operating mode, supply air flow rate, and outdoor air faction. Emperical lookup tables are required to map supply air temperature supply air humidity, electricity use, fuel uses, water use, fan electricity use, and external static pressure as a function of each indpednent varaible and each controlled input. In each timestep the model will choose one or more combinations of settings for mode, supply air flow rate, outdoor air faction, and part runtime fraction so as to satisfy zone requests for sensible cooling, heating, ventilation, and/or dehumidification with the least resource consumption. Equipment in this class may consume electricity, water, and up to two additional fuel types.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in this schedule are used as a constraint in choosing the feasible settings for supply air flow rate and ouside air fraction in each operating mode. If this field is blank, no minimum is imposed.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in this schedule are used as a constraint in choosing the feasible settings for supply air flow rate and outdoor air fraction in each operating mode. If this field is blank, no maximum is imposed.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Air Humidity Ratio Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in this schedule are used as a constraint in choosing the feasible settings for supply air flow rate and outdoor air fraction in each operating mode. If this field is blank, no minimum is imposed.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Humidity Ratio Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in this schedule are used as a constraint in choosing the feasible settings for supply air flow rate and outdoor air fraction in each operating mode. If this field is blank, no maximum is imposed.

fields.name: Method to Choose Controlled Inputs and Part Runtime Fraction
fields.memo: Select the method that will be used to choose operating mode(s), supply air flow rate(s), outdoor air fraction(s) and part runtime fraction(s) in each time step. "Automatic" = chooses controlled inputs and part runtime fraction(s) to minimize resource use within each time step while best satisfying requested sensible cooling, dehumidification and ventilation, and subject to constraints. "User Defined" = EMS will be used to choose controlled inputs and part runtime fraction(s) in each time step. If this field is blank, default to "Automatic".

fields.name: Return Air Node Name
fields.memo: Return air node for the hybrid unit must be a zone exhaust node.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: Outdoor air node for the hybrid unit must be an outdoor air node.

fields.name: Supply Air Node Name
fields.memo: Supply air node for the hybrid unit must be a zone air inlet node.

fields.name: Relief Node Name
fields.memo: Relief node for the hybrid unit must be a zone exhaust node, unless flow is being balanced elsewhere.

fields.name: System Maximum Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: The value in this field represents the maximum supply air volume flow rate among all operating modes. Values of extensive variables in lookup tables are normalized by the system maximum supply air mass flow rate that was used to build performance curves. The value in this field is used to rescale the output from exenstive variables to a desired system size.

fields.name: External Static Pressure at System Maximum Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Input the external static pressure when the system operates at maximum supply air flow rate. Fan affinity laws are used to scale supply fan power from the values tabulated in lookup tables, to values that match the external static pressure input to this field. If this field is blank, the supply fan power is not scaled from the values tabulated in lookup tables.

fields.name: Scaling Factor
fields.memo: The value in this field scales all extensive performance variables including: supply air mass flow rate, fuel uses, and water use. If this field is blank, the default scaling factor is 1.

fields.name: Number of Operating Modes
fields.memo: The value in this field defines the number of discrete operating modes for the unitary hybrid equipment. Supply air mass flow rate ratio and outdoor air fraction are treated as continuous controlled inputs within each discrete operating mode. Mode 0 always describes standby. Mode 1 - Mode 25 describe active operating modes that provide ventilation, heating, cooling, humidification or dehumidification. 26 modes are allowed (including Mode 0). If the value input to this field is 1, only Mode 0 will be considered. If this field is blank, the default number of operating modes is 1.

fields.name: Minimum Time Between Mode Change
fields.memo: Any mode selected will not operate for less time than the value input in this field. If the value in this field is larger than each timestep, the mode selected in one time step will persist in later time steps until the minimum time between mode change is satisfied. Supply air mass flow rate and outdoor air fraction within a mode are not subject to minimum runtime and may change in every time step. Mode 0 does not have a minimum time. If this field is blank, the default minimum time between mode change is 10 minutes.

fields.name: First Fuel Type
fields.memo: Select the fuel type associated with field: "System Electric Power Lookup Table" in each mode. If this field is blank, default first fuel type = Electricity.

fields.name: Second Fuel Type
fields.memo: Select the fuel type associated with field: "System Second Fuel Consumption Lookup Table" in each mode. If this field is blank, default second fuel type = None.

fields.name: Third Fuel Type
fields.memo: Select the fuel type associated with field: "System Third Fuel Consumption Lookup Table" in each mode. If this field is blank, default third fuel type = None.

fields.name: Objective Function to Minimize
fields.memo: In each time step, controlled variables will be chosen to minimize the selection in this field, subject to constraints. If this field is blank, the objective function will minimize electricity use.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object. Information in that object will be used to compute the minimum outdoor air flow rate in each time step. If this field is blank, the system may still supply outdoor air, if it is capable as described by lookup tables, when doing so is the most efficient way to satisfy other constraints.

fields.name: Mode 0 Name
fields.memo: Enter a name for Mode 0. Mode 0 describes equipment performance in standby.  Mode 0 is usually characterized by electricity use for controls and crankcase heaters, or other standby resouce consumption. Mode 0 will be chosen for any timestep, or portion of timestep, when no ventilation, cooling, humidification, or dehumidification is required.  Mode 0 is available at any environmental condition.

fields.name: Mode 0 Supply Air Temperature Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the Supply Air Temperature Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 will not be considered for any period that requires ventilation, heating, cooling, humidification, or dehumidification. If this field is blank, when Mode 0 is chosen (during standby periods) the supply air temperature will equal the return air temperature.

fields.name: Mode 0 Supply Air Humidity Ratio Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the Supply Air Humidity Ratio Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 will not be considered for any period that requires ventilation, heating, cooling, humidification, or dehumidification. If this field is blank, when Mode 0 is chosen (during standby periods) the supply air humidty ratio will equal the return air humidity ratio.

fields.name: Mode 0 System Electric Power Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the Electric Power Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 does not consume electricity.

fields.name: Mode 0 Supply Fan Electric Power Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the Supply Fan Electric Power Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 does not consume electricity for supply fan.

fields.name: Mode 0 External Static Pressure Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the External Static Pressure Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, external static pressure will not be reported.

fields.name: Mode 0 System Second Fuel Consumption Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the System Second Fuel Consumption Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 does not consume a second fuel.

fields.name: Mode 0 System Third Fuel Consumption Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the System Third Fuel Consumption Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 does not consume a third fuel.

fields.name: Mode 0 System Water Use Lookup Table Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the System Water Use Lookup Table for Mode 0. If this field is blank, Mode 0 does not consume water.

fields.name: Mode 0 Outdoor Air Fraction
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor air fraction for Mode 0. If this field is blank, the outdoor air fraction for Mode 0 will be 0.00.

fields.name: Mode 0 Supply Air Mass Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the supply air mass flow rate ratio for Mode 0. The value in this field will be used to determine the supply air mass flow rate in Mode 0. Supply air mass flow rate ratio describes supply air mass flow rate as a fraction of mass flow rate associated with the value in field: "System Maximum Supply Air Flow Rate". If this field is blank, the supply air mass flow rate ratio for Mode 0 will be 0.

airflownetwork:multizone:referencecrackc.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ReferenceCrackConditions
airflownetwork:multizone:referencecrackc.memo: This object specifies the conditions under which the air mass flow coefficient was measured.

fields.name: Reference Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the reference temperature under which the surface crack data were obtained.

fields.name: Reference Barometric Pressure
fields.memo: Enter the reference barometric pressure under which the surface crack data were obtained.

fields.name: Reference Humidity Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the reference humidity ratio under which the surface crack data were obtained.

daylighting:controls.name: Daylighting:Controls
daylighting:controls.memo: Dimming of overhead electric lighting is determined from each reference point. Glare from daylighting is also calculated.

fields.name: Minimum Input Power Fraction for Continuous or ContinuousOff Dimming Control
Minimum Light Output Fraction for Continuous or ContinuousOff Dimming Control
Number of Stepped Control Steps
fields.memo: The number of steps, excluding off, in a stepped lighting control system. If Lighting Control Type is Stepped, this field must be greater than zero. The steps are assumed to be equally spaced.

fields.name: Probability Lighting will be Reset When Needed in Manual Stepped Control
Glare Calculation Daylighting Reference Point Name
Glare Calculation Azimuth Angle of View Direction Clockwise from Zone y-Axis
Maximum Allowable Discomfort Glare Index
fields.memo: The default is for general office work

fields.name: DElight Gridding Resolution
fields.memo: Maximum surface area for nodes in gridding all surfaces in the DElight zone. All reflective and transmitting surfaces will be subdivided into approximately square nodes that do not exceed this maximum. Higher resolution subdivisions require greater calculation times, but generally produce more accurate results.

fluidproperties:saturated.name: FluidProperties:Saturated
fluidproperties:saturated.memo: fluid properties for the saturated region

fields.name: Fluid Property Type
fields.memo: Enthalpy Units are J/kg Density Units are kg/m3 SpecificHeat Units are J/kg-K Pressure Units are Pa

fields.name: Fluid Phase
fields.memo: Fluid=saturated fluid FluidGas=saturated vapor

fields.name: Temperature Values Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a FluidProperties:Temperatures object.

solarcollector:integralcollectorstorage.name: SolarCollector:IntegralCollectorStorage
solarcollector:integralcollectorstorage.memo: Glazed solar collector with integral storage unit. Thermal and optical properties are taken from the referenced SolarCollectorPerformance:IntegralCollectorStorage object. Collector tilt, azimuth, and gross area are taken from the referenced building surface or shading surface. The collector surface participates normally in all shading calculations.

airflownetwork:distribution:component:le.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:Leak
airflownetwork:distribution:component:le.memo: This object defines the characteristics of a supply or return air leak.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient
fields.memo: Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference across this component. Enter the coefficient used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent

setpointmanager:multizone:humidity:maxim.name: SetpointManager:MultiZone:Humidity:Maximum
setpointmanager:multizone:humidity:maxim.memo: This setpoint manager sets the maximum supply air humidity ratio based on dehumidification requirements of a controlled zone with critical humidity ratio setpoint (i.e., a zone with the lowest humidity ratio setpoint) in an air loop served by a central air-conditioner.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the humidity ratio will be set

surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm:co.name: SurfaceProperty:HeatTransferAlgorithm:Construction
surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm:co.memo: Determines which Heat Balance Algorithm will be used for surfaces that have a specific type of construction Allows selectively overriding the global setting in HeatBalanceAlgorithm CTF (Conduction Transfer Functions), EMPD (Effective Moisture Penetration Depth with Conduction Transfer Functions). Advanced/Research Usage: CondFD (Conduction Finite Difference) Advanced/Research Usage: HAMT (Combined Heat And Moisture Finite Element)

nodelist.name: NodeList
nodelist.memo: This object is used in places where lists of nodes may be needed, e.g. ZoneHVAC:EquipmentConnections field Zone Air Inlet Node or NodeList Name

shading:overhang.name: Shading:Overhang
shading:overhang.memo: Overhangs are usually flat shading surfaces that reference a window or door.

fields.name: Right extension from Window/Door Width
fields.memo: N3 + N4 + Window/Door Width is Overhang Length

hvactemplate:system:dualduct.name: HVACTemplate:System:DualDuct
hvactemplate:system:dualduct.memo: Dual-duct constant volume or variable volume air loop

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on;  Schedule is used in availability manager and fan scheduling. Also see "Night Cycle Control" field.

fields.name: System Configuration Type
fields.memo: SingleFan - a single supply fan before the split to dual ducts DualFan - two supply fans, one each for the cold and hot ducts ConstantVolume - constant volume VariableVolume - variable volume

fields.name: Main Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Main Supply Fan Minimum Flow Fraction
Main Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Main Supply Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

fields.name: Cold Duct Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Cold Duct Supply Fan Minimum Flow Fraction
Cold Duct Supply Fan Total Efficiency
Cold Duct Supply Fan Delta Pressure
Cold Duct Supply Fan Motor Efficiency
Cold Duct Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cold Duct Supply Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

fields.name: Hot Duct Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Hot Duct Supply Fan Minimum Flow Fraction
Hot Duct Supply Fan Total Efficiency
Hot Duct Supply Fan Delta Pressure
Hot Duct Supply Fan Motor Efficiency
Hot Duct Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Hot Duct Supply Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Design Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control. Defaults are 15.6C (60F) at 15.6C (60F) to 12.8C (55F) at 23.3C (74F)

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control. Defaults are 15.6C (60F) at 15.6C (60F) to 12.8C (55F) at 23.3C (74F)

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
