fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Preheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Preheat Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Preheat Coil Setpoint Schedule Name specified.

fields.name: Preheat Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Gas Preheat Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the Minimum Outdoor Air Flow Rate If blank, multiplier is always one

fields.name: Economizer Upper Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Lower Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature below which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Upper Enthalpy Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor enthalpy above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Cold Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves the cold inlets of all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Hot Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves the hot inlets of all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Night Cycle Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Applicable only if Night Cycle Control is Cycle On Control Zone.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100) Ignored if Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint above. Schedule values must be in percent relative humidity (0 to 100).

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100). Ignored if Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint above.Schedule values must be in percent relative humidity (0 to 100).

fields.name: Sizing Option
fields.memo: Select whether autosized system supply flow rate is the sum of Coincident or NonCoincident zone air flow rates.

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Return Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

pipe:adiabatic:steam.name: Pipe:Adiabatic:Steam
pipe:adiabatic:steam.memo: Passes Inlet Node state variables to Outlet Node state variables

generator:fuelcell:auxiliaryheater.name: Generator:FuelCell:AuxiliaryHeater
generator:fuelcell:auxiliaryheater.memo: Intended for modeling an auxiliary heater for a fuel cell power generator, however this portion of the model is not yet available. The program still requires one of these objects be included even though the data are not yet used (so that internal data structures can be allocated).

fields.name: Skin Loss U-Factor Times Area Value
Zone Name to Receive Skin Losses
Maximum Heating Capacity in Kmol per Second
Minimum Heating Capacity in Kmol per Second

thermalstorage:ice:detailed.name: ThermalStorage:Ice:Detailed
thermalstorage:ice:detailed.memo: This input syntax is intended to describe a thermal storage system that includes smaller containers filled with water that are placed in a larger tank or series of tanks. The model uses polynomial equations to describe the system performance.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Capacity
fields.memo: This includes only the latent storage capacity

fields.name: Tank Loss Coefficient
fields.memo: This is the fraction the total storage capacity that is lost or melts each hour

fields.name: Freezing Temperature of Storage Medium
fields.memo: This temperature is typically 0C for water. Simply changing this temperature without adjusting the performance parameters input above is inappropriate and not advised.

fields.name: Thaw Process Indicator
fields.memo: This field determines whether the system uses internal or external melt during discharging.  This will then have an impact on charging performance.

faultmodel:fouling:evaporativecooler.name: FaultModel:Fouling:EvaporativeCooler
faultmodel:fouling:evaporativecooler.memo: This object describes the fouling fault of the wetted coil evaporative cooler

fields.name: Evaporative Cooler Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of a Evaporative Cooler object The fault applies to the wetted coil evaporative cooler The fault does not apply to direct evaporative coolers or the dry coil indirect evaporative coolers

fields.name: Evaporative Cooler Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of aN Evaporative Cooler object

fields.name: Fouling Factor
fields.memo: The factor indicates the decrease of the indirect stage efficiency It is the ratio between the indirect stage efficiency at fouling case and that at fault free case

curve:triquadratic.name: Curve:Triquadratic
curve:triquadratic.memo: Quadratic curve with three independent variables. Input consists of the curve name, the twenty seven coefficients, and min and max values for each of the independent variables. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = a0 + a1*x**2 + a2*x + a3*y**2 + a4*y + a5*z**2 + a6*z + a7*x**2*y**2 + a8*x*y + a9*x*y**2 + a10*x**2*y + a11*x**2*z**2 + a12*x*z + a13*x*z**2 + a14*x**2*z + a15*y**2*z**2 + a16*y*z + a17*y*z**2 + a18*y**2*z + a19*x**2*y**2*z**2 + a20*x**2*y**2*z + a21*x**2*y*z**2 + a22*x*y**2*z**2 + a23*x**2*y*z + a24*x*y**2*z + a25*x*y*z**2 +a26*x*y*z

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

groundheattransfer:basement:equivslab.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:EquivSlab
groundheattransfer:basement:equivslab.memo: Using an equivalent slab allows non-rectangular shapes to be modeled accurately. The simulation default should be EquivSizing=True

fields.name: APRatio: The area to perimeter ratio for this slab
EquivSizing: Flag
fields.memo: Will the dimensions of an equivalent slab be calculated (TRUE) or will the dimensions be input directly? (FALSE)] Only advanced special simulations should use FALSE.

energymanagementsystem:curveortableindex.name: EnergyManagementSystem:CurveOrTableIndexVariable
energymanagementsystem:curveortableindex.memo: Declares EMS variable that identifies a curve or table

demandmanager:exteriorlights.name: DemandManager:ExteriorLights
demandmanager:exteriorlights.memo: used for demand limiting Exterior:Lights objects.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Limit Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

fields.name: Limit Step Change
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Rotation Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

zonehvac:terminalunit:variablerefrigeran.name: ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow
zonehvac:terminalunit:variablerefrigeran.memo: Zone terminal unit with variable refrigerant flow (VRF) DX cooling and heating coils (air-to-air heat pump). The VRF terminal units are served by an AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow system.

fields.name: Terminal Unit Availability Schedule
fields.memo: The unit is available the entire simulation if this field is left blank Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off.

fields.name: Terminal Unit Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: the inlet node to the terminal unit

fields.name: Terminal Unit Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: the outlet node of the terminal unit

fields.name: No Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
No Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
Cooling Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is set to zero flow when the VRF terminal unit is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Heating Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is set to zero flow when the VRF terminal unit is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: No Load Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is set to zero flow when the VRF terminal unit is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
Supply Air Fan Placement
fields.memo: Select fan placement as either blow through or draw through.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Supply Air Fan Object Type must be Fan:SystemModel, Fan:OnOff, or Fan:ConstantVolume if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow is used to model VRF outdoor unit Supply Air Fan Object Type must be Fan:SystemModel or Fan:VariableVolume if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl or AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl:HR is used to model VRF outdoor unit

fields.name: Outside Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: Currently only one type OutdoorAir:Mixer object is available. If this field is blank, and outside air mixer is not used. This field should be left blank if the VRF terminal unit is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Outside Air Mixer Object Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the OutdoorAir:Mixer is not used. This optional field specifies the name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. When used, this name needs to match name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. This field should be left blank if the VRF terminal unit is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Cooling Coil Type must be Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow is used to model VRF outdoor unit Cooling Coil Type must be Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl or if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl:HR is used to model VRF outdoor unit This field may be left blank if heating-only mode is used

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Name
fields.memo: Cooling Coil Type must be Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow This field may be left blank if heating-only mode is used

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Heating Coil Type must be Coil:Heating:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow is used to model VRF outdoor unit Heating Coil Type must be Coil:Heating:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl or if AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl:HR is used to model VRF outdoor unit This field may be left blank if cooling-only mode is used

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Name
fields.memo: Heating Coil Type must be Coil:Heating:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow This field may be left blank if cooling-only mode is used

fields.name: Zone Terminal Unit On Parasitic Electric Energy Use
Zone Terminal Unit Off Parasitic Electric Energy Use
Rated Heating Capacity Sizing Ratio
fields.memo: If this terminal unit's heating coil is autosized, the heating capacity is sized to be equal to the cooling capacity multiplied by this sizing ratio. This input applies to the terminal unit heating coil and overrides the sizing ratio entered in the AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow object.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

groundheattransfer:slab:insulation.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:Insulation
groundheattransfer:slab:insulation.memo: This object supplies the information about insulation used around the slab. There are two possible configurations: under the slab or vertical insulation around the slab.

fields.name: RINS: R value of under slab insulation
fields.memo: This field provides the thermal resistance value of the under slab insulation. It should be zero if the vertical insulation configuration is selected. typical value= 0-2.0

fields.name: DINS: Width of strip of under slab insulation
fields.memo: This specifies the width of the perimeter strip of insulation under the slab. It should be zero if for the vertical insulation configuration is selected. typical value= 0-2.0

fields.name: RVINS: R value of vertical insulation
fields.memo: This field specifies the thermal resistance of the vertical insulation. It should be zero if the under slab insulation configuration is selected. typical value= 0-3.0

fields.name: ZVINS: Depth of vertical insulation
fields.memo: This field specifies the depth of the vertical insulation into the ground in meters. It starts at the slab upper surface and extends into the ground. It should be zero if the under slab insulation configuration is selected. only use values= .2 .4 .6 .8 1.0 1.5 2.0 2.5 3.0

fields.name: IVINS: Flag: Is there vertical insulation
fields.memo: Specifies if the vertical insulation configuration is being used. values: 1=yes vertical insulation 0=no under-slab insulation

utilitycost:computation.name: UtilityCost:Computation
utilitycost:computation.memo: The object lists a series of computations that are used to perform the utility bill calculation. The object is only used for complex tariffs that cannot be modeled any other way. For most utility tariffs, UtilityCost:Computation is unnecessary and should be avoided. If UtilityCost:Computation is used, it must contain references to all objects involved in the rate in the order that they should be computed.

fields.name: Tariff Name
fields.memo: The name of the UtilityCost:Tariff that is associated with this UtilityCost:Variable.

fields.name: Compute Step 1
fields.memo: Contain a simple language that describes the steps used in the computation process similar to a programming language.

energymanagementsystem:globalvariable.name: EnergyManagementSystem:GlobalVariable
energymanagementsystem:globalvariable.memo: Declares Erl variable as having global scope No spaces allowed in names used for Erl variables

utilitycost:qualify.name: UtilityCost:Qualify
utilitycost:qualify.memo: The qualify object allows only tariffs to be selected based on limits which may apply such as maximum or minimum demand requirements. If the results of the simulation fall outside of the range of qualifications, that tariff is still calculated but the "Qualified" entry will say "No" and the UtilityCost:Qualify that caused its exclusion is shown. Multiple UtilityCost:Qualify objects can appear for the same tariff and they can be based on any variable.

fields.name: Utility Cost Qualify Name
fields.memo: Displayed in the report if the tariff does not qualify

fields.name: Tariff Name
fields.memo: The name of the UtilityCost:Tariff that is associated with this UtilityCost:Qualify.

fields.name: Variable Name
fields.memo: The name of the variable used. For energy and demand the automatically created variables totalEnergy and totalDemand should be used respectively.

fields.name: Threshold Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: The minimum or maximum value for the qualify. If the variable has values that are less than this value when the qualify type is minimum then the tariff may be disqualified.  If the variable has values that are greater than this value when the qualify type is maximum then the tariff may be disqualified.

fields.name: Season
fields.memo: If the UtilityCost:Qualify only applies to a season enter the season name. If this field is left blank it defaults to Annual.

fields.name: Threshold Test
fields.memo: Uses the number in Number of Months in one of two different ways depending on the Threshold  Test. If the Threshold Test is set to Count then the qualification is based on the count of the total number of months per year.  If the Threshold Test is set to consecutive then the qualification is based on a consecutive number of months.

fields.name: Number of Months
fields.memo: A number from 1 to 12.  If no value entered 12 is assumed when the qualify type is minimum and 1 when the qualify type is maximum.  This is the number of months that the threshold test applies to determine if the rate qualifies or not.  If the season is less than 12 months (if it is not annual) then the value is automatically reduced to the number of months of the season.

airloophvac:controllerlist.name: AirLoopHVAC:ControllerList
airloophvac:controllerlist.memo: List controllers in order of control sequence

parametric:filenamesuffix.name: Parametric:FileNameSuffix
parametric:filenamesuffix.memo: Defines the suffixes to be appended to the idf and output file names for each parametric run. If this object is omitted, the suffix will default to the run number.

thermalstorage:chilledwater:mixed.name: ThermalStorage:ChilledWater:Mixed
thermalstorage:chilledwater:mixed.memo: Chilled water storage with a well-mixed, single-node tank. The chilled water is "used" by drawing from the "Use Side" of the water tank.  The tank is indirectly charged by circulating cold water through the "Source Side" of the water tank.

fields.name: Ambient Temperature Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: required when field Ambient Temperature Indicator=Outdoors

fields.name: Heat Gain Coefficient from Ambient Temperature
Use Side Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for use side. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Source Side Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for source side. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Tank Recovery Time
fields.memo: Parameter for autosizing design flow rates for indirectly cooled water tanks time required to lower temperature of entire tank from 14.4C to 9.0C

solarcollector:flatplate:photovoltaicthe.name: SolarCollector:FlatPlate:PhotovoltaicThermal
solarcollector:flatplate:photovoltaicthe.memo: Models hybrid photovoltaic-thermal (PVT) solar collectors that convert incident solar energy into both electricity and useful thermal energy by heating air or water.

fields.name: Photovoltaic Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:Photovoltaic object.

groundheattransfer:slab:yface.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:YFACE
groundheattransfer:slab:yface.memo: This is only needed when using manual gridding (not recommended) YFACE: Y Direction cell face coordinates: m,

output:table:annual.name: Output:Table:Annual
output:table:annual.memo: Provides a generic method of setting up tables of annual results with one row per object. The report has multiple columns that are each defined using a repeated group of fields for any number of columns. A single Output:Table:Annual produces a single table in the output.

fields.name: Filter
fields.memo: An optional text string that is compared to the names of the objects referenced by the variables and if they match are included in the table. A footnote will appear that indicates that the objects shown may not be all the objects that of that type that occur in the file.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Optional schedule name. If left blank, aggregation is performed for all hours simulated. If a schedule is specified, aggregation is performed for non-zero hours in the schedule.

faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:coils.name: FaultModel:TemperatureSensorOffset:CoilSupplyAir
faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:coils.memo: This object describes fault of coil supply air temperature sensor offset

fields.name: Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of the coil affected

fields.name: Coil Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the coil affected

fields.name: Water Coil Controller Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of controller for the water coil affected Required for water coils

curve:exponent.name: Curve:Exponent
curve:exponent.memo: Exponent curve with one independent variable. Input for a exponent curve consists of the curve name, the 3 coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x**C3 The independent variable x is raised to the C3 power, multiplied by C2, and C1 is added to the result.

fields.name: Minimum Value of x
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value of the independent variable x allowed

fields.name: Maximum Value of x
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value of the independent variable x allowed

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

windowgap:supportpillar.name: WindowGap:SupportPillar
windowgap:supportpillar.memo: used to define pillar geometry for support pillars

solarcollectorperformance:flatplate.name: SolarCollectorPerformance:FlatPlate
solarcollectorperformance:flatplate.memo: Thermal and optical performance parameters for a single flat plate solar collector module. These parameters are based on the testing methodologies described in ASHRAE Standards 93 and 96 which are used Solar Rating and Certification Corporation (SRCC) Directory of SRCC Certified Solar Collector Ratings. See EnergyPlus DataSets file SolarCollectors.idf.

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of Efficiency Equation
fields.memo: Y-intercept term

fields.name: Coefficient 2 of Efficiency Equation
fields.memo: 1st Order term

fields.name: Coefficient 3 of Efficiency Equation
fields.memo: 2nd order term

fields.name: Coefficient 2 of Incident Angle Modifier
fields.memo: 1st order term

fields.name: Coefficient 3 of Incident Angle Modifier
fields.memo: 2nd order term

setpointmanager:scheduled.name: SetpointManager:Scheduled
setpointmanager:scheduled.memo: The simplest Setpoint Manager simply uses a schedule to determine one or more setpoints. Values of the nodes are not used as input.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which control variable will be set

windowmaterial:gasmixture.name: WindowMaterial:GasMixture
windowmaterial:gasmixture.memo: Gas mixtures that are used in Windows or Glass Doors

zoneairmassflowconservation.name: ZoneAirMassFlowConservation
zoneairmassflowconservation.memo: Enforces the zone air mass flow balance by adjusting zone mixing object and/or infiltration object mass flow rates. If either mixing or infiltration is active, then the zone air mass flow balance calculation will attempt to enforce conservation of mass for each zone. If mixing is "No" and infiltration is "None", then the zone air mass flow calculation defaults to assume self-balanced simple flow mixing and infiltration objects.

fields.name: Adjust Zone Mixing For Zone Air Mass Flow Balance
fields.memo: If Yes, Zone mixing object flow rates are adjusted to balance the zone air mass flow and additional infiltration air flow may be added if required in order to balance the zone air mass flow.

fields.name: Infiltration Balancing Method
fields.memo: This input field allows user to choose how zone infiltration flow is treated during the zone air mass flow balance calculation. AddInfiltrationFlow may add infiltration to the base flow specified in the infiltration object to balance the zone air mass flow. The additional infiltration air mass flow is not self-balanced. The base flow is assumed to be self-balanced. AdjustInfiltrationFlow may adjust the base flow calculated using the base flow specified in the infiltration object to balance the zone air mass flow. If it If no adjustment is required, then the base infiltration is assumed to be self-balanced. None will make no changes to the base infiltration flow.

fields.name: Infiltration Balancing Zones
fields.memo: This input field allows user to choose which zones are included in infiltration balancing. MixingSourceZonesOnly allows infiltration balancing only in zones which as source zones for mixing which also have an infiltration object defined. AllZones allows infiltration balancing in any zone which has an infiltration object defined.

hvactemplate:zone:dualduct.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:DualDuct
hvactemplate:zone:dualduct.memo: Zone terminal unit, dual-duct, constant or variable volume.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Dual Duct System Name
fields.memo: Name of a HVACTemplate:System:DualDuct object serving this zone

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: This field is the Zone Minimum Air Flow Fraction specified as a fraction of the maximum air flow rate. This field is ignored if the system serving this zone is constant volume.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Sizing
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification. Note that this field is used only for specifying the design outdoor air flow rate used for sizing. The field Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Control (see above) is used to actively control the VAV terminal air flow rate.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Control
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will increase flow as needed to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow. Note that this field is used only for specifying the design outdoor air flow rate used for control. The field Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Sizing (see below) is used to specify the design outdoor air flow rate.

fields.name: Cold Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Cold supply plenum that serves only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Hot Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Hot supply plenum that serves only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum that serves only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:DualDuct Cooling Coil Design Setpoint

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:DualDuct Heating Coil Design Setpoint

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

groundheattransfer:basement:autogrid.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:AutoGrid
groundheattransfer:basement:autogrid.memo: AutoGrid only necessary when EquivSizing is false If the modeled building is not a rectangle or square, Equivalent sizing MUST be used to get accurate results

fields.name: CLEARANCE: Distance from outside of wall to edge,
SLABX: X dimension of the building slab
SLABY: Y dimension of the building slab
ConcAGHeight: Height of the foundation wall above grade
SlabDepth: Thickness of the floor slab
BaseDepth: Depth of the basement wall below grade

environmentalimpactfactors.name: EnvironmentalImpactFactors
environmentalimpactfactors.memo: Used to help convert district and ideal energy use to a fuel type and provide total carbon equivalent with coefficients Also used in Source=>Site conversions.

fields.name: District Heating Efficiency
fields.memo: District heating efficiency used when converted to natural gas

fields.name: District Cooling COP
fields.memo: District cooling COP used when converted to electricity

fields.name: Steam Conversion Efficiency
fields.memo: Steam conversion efficiency used to convert steam usage to natural gas

fields.name: Total Carbon Equivalent Emission Factor From N2O
Total Carbon Equivalent Emission Factor From CH4
Total Carbon Equivalent Emission Factor From CO2

fan:zoneexhaust.name: Fan:ZoneExhaust
fan:zoneexhaust.memo: Models a fan that exhausts air from a zone.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Flow Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: If field is used, then when fan runs the exhausted air flow rate is controlled to be the scheduled fraction times the Maximum Flow Rate

fields.name: System Availability Manager Coupling Mode
fields.memo: Control if fan is to be interlocked with HVAC system Availability Managers or not.

fields.name: Minimum Zone Temperature Limit Schedule Name
fields.memo: If field is used, the exhaust fan will not run if the zone temperature is lower than this limit

fields.name: Balanced Exhaust Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used to control fan's impact on flow at the return air node. Enter the portion of the exhaust that is balanced by simple airflows.

setpointmanager:coldest.name: SetpointManager:Coldest
setpointmanager:coldest.memo: This SetpointManager is used in dual duct systems to reset the setpoint temperature of the air in the heating supply duct. Usually it is used in conjunction with a SetpointManager:Warmest resetting the temperature of the air in the cooling supply duct.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

availabilitymanager:hybridventilation.name: AvailabilityManager:HybridVentilation
availabilitymanager:hybridventilation.memo: Depending on zone and outdoor conditions overrides window/door opening controls to maximize natural ventilation and turn off an HVAC system when ventilation control conditions are met. This object (zone ventilation object name) has not been instrumented to work with global Zone or Zone List names option for Ventilation:DesignFlowRate.  In order to use, you must enter the single <Ventilation:DesignFlowRate> name in that field. If it is a part of a global ventilation assignment the name will be <Zone Name> <global Ventilation:DesignFlowRate> name. Currently, hybrid ventilation manager is restricted to one per zone. It can either be applied through the air loop or directly to the zone. If hybrid ventilation manager is applied to an air loop and one of the zones served by that air loop also has hybrid ventilation manager, then zone hybrid ventilation manager is disabled.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC or HVACTemplate:System:* object. If this field is left blank, hybrid ventilation managers will be simulated for zone equipment control

fields.name: Control Zone Name
fields.memo: the zone name should be a zone where a thermostat or humidistat is located served by an air primary loop.

fields.name: Ventilation Control Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: The Ventilation control mode contains appropriate integer control types. 0 - uncontrolled (Natural ventilation and HVAC system are controlled by themselves) 1 = Temperature control 2 = Enthalpy control 3 = Dewpoint control 4 = Outdoor ventilation air control 5 = Operative temperature control with 80% adaptive comfort acceptability limits 6 = Operative temperature control with 90% adaptive comfort acceptability limits 7 = Carbon dioxide control

fields.name: Use Weather File Rain Indicators
fields.memo: If Yes, ventilation is shutoff when there is rain If No, there is no rain control

fields.name: Maximum Wind Speed
fields.memo: this is the wind speed above which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature
fields.memo: this is the outdoor temperature below which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature
fields.memo: this is the outdoor temperature above which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Enthalpy
fields.memo: this is the outdoor Enthalpy below which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Enthalpy
fields.memo: this is the outdoor Enthalpy above which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dewpoint
fields.memo: this is the outdoor temperature below which ventilation is shutoff Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = 3

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dewpoint
fields.memo: this is the outdoor dewpoint above which ventilation is shutoff Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = 3

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Ventilation Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Ventilation Control Mode = 4

fields.name: Opening Factor Function of Wind Speed Curve Name
fields.memo: linear curve = a + b*WS quadratic curve = a + b*WS + c*WS**2 WS = wind speed (m/s)

fields.name: AirflowNetwork Control Type Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule is used to incorporate operation of AirflowNetwork large opening objects and HVAC system operation.

fields.name: Simple Airflow Control Type Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule is used to incorporate operation of simple airflow objects and HVAC system operation. The simple airflow objects are Ventilation and Mixing only

fields.name: ZoneVentilation Object Name
fields.memo: This field has not been instrumented to work with global Zone or Zone List names option for Ventilation:DesignFlowRate.  In order to use, you must enter the single <Ventilation:DesignFlowRate> name in this field. If it is a part of a global ventilation assignment the name will be <Zone Name> <global Ventilation:DesignFlowRate> name. The other ZoneVentilation:* and ZoneMixing objects controlled in the same AirLoopHVAC will work in the same way as this ventilation object.

fields.name: Minimum HVAC Operation Time
fields.memo: Minimum operation time when HVAC system is forced on.

fields.name: Minimum Ventilation Time
fields.memo: Minimum ventilation time when natural ventilation is forced on.

hvactemplate:plant:chilledwaterloop.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop
hvactemplate:plant:chilledwaterloop.memo: Plant and condenser loops to serve all HVACTemplate chilled water coils, chillers, and towers.

fields.name: Pump Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available Applies to both chilled water and condenser loop pumps

fields.name: Pump Control Type
fields.memo: Applies to both chilled water and condenser loop pumps

fields.name: Chiller Plant Operation Scheme Type
fields.memo: Default operation type makes all equipment available at all times operating in order of Priority specified in HVACTemplate:Plant:Chiller objects.

fields.name: Chiller Plant Equipment Operation Schemes Name
fields.memo: Name of a PlantEquipmentOperationSchemes object Ignored if Chiller Plant Operation Scheme Type = Default

fields.name: Chilled Water Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Chilled Water Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Chilled Water Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Chilled Water Pump Configuration
fields.memo: VariablePrimaryNoSecondary - variable flow to chillers and coils ConstantPrimaryNoSecondary - constant flow to chillers and coils, excess bypassed ConstantPrimaryVariableSecondary - constant flow to chillers, variable flow to coils VariablePrimaryConstantSecondary - currently unsupported - variable flow to chillers, constant flow to coils

fields.name: Primary Chilled Water Pump Rated Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet H2O

fields.name: Secondary Chilled Water Pump Rated Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet H2O

fields.name: Condenser Plant Operation Scheme Type
fields.memo: Default operation type makes all equipment available at all times operating in order of Priority specified in HVACTemplate:Plant:Tower objects. May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Condenser Equipment Operation Schemes Name
fields.memo: Name of a CondenserEquipmentOperationSchemes object Ignored if Condenser Plant Operation Scheme Type = Default May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Condenser Water Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Condenser Water Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Condenser Water Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Condenser Water Setpoint Schedule Name is specified. May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Condenser Water Pump Rated Head
fields.memo: May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers default head is 60 feet H2O

fields.name: Chilled Water Setpoint Reset Type
fields.memo: Overrides Chilled Water Setpoint Schedule Name

fields.name: Chilled Water Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Chilled Water Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Chilled Water Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Chilled Water Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Chilled Water Primary Pump Type
fields.memo: Describes the type of pump configuration used for the primary portion of the chilled water loop.

fields.name: Chilled Water Secondary Pump Type
fields.memo: Describes the type of pump configuration used for the secondary portion of the chilled water loop.

fields.name: Condenser Water Pump Type
fields.memo: Describes the type of pump configuration used for the condenser water loop.

fields.name: Chilled Water Supply Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a supply side bypass pipe is present in the chilled water loop.

fields.name: Chilled Water Demand Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a demand side bypass pipe is present in the chilled water loop.

fields.name: Condenser Water Supply Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a supply side bypass pipe is present in the condenser water loop.

fields.name: Condenser Water Demand Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a demand side bypass pipe is present in the condenser water loop.

fields.name: Loop Design Delta Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature difference used in sizing the loop flow rate.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: The minimum outdoor dry-bulb temperature that the chilled water loops operate. Leave blank for no limit.

designspecification:zoneairdistribution.name: DesignSpecification:ZoneAirDistribution
designspecification:zoneairdistribution.memo: This object is used to describe zone air distribution in terms of air distribution effectiveness and secondary recirculation fraction. It is referenced by Sizing:Zone and Controller:MechanicalVentilation objects

fields.name: Zone Air Distribution Effectiveness in Cooling Mode
Zone Air Distribution Effectiveness in Heating Mode
Zone Air Distribution Effectiveness Schedule Name
fields.memo: optionally used to replace Zone Air Distribution Effectiveness in Cooling and Heating Mode

availabilitymanager:scheduledon.name: AvailabilityManager:ScheduledOn
availabilitymanager:scheduledon.memo: Determines the availability of a loop or system: only controls the turn on action. Schedule overrides fan/pump schedule.

plantequipmentoperation:thermalenergysto.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:ThermalEnergyStorage
plantequipmentoperation:thermalenergysto.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for simpler input to control thermal (ice) energy storage systems.  It replaces a host of setpoint managers with simple, single input values.  For more complex controls, use the ComponentSetpoint scheme.

fields.name: Non-Charging Chilled Water Temperature
fields.memo: Single temperature for chiller outlet when not in cooling season or during on-peak cooling (discharge)

fields.name: Charging Chilled Water Temperature
fields.memo: Single temperature for chiller outlet when off-peak during cooling season (charging)

fields.name: Component 1 Object Type
fields.memo: This field is the type of object and should either be a chiller or some ice storage equipment.

fields.name: Component 1 Name
fields.memo: This field is the name of either the chiller or ice storage equipment on the loop.

fields.name: Component 1 Demand Calculation Node Name
fields.memo: This field is the name of the inlet node for the component defined in the two previous input fields.

fields.name: Component 1 Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: This field is the name of the outlet node for the component listed above.

fields.name: Component 1 Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is the flow rate for the component listed above.

fields.name: Component 1 Operation Type
fields.memo: This field is the operation type for the component listed above.  For this plant equipment operation scheme, "Cooling" should be selected for chiller equipment while ice storage equipment should be defined as "Dual".

schedule:file:shading.name: Schedule:File:Shading
schedule:file:shading.memo: A Schedule:File:Shading points to a CSV file that has 8760-8784 hours of sunlit fraction data for all or some of the exterior surfaces.

fields.name: File Name
fields.memo: The name of the file that writes all shading data.

groundheatexchanger:horizontaltrench.name: GroundHeatExchanger:HorizontalTrench
groundheatexchanger:horizontaltrench.memo: This models a horizontal heat exchanger placed in a series of trenches The model uses the PipingSystem:Underground underlying algorithms, but provides a more usable input interface.

fields.name: Trench Length in Pipe Axial Direction
fields.memo: This is the total pipe axial length of the heat exchanger If all pipe trenches are parallel, this is the length of a single trench.  If a single, long run of pipe is used with one trench, this is the full length of the pipe run.

fields.name: Number of Trenches
fields.memo: This is the number of horizontal legs that will be used in the entire heat exchanger, one pipe per trench

fields.name: Horizontal Spacing Between Pipes
fields.memo: This represents the average horizontal spacing between any two trenches for heat exchangers that have multiple trenches

fields.name: Burial Depth
fields.memo: This is the burial depth of the pipes, or the trenches containing the pipes

fields.name: Soil Moisture Content Percent at Saturation
Evapotranspiration Ground Cover Parameter
fields.memo: This specifies the ground cover effects during evapotranspiration calculations.  The value roughly represents the following cases: = 0   : concrete or other solid, non-permeable ground surface material = 0.5 : short grass, much like a manicured lawn = 1   : standard reference state (12 cm grass) = 1.5 : wild growth

shading:site.name: Shading:Site
shading:site.memo: used for shading elements such as trees these items are fixed in space and would not move with relative geometry

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of shading device (S=180,N=0,E=90,W=270)

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Starting coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Shade

airloophvac:unitaryheatcool:vavchangeove.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatCool:VAVChangeoverBypass
airloophvac:unitaryheatcool:vavchangeove.memo: Unitary system, heating and cooling with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling), direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, steam, or DX air-to-air heat pump) and bypass damper for variable volume flow to terminal units. Used with AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:HeatAndCool:Reheat or AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:HeatAndCool:NoReheat.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Enter the availability schedule name. Schedule values of zero denote system is Off. Non-zero schedule values denote system is available to operate.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the system air flow rate during cooling operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the system air flow rate during heating operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when the supply air fan operating mode is continuous (see field Supply air fan operating mode schedule name). This system air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the coils are off. If this field is left blank or zero, the system air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Cooling Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor air flow rate during cooling operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Heating Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor air flow rate during heating operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: No Load Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when the supply air fan operating mode is continuous (see field Supply air fan operating mode schedule name). This outdoor air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the coils are off. If this field is left blank or zero, the outdoor air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate Multiplier Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that contains multipliers for the outdoor air flow rates. Schedule values must be from 0 to 1. If field is left blank, model assumes multiplier is 1 for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the unitary system's air inlet node.

fields.name: Bypass Duct Mixer Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the bypass duct mixer node. This name should be the name of the return air node for the outdoor air mixer associated with this system. This node name must be different from the air inlet node name.

fields.name: Bypass Duct Splitter Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the bypass duct splitter node. This splitter air node is the outlet node of the last component in this unitary system. For blow through fan placement, the splitter air node is the outlet node of the heating coil. For draw through fan placement, the splitter node is the outlet node of the supply air fan.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the unitary system's air outlet node.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: currently only one type OutdoorAir:Mixer object is available.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the outdoor air mixer used with this unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of supply air fan used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the supply air fan used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Placement
fields.memo: Specify supply air fan placement as either blow through or draw through. BlowThrough means the supply air fan is located before the cooling coil. DrawThrough means the supply air fan is located after the heating coil.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule to control the supply air fan. Schedule Name values of zero mean that the supply air fan will cycle off if there is no cooling or heating load in any of the zones being served by this system. Non-zero schedule values mean that the supply air fan will operate continuously even if there is no cooling or heating load in any of the zones being served. If this field is left blank, the supply air fan will operate continuously for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of cooling coil used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the cooling coil used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with DX, gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils Specify the type of heating coil used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the heating coil used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Priority Control Mode
fields.memo: CoolingPriority = system provides cooling if any zone requires cooling. HeatingPriority = system provides heating if any zone requires heating. ZonePriority = system controlled based on the total number of zones requiring cooling or heating (highest number of zones in cooling or heating determines the system's operating mode).

fields.name: Minimum Outlet Air Temperature During Cooling Operation
fields.memo: Specify the minimum outlet air temperature allowed for this unitary system during cooling operation. This value should be less than the maximum outlet air temperature during heating operation.

fields.name: Maximum Outlet Air Temperature During Heating Operation
fields.memo: Specify the maximum outlet air temperature allowed for this unitary system during heating operation. This value should be greater than the minimum outlet air temperature during cooling operation.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only. Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load.  Valid only with Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoStageWithHumidityControlMode. CoolReheat = cool beyond the Dry-Bulb temperature setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint.  Valid only with Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoStageWithHumidityControlMode. For all dehumidification controls, the max humidity setpoint on this unitary system's air outlet node is used. This must be set using ZoneControl:Humidistat and SetpointManager:SingleZone:Humidity:Maximum, SetpointManager:MultiZone:Humidity:Maximum or SetpointManager:MultiZone:MaximumHumidity:Average objects.

plantequipmentoperation:outdoordewpointd.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorDewpointDifference
plantequipmentoperation:outdoordewpointd.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor dewpoint temperature difference operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive ranges based the difference between a reference node temperature and the outdoor dewpoint temperature.

fields.name: Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 1 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 1 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 2 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 2 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 3 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 3 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 4 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 4 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 5 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 5 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 6 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 6 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 7 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 7 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 8 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 8 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 9 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 9 Upper Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 10 Lower Limit
Dewpoint Temperature Difference Range 10 Upper Limit

externalinterface:schedule.name: ExternalInterface:Schedule
externalinterface:schedule.memo: A ExternalInterface:Schedule contains only one value, which is used during the warm-up period and the system sizing.

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during warm-up and system sizing.

schedule:compact.name: Schedule:Compact
schedule:compact.memo: Irregular object.  Does not follow the usual definition for fields.  Fields A3... are: Through: Date For: Applicable days (ref: Schedule:Week:Compact) Interpolate: Average/Linear/No (ref: Schedule:Day:Interval) -- optional, if not used will be "No" Until: <Time> (ref: Schedule:Day:Interval) <numeric value> words "Through","For","Interpolate","Until" must be included.

output:meter:cumulative.name: Output:Meter:Cumulative
output:meter:cumulative.memo: Each Output:Meter:Cumulative command picks meters to be reported cumulatively onto the standard output file (.eso) and meter file (.mtr). Not all meters are reported in every simulation. a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Key Name
fields.memo: Form is EnergyUseType:..., e.g. Electricity:* for all Electricity meters or EndUse:..., e.g. GeneralLights:* for all General Lights Output:Meter:Cumulative puts results on both the eplusout.mtr and eplusout.eso files

fields.name: Reporting Frequency
fields.memo: Timestep refers to the zone Timestep/Number of Timesteps in hour value RunPeriod and Environment are the same

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitImport:To:Actuator
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.memo: Hardware portion of EMS used to set up actuators in the model that are dynamically updated from the FMU.

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during the first call of EnergyPlus.

output:energymanagementsystem.name: Output:EnergyManagementSystem
output:energymanagementsystem.memo: This object is used to control the output produced by the Energy Management System

fields.name: EMS Runtime Language Debug Output Level

material:infraredtransparent.name: Material:InfraredTransparent
material:infraredtransparent.memo: Special infrared transparent material.  Similar to a Material:Nomass with low thermal resistance. High absorptance in both wavelengths. Area will be doubled internally to make internal radiant exchange accurate. Should be only material in single layer surface construction. All thermal properties are set internally. User needs only to supply name. Cannot be used with ConductionFiniteDifference solution algorithms

output:variabledictionary.name: Output:VariableDictionary
output:variabledictionary.memo: Produces a list summarizing the output variables and meters that are available for reporting for the model being simulated (rdd output file). The list varies depending on the types of objects present in the idf file.  For example, variables related to lights will only appear if a Lights object is present. The IDF option generates complete Output:Variable objects to simplify adding the desired output to the idf file.

airloophvac:unitaryheatpump:watertoair.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatPump:WaterToAir
airloophvac:unitaryheatpump:watertoair.memo: Unitary heat pump system, heating and cooling, single-speed with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling), direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, DX heating coil (water-to-air heat pump), and supplemental heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This value should be > 0 and <= than the fan air flow rate.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with On/Off Fan

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match Fan:OnOff object

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the water-to-air heat pump heating coil object

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the water-to-air heat pump cooling coil object

fields.name: Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: The maximum on-off cycling rate for the compressor Suggested value is 2.5 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Heat Pump Time Constant
fields.memo: Time constant for the cooling coil's capacity to reach steady state after startup Suggested value is 60 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Fraction of On-Cycle Power Use
fields.memo: The fraction of on-cycle power use to adjust the part load fraction based on the off-cycle power consumption due to crankcase heaters, controls, fans, and etc. Suggested value is 0.01 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Heat Pump Fan Delay Time
fields.memo: Programmed time delay for heat pump fan to shut off after compressor cycle off. Only required when fan operating mode is cycling Enter 0 when fan operating mode is continuous

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the supplemental heating coil object

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature from Supplemental Heater
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Supplemental Heater Operation
Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature Sensor Node Name
Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling or heating coil). Schedule values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this field is left blank.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint. as required to meet the humidity setpoint.  Valid only with Coil:Cooling:WaterToAirHeatPump:EquationFit or Coil:Cooling:WaterToAirHeatPump:VariableSpeedEquationFit

fields.name: Heat Pump Coil Water Flow Mode
fields.memo: used only when the heat pump coils are of the type WaterToAirHeatPump:EquationFit Constant results in 100% water flow regardless of compressor PLR Cycling results in water flow that matches compressor PLR ConstantOnDemand results in 100% water flow whenever the coil is on, but is 0% whenever the coil has no load

zonecooltower:shower.name: ZoneCoolTower:Shower
zonecooltower:shower.memo: A cooltower (sometimes referred to as a wind tower or a shower cooling tower) models passive downdraught evaporative cooling (PDEC) that is designed to capture the wind at the top of a tower and cool the outdoor air using water evaporation before delivering it to a space.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Water Supply Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: In case of stand alone tank or underground water, leave this input blank

fields.name: Flow Control Type
fields.memo: Water flow schedule should be selected when the water flow rate is known. Wind-driven flow should be selected when the water flow rate is unknown.

fields.name: Effective Tower Height
fields.memo: This field is from either the spray or the wet pad to the top of the outlet.

fields.name: Airflow Outlet Area
fields.memo: User have to specify effective area when outlet area is relatively bigger than the cross sectional area of cooltower. If the number of outlet is more than one, assume the air passes through only one.

fields.name: Minimum Indoor Temperature
fields.memo: This field is to specify the indoor temperature below which cooltower is shutoff.

sizing:system.name: Sizing:System
sizing:system.memo: Specifies the input needed to perform sizing calculations for a central forced air system. System design air flow, heating capacity, and cooling capacity will be calculated using this input data.

fields.name: Type of Load to Size On
fields.memo: Specifies the basis for sizing the system supply air flow rate Sensible and Total use the zone design air flow rates to size the system supply air flow rate The cooling coil will then be sized at either the peak Sensible or Total flow rate and conditions The heating coil is always sized at the peak sensible heating load. VentilationRequirement uses the system ventilation requirement

fields.name: Central Heating Maximum System Air Flow Ratio
Central Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
Central Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
Type of Zone Sum to Use
Central Cooling Design Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Central Heating Design Supply Air Humidity Ratio
Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method
Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This input is used if Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is Flow/System This value will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers. If using zone multipliers, this value must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the cooling supply air volume flow rate per total conditioned floor area. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Cooling Fraction of Autosized Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling supply air flow rate. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingAirflow.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate per unit cooling capacity. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerCoolingCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method
Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is Flow/System This value will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers. If using zone multipliers, this value must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating supply air volume flow rate per total conditioned floor area. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Heating Fraction of Autosized Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating supply air flow rate. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingAirflow.

fields.name: Heating Fraction of Autosized Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling supply air flow rate. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingAirflow.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the heating supply air volume flow rate per unit heating capacity. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the system cooling design capacity for scalable sizing. None is used when a cooling coils is not included in an airloop or this field may be blank. If this input field is left blank, then the design cooling capacity is set to zero. CoolingDesignCapacity => selected when the design cooling capacity value is specified or auto-sized. CapacityPerFloorArea => selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from user specified cooling capacity per floor area and total floor area of cooled zones served by an airloop. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity => is selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design cooling capacity of the system.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design cooling capacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the cooling design capacity per total floor area of cooled zones served by an airloop. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto-sized cooling design capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity for scalable sizing. None is used when a heating coil not included in an airloop or this field may be blank. If this input field is left blank, then the design heating capacity is set to zero. HeatingDesignCapacity => selected when the design heating capacity value is specified or auto-sized. CapacityPerFloorArea => selected when the design heating capacity is determined from user specified heating capacity per flow area and total floor area of heated zones served by an airloop. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity => is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity of the system.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area. Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto-sized heating design capacity. Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Central Cooling Capacity Control Method
fields.memo: Method used to control the coil's output

setpointmanager:singlezone:humidity:mini.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:Humidity:Minimum
setpointmanager:singlezone:humidity:mini.memo: The Single Zone Minimum Humidity Setpoint Manager allows the control of a single zone minimum humidity level. This setpoint manager can be used in conjunction with object ZoneControl:Humidistat to detect humidity levels.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which humidity ratio setpoint will be set

fields.name: Control Zone Air Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the zone air node for the humidity control zone

wateruse:connections.name: WaterUse:Connections
wateruse:connections.memo: A subsystem that groups together multiple WaterUse:Equipment components. As its name suggests, the object provides connections that are shared by these components, including: 1. Inlet node and outlet node connections to a plant loop 2. Connections to WaterUse:Storage objects to store and draw reclaimed water 3. Internal connections to simulate drainwater heat recovery.

fields.name: Supply Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: If blank, or tank is empty, defaults to fresh water from the mains

fields.name: Hot Water Supply Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to cold water supply temperature

fields.name: Cold Water Supply Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to water temperatures calculated by Site:WaterMainsTemperature object

fields.name: Drain Water Heat Exchanger U-Factor Times Area

zone.name: Zone
zone.memo: Defines a thermal zone of the building.

fields.name: Ceiling Height
fields.memo: If this field is 0.0, negative or autocalculate, then the average height of the zone is automatically calculated and used in subsequent calculations. If this field is positive, then the number entered here will be used. Note that the Zone Ceiling Height is the distance from the Floor to the Ceiling in the Zone, not an absolute height from the ground.

fields.name: Volume
fields.memo: If this field is 0.0, negative or autocalculate, then the volume of the zone is automatically calculated and used in subsequent calculations. If this field is positive, then the number entered here will be used.

fields.name: Floor Area
fields.memo: If this field is 0.0, negative or autocalculate, then the floor area of the zone is automatically calculated and used in subsequent calculations. If this field is positive, then the number entered here will be used.

fields.name: Zone Inside Convection Algorithm
fields.memo: Will default to same value as SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Inside object setting this field overrides the default SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Inside for this zone Simple = constant natural convection (ASHRAE) TARP = variable natural convection based on temperature difference (ASHRAE) CeilingDiffuser = ACH based forced and mixed convection correlations for ceiling diffuser configuration with simple natural convection limit AdaptiveConvectionAlgorithm = dynamic selection of convection models based on conditions TrombeWall = variable natural convection in an enclosed rectangular cavity

fields.name: Zone Outside Convection Algorithm
fields.memo: Will default to same value as SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside object setting this field overrides the default SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside for this zone SimpleCombined = Combined radiation and convection coefficient using simple ASHRAE model TARP = correlation from models developed by ASHRAE, Walton, and Sparrow et. al. MoWiTT = correlation from measurements by Klems and Yazdanian for smooth surfaces DOE-2 = correlation from measurements by Klems and Yazdanian for rough surfaces AdaptiveConvectionAlgorithm = dynamic selection of correlations based on conditions

zonehvac:outdoorairunit.name: ZoneHVAC:OutdoorAirUnit
zonehvac:outdoorairunit.memo: The zone outdoor air unit models a single-zone dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Forced-convection 100% outdoor air unit with supply fan and optional equipment including exhaust fan, heating coil, cooling coil, and heat recovery.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: (name of zone system is serving)

fields.name: Supply Fan Name
fields.memo: Allowable fan types are Fan:SystemModel and Fan:ConstantVolume and Fan:VariableVolume

fields.name: Exhaust Fan Name
fields.memo: Allowable fan types are Fan:ConstantVolume and Fan:VariableVolume

fields.name: High Air Control Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Air and control temperatures for cooling. If outdoor air temperature is above the high air control temperature, then the zone inlet air temperature is set to the high air control temperature. If the outdoor air is between high and low air control temperature, then there is no cooling/heating requirements.

fields.name: Low Air Control Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Air and control temperatures for Heating. If outdoor air temperature is below the low air control temperature, then the zone inlet air temperature is set to the low air control temperature. If the outdoor air is between high and low air control temperature, then there is no cooling/heating requirements.

fields.name: AirInlet Node Name
fields.memo: air leaves zone

fields.name: Outdoor Air Unit List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an ZoneHVAC:OutdoorAirUnit:EquipmentList object.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

site:groundtemperature:shallow.name: Site:GroundTemperature:Shallow
site:groundtemperature:shallow.memo: These temperatures are specifically for the Surface Ground Heat Exchanger and should probably be close to the average outdoor air temperature for the location. They are not used in other models.

runperiod.name: RunPeriod
runperiod.memo: Specified a range of dates and other parameters for a weather file simulation. Multiple run periods may be input, but they may not overlap.

fields.name: Day of Week for Start Day
fields.memo: =<blank - use WeatherFile>|Sunday|Monday|Tuesday|Wednesday|Thursday|Friday|Saturday];

fields.name: Use Weather File Holidays and Special Days
fields.memo: If yes or blank, use holidays as specified on Weatherfile. If no, do not use the holidays specified on the Weatherfile. Note: You can still specify holidays/special days using the RunPeriodControl:SpecialDays object(s).

fields.name: Use Weather File Daylight Saving Period
fields.memo: If yes or blank, use daylight saving period as specified on Weatherfile. If no, do not use the daylight saving period as specified on the Weatherfile.

fields.name: Apply Weekend Holiday Rule
fields.memo: if yes and single day holiday falls on weekend, "holiday" occurs on following Monday

fields.name: Number of Times Runperiod to be Repeated
Increment Day of Week on repeat
Start Year
fields.memo: this is the start year for the start date.  If the leap year is "Yes" in the weather file header (that is HOLIDAYS/SPECIAL DAYS header first field), then any year which is a leap year will assume there will be a Feb 29. A repeat of this runperiod will automatically increment the year.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during cooling operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during heating operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
