fields.memo: Supply air flow rate when no cooling or heating is needed Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. A value entered in this field will *not* be multiplied by the sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  It is best to autosize or leave blank when using zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include effect of supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Capacity excluding supply air fan heat Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Heat Pump Heating Coil Rated Capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, Does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
Heat Pump Defrost Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
Heat Pump Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode only applicable if Timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Supplemental heater will not operate when outdoor temperature exceeds this value.

fields.name: Supplemental Gas Heating Coil Efficiency
fields.memo: Applies only if Supplemental Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Supplemental Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Applies only if Supplemental Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:DedicatedOutdoorAir object if this zone is served by a separate dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Leave field blank if no DOAS serves this zone.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

solarcollectorperformance:photovoltaicth.name: SolarCollectorPerformance:PhotovoltaicThermal:Simple
solarcollectorperformance:photovoltaicth.memo: Thermal performance parameters for a hybrid photovoltaic-thermal (PVT) solar collector.

fields.name: Fraction of Surface Area with Active Thermal Collector
Thermal Conversion Efficiency Input Mode Type
Value for Thermal Conversion Efficiency if Fixed
fields.memo: Efficiency = (thermal power generated [W])/(incident solar[W])

waterheater:sizing.name: WaterHeater:Sizing
waterheater:sizing.memo: This input object is used with WaterHeater:Mixed or with WaterHeater:Stratified to autosize tank volume and heater capacity This object is not needed if water heaters are not autosized.

fields.name: Time Storage Can Meet Peak Draw
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PeakDraw

fields.name: Time for Tank Recovery
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PeakDraw

fields.name: Nominal Tank Volume for Autosizing Plant Connections
fields.memo: Only used if Design Mode = PeakDraw and the water heater also has autosized flow rates for connections on the demand side of a plant loop

fields.name: Number of Bedrooms
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = ResidentialHUD-FHAMinimum

fields.name: Number of Bathrooms
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = ResidentialHUD-FHAMinimum

fields.name: Storage Capacity per Person
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerPerson

fields.name: Recovery Capacity per Person
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerPerson

fields.name: Storage Capacity per Floor Area
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerFloorArea

fields.name: Recovery Capacity per Floor Area
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerFloorArea

fields.name: Number of Units
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerUnit

fields.name: Storage Capacity per Unit
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerUnit

fields.name: Recovery Capacity PerUnit
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerUnit

fields.name: Storage Capacity per Collector Area
fields.memo: Only used for Design Mode = PerSolarCollectorArea

fields.name: Height Aspect Ratio
fields.memo: only used if for WaterHeater:Stratified

faultmodel:enthalpysensoroffset:returnai.name: FaultModel:EnthalpySensorOffset:ReturnAir
faultmodel:enthalpysensoroffset:returnai.memo: This object describes return air enthalpy sensor offset

site:precipitation.name: Site:Precipitation
site:precipitation.memo: Used to describe the amount of water precipitation at the building site. Precipitation includes both rain and the equivalent water content of snow.

fields.name: Design Level for Total Annual Precipitation
fields.memo: meters of water per year used for design level

fields.name: Precipitation Rates Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values in meters of water per hour values should be non-negative

fields.name: Average Total Annual Precipitation
fields.memo: meters of water per year from average weather statistics

airflownetwork:distribution:component:re.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:ReliefAirFlow
airflownetwork:distribution:component:re.memo: This object allows variation of air flow rate to perform pressure.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient When No Outdoor Air Flow at Reference Conditions
fields.memo: Enter the air mass flow coefficient at the conditions defined in the Reference Crack Conditions object. Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference. Enter the coefficient used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when no outdoor air flow rate.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent When No Outdoor Air Flow
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when no outdoor air flow rate.

fields.name: Reference Crack Conditions
fields.memo: Select a AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ReferenceCrackConditions name associated with the air mass flow coefficient entered above.

curve:linear.name: Curve:Linear
curve:linear.memo: Linear curve with one independent variable. Input for the linear curve consists of a curve name, the two coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

outputcontrol:table:style.name: OutputControl:Table:Style
outputcontrol:table:style.memo: default style for the OutputControl:Table:Style is comma -- this works well for importing into spreadsheet programs such as Excel(tm) but not so well for word processing programs -- there tab may be a better choice.  fixed puts spaces between the "columns".  HTML produces tables in HTML. XML produces an XML file. note - if no OutputControl:Table:Style is included, the defaults are comma and None.

material.name: Material
material.memo: Regular materials described with full set of thermal properties

componentcost:lineitem.name: ComponentCost:LineItem
componentcost:lineitem.memo: Each instance of this object creates a cost line item and will contribute to the total for a cost estimate.

fields.name: Line Item Type
fields.memo: extend choice-keys as Cases are added to code

fields.name: Item Name
fields.memo: wildcard "*" is acceptable for some components

fields.name: Object End-Use Key
fields.memo: not yet used

fields.name: Cost per Unit of Output Capacity
Cost per Unit of Output Capacity per COP
fields.memo: The value is per change in COP.

fields.name: Cost per Energy per Temperature Difference
fields.memo: as in for use with UA sizing of Coils

fields.name: Quantity
fields.memo: optional for use with Cost per Each and "General" object Type

construction.name: Construction
construction.memo: Start with outside layer and work your way to the inside layer Up to 10 layers total, 8 for windows Enter the material name for each layer

roomairsettings:threenodedisplacementven.name: RoomAirSettings:ThreeNodeDisplacementVentilation
roomairsettings:threenodedisplacementven.memo: The UCSD model for Displacement Ventilation

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of Zone being described. Any existing zone name

fields.name: Gain Distribution Schedule Name
fields.memo: Distribution of the convective heat gains between the occupied and mixed zones. 0<= Accepted Value <= 1. In the DV model 1 means all convective gains in the lower layer.

fields.name: Number of Plumes per Occupant
fields.memo: Used only in the UCSD displacement ventilation model. Effective number of separate plumes per occupant in the occupied zone. Plumes that merge together in the occupied zone count as one.

fields.name: Thermostat Height
fields.memo: Height of thermostat/temperature control sensor above floor

fields.name: Comfort Height
fields.memo: Height at which air temperature is calculated for comfort purposes

fields.name: Temperature Difference Threshold for Reporting
fields.memo: Minimum temperature difference between predicted upper and lower layer temperatures above which DV auxiliary outputs are calculated. These outputs are 'DV Transition Height', 'DV Fraction Min Recommended Flow Rate' 'DV Average Temp Gradient' and 'DV Maximum Temp Gradient'.  They are set to negative values when the temperature difference is less than the threshold and the output 'DV Zone Is Mixed' is set to 1

hvactemplate:plant:boiler:objectreferenc.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:Boiler:ObjectReference
hvactemplate:plant:boiler:objectreferenc.memo: This object references a detailed boiler object and adds it to an HVACTemplate:Plant:HotWaterLoop or MixedWaterLoop. The user must create a complete detailed boiler object with all required curve or performance objects.

fields.name: Boiler Name
fields.memo: The name of the detailed boiler object.

fields.name: Priority
fields.memo: If Hot Water Plant Operation Scheme Type=Default in HVACTemplate:Plant:HotWaterLoop or MixedWaterLoop, then equipment operates in Priority order, 1, 2, 3, etc.

fields.name: Template Plant Loop Type
fields.memo: Specifies if this boiler serves a template hot water loop or mixed water loop If left blank, will serve a hot water loop if present, or a mixed water loop (if no hot water loop is present).

plantequipmentoperation:outdoordrybulb.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorDryBulb
plantequipmentoperation:outdoordrybulb.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor dry-bulb temperature range operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive outdoor dry-bulb temperature ranges.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on; Unitary System always on.  Schedule is used in availability manager and fan scheduling. Also see "Night Cycle Control" field.

fields.name: Control Zone or Thermostat Location Name
Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross SHR

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electric power

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing.

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the minimum outdoor air flow rate If blank, always one

fields.name: Economizer Upper Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Lower Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature below which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Upper Enthalpy Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor enthalpy above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Night Cycle Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Applicable only if Night Cycle Control is Cycle On Control Zone.

fields.name: Latent Heat Recovery Effectiveness
fields.memo: Applicable only if Heat Recovery Type is Enthalpy.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible cooling load only CoolReheatHeatingCoil = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint, reheat with main heating coil. CoolReheatDesuperheater = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint, reheat with desuperheater coil.

fields.name: Dehumidification Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction

zonegroup.name: ZoneGroup
zonegroup.memo: Adds a multiplier to a ZoneList. This can be used to reduce the amount of input necessary for simulating repetitive structures, such as the identical floors of a multi-story building.

coil:cooling:dx:twospeed.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoSpeed
coil:cooling:dx:twospeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and condensing unit (includes electric compressor and condenser fan), two-speed (or variable-speed). Requires two sets of performance data and will interpolate between speeds. Modeled as a single coil (multi-speed compressor or multiple compressors with row split or intertwined coil).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: High Speed Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: High Speed Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: High Speed Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: High Speed Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total cooling capacity, Rated SHR and Rated COP. Should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total cooling capacity.

fields.name: Unit Internal Static Air Pressure
fields.memo: Enter pressure drop for the unit containing the coil. This value is only used to calculate Energy Efficiency Ratio (EER), Integrated Energy Efficiency Ratio (IEER), and the Standard Rating (Net) Cooling Capacity. This value is not used for modeling the evaporator fan during simulations.

fields.name: Total Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Total Cooling Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Low Speed Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Low Speed Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Low Speed Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Low Speed Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total cooling capacity, Rated SHR and Rated COP. Should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total cooling capacity.

fields.name: Low Speed Total Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Low Speed Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
High Speed Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use

fields.name: High Speed Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump at high speed

fields.name: Low Speed Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use

fields.name: Low Speed Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump at low speed

fields.name: Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*wb*db wb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) db = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) entering temperature can be outside air or pretreated air.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Low Speed Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*wb*db wb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) db = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) entering temperature can be outside air or pretreated air.

fields.name: Low Speed Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Zone Name for Condenser Placement
fields.memo: This input field is name of a conditioned or unconditioned zone where the secondary coil (condenser) of DX system or a heat pump is to be placed.  This is an optional input field specified only when user desires to reject the condenser heat into a zone. The heat rejected is modelled as internal sensible heat gain of the zone.

wall:underground.name: Wall:Underground
wall:underground.memo: Allows for simplified entry of underground walls.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file. If the construction is type "Construction:CfactorUndergroundWall", then the GroundFCfactorMethod will be used.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of wall (S=180,N=0,E=90,W=270)

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Walls are usually tilted 90 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Starting (x,y,z) coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Wall

heatexchanger:airtoair:sensibleandlatent.name: HeatExchanger:AirToAir:SensibleAndLatent
heatexchanger:airtoair:sensibleandlatent.memo: This object models an air-to-air heat exchanger using effectiveness relationships. The heat exchanger can transfer sensible energy, latent energy, or both between the supply (primary) and exhaust (secondary) air streams.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Sensible Effectiveness at 100% Heating Air Flow
Latent Effectiveness at 100% Heating Air Flow
Sensible Effectiveness at 75% Heating Air Flow
Latent Effectiveness at 75% Heating Air Flow
Sensible Effectiveness at 100% Cooling Air Flow
Latent Effectiveness at 100% Cooling Air Flow
Sensible Effectiveness at 75% Cooling Air Flow
Latent Effectiveness at 75% Cooling Air Flow
Threshold Temperature
fields.memo: Supply (outdoor) air inlet temp threshold for exhaust air recirculation and exhaust only frost control types. Exhaust air outlet threshold Temperature for minimum exhaust temperature frost control type.

fields.name: Initial Defrost Time Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of the time when frost control will be invoked at the threshold temperature. This field only used for exhaust air recirc and exhaust-only frost control types.

fields.name: Rate of Defrost Time Fraction Increase
fields.memo: Rate of increase in defrost time fraction as actual temp falls below threshold temperature. This field only used for exhaust air recirc and exhaust-only frost control types.

fields.name: Economizer Lockout
fields.memo: Yes means that the heat exchanger will be locked out (off) when the economizer is operating or high humidity control is active

coil:heating:watertoairheatpump:equation.name: Coil:Heating:WaterToAirHeatPump:EquationFit
coil:heating:watertoairheatpump:equation.memo: Direct expansion (DX) heating coil for water-to-air heat pump (includes electric compressor), single-speed, equation-fit model. Equation-fit model uses normalized curves to describe the heat pump performance.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

hvactemplate:plant:tower.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:Tower
hvactemplate:plant:tower.memo: This object adds a cooling tower to an HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop or MixedWaterLoop.

fields.name: High Speed Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Applicable for tower type SingleSpeed and TwoSpeed Nominal tower capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature, with the tower fan operating at high speed. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt(3 gpm/ton). Nominal tower capacity times (1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: High Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: Applicable for tower type SingleSpeed and TwoSpeed

fields.name: Low Speed Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Applicable only for Tower Type TwoSpeed Nominal tower capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature, with the tower fan operating at low speed. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt of tower high-speed nominal capacity (3 gpm/ton). Nominal tower capacity times (1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Low Speed Fan Power
fields.memo: Applicable only for Tower Type TwoSpeed

fields.name: Free Convection Capacity
fields.memo: Applicable for Tower Type SingleSpeed and TwoSpeed Tower capacity in free convection regime with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt of tower high-speed nominal capacity (3 gpm/ton). Tower free convection capacity times (1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Priority
fields.memo: Applicable for all Tower Types If Condenser Plant Operation Scheme Type=Default in HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop, then equipment operates in Priority order, 1, 2, 3, etc.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Template Plant Loop Type
fields.memo: Specifies if this tower serves a template chilled water loop or mixed water loop If left blank, will serve a chilled water loop if present, or a mixed water loop (if no chilled water loop is present).

chiller:electric:reformulatedeir.name: Chiller:Electric:ReformulatedEIR
chiller:electric:reformulatedeir.memo: This chiller model is an empirical model, a reformulated version of Chiller:Electric:EIR where the performance is a function of condenser leaving fluid Temperature instead of condenser entering fluid Temperature. Chiller performance at off-reference conditions is modeled using three polynomial equations. Three curve objects are required.

fields.name: Reference COP
fields.memo: Efficiency of the chiller compressor (cooling output/compressor energy input). Condenser fan power should not be included here.

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Cooling capacity as a function of supply (leaving) chilled water temperature and leaving condenser fluid temperature curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*LCT + e*LCT**2 + f*CWS*LCT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of supply (leaving) chilled water temperature and leaving condenser fluid temperature.   EIR = 1/COP. curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*LCT + e*LCT**2 + f*CWS*LCT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Type
fields.memo: Two curve types are available: Type LeavingCondenserWaterTemperature: based on the leaving condenser water temperature. Type Lift: based on the normalized lift, which is the temperature difference between the leaving condenser water temperature and the leaving evaporator water temperature.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) EIR = 1/COP The form of this curve is based on the input for Electric Input to Cooling Output RatioFunction of Part Load Ratio Curve Type Type=LeavingCondenserWaterTemperature: Calculated based on LCT and PLR Curve object type should be Curve:Bicubic or Table:TwoIndependentVariables Bicubic curve = a + b*LCT + c*LCT**2 + d*PLR + e*PLR**2 + f*LCT*PLR + g*0 + h*PLR**3 + i*0 + j*0 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) Type=Lift: Calculated based on dT*, Tdev* and PLR Curve object type should be Curve:ChillerPartLoadWithLiftCurves or Table:MultiVariableLookup ChillerPartLoadWithLiftCurves curve = a + b*(dT*) + c*(dT*)**2 + d*PLR + e*PLR**2 + f*(dT*)*PLR + g*(dT*)**3 + h*PLR**3 + i*(dT*)**2*PLR + j*(dT*)*PLR**2 + k*(dT*)**2*PLR**2 + l*(Tdev*)*PLR**3 x = dT* = normalized fractional Lift = dT / dTref y = PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity) z = Tdev* = normalized Tdev = Tdev / dTref Where: dT = Lift = Leaving Condenser Water Temperature - Leaving Chilled Water Temperature dTref = dT at the reference condition Tdev = Leaving Chilled Water Temperature - Reference Chilled Water Temperature

fields.name: Minimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Part load ratio below which the chiller starts cycling on/off to meet the load. Must be less than or equal to Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Maximum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Maximum allowable part load ratio. Must be greater than or equal to Minimum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Optimum part load ratio where the chiller is most efficient. Must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Minimum Unloading Ratio
fields.memo: Part load ratio where the chiller can no longer unload and false loading begins. Minimum unloading ratio must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Fraction of Compressor Electric Consumption Rejected by Condenser
fields.memo: Fraction of compressor electrical energy that must be rejected by the condenser. Enter a value of 1.0 when modeling hermetic chillers. For open chillers, enter the compressor motor efficiency. This value should be greater than 0.6 for practical applications.

fields.name: Leaving Chilled Water Lower Temperature Limit
Chiller Flow Mode Type
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Condenser Heat Recovery Relative Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This optional field is the fraction of total rejected heat that can be recovered at full load

fields.name: Heat Recovery Inlet High Temperature Limit Schedule Name
fields.memo: This optional schedule of temperatures will turn off heat recovery if inlet exceeds the value

fields.name: Heat Recovery Leaving Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: This optional field provides control over the heat recovery Using this triggers a model more suited to series bundle and chillers with higher temperature heat recovery If this field is not used, the bundles are modeled as being in parallel

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

dehumidifier:desiccant:system.name: Dehumidifier:Desiccant:System
dehumidifier:desiccant:system.memo: This compound object models a desiccant heat exchanger, an optional heater, and associated fans. The process air stream is the air which is dehumidified. The regeneration air stream is the air which is heated to regenerate the desiccant. The desiccant heat exchanger transfers both sensible and latent energy between the process and regeneration air streams. The desiccant dehumidifier is typically used in an AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem, but can also be specified in any AirLoopHVAC.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Regeneration Air Heater Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils. For autosizing the regeneration air heating coil the Design Coil Inlet Air Condition used is the outdoor air condition if the desiccant system is on the primary air loop, or else if the desiccant system is on outdoor air system then it is the return air condition. The Design Coil Outlet Air Temperature is the Regeneration Inlet Air Setpoint Temperature specified in the input field below.

fields.name: Regeneration Inlet Air Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This value is also used as regeneration air heater design coil air outlet temperature for autosizing calculation of the heater.

fields.name: Companion Cooling Coil Upstream of Dehumidifier Process Inlet
fields.memo: Select Yes if the companion cooling coil is located directly upstream of the desiccant heat exchanger's process air inlet node.

fields.name: Exhaust Fan Power Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve object type must be Curve:Quadratic or Curve:Cubic

groundheattransfer:slab:xface.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:XFACE
groundheattransfer:slab:xface.memo: This is only needed when using manual gridding (not recommended) XFACE: X Direction cell face coordinates: m

scheduletypelimits.name: ScheduleTypeLimits
scheduletypelimits.memo: ScheduleTypeLimits specifies the data types and limits for the values contained in schedules

fields.name: Lower Limit Value
fields.memo: lower limit (real or integer) for the Schedule Type.  e.g. if fraction, this is 0.0

fields.name: Upper Limit Value
fields.memo: upper limit (real or integer) for the Schedule Type.  e.g. if fraction, this is 1.0

fields.name: Numeric Type
fields.memo: Numeric type is either Continuous (all numbers within the min and max are valid or Discrete (only integer numbers between min and max are valid.  (Could also allow REAL and INTEGER to mean the same things)

fields.name: Unit Type
fields.memo: Temperature (C or F) DeltaTemperature (C or F) PrecipitationRate (m/hr or ft/hr) Angle (degrees) Convection Coefficient (W/m2-K or Btu/sqft-hr-F) Activity Level (W/person) Velocity (m/s or ft/min) Capacity (W or Btu/h) Power (W)

sizingperiod:weatherfiledays.name: SizingPeriod:WeatherFileDays
sizingperiod:weatherfiledays.memo: Use a weather file period for design sizing calculations.

fields.name: Day of Week for Start Day
fields.memo: =[|Sunday|Monday|Tuesday|Wednesday|Thursday|Friday|Saturday|SummerDesignDay|WinterDesignDay| |CustomDay1|CustomDay2]; if you use SummerDesignDay or WinterDesignDay or the CustomDays then this will apply to the whole period; other days (i.e., Monday) will signify a start day and normal sequence of subsequent days

fields.name: Use Weather File Daylight Saving Period
fields.memo: If yes or blank, use daylight saving period as specified on Weatherfile. If no, do not use the daylight saving period as specified on the Weatherfile.

fields.name: Use Weather File Rain and Snow Indicators

faultmodel:fouling:coil.name: FaultModel:Fouling:Coil
faultmodel:fouling:coil.memo: This object describes fouling water heating or cooling coils

fields.name: UAFouled
fields.memo: Fouling coil UA value under rating conditions For Fouling Input Method: FouledUARated

fields.name: Water Side Fouling Factor
fields.memo: For Fouling Input Method: FoulingFactor

fields.name: Air Side Fouling Factor
fields.memo: For Fouling Input Method: FoulingFactor

fields.name: Outside Coil Surface Area
fields.memo: For Fouling Input Method: FoulingFactor

fields.name: Inside to Outside Coil Surface Area Ratio
fields.memo: For Fouling Input Method: FoulingFactor

faultmodel:humiditysensoroffset:outdoora.name: FaultModel:HumiditySensorOffset:OutdoorAir
faultmodel:humiditysensoroffset:outdoora.memo: This object describes outdoor air humidity sensor offset

people.name: People
people.memo: Sets internal gains and contaminant rates for occupants in the zone. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Number of People Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in schedule should be fraction applied to number of people (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Number of People Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum number of people for this set of attributes (i.e. sensible fraction, schedule, etc) Choices: People -- simply enter number of occupants. People per Zone Floor Area -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Floor Area = Number of people Zone Floor Area per Person -- enter the number to apply.  Floor Area / Value = Number of people

fields.name: Fraction Radiant
fields.memo: This is radiant fraction of the sensible heat released by people in a zone. This value will be multiplied by the total sensible heat released by people yields the amount of long wavelength radiation gain from people in a zone. Default value is 0.30.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Fraction
fields.memo: if input, overrides program calculated sensible/latent split

fields.name: Activity Level Schedule Name
fields.memo: Note that W has to be converted to mets in TC routine units in schedule are W/person

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Generation Rate
fields.memo: CO2 generation rate per unit of activity level. The default value is obtained from ASHRAE Std 62.1 at 0.0084 cfm/met/person over the general adult population.

fields.name: Mean Radiant Temperature Calculation Type
fields.memo: optional (only required for thermal comfort runs)

fields.name: Surface Name/Angle Factor List Name
fields.memo: optional (only required for runs of thermal comfort models: Fanger, Pierce and KSU)

fields.name: Work Efficiency Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in schedule are 0.0 to 1.0 optional (only required for runs of thermal comfort models: Fanger, Pierce and KSU)

fields.name: Clothing Insulation Calculation Method Schedule Name
fields.memo: a schedule value of 1 for the Scheduled method, and 2 for the DynamicClothingModelASHRAE55 method

fields.name: Clothing Insulation Schedule Name
fields.memo: use "Clo" from ASHRAE or Thermal Comfort guides optional (only required for runs of thermal comfort models: Fanger, Pierce and KSU)

fields.name: Air Velocity Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in the schedule are m/s optional (only required for runs of thermal comfort models: Fanger, Pierce and KSU)

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Model 1 Type
fields.memo: optional (only needed for people thermal comfort results reporting)

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Model 2 Type
fields.memo: optional (second type of thermal comfort model and results reporting)

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Model 3 Type
fields.memo: optional (third thermal comfort model and report type)

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Model 4 Type
fields.memo: optional (fourth thermal comfort model and report type)

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Model 5 Type
fields.memo: optional (fifth thermal comfort model and report type)

refrigeration:subcooler.name: Refrigeration:Subcooler
refrigeration:subcooler.memo: Two types of subcoolers are modeled by the detailed refrigeration system.  The liquid suction heat exchanger uses cool suction gas to subcool the hot condensate after it leaves the condenser and before it reaches the thermal expansion valve. A mechanical subcooler is used to transfer cooling capacity from one refrigeration system to another.

fields.name: Subcooler Type
fields.memo: plan to add ambient subcoolers at future time

fields.name: Liquid Suction Design Subcooling Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Applicable only and required for liquid suction heat exchangers design liquid suction subcooling

fields.name: Design Liquid Inlet Temperature
fields.memo: design inlet temperature on liquid side Applicable only and required for liquid suction heat exchangers (LSHX)

fields.name: Design Vapor Inlet Temperature
fields.memo: design inlet temperature on vapor side Applicable only and required for liquid suction heat exchangers (LSHX) Design vapor inlet temperature must be less than or equal to the Liquid inlet design temp

fields.name: Capacity-Providing System
fields.memo: Name of the Detailed Refrigeration System providing cooling capacity Applicable only and required for mechanical subcoolers

fields.name: Outlet Control Temperature
fields.memo: Control Temperature Out for subcooled liquid Applicable only and required for mechanical subcoolers

foundation:kiva:settings.name: Foundation:Kiva:Settings
foundation:kiva:settings.memo: Settings applied across all Kiva foundation calculations. Object is not required. If not defined, defaults will be applied.

airterminal:dualduct:vav:outdoorair.name: AirTerminal:DualDuct:VAV:OutdoorAir
airterminal:dualduct:vav:outdoorair.memo: Central air system terminal unit, dual duct, variable volume with special controls. One VAV duct is controlled to supply ventilation air and the other VAV duct is controlled to meet the zone cooling load.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The outlet node of the terminal unit. This is also the zone inlet node.

fields.name: Maximum Terminal Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: If autosized this is the sum of flow needed for cooling and maximum required outdoor air

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will increase flow as needed to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based mode selected in the next field. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate.

fields.name: Per Person Ventilation Rate Mode
fields.memo: CurrentOccupancy models demand controlled ventilation using the current number of people DesignOccupancy uses the total Number of People in the zone and is constant

groundheattransfer:slab:boundconds.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:BoundConds
groundheattransfer:slab:boundconds.memo: Supplies some of the boundary conditions used in the ground heat transfer calculations.

fields.name: EVTR: Is surface evapotranspiration modeled
fields.memo: This field specifies whether or not to use the evapotransporation model. The inclusion of evapotransporation in the calculation has the greatest effect in warm dry climates, primarily on the ground surface temperature. This field can be used to turn the evapotransporation off and on to check sensitivity to it.

fields.name: FIXBC: is the lower boundary at a fixed temperature
fields.memo: This field permits using a fixed temperature at the lower surface of the model instead of a zero heat flux condition. This change normally has a very small effect on the results. FALSE selects the zero flux lower boundary condition

fields.name: TDEEPin
fields.memo: User input lower boundary temperature if FIXBC is TRUE Blank for FIXBC FALSE or to use the calculated 1-D deep ground temperature.

fields.name: USRHflag: Is the ground surface h specified by the user?
fields.memo: This field flags the use of a user specified heat transfer coefficient on the ground surface. This condition is used primarily for testing. For normal runs (USPHflag is FALSE) and the program calculates the heat transfer coefficient using the weather conditions.

fields.name: USERH: User specified ground surface heat transfer coefficient
fields.memo: Used only if USRHflag is TRUE and the heat transfer coefficient value is specified in this field.

site:weatherstation.name: Site:WeatherStation
site:weatherstation.memo: This object should only be used for non-standard weather data.  Standard weather data such as TMY2, IWEC, and ASHRAE design day data are all measured at the default conditions and do not require this object.

fields.name: Wind Speed Profile Boundary Layer Thickness
Air Temperature Sensor Height Above Ground

airflownetwork:distribution:component:co.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:Coil
airflownetwork:distribution:component:co.memo: This object defines the name of a coil used in an air loop.

fields.name: Coil Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a cooling or heating coil in the primary Air loop.

fields.name: Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Select the type of coil corresponding to the name entered in the field above.

fields.name: Air Path Length
fields.memo: Enter the air path length (depth) for the coil.

fields.name: Air Path Hydraulic Diameter
fields.memo: Enter the hydraulic diameter of this coil. The hydraulic diameter is defined as 4 multiplied by the cross section area divided by perimeter.

humidifier:steam:electric.name: Humidifier:Steam:Electric
humidifier:steam:electric.memo: Electrically heated steam humidifier with fan.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Capacity is m3/s of water at 5.05 C

fields.name: Rated Power
fields.memo: if autosized the rated power is calculated from the rated capacity and enthalpy rise of water from 20.0C to 100.0C steam and assumes electric to thermal energy conversion efficiency of 100.0%

lifecyclecost:useadjustment.name: LifeCycleCost:UseAdjustment
lifecyclecost:useadjustment.memo: Used by advanced users to adjust the energy or water use costs for future years. This should not be used for compensating for inflation but should only be used to increase the costs of energy or water based on assumed changes to the actual usage, such as anticipated changes in the future function of the building. The adjustments begin at the start of the service period.

coil:cooling:dx:singlespeed:thermalstora.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:SingleSpeed:ThermalStorage
coil:cooling:dx:singlespeed:thermalstora.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and condensing unit (includes electric compressor and condenser fan), single-speed with packaged integrated thermal storage for cooling.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Operation Mode Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is used if the control method is set to ScheduledModes Schedule values control operating mode: 0=off, 1=cooling only, 2= cooling and charge, 3= cooling and discharge, 4= charge only, and 5= discharge only

fields.name: User Defined Fluid Type
fields.memo: This field is required when Storage Type is UserDefinedFluidType

fields.name: Fluid Storage Volume
fields.memo: required field if Storage Type is Water or UserDefinedFluidType

fields.name: Ice Storage Capacity
fields.memo: required field if Storage Type is Ice

fields.name: Storage Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If one of the previous two fields is set to autocalculate, this determines the storage capacity as a function of Cooling Only Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity

fields.name: Storage Tank Ambient Temperature Node Name
Storage Tank to Ambient U-value Times Area Heat Transfer Coefficient
Fluid Storage Tank Rating Temperature
fields.memo: required field if Storage Type is Water or UserDefinedFluidType

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total cooling capacity, Rated SHR and Rated COP

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available or if autocalculating sizes gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input required field if Cooling Only Mode is available

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with two independent variables can be used biquadratic curve = a + b*ewb + c*ewb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*ewb*db x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature (C) y = db = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow rate

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with two independent variables can be used curve = a + b*ewb + c*ewb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*ewb*db x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature (C) y = db = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 x = PLR = part load ratio (evaporator cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with two independent variables can be used curve = a + b*ewb + c*ewb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*ewb*edb x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the cooling coil (C) y = edb = evaporator entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the cooling coil (C)

fields.name: Cooling Only Mode Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling Only Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb thermal storage tank at Fluid Storage Tank Rating Temperature (water or fluid) or storage faction of 0.5 (ice)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If previous field is autocalculate, this determines the evaporator capacity as a multiplier on the Cooling Only Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Rated Storage Charging Capacity
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available net capacity including any internal devices rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb thermal storage tank at Fluid Storage Tank Rating Temperature (water or fluid) or storage faction of 0.5 (ice)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Storage Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If previous field is autocalculate, this determines the storage cooling capacity as a multiplier on the Cooling Only Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible evaporator capacity/gross total evaporator capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Cooling Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross evaporator cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor (for cooling) and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Charging Rated COP
fields.memo: net cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor (for charging) and outdoor fan, includes any internal devices required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Allowed curve or table objects are Curve:Triquadratic and Table:MultiVariableLookup curve or table = func(x = ewb, y = db, z = stes) x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature (C) y = db = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C) z = stes = state of thermal energy storage (C or fraction)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Evaporator Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Allowed curve or table objects are Curve:Triquadratic and Table:MultiVariableLookup curve or table = func(x = ewb, y = db, z = stes) x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature (C) y = db = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C) z = stes = state of thermal energy storage (C or fraction)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Evaporator Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Evaporator Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 x = PLR = part load ratio (evaporator cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Storage Charge Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Allowed curve or table objects are Curve:Triquadratic and Table:MultiVariableLookup curve or table = func(x = ewb, y = db, z = stes) x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature (C) y = db = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C) z = stes = state of thermal energy storage (C or fraction)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Storage Charge Capacity Function of Total Evaporator PLR Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 x = PLR = part load ratio (evaporator cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Storage Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Allowed curve or table objects are Curve:Triquadratic and Table:MultiVariableLookup curve or table = func(x = ewb, y = db, z = stes) x = ewb = evaporator entering wet-bulb temperature (C) y = db = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C) z = stes = state of thermal energy storage (C or fraction)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Storage Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Storage Energy Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 x = PLR = part load ratio (evaporator cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Curves or tables with either two or three independent variables can be used. Curve:Biquadratic, Table:TwoIndependentVariables, Curve:Bicubic and Curve:QuadraticLinear allowed curve = a + b*ewb + c*ewb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*ewb*edb x = ewb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the cooling coil (C) y = edb = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the cooling coil (C) Also allows Curve:Triquadratic and Table:MultiVariableLookup curve or table = func(x = ewb, y = edb, z = stes) z = stes = state of thermal energy storage (C or fraction)

fields.name: Cooling And Charge Mode Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Charge Mode is available Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 x = ff = Fraction of the full load evaporator air flow

fields.name: Cooling And Discharge Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Discharge Mode is available gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb thermal storage tank at Fluid Storage Tank Rating Temperature (water or fluid) or storage faction of 0.5 (ice)

fields.name: Cooling And Discharge Mode Evaporator Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If previous field is autocalculate, this determines the charging capacity as a multiplier on the Cooling Only Mode Rated Total Evaporator Cooling Capacity

fields.name: Cooling And Discharge Mode Rated Storage Discharging Capacity

fields.name: Cooling And Discharge Mode Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: required field if Cooling And Discharge Mode is available Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible evaporator capacity/gross total evaporator capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling And Discharge Mode Cooling Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross evaporator cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor (for cooling) and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input required field if Cooling And Discharge Mode is available

fields.name: Ancillary Electric Power
fields.memo: controls and miscellaneous standby ancillary electric power draw, when available

fields.name: Cold Weather Operation Minimum Outdoor Air Temperature
Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Condenser Design Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate condenser leaving conditions and water use if evaporatively cooled.

fields.name: Condenser Air Flow Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If previous field is autocalculate, this determines the condenser air flow size as a multiplier on the Rated Evaporator Air Flow Rate.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Effectiveness
fields.memo: required field if condenser type is evaporatively cooled

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off. If this field is blank, the basin heater is always available.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Storage Tank Plant Connection Inlet Node Name
Storage Tank Plant Connection Outlet Node Name
Storage Tank Plant Connection Design Flow Rate
Storage Tank Plant Connection Heat Transfer Effectiveness
Storage Tank Minimum Operating Limit Fluid Temperature
fields.memo: For fluid storage tanks only, minimum limit for storage tank If omitted,then the minimum temperature limit is that used for fluid property data.

fields.name: Storage Tank Maximum Operating Limit Fluid Temperature
fields.memo: For fluid storage tanks only, maximum limit for storage tank If omitted,then the maximum temperature limit is that used for fluid property data.

groundheattransfer:slab:bldgprops.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:BldgProps
groundheattransfer:slab:bldgprops.memo: Object provides information about the building and its operating conditions Monthly Average Temperature SetPoint fields specify the average indoor building set point temperatures for each month of the year. These fields are useful for simulating a building that is not temperature controlled for some of the year. In such a case, the average indoor set point temperatures can be obtained by first running the model in EnergyPlus with an insulated floor boundary condition, and then using the resulting monthly average zone temperatures in these fields.

fields.name: IYRS: Number of years to iterate
fields.memo: This field specifies the number of years to iterate. Either the ground heat transfer calculations come to an an annual steady periodic condition by converging to a tolerance (see ConvTol field) or it runs for this number of years. A ten year maximum is usually sufficient.

fields.name: Shape: Slab shape
fields.memo: Use only the value 0 here. Only a rectangular shape is implemented.

fields.name: HBLDG: Building height
fields.memo: This field supplies the building height. This is used to calculate the building shadowing on the ground. typical value= 0-20

fields.name: TIN1: January Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN2: February Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN3: March Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN4: April Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN5: May Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN6: June Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN7: July Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN8: August Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN9: September Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN10: October Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN11: November Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TIN12: December Indoor Average Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: see memo on object for more information

fields.name: TINAmp: Daily Indoor sine wave variation amplitude
fields.memo: This field permits imposing a daily sinusoidal variation in the indoor setpoint temperature to simulate the effect of a setback profile. The value specified is the amplitude of the sine wave.

fields.name: ConvTol: Convergence Tolerance
fields.memo: This field specifies the convergence tolerance used to control the iteration. When the temperature change of all nodes is less than the convergence value, iteration ceases.

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitExport:To:Variable
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.memo: Declares Erl variable as having global scope No spaces allowed in names used for Erl variables

fields.name: Initial Value

zoneproperty:userviewfactors:bysurfacena.name: ZoneProperty:UserViewFactors:bySurfaceName
zoneproperty:userviewfactors:bysurfacena.memo: View factors for Surface to Surface in a zone. (Number of Surfaces)**2 must be entered.

zonehvac:forcedair:userdefined.name: ZoneHVAC:ForcedAir:UserDefined
zonehvac:forcedair:userdefined.memo: Defines a generic zone air unit for custom modeling using Energy Management System or External Interface

Model Setup and Sizing Program Calling Manager Name
Primary Air Inlet Node Name

fields.name: Primary Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air outlet node for the unit must be a zone air inlet node.

fields.name: Secondary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Inlet air used for heat rejection or air source

fields.name: Secondary Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Outlet air used for heat rejection or air source

fields.name: Supply Inlet Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: Water use storage tank for alternate source of water consumed by device

fields.name: Collection Outlet Water Storage Tank Name

fields.name: Ambient Zone Name

zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:variablef.name: ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:VariableFlow
zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:variablef.memo: Low temperature hydronic radiant heating and/or cooling system embedded in a building surface (wall, ceiling, or floor). Controlled by varying the hot or chilled water flow to the unit.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of zone system is serving

fields.name: Surface Name or Radiant Surface Group Name
fields.memo: Identifies surfaces that radiant system is embedded in. For a system with multiple surfaces, enter the name of a ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:SurfaceGroup object.

fields.name: Hydronic Tubing Length
fields.memo: (total length of pipe embedded in surface)

fields.name: Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: (Temperature on which unit is controlled)

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the cooling design capacity for scalable sizing. CoolingDesignCapacity => selected when the design cooling capacity value is specified or auto-sized. CapacityPerFloorArea => selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from user specified cooling capacity per floor area and total floor area of cooled zone served by the hydrolic unit. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity => is selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design cooling capacity of the system.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design cooling capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method CoolingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the cooling design capacity per total floor area of cooled zones served by the unit. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto-sized cooling design capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity.

fluidproperties:glycolconcentration.memo: glycol and what concentration it is

fields.name: Glycol Type
fields.memo: or UserDefined Fluid (must show up as a glycol in FluidProperties:Name object)

availabilitymanager:scheduledoff.name: AvailabilityManager:ScheduledOff
availabilitymanager:scheduledoff.memo: Determines the availability of a loop or system: only controls the turn off action. Schedule overrides fan/pump schedule.

fluidproperties:concentration.name: FluidProperties:Concentration
fluidproperties:concentration.memo: fluid properties for water/other fluid mixtures

fields.name: Fluid Name
fields.memo: should not be any of the defaults (Water, EthyleneGlycol, or PropyleneGlycol)

fields.name: Fluid Property Type
fields.memo: Density Units are kg/m3 SpecificHeat Units are J/kg-K Conductivity Units are W/m-K Viscosity Units are N-s/m2

fields.name: Temperature Values Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a FluidProperties:Temperatures object.

fields.name: Concentration
