coil:cooling:water.name: Coil:Cooling:Water
coil:cooling:water.memo: Chilled water cooling coil, NTU-effectiveness model, with inputs for design entering and leaving conditions.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Design Water Temperature Difference
fields.memo: This input field is optional. If specified, it is used for sizing the Design Water Flow Rate. If blank or omitted, the Loop Design Temperature Difference value specified in Sizing:Plant object is used for sizing the Design Water Flow Rate.

componentcost:reference.name: ComponentCost:Reference
componentcost:reference.memo: Used to allow comparing the current cost estimate to the results of a previous estimate for a reference building. This object parallels the ComponentCost:Adjustments object but adds a field for entering the cost line item model result for the reference building. The factors entered in this object are applied to the reference building while the factors listed in the ComponentCost:Adjustments object are applied to the current building model cost estimate.

fields.name: Reference Building Line Item Costs
fields.memo: should be comparable to the components in current line item cost model

fields.name: Reference Building Miscellaneous Cost per Conditioned Area
fields.memo: based on conditioned floor area for cost not accounted for in reference line item costs

fields.name: Reference Building Design and Engineering Fees
Reference Building Permits, Bonding and Insurance
Reference Building Regional Adjustment Factor
fields.memo: for use with average data in line item and Misc cost models

thermostatsetpoint:singlecooling.name: ThermostatSetpoint:SingleCooling
thermostatsetpoint:singlecooling.memo: Used for a cooling only thermostat. The setpoint can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation but only cooling is allowed.

zonecontrol:thermostat:operativetemperat.name: ZoneControl:Thermostat:OperativeTemperature
zonecontrol:thermostat:operativetemperat.memo: This object can be used with the ZoneList option on a thermostat or with one of the zones on that list (but you won't be able to use the object list to pick only one of those zones.  Thermostat names are <Zone Name> <global Thermostat name> internally.

fields.name: Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneControl:Thermostat object. This object modifies a ZoneControl:Thermostat object to add a radiative fraction.

fields.name: Radiative Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values of 0.0 indicate no operative temperature control

fields.name: Adaptive Comfort Model Type

districtcooling.name: DistrictCooling

evaporativecooler:direct:celdekpad.memo: Direct evaporative cooler with rigid media evaporative pad and recirculating water pump. This model has no controls other than its availability schedule.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: This field is not currently used and can be left blank

zonecontrol:contaminantcontroller.name: ZoneControl:ContaminantController
zonecontrol:contaminantcontroller.memo: Used to control a zone to a specified indoor level of CO2 or generic contaminants, or to specify minimum CO2 concentration schedule name for a zone.

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Control Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for CO2 controller. Schedule value > 0 means the CO2 controller is enabled. If this field is blank, then CO2 controller is always enabled.

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Setpoint Schedule Name

fields.name: Minimum Carbon Dioxide Concentration Schedule Name

fields.name: Maximum Carbon Dioxide Concentration Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be carbon dioxide concentration in parts per million (ppm) This field is used when the field System Outdoor Air Method = ProportionalControlBasedonOccupancySchedule or ProportionalControlBasedOnDesignOccupancy or ProportionalControlBasedOnDesignOARate.

fields.name: Generic Contaminant Control Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for generic contaminant controller. Schedule value > 0 means the generic contaminant controller is enabled. If this field is blank, then generic contaminant controller is always enabled.

fields.name: Generic Contaminant Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be generic contaminant concentration in parts per million (ppm) This field is used when the field System Outdoor Air Method = IndoorAirQualityProcedureGenericContaminant in Controller:MechanicalVentilation

shading:fin.name: Shading:Fin
shading:fin.memo: Fins are usually shading surfaces that are perpendicular to a window or door.

fields.name: Left Distance Above Top of Window
Left Distance Below Bottom of Window
fields.memo: N2 + N3 + height of Window/Door is height of Fin

fields.name: Right Distance Above Top of Window
Right Distance Below Bottom of Window
fields.memo: N7 + N8 + height of Window/Door is height of Fin

plantequipmentoperation:componentsetpoin.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:ComponentSetpoint
plantequipmentoperation:componentsetpoin.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for component setpoint operation. Specifies one or pieces of equipment which are controlled to meet the temperature setpoint at the component outlet node.

groundheattransfer:basement:insulation.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:Insulation
groundheattransfer:basement:insulation.memo: Describes the insulation used on an exterior basement wall for the Basement preprocessor ground heat transfer simulation.

fields.name: REXT: R Value of any exterior insulation
INSFULL: Flag: Is the wall fully insulated?
fields.memo: True for full insulation False for insulation half way down side wall from grade line

currencytype.name: CurrencyType
currencytype.memo: If CurrencyType is not specified, it will default to USD and produce $ in the reports.

fields.name: Monetary Unit
fields.memo: The commonly used three letter currency code for the units of money for the country or region. Based on ISO 4217 currency codes.  Common currency codes are USD for $ and EUR for Euros.

construction:complexfenestrationstate.name: Construction:ComplexFenestrationState
construction:complexfenestrationstate.memo: Describes one state for a complex glazing system These input objects are typically generated by using WINDOW software and export to IDF syntax

fields.name: Solar Optical Complex Front Transmittance Matrix Name
Solar Optical Complex Back Reflectance Matrix Name
Visible Optical Complex Front Transmittance Matrix Name
Visible Optical Complex Back Transmittance Matrix Name
Outside Layer Directional Front Absoptance Matrix Name
Outside Layer Directional Back Absoptance Matrix Name
CFS Gap 1 Directional Front Absoptance Matrix Name
fields.memo: Reserved for future use. Leave it blank for this version

fields.name: CFS Gap 1 Directional Back Absoptance Matrix Name
fields.memo: Reserved for future use. Leave it blank for this version

fields.name: Layer 2 Directional Front Absoptance Matrix Name
Layer 2 Directional Back Absoptance Matrix Name
Gap 2 Directional Front Absoptance Matrix Name

fields.memo: Reserved for future use. Leave it blank for this version

Layer 3 Directional Back Absoptance Matrix Name
Gap 3 Directional Front Absoptance Matrix Name

fields.memo: Reserved for future use. Leave it blank for this version

Layer 4 Directional Back Absoptance Matrix Name
Gap 4 Directional Front Absoptance Matrix Name

Layer 5 Directional Back Absoptance Matrix Name

thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.name: ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:DualSetpoint
thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.memo: Used for heating and cooling thermal comfort control with dual setpoints. The PMV setpoints can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation for both heating and cooling.

fields.name: Fanger Thermal Comfort Heating Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be Predicted Mean Vote (PMV)

fields.name: Fanger Thermal Comfort Cooling Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be Predicted Mean Vote (PMV)

availabilitymanager:hightemperatureturno.name: AvailabilityManager:HighTemperatureTurnOff
availabilitymanager:hightemperatureturno.memo: Overrides fan/pump schedules depending on temperature at sensor node.

coil:heating:electric:multistage.name: Coil:Heating:Electric:MultiStage
coil:heating:electric:multistage.memo: Electric heating coil, multi-stage. If the coil is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list, then it is controlled on leaving air temperature and the Temperature Setpoint Node Name must be specified. If the coil is contained within another component such as an air terminal unit, zone HVAC equipment, or unitary system, then the coil is controlled by the parent component and the setpoint node name is not entered.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: Required if coil is temperature controlled. controlled

fields.name: Number of Stages
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for coil capacity and Efficiency.

humidifier:steam:gas.name: Humidifier:Steam:Gas
humidifier:steam:gas.memo: Natural gas fired steam humidifier with optional blower fan.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Capacity is m3/s of water at 5.05 C The nominal full capacity water addition rate in m3/s of water at 5.05 C

fields.name: Rated Gas Use Rate
fields.memo: if auto-sized, the rated gas use rate is calculated from the rated capacity and enthalpy rise of water from 20.0C to 100.0C steam and user input thermal efficiency value specified in the next input field. If this input field is hard-sized and Inlet Water Temperature Option input field is selected as FixedInletWaterTemperature, then the thermal efficiency input field will not be used or else if the Inlet Water Temperature Option input field is selected as VariableInletWaterTemperature, then the thermal efficiency input value is overridden by a value calculated from the capacity, rated gas use rate and design condition.

fields.name: Thermal Efficiency
fields.memo: Based on the higher heating value of fuel. If "Rated Gas Use Rate" in the field above is not auto-sized and the Inlet Water Temperature Option input field is specified as FixedInletWaterTemperature, then the thermal efficiency specified will not be used in the calculation, or else if the Inlet Water Temperature Option input field is selected as VariableInletWaterTemperature, then the thermal efficiency value is overridden by a value calculated from the capacity, rated gas use rate and design condition.

fields.name: Thermal Efficiency Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: Linear, Quadratic and Cubic efficiency curves are solely a function of PLR. Linear = C1 + C2*PLR Quadratic = C1 + C2*PLR + C3*PLR^2 Cubic = C1 + C2*PLR + C3*PLR^2 + C4*PLR^3 This is thermal efficiency modifier curve name of gas fired steam humidifier. This curve is normalized, i.e., curve output value at rated condition is 1.0.

fields.name: Rated Fan Power
fields.memo: The nominal full capacity electric power input to the blower fan in Watts. If no blower fan is required to inject the dry steam to the supply air stream, then this input field is set to zero.

fields.name: Auxiliary Electric Power
fields.memo: The auxiliary electric power input in watts. This amount of power will be consumed whenever the unit is available (as defined by the availability schedule). This electric power is used for control purpose only.

fields.name: Inlet Water Temperature Option
fields.memo: The inlet water temperature can be fixed at 20C as it is done for electric steam humidifier or it can be allowed to vary with temperature of the water source. Currently allowed water sources are main water or water storage tank in water use objects. if FixedInletWaterTemperature is specified, then a fixed 20C water temperature will be used, or else if VariableInletWaterTemperature is specified, then inlet water will vary depending the source water temperature. If this input field is left blank, then fixed inlet water temperature of 20C will be assumed.

refrigeration:airchiller.name: Refrigeration:AirChiller
refrigeration:airchiller.memo: Works in conjunction with a refrigeration chiller set, compressor rack, a refrigeration system, or a refrigeration secondary system to simulate the performance of an air chiller, similar to one found in a refrigerated warehouse. Energy use for fans and heaters is modeled based on inputs for nominal power, schedules, and control type. The air chiller model accounts for the sensible and latent heat exchange with the surrounding environment.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Capacity Rating Type
fields.memo: In each case, select the rating option that corresponds to the expected service conditions. For example, U.S. manufacturers quote a separate Unit Load Factor for wet or frosted coils. If the evaporating temperature is less than 0C, input the frosted coil value. Within the European convention, select SC1, 2, 3, 4, or 5 depending upon the expected evaporating temperature.

fields.name: Rated Unit Load Factor
fields.memo: The sensible cooling capacity in watts (W/C) at rated conditions. The value entered for this field must be greater than zero, with no default value. This value is only used if the Capacity Rating Type is UnitLoadFactorSensibleOnly. The value given must be based upon the difference between the chiller inlet and outlet air temperatures, not on the difference between the zone mean temperature and the outlet air temperature

fields.name: Rated Capacity
fields.memo: This value is only used if the Capacity Rating Type is NOT UnitLoadFactorSensibleOnly. For CapacityTotalSpecificConditions, this capacity includes both sensible and latent at the conditions given in the next two fields. Note that the European Standard ratings are sensible only and the European Nominal ratings include latent capacity as well. The value given here must correspond to the capacity rating type given previously

fields.name: Rated Relative Humidity
fields.memo: This field is ONLY used if the Capacity Rating Type is CapacityTotalSpecificConditions and represents the relative humidity at rated conditions. The default is 85.

fields.name: Rated Cooling Source Temperature
fields.memo: If DXEvaporator, use evaporating temperature (saturated suction temperature) If BrineCoil, use Brine entering temperature used to set minimum suction pressure for DX systems and minimum brine temp for secondary systems

fields.name: Rated Temperature Difference DT1
fields.memo: The rated difference between the air entering the refrigeration chiller and the cooling source temperature in degC.

fields.name: Maximum Temperature Difference Between Inlet Air and Evaporating Temperature
fields.memo: The maximum difference between the air entering the refrigeration chiller and the cooling source temperature in degC used to limit capacity during pull-down. defaults to 1.3 times the Rated Temperature Difference DT1

fields.name: Coil Material Correction Factor
fields.memo: This is the manufacturer's correction factor for coil material corresponding to rating

fields.name: Refrigerant Correction Factor
fields.memo: This is the manufacturer's correction factor for refrigerant corresponding to rating

fields.name: Capacity Correction Curve Type
fields.memo: In each case, select the correction curve type that corresponds to the rating type. default LinearSHR60 unless Capacity Rating Type = CapacityTotalSpecificConditions

fields.name: Capacity Correction Curve Name
fields.memo: Can also be the name of a "Table:OneIndependentVariable" or a "Table:MultiVariableLookup" Should be blank for LinearSHR60 correction curve type

fields.name: SHR60 Correction Factor
fields.memo: only used when the capacity correction curve type is LinearSHR60

fields.name: Rated Total Heating Power
fields.memo: Include total for all heater power Do not include defrost heater power

fields.name: Heating Power Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values will be used to multiply the total heating power Values in the schedule should be between 0.0 and 1.0 Defaults to always on if schedule name left blank.

fields.name: Minimum Fan Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Minimum air flow fraction through fan

fields.name: Defrost Type
fields.memo: HotFluid includes either hot gas defrost for a DX system or Hot Brine defrost if this walk in is cooled by brine from a secondary chiller

fields.name: Defrost Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule values should be 0 (off) or 1 (on)

fields.name: Defrost Drip-Down Schedule Name
fields.memo: The schedule values should be 0 (off) or 1 (on) The start time for each defrost period in this drip-down schedule should coincide with the start time for each defrost period in the defrost schedule (previous input field).The length of each defrost drip-down period must be greater than or equal to the corresponding defrost period specified in the defrost schedule. This extra time allows the melted frost to drip from the coil before refrigeration is restarted.

fields.name: Defrost Power
fields.memo: needed for all defrost types except none and offcycle

fields.name: Temperature Termination Defrost Fraction to Ice
fields.memo: This is the portion of the defrost energy that is available to melt frost Needed only for defrost control type TemperatureTermination defaults to 0.7 for electric defrost and to 0.3 for hot fluid defrost

fields.name: Average Refrigerant Charge Inventory
fields.memo: This value is only used if the Cooling Source Type is DXEvaporator

groundheatexchanger:surface.name: GroundHeatExchanger:Surface
groundheatexchanger:surface.memo: A hydronic surface/panel consisting of a multi-layer construction with embedded rows of tubes. Typically used in hybrid geothermal systems and included in the condenser loop. This component may also be used as a simple solar collector. The bottom surface may be defined as ground-coupled or exposed to wind (eg. bridge deck).

material:roofvegetation.name: Material:RoofVegetation
material:roofvegetation.memo: EcoRoof model, plant layer plus soil layer Implemented by Portland State University (Sailor et al., January, 2007) only one material must be referenced per simulation though the same EcoRoof material could be used in multiple constructions. New moisture redistribution scheme (2010) requires higher number of timesteps per hour (minimum 12 recommended).

fields.name: Height of Plants
fields.memo: The ecoroof module is designed for short plants and shrubs.

fields.name: Leaf Area Index
fields.memo: Entire surface is assumed covered, so decrease LAI accordingly.

fields.name: Leaf Reflectivity
fields.memo: Leaf reflectivity (albedo) is typically 0.18-0.25

fields.name: Minimum Stomatal Resistance
fields.memo: This depends upon plant type

fields.name: Thickness
fields.memo: thickness of the soil layer of the EcoRoof Soil depths of 0.15m (6in) and 0.30m (12in) are common.

fields.name: Conductivity of Dry Soil
fields.memo: Thermal conductivity of dry soil. Typical ecoroof soils range from 0.3 to 0.5

fields.name: Density of Dry Soil
fields.memo: Density of dry soil (the code modifies this as the soil becomes moist) Typical ecoroof soils range from 400 to 1000 (dry to wet)

fields.name: Specific Heat of Dry Soil
fields.memo: Specific heat of dry soil

fields.name: Thermal Absorptance
fields.memo: Soil emissivity is typically in range of 0.90 to 0.98

fields.name: Solar Absorptance
fields.memo: Solar absorptance of dry soil (1-albedo) is typically 0.60 to 0.85 corresponding to a dry albedo of 0.15 to 0.40

fields.name: Saturation Volumetric Moisture Content of the Soil Layer
fields.memo: Maximum moisture content is typically less than 0.5

fields.name: Residual Volumetric Moisture Content of the Soil Layer
Initial Volumetric Moisture Content of the Soil Layer
Moisture Diffusion Calculation Method
fields.memo: Advanced calculation requires increased number of timesteps (recommended >20).

solarcollector:flatplate:water.name: SolarCollector:FlatPlate:Water
solarcollector:flatplate:water.memo: Flat plate water solar collector (single glazed, unglazed, or evacuated tube). Thermal and optical properties are taken from the referenced SolarCollectorPerformance:FlatPlate object. Collector tilt, azimuth, and gross area are taken from the referenced building surface or shading surface. The collector surface participates normally in all shading calculations.

runperiodcontrol:specialdays.name: RunPeriodControl:SpecialDays
runperiodcontrol:specialdays.memo: This object sets up holidays/special days to be used during weather file run periods.  (These are not used with SizingPeriod:* objects.) Depending on the value in the run period, days on the weather file may also be used.  However, the weather file specification will take precedence over any specification shown here.  (No error message on duplicate days or overlapping days).

fields.name: Start Date
fields.memo: Dates can be several formats: <number>/<number>  (month/day) <number> <Month> <Month> <number> <Nth> <Weekday> in <Month) Last <WeekDay> in <Month> <Month> can be January, February, March, April, May, June, July, August, September, October, November, December Months can be the first 3 letters of the month <Weekday> can be Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday <Nth> can be 1 or 1st, 2 or 2nd, etc. up to 5(?)

fields.name: Special Day Type
fields.memo: Special Day Type selects the schedules appropriate for each day so labeled

groundheattransfer:basement:equivautogri.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:EquivAutoGrid
groundheattransfer:basement:equivautogri.memo: EquivAutoGrid necessary when EquivSizing=TRUE, TRUE is is the normal case.

fields.name: CLEARANCE: Distance from outside of wall to edge of 3-D ground domain
SlabDepth: Thickness of the floor slab
BaseDepth: Depth of the basement wall below grade

runperiod:customrange.name: RunPeriod:CustomRange
runperiod:customrange.memo: run simulation for a custom created weather file

fields.name: Begin Year
fields.memo: must be start year of this date on weather file

fields.name: End Year
fields.memo: must be end year of this date on weather file

fields.name: Day of Week for Start Day
fields.memo: =<blank - use WeatherFile>|Sunday|Monday|Tuesday|Wednesday|Thursday|Friday|Saturday];

fields.name: Use Weather File Holidays and Special Days
fields.memo: If yes or blank, use holidays as specified on Weatherfile. If no, do not use the holidays specified on the Weatherfile. Note: You can still specify holidays/special days using the RunPeriodControl:SpecialDays object(s).

fields.name: Use Weather File Daylight Saving Period
fields.memo: If yes or blank, use daylight saving period as specified on Weatherfile. If no, do not use the daylight saving period as specified on the Weatherfile.

fields.name: Apply Weekend Holiday Rule
fields.memo: if yes and single day holiday falls on weekend, "holiday" occurs on following Monday

groundheatexchanger:vertical:properties.name: GroundHeatExchanger:Vertical:Properties
groundheatexchanger:vertical:properties.memo: Properties for vertical ground heat exchanger systems

setpointmanager:condenserenteringreset.name: SetpointManager:CondenserEnteringReset
setpointmanager:condenserenteringreset.memo: This setpoint manager uses one curve to determine the optimum condenser entering water temperature for a given timestep and two other curves to place boundary conditions on the setpoint value.

fields.name: Default Condenser Entering Water Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This scheduled setpoint value is only used in a given timestep if the "Optimized" Condenser Entering Temperature does not fall within the prescribed boundary conditions.

fields.name: Minimum Design Wetbulb Temperature Curve Name
Minimum Outside Air Wetbulb Temperature Curve Name
Optimized Cond Entering Water Temperature Curve Name
Cooling Tower Design Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which control variable will be set

schedule:day:interval.name: Schedule:Day:Interval
schedule:day:interval.memo: A Schedule:Day:Interval contains a full day of values with specified end times for each value Currently, is set up to allow for 10 minute intervals for an entire day.

fields.name: Interpolate to Timestep
fields.memo: when the interval does not match the user specified timestep a Average choice will average between the intervals request (to timestep resolution. A No choice will use the interval value at the simulation timestep without regard to if it matches the boundary or not. A Linear choice will interpolate linearly between successive values.

coil:heating:dx:singlespeed.name: Coil:Heating:DX:SingleSpeed
coil:heating:dx:singlespeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) heating coil (air-to-air heat pump) and compressor unit (includes electric compressor and outdoor fan), single-speed, with defrost controls.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating COP
fields.memo: Rated heating capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total capacity should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated heating capacity

fields.name: Rated Supply Fan Power Per Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply fan power per air volume flow rate at the rated test conditions. The test conditions vary external static pressure based on heating capacity. This value is only used to calculate Heating Seasonal Performance Factor(HSPF). This value is not used for modeling the supply (condenser) fan during simulations.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 cubic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 + d*oat**3 biquadratic curve = a + b*iat + c*iat**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*iat*oat oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) iat = indoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) Biquadratic curve is recommended if sufficient manufacturer data is available for the heating capacity to be sensitive to both iat and oat.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 cubic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 + d*oat**3 biquadratic curve = a + b*iat + c*iat**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*iat*oat oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) iat = indoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) biquadratic curve is recommended if sufficient manufacturer data is available for the energy input ratio to be sensitive to both iat and oat.

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (sensible heating load/steady state heating capacity)

fields.name: Defrost Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: biquadratic curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*wb*oat wb = wet-bulb temperature (C) of air entering the indoor coil oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) only required if ReverseCycle defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature to Turn On Compressor
fields.memo: The outdoor temperature when the compressor is automatically turned back on following an automatic shut off because of low outdoor dry-bulb temperature. This field is only used for the calculation of HSPF. If this field is not provided, then outdoor bin temperature used in the HSPF calculation is always considered to be greater than this temperature and 'Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation' field described above. This assumption is based on AHRI standard 210/240 (2008) and can introduce significant error in the final value of HSPF.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode only applicable if timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Region number for calculating HSPF
fields.memo: Standard Region number for which HSPF and other standard ratings are calculated

fields.name: Evaporator Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Zone Name for Evaporator Placement
fields.memo: This input field is name of a conditioned or unconditioned zone where the secondary coil (evaporator) of a heat pump is to be placed.  This is an optional input field specified only when user desires to extract heat from the zone.  The heat extracted is modelled as internal gain of the zone. If the primary DX system is a heat pump, then the zone name should be the same as the zone name specified for placing the secondary cooling DX coil.

fields.name: Secondary Coil Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This input value is the secondary coil (evaporator) air flow rate when the heat pump is working in heating mode or the secondary DX coil (condenser) air flow rate when the heat pump is working in cooling mode.

fields.name: Secondary Coil Fan Flow Scaling Factor
fields.memo: This input field is scaling factor for autosizing the secondary DX coil fan flow rate. The secondary air flow rate is determined by multiplying the primary DX coil rated air flow rate by the fan flow scaling factor. Default value is 1.25. If the secondary coil fan flow rate is not autosized, then the secondary coil fan flow scaling factor is set to 1.0.

fields.name: Nominal Sensible Heat Ratio of Secondary Coil
fields.memo: This input value is the nominal sensible heat ratio used to split the heat extracted by a secondary DX coil (evaporator) of a heat pump into sensible and latent components. This is an optional input field.  If this input field is left blank, then pure sensible internal heat gain is assumed, i.e., sensible heat ratio of 1.0.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*wb*db wb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the secondary DX coil (C) db = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the primary DX coil (C) This input field is name of sensible heat ratio modifier biquadratic curve.  The value of this curve modifies the nominal sensible heat ratio for current time step depending on the secondary zone air node wet-bulb temperature and the heating DX coil entering air dry-bulb temperature.  This is an optional input field.  If this input field is left blank, then the nominal sensible heat ratio specified in the field above will be used.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Modifier Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = secondary air flow fraction of the full load flow This input field is name of sensible heat ratio modifier curve.  The value of this curve modifies the nominal sensible heat ratio for current time step depending on the secondary coil air flow fraction. This is an optional input field.  If this input field is left blank, then the nominal sensible heat ratio specified will be used.

pump:constantspeed.name: Pump:ConstantSpeed
pump:constantspeed.memo: This pump model is described in the ASHRAE secondary HVAC toolkit.

fields.name: Design Pump Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet

fields.name: Design Power Consumption
fields.memo: When autosized the type of scaling factor is chosen in the input field Design Power Sizing Method

fields.name: Motor Efficiency
fields.memo: This is the motor efficiency only. When the Design Power Consumption is autosized using PowerPerFlowPerPressure, the Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used in addition to the motor efficiency.

fields.name: Fraction of Motor Inefficiencies to Fluid Stream
Pump Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the rated flow rate of the pump on a time basis. Default is that the pump is on and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations.

fields.name: Pump Curve Name
fields.memo: This references any single independent variable polynomial curve in order to do pressure vs. flow calculations for this pump.  The available types are then: Linear, Quadratic, Cubic, and Quartic The non-dimensional pump pressure relationship is of the following form: (psi = C4*phi^4 + C3*phi^3 + C2*phi^2 + C1*phi + C0) Where the non-dimensional variables are defined as: delP = rho * ((N/60)^2) * (D^2) * psi mdot = rho * (N/60) * (D^3) * phi

fields.name: Impeller Diameter
fields.memo: "D" in above expression in field A6

fields.name: Rotational Speed
fields.memo: "N" in above expression in field A6

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: optional, if used pump losses transfered to zone as internal gains

fields.name: Skin Loss Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: optional. If zone identified in previous field then this determines the split between convection and radiation for the skin losses

fields.name: Design Power Sizing Method
fields.memo: Used to indicate which sizing factor is used to calculate Design Power Consumption. PowerPerFlow indicates that Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * scaling factor PowerPerFlowPerPressure indicates that Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * Design Pump Head * scaling factor / Motor Efficiency

fields.name: Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate

fields.name: Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate for head and motor efficiency

evaporativecooler:indirect:celdekpad.name: EvaporativeCooler:Indirect:CelDekPad
evaporativecooler:indirect:celdekpad.memo: Indirect evaporative cooler with rigid media evaporative pad, recirculating water pump, and secondary air fan. This model has no controls other than its availability schedule.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: This field is not currently used and can be left blank

fields.name: Secondary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

utilitycost:charge:simple.name: UtilityCost:Charge:Simple
utilitycost:charge:simple.memo: UtilityCost:Charge:Simple is one of the most often used objects for tariff calculation. It is used to compute energy and demand charges that are very simple. It may also be used for taxes, surcharges and any other charges that occur on a utility bill. Multiple UtilityCost:Charge:Simple objects may be defined for a single tariff and they will be added together.

fields.name: Utility Cost Charge Simple Name
fields.memo: Charge Variable Name This is the name associated with the UtilityCost:Charge:Simple object and will appear in the report. In addition the results of the UtilityCost:Charge:Simple calculation are stored in a variable with the same name.  That way the results may be used for further calculation.  Spaces are not significant in Charge variable names. They are removed during the utility bill calculation process.

fields.name: Tariff Name
fields.memo: The name of the UtilityCost:Tariff that is associated with this UtilityCost:Charge:Simple.

fields.name: Source Variable
fields.memo: The name of the source used by the UtilityCost:Charge:Simple.  This is usually the name of the variable holding the energy or demand but may also be the name of any variable including the subtotal or basis if other charges are based on those. Typical values include totalEnergy totalDemand EnergyCharges DemandCharges ServiceCharges Basis Adjustments Surcharges Subtotal Taxes and Total. If it is a time-of-use rate then peakEnergy peakDemand shoulderEnergy shoulderDemand offPeakEnergy offPeakDemand midPeakEnergy and midPeakDemand. In addition see the Tariff Report to see other native variables that may be available. Also you can create additional user defined variables to model complex tariffs.

fields.name: Season
fields.memo: If this is set to annual the calculations are performed for the UtilityCost:Charge:Simple for the entire year (all months) otherwise it is calculated only for those months in the season defined.

fields.name: Category Variable Name
fields.memo: This field shows where the charge should be added. The reason to enter this field appropriately is so that the charge gets reported in a reasonable category.  The charge automatically gets added to the variable that is the category.

fields.name: Cost per Unit Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: This field contains either a single number or the name of a variable.  The number is multiplied with all of the energy or demand or other source that is specified in the source field.  If a variable is used then the monthly values of the variable are multiplied against the variable specified in the source field.  This field makes it easy to include a simple charge without specifying block sizes. This is a good way to include a tax or cost adjustment.

airflownetwork:distribution:component:du.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:Duct
airflownetwork:distribution:component:du.memo: This object defines the relationship between pressure and air flow through the duct.

fields.name: Duct Length
fields.memo: Enter the length of the duct.

fields.name: Hydraulic Diameter
fields.memo: Enter the hydraulic diameter of the duct. Hydraulic diameter is defined as 4 multiplied by cross section area divided by perimeter

fields.name: Cross Section Area
fields.memo: Enter the cross section area of the duct.

fields.name: Surface Roughness
fields.memo: Enter the inside surface roughness of the duct.

fields.name: Coefficient for Local Dynamic Loss Due to Fitting
fields.memo: Enter the coefficient used to calculate dynamic losses of fittings (e.g. elbows).

fields.name: Heat Transmittance Coefficient (U-Factor) for Duct Wall Construction
fields.memo: conduction only Default value of 0.943 is equivalent to 1.06 m2-K/W (R6) duct insulation.

fields.name: Overall Moisture Transmittance Coefficient from Air to Air
fields.memo: Enter the overall moisture transmittance coefficient including moisture film coefficients at both surfaces.

fields.name: Outside Convection Coefficient
fields.memo: optional. convection coefficient calculated automatically, unless specified

fields.name: Inside Convection Coefficient
fields.memo: optional. convection coefficient calculated automatically, unless specified

electricloadcenter:inverter:simple.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Inverter:Simple
electricloadcenter:inverter:simple.memo: Electric power inverter to convert from direct current (DC) to alternating current (AC) in an electric load center that contains photovoltaic modules. This input object is for the simplest inverter model and uses a fixed efficiency.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: enter name of zone to receive inverter losses as heat if blank then inverter is assumed to be outdoors

compliance:building.name: Compliance:Building
compliance:building.memo: Building level inputs related to compliance to building standards, building codes, and beyond energy code programs.

fields.name: Building Rotation for Appendix G
fields.memo: Additional degrees of rotation to be used with the requirement in ASHRAE Standard 90.1 Appendix G that states that the baseline building should be rotated in four directions.

shading:building:detailed.name: Shading:Building:Detailed
shading:building:detailed.memo: used for shading elements such as trees, other buildings, parts of this building not being modeled these items are relative to the current building and would move with relative geometry

fields.name: Transmittance Schedule Name
fields.memo: Transmittance schedule for the shading device, defaults to zero (always opaque)

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 6 vertex coordinates -- extensible object Rules for vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- For this object all surface coordinates are relative to the building origin (0,0,0) and will rotate with the BUILDING north axis.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during cooling operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during heating operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate when no cooling or heating is needed Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. A value entered in this field will *not* be multiplied by the sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  It is best to autosize or leave blank when using zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule Name values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include effect of supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Efficiency
fields.memo: Applies only if Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Applies only if Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:DedicatedOutdoorAir object if this zone is served by a separate dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Leave field blank if no DOAS serves this zone.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

pipe:underground.name: Pipe:Underground
pipe:underground.memo: Buried Pipe model: For pipes buried at a depth less than one meter, this is an alternative object to: HeatExchanger:Surface

fields.name: Pipe Inside Diameter
fields.memo: pipe thickness is defined in the Construction object

hvactemplate:zone:vav.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:VAV
hvactemplate:zone:vav.memo: Zone terminal unit, variable volume, reheat optional. For heating, this unit activates reheat coil first, then increases airflow (if reverse action specified).

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template VAV System Name
fields.memo: Name of a HVACTemplate:System:VAV or HVACTemplate:System:PackagedVAV object serving this zone

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method
fields.memo: Constant = Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction (a fraction of Maximum Air Flow Rate) FixedFlowRate = Fixed Minimum Air Flow Rate (a fixed minimum air volume flow rate) Scheduled = Scheduled Minimum Air Flow Fraction (a fraction of Maximum Air Flow

fields.name: Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Constant If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional. If a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the following field are entered, the larger result is used.

fields.name: Fixed Minimum Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is FixedFlowRate. If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional. If a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the previous field are entered, the larger result is used.

fields.name: Minimum Air Flow Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled Schedule values are fractions, 0.0 to 1.0. If the field Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction is blank, then the average of the minimum and maximum schedule values is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Reheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Maximum Flow per Zone Floor Area During Reheat
fields.memo: Used only when Reheat Coil Object Type = Coil:Heating:Water and Damper Heating Action = Reverse When autocalculating, the maximum flow per zone is set to 0.002032 m3/s-m2 (0.4 cfm/sqft) This optional field limits the maximum flow allowed in reheat mode. If this field and the following field are left blank, the maximum flow will not be limited. At no time will the maximum flow rate calculated here exceed the value of Maximum Air Flow Rate.

fields.name: Maximum Flow Fraction During Reheat
fields.memo: Used only when Reheat Coil Object Type = Coil:Heating:Water and Damper Heating Action = Reverse When autocalculating, the maximum flow fraction is set to the ratio of 0.002032 m3/s-m2 (0.4 cfm/sqft) multiplied by the zone floor area and the Maximum Air Flow Rate. This optional field limits the maximum flow allowed in reheat mode. If this field and the previous field are left blank, the maximum flow will not be limited. At no time will the maximum flow rate calculated here exceed the value of Maximum Air Flow Rate.

fields.name: Maximum Reheat Air Temperature
fields.memo: Specifies the maximum allowable supply air temperature leaving the reheat coil. If left blank, there is no limit and no default. If unknown, 35C (95F) is recommended.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Control
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will increase flow as needed to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow. Note that this field is used only for specifying the design outdoor air flow rate used for control. The field Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Sizing (see below) is used to specify the design outdoor air flow rate.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:VAV Cooling Coil Design Setpoint

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Sizing
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification. Note that this field is used only for specifying the design outdoor air flow rate used for sizing. The field Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name for Control (see above) is used to actively control the VAV terminal air flow rate.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

curve:quadratic.name: Curve:Quadratic
curve:quadratic.memo: Quadratic curve with one independent variable. Input for a quadratic curve consists of the curve name, the three coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

coil:heating:dx:variablespeed.name: Coil:Heating:DX:VariableSpeed
coil:heating:dx:variablespeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) heating coil (air-to-air heat pump) and compressor unit (includes electric compressor and outdoor fan), variable-speed, with defrost controls. Requires two to ten sets of performance data and will interpolate between speeds.

fields.name: Nominal Speed Level
fields.memo: must be lower than or equal to the highest speed number

fields.name: Rated Heating Capacity At Selected Nominal Speed Level
Rated Air Flow Rate At Selected Nominal Speed Level
Energy Part Load Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (heating load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Defrost Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: biquadratic curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*wb*oat wb = wet-bulb temperature (C) of air entering the indoor coil oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) only required if ReverseCycle defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature to Turn On Compressor
fields.memo: The outdoor temperature when the compressor is automatically turned back on following an automatic shut off because of low outdoor dry-bulb temperature. This field is only used for the calculation of HSPF. If this field is not provided, then outdoor bin temperature used in the HSPF calculation is always considered to be greater than this temperature and 'Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation' field described above. This assumption is based on AHRI standard 210/240 (2008) and can introduce significant error in the final value of HSPF.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode only applicable if timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Speed 1 Reference Unit Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Speed 1 Reference Unit Gross Rated Heating COP
Speed 1 Reference Unit Rated Air Flow Rate
Speed 1 Heating Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*db + c*db**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*db*oat db = entering air dry-bulb temperature (C) oat = air entering temperature seen by the evaporator (C)

fields.name: Speed 1 Total  Heating Capacity Function of Air Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ffa + c*ffa**2 cubic curve = a + b*ffa + c*ffa**2 + d*ffa**3 ffa = Fraction of the full load Air Flow

fields.name: Speed 1 Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*db + c*db**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*db*oat db = entering air dry-bulb temperature (C) oat = air entering temperature seen by the evaporator (C)

duct.name: Duct
duct.memo: Passes inlet node state variables to outlet node state variables

surfacecontrol:movableinsulation.name: SurfaceControl:MovableInsulation
surfacecontrol:movableinsulation.memo: Exterior or Interior Insulation on opaque surfaces

airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:fo.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:ConstantVolume:FourPipeBeam
airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:fo.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, constant volume, with heating and/or cooling. Operates as two-pipe unit if heating or cooling water is omitted. Heating and/or cooling can be scheduled off for dedicated ventilation.

fields.name: Primary Air Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Primary air is supplied by central air handling unit and must be on for heating or cooling. Schedule value > 0 means the primary air supply is available. If this field is blank, the primary air supply is always available.

fields.name: Cooling Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Cooling operation can be controlled separately using this availability schedule. Schedule value > 0 means beam cooling is available. If this field is blank, the beam cooling is always available (as long as primary air is also available).

fields.name: Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Heating operation can be controlled separately using this availability schedule. Schedule value > 0 means beam heating is available. If this field is blank, the beam heating is always available (as long as primary air is also available).

fields.name: Primary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the air system node for primary supply air entering the air distribution unit.

fields.name: Primary Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the air system node for primary supply air leaving the air distribution unit and entering the zone.

fields.name: Chilled Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the plant system node for chilled water entering the beam. The two chilled water nodes can (only) be omitted to model a two-pipe heating only beam.

fields.name: Chilled Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the plant system node for chilled water leaving the beam.

fields.name: Hot Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the plant system node for hot water entering the beam. The two hot water nodes can (only) be omitted to model a two-pipe cooling-only beam.

fields.name: Hot Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the plant system node for hot water leaving the beam.

fields.name: Design Primary Air Volume Flow Rate
Design Chilled Water Volume Flow Rate
Design Hot Water Volume Flow Rate
Zone Total Beam Length
fields.memo: Sum of the length of all the beam units in the zone represented by this terminal unit.

fields.name: Rated Primary Air Flow Rate per Beam Length
fields.memo: Primary air supply flow rate normalized by beam length.

fields.name: Beam Rated Cooling Capacity per Beam Length
fields.memo: Sensible cooling capacity per meter of beam length at the rating point.

fields.name: Beam Rated Cooling Room Air Chilled Water Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Difference in temperature between the zone air and the entering chilled water at the rating point.

fields.name: Beam Rated Chilled Water Volume Flow Rate per Beam Length
fields.memo: The volume flow rate of chilled water per meter of beam length at the rating point.

fields.name: Beam Cooling Capacity Temperature Difference Modification Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Adjusts beam cooling capacity when the temperature difference between entering water and zone air is different than at the rating point.  Single independent variable is the ratio of the current temperature difference divided by the rating point temperature difference. This field is required when beam is connected to a chilled water plant.

fields.name: Beam Cooling Capacity Air Flow Modification Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Adjusts beam cooling capacity when the primary air supply flow rate is different than at the rating point. The single independent variable is the current normalized air flow rate divided by the normalized air flow rate at the rating point. This field is required when beam is connected to a chilled water plant.

fields.name: Beam Cooling Capacity Chilled Water Flow Modification Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Adjusts beam cooling capacity when the normalized chilled water flow rate is different than at the rating point. The single independent variable is the current normalized chilled water flow rate divided by the normalized chilled water flow rate at the rating point. This field is required when beam is connected to a chilled water plant.

fields.name: Beam Rated Heating Capacity per Beam Length
fields.memo: Sensible heating capacity per meter of beam length at the rating point.

fields.name: Beam Rated Heating Room Air Hot Water Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Difference in temperature between the zone air and the entering hot water at the rating point.

fields.name: Beam Rated Hot Water Volume Flow Rate per Beam Length
fields.memo: The volume flow rate of hoy water per meter of beam length at the rating point.

fields.name: Beam Heating Capacity Temperature Difference Modification Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Adjusts beam heating capacity when the temperature difference between entering water and zone air is different than at the rating point.  Single independent variable is the ratio of the current temperature difference divided by the rating point temperature difference. This field is required when beam is connected to a hot water plant.

fields.name: Beam Heating Capacity Air Flow Modification Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Adjusts beam heating capacity when the primary air supply flow rate is different than at the rating point. The single independent variable is the current normalized air flow rate divided by the normalized air flow rate at the rating point. This field is required when beam is connected to a hot water plant.

fields.name: Beam Heating Capacity Hot Water Flow Modification Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Adjusts beam heating capacity when the normalized hot water flow rate is different than at the rating point. The single independent variable is the current normalized hot water flow rate divided by the normalized hot water flow rate at the rating point. This field is required when beam is connected to a hot water plant.

availabilitymanagerassignmentlist.name: AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList
availabilitymanagerassignmentlist.memo: Defines the applicable managers used for an AirLoopHVAC or PlantLoop. The priority of availability managers is based on a set of rules and are specific to the type of loop. The output from each availability manager is an availability status flag: NoAction, ForceOff, CycleOn, or CycleOnZoneFansOnly (used only for air loops).

refrigeration:condenser:aircooled.name: Refrigeration:Condenser:AirCooled
refrigeration:condenser:aircooled.memo: Air cooled condenser for a refrigeration system (Refrigeration:System).

fields.name: Rated Effective Total Heat Rejection Rate Curve Name
fields.memo: Rating as per ARI 460 Be sure the rating corresponds to the correct refrigerant HeatRejection(W)=C1 +C2(Condensing Temp - Entering Air Temp, deg C) Will be adjusted for elevation automatically

fields.name: Rated Subcooling Temperature Difference
fields.memo: must correspond to rating given for total heat rejection effect

fields.name: Rated Fan Power
fields.memo: Power for condenser fan(s) corresponding to rated total heat rejection effect.

fields.name: Minimum Fan Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Minimum air flow fraction through condenser fan

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name or Zone Name
fields.memo: If field is left blank, then the model assumes that the inlet air conditions are the outdoor air conditions for the current timestep (e.g., no adjustment for height above ground). If the condenser rejects heat to a conditioned zone, enter the zone name here.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Condenser Refrigerant Operating Charge Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Receiver Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Piping Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

zoneventilation:windandstackopenarea.name: ZoneVentilation:WindandStackOpenArea
zoneventilation:windandstackopenarea.memo: This object is specified as natural ventilation driven by wind and stack effect only: Ventilation Wind = Cw * Opening Area * Schedule * WindSpd Ventilation Stack = Cd * Opening Area * Schedule * SQRT(2*g*DH*(|(Tzone-Todb)|/Tzone)) Total Ventilation = SQRT((Ventilation Wind)^2 + (Ventilation Stack)^2)

fields.name: Opening Area
fields.memo: This is the opening area used to calculate stack effect and wind driven ventilation.

fields.name: Opening Area Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the fraction values applied to the opening area given in the previous input field (0.0 - 1.0).

fields.name: Opening Effectiveness
fields.memo: This field is used to calculate wind driven ventilation. "Cw" in the wind-driven equation and the maximum value is 1.0. When the input is Autocalculate, the program calculates Cw based on an angle between wind direction and effective angle Cw = 0.55 at angle = 0, and Cw = 0.3 at angle=180 Linear interpolation is used to calculate Cw based on the above two values.

fields.name: Effective Angle
fields.memo: This field is defined as normal angle of the opening area and is used when input field Opening Effectiveness = Autocalculate.

fields.name: Height Difference
fields.memo: This is the height difference between the midpoint of an opening and the neutral pressure level. "DH" in the stack equation.

fields.name: Discharge Coefficient for Opening
fields.memo: This is the discharge coefficient used to calculate stack effect. "Cd" in the stack equation and the maximum value is 1.0. When the input is Autocalculate, the following equation is used to calculate the coefficient: Cd = 0.4 + 0.0045*|(Tzone-Todb)|

fields.name: Minimum Indoor Temperature
fields.memo: This is the indoor temperature below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Indoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the indoor temperature versus time below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Indoor Temperature
fields.memo: This is the indoor temperature above which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Indoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the indoor temperature versus time above which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Delta Temperature
fields.memo: This is the temperature differential between indoor and outdoor below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Delta Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the temperature differential between indoor and outdoor versus time below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature
fields.memo: This is the outdoor temperature below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature
fields.memo: This is the outdoor temperature above which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time above which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Wind Speed
fields.memo: This is the outdoor wind speed above which ventilation is shutoff.

setpointmanager:followsystemnodetemperat.name: SetpointManager:FollowSystemNodeTemperature
setpointmanager:followsystemnodetemperat.memo: This setpoint manager is used to place a temperature setpoint on a system node that is derived from the current temperatures at a separate system node.  The current value of the temperature at a reference node is obtained and used to generate setpoint on a second system node. If the reference node is also designated to be an outdoor air (intake) node, then this setpoint manager can be used to follow outdoor air conditions that are adjusted for altitude.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which control variable will be set

headeredpumps:constantspeed.name: HeaderedPumps:ConstantSpeed
headeredpumps:constantspeed.memo: This Headered pump object describes a pump bank with more than 1 pump in parallel

fields.name: Total Design Flow Rate
fields.memo: If the field is not autosized set to the flow rate to the total flow when all pumps are running at full load

fields.name: Design Pump Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet

fields.name: Design Power Consumption
fields.memo: If the field is not autosized set to the power consumed by the pump bank when all the pumps are running at nominal flow When autosized the type of scaling factor is chosen in the input field Design Power Sizing Method

fields.name: Motor Efficiency
fields.memo: This is the motor efficiency only. When the Design Power Consumption is autosized using PowerPerFlowPerPressure, the Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used in addition to the motor efficiency.

fields.name: Fraction of Motor Inefficiencies to Fluid Stream
Pump Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the rated flow rate of the pump on a time basis. Default is that the pump is on and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: optional, if used pump losses transfered to zone as internal gains

fields.name: Skin Loss Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: optional. If zone identified in previous field then this determines the split between convection and radiation for the skin losses

fields.name: Design Power Sizing Method
fields.memo: Used to indicate which sizing factor is used to calculate Design Power Consumption. PowerPerFlow indicates that Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * scaling factor PowerPerFlowPerPressure indicates that Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * Design Pump Head * scaling factor / Motor Efficiency

fields.name: Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate

fields.name: Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate for head and motor efficiency

electricloadcenter:inverter:pvwatts.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Inverter:PVWatts
electricloadcenter:inverter:pvwatts.memo: Electric power inverter to convert from direct current (DC) to alternating current (AC) in an electric load center that contains Generator:PVWatts objects. It implements the PVWatts inverter performance curves.

heatexchanger:desiccant:balancedflow:per.name: HeatExchanger:Desiccant:BalancedFlow:PerformanceDataType1
heatexchanger:desiccant:balancedflow:per.memo: RTO = B1 + B2*RWI + B3*RTI + B4*(RWI/RTI) + B5*PWI + B6*PTI + B7*(PWI/PTI) + B8*RFV RWO = C1 + C2*RWI + C3*RTI + C4*(RWI/RTI) + C5*PWI + C6*PTI + C7*(PWI/PTI) + C8*RFV where, RTO = Dry-bulb temperature of the regeneration outlet air (C) RWO = Humidity ratio of the regeneration outlet air (kgWater/kgDryAir) RWI = Humidity ratio of the regeneration inlet air (kgWater/kgDryAir) RTI = Dry-bulb temperature of the regeneration inlet air (C) PWI = Humidity ratio of the process inlet air (kgWater/kgDryAir) PTI = Dry-bulb temperature of the process inlet air (C) RFV = Regeneration Face Velocity (m/s)

fields.name: Nominal Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Air flow rate at nominal conditions (assumed to be the same for both sides of the heat exchanger).

fields.name: Nominal Electric Power
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power (e.g., desiccant wheel motor)
