sizing:parameters.name: Sizing:Parameters
sizing:parameters.memo: Specifies global heating and cooling sizing factors/ratios. These ratios are applied at the zone level to all of the zone heating and cooling loads and air flow rates. Then these new loads and air flow rates are used to calculate the system level flow rates and capacities and are used in all component sizing calculations. Specifies the width (in load timesteps) of a moving average window which is used to smooth the peak load across more than one timestep.

fields.name: Timesteps in Averaging Window
fields.memo: blank => set the timesteps in averaging window to Number of Timesteps per Hour resulting in a 1 hour averaging window default is number of timesteps for 1 hour averaging window

fuelfactors.name: FuelFactors
fuelfactors.memo: Provides Fuel Factors for Emissions as well as Source=>Site conversions. OtherFuel1, OtherFuel2 provide options for users who want to create and use fuels that may not be mainstream (biomass, wood, pellets).

fields.name: Nuclear High Level Emission Factor Schedule Name
Nuclear Low Level Emission Factor Schedule Name

output:variable.name: Output:Variable
output:variable.memo: each Output:Variable command picks variables to be put onto the standard output file (.eso) some variables may not be reported for every simulation. a list of variables that can be reported are available after a run on the report dictionary file (.rdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Key Value
fields.memo: use '*' (without quotes) to apply this variable to all keys

fields.name: Reporting Frequency
fields.memo: Detailed lists every instance (i.e. HVAC variable timesteps) Timestep refers to the zone Timestep/Number of Timesteps in hour value RunPeriod and Environment are the same

hvactemplate:zone:watertoairheatpump.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:WaterToAirHeatPump
hvactemplate:zone:watertoairheatpump.memo: Water to Air Heat Pump to be used with HVACTemplate:Plant:MixedWaterLoop

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during cooling operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during heating operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate when no cooling or heating is needed Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. A value entered in this field will *not* be multiplied by the sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  It is best to autosize or leave blank when using zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include effect of supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electric power input

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Capacity excluding supply air fan heat

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Heat Pump Heating Coil Rated Capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electric power input

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: The maximum on-off cycling rate for the compressor Suggested value is 2.5 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Heat Pump Time Constant
fields.memo: Time constant for the cooling coil's capacity to reach steady state after startup Suggested value is 60 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Fraction of On-Cycle Power Use
fields.memo: The fraction of on-cycle power use to adjust the part load fraction based on the off-cycle power consumption due to crankcase heaters, controls, fans, and etc. Suggested value is 0.01 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Heat Pump Fan Delay Time
fields.memo: Programmed time delay for heat pump fan to shut off after compressor cycle off. Only required when fan operating mode is cycling Enter 0 when fan operating mode is continuous

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:DedicatedOutdoorAir object if this zone is served by a separate dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Leave field blank if no DOAS serves this zone.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Heat Pump Coil Water Flow Mode
fields.memo: used only when the heat pump coils are of the type WaterToAirHeatPump:EquationFit Constant results in 100% water flow regardless of compressor PLR Cycling results in water flow that matches compressor PLR ConstantOnDemand results in 100% water flow whenever the coil is on, but is 0% whenever the coil has no load

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

surfaceproperty:surroundingsurfaces.name: SurfaceProperty:SurroundingSurfaces
surfaceproperty:surroundingsurfaces.memo: This object defines a list of surrounding surfaces for an exterior surface.

fields.name: Sky View Factor
fields.memo: optional

fields.name: Sky Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are real numbers, -100.0 to 100.0, units C optional

fields.name: Ground View Factor
fields.memo: optional

fields.name: Ground Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are real numbers, -100.0 to 100.0, units C optional

coolingtowerperformance:cooltools.name: CoolingTowerPerformance:CoolTools
coolingtowerperformance:cooltools.memo: This object is used to define coefficients for the approach temperature correlation for a variable speed cooling tower when tower Model Type is specified as CoolToolsUserDefined in the object CoolingTower:VariableSpeed.

fields.name: Minimum Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum valid inlet air wet-bulb temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Maximum valid inlet air wet-bulb temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Minimum Range Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum valid range temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Range Temperature
fields.memo: Maximum valid range temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Minimum Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum valid approach temperature for this correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Maximum valid approach temperature for this correlation.

fields.name: Minimum Water Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Minimum valid water flow rate ratio for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Water Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Maximum valid water flow rate ratio for this approach temperature correlation.

airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:fo.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:ConstantVolume:FourPipeInduction
airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:fo.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume, induction unit with hot water reheat coil and chilled water recool coil.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Induction Ratio
fields.memo: ratio of induced air flow rate to primary air flow rate

fields.name: Induced Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: should be a zone exhaust node, also the heating coil inlet node

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: should be a zone inlet node

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when heating coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when heating coil type is gas or electric

surfaceconvectionalgorithm:outside:userc.name: SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve
surfaceconvectionalgorithm:outside:userc.memo: Used to describe a custom model equation for surface convection heat transfer coefficient If more than one curve is referenced they are all used and added together.

fields.name: Hf Function of Wind Speed Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is wind speed of the type determined in the previous field (m/s)

fields.name: Hn Function of Temperature Difference Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is absolute value of delta-T (Surface temperature minus air temperature, (C))

fields.name: Hn Function of Temperature Difference Divided by Height Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is absolute value of delta-T/Height (Surface temp minus Air temp)/(vertical length scale), (C/m) when used for an outside face the vertical length scale is the exterior facade's overall height

airflownetwork:distribution:component:le.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:LeakageRatio
airflownetwork:distribution:component:le.memo: This object is used to define supply and return air leaks with respect to the fan's maximum air flow rate.

fields.name: Effective Leakage Ratio
fields.memo: Defined as a ratio of leak flow rate to the maximum flow rate.

fields.name: Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the maximum air flow rate in this air loop.

fields.name: Reference Pressure Difference
fields.memo: Enter the pressure corresponding to the Effective leakage ratio entered above.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the air mass flow equation.

roomairsettings:crossventilation.name: RoomAirSettings:CrossVentilation
roomairsettings:crossventilation.memo: This UCSD Cross Ventilation Room Air Model provides a simple model for heat transfer and vertical temperature profile prediction in cross ventilated rooms. The model distinguishes two regions in the room, the main jet region and the recirculations, and predicts characteristic airflow velocities and average air temperatures. Used with RoomAirModelType = CrossVentilation.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of Zone being described. Any existing zone name

fields.name: Gain Distribution Schedule Name
fields.memo: Distribution of the convective heat gains between the jet and recirculation zones. 0<= Accepted Value <= 1. In the CV model 1 means all convective gains in the jet region.

fields.name: Airflow Region Used for Thermal Comfort Evaluation
fields.memo: Required field whenever thermal comfort is predicted defines Air temperature and Airflow velocity that will be used in the Fanger model conditions must refer to one of the two regions: jet or recirculation

window.name: Window
window.memo: Allows for simplified entry of Windows.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Building Surface Name
fields.memo: Name of Surface (Wall, usually) the Window is on (i.e., Base Surface) Window assumes the azimuth and tilt angles of the surface it is on.

fields.name: Shading Control Name
fields.memo: enter the name of a WindowProperty:ShadingControl object used for windows and glass doors only If not specified, window or glass door has no shading (blind, roller shade, etc.)

fields.name: Frame and Divider Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a WindowProperty:FrameAndDivider object Used only for exterior windows (rectangular) and glass doors. Unused for triangular windows. If not specified (blank), window or glass door has no frame or divider and no beam solar reflection from reveal surfaces.

fields.name: Multiplier
fields.memo: Used only for Surface Type = WINDOW, GLASSDOOR or DOOR Non-integer values will be truncated to integer

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Window starting coordinate is specified relative to the Base Surface origin.

fields.name: Starting Z Coordinate
fields.memo: How far up the wall the Window starts. (in 2-d, this would be a Y Coordinate)

shadowcalculation.name: ShadowCalculation
shadowcalculation.memo: This object is used to control details of the solar, shading, and daylighting models

fields.name: Calculation Method
fields.memo: choose calculation method. note that TimestepFrequency is only needed for certain cases and can increase execution time significantly.

fields.name: Calculation Frequency
fields.memo: enter number of days this field is only used if the previous field is set to AverageOverDaysInFrequency 0=Use Default Periodic Calculation|<else> calculate every <value> day only really applicable to RunPeriods warning issued if >31

fields.name: Maximum Figures in Shadow Overlap Calculations
fields.memo: Number of allowable figures in shadow overlap calculations

fields.name: Polygon Clipping Algorithm
fields.memo: Advanced Feature.  Internal default is SutherlandHodgman Refer to InputOutput Reference and Engineering Reference for more information

fields.name: Sky Diffuse Modeling Algorithm
fields.memo: Advanced Feature.  Internal default is SimpleSkyDiffuseModeling If you have shading elements that change transmittance over the year, you may wish to choose the detailed method. Refer to InputOutput Reference and Engineering Reference for more information

fields.name: External Shading Calculation Method
fields.memo: If ScheduledShading is chosen, the External Shading Fraction Schedule Name is required in SurfaceProperty:LocalEnvironment. If ImportedShading is chosen, the Schedule:File:Shading object is required.

fields.name: Output External Shading Calculation Results
fields.memo: If Yes is chosen, the calculated external shading fraction results will be saved to an external CSV file with surface names as the column headers.

fields.name: Disable Self-Shading Within Shading Zone Groups
fields.memo: If Yes, self-shading will be disabled from all exterior surfaces in a given Shading Zone Group to surfaces within the same Shading Zone Group. If both Disable Self-Shading Within Shading Zone Groups and Disable Self-Shading From Shading Zone Groups to Other Zones = Yes, then all self-shading from exterior surfaces will be disabled. If only one of these fields = Yes, then at least one Shading Zone Group must be specified, or this field will be ignored. Shading from Shading:* surfaces, overhangs, fins, and reveals will not be disabled.

fields.name: Disable Self-Shading From Shading Zone Groups to Other Zones
fields.memo: If Yes, self-shading will be disabled from all exterior surfaces in a given Shading Zone Group to all other zones in the model. If both Disable Self-Shading Within Shading Zone Groups and Disable Self-Shading From Shading Zone Groups to Other Zones = Yes, then all self-shading from exterior surfaces will be disabled. If only one of these fields = Yes, then at least one Shading Zone Group must be specified, or this field will be ignored. Shading from Shading:* surfaces, overhangs, fins, and reveals will not be disabled.

outputcontrol:surfacecolorscheme.name: OutputControl:SurfaceColorScheme
outputcontrol:surfacecolorscheme.memo: This object is used to set colors for reporting on various building elements particularly for the DXF reports.  We know the user can enter 0 to 255 and the color map is available in DXF output. Therefore, we are limiting the colors in that range.  You can extend by editing the IDD but you do so on your own.  Colors not changed in any scheme will remain as the default scheme uses.

fields.name: Color for Drawing Element 1
fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.name: Color for Drawing Element 2
fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.name: Color for Drawing Element 3
fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

fields.name: Color for Drawing Element 15
fields.memo: use color number for output assignment (e.g. DXF)

pipe:adiabatic.name: Pipe:Adiabatic
pipe:adiabatic.memo: Passes Inlet Node state variables to Outlet Node state variables

chiller:electric:eir.name: Chiller:Electric:EIR
chiller:electric:eir.memo: This chiller model is the empirical model from the DOE-2 building Energy simulation program. Chiller performance at off-reference conditions is modeled using three polynomial equations. Three curves objects are required.

fields.name: Reference COP
fields.memo: Efficiency of the chiller compressor (cooling output/compressor energy input). Condenser fan power should not be included here.

fields.name: Reference Condenser Fluid Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = AirCooled or EvaporativelyCooled when Heat Recovery is specified

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Cooling capacity as a function of CW supply temp and entering condenser temp curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*ECT + e*ECT**2 + f*CWS*ECT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of temperature EIR = 1/COP curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*ECT + e*ECT**2 + f*CWS*ECT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) EIR = 1/COP quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 is typical, other univariate curves may be used PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Minimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Part load ratio below which the chiller starts cycling on/off to meet the load. Must be less than or equal to Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Maximum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Maximum allowable part load ratio. Must be greater than or equal to Minimum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Optimum part load ratio where the chiller is most efficient. Must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Minimum Unloading Ratio
fields.memo: Part load ratio where the chiller can no longer unload and false loading begins. Minimum unloading ratio must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Condenser Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Not required if air-cooled or evaporatively-cooled

fields.name: Condenser Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Not required if air-cooled or evaporatively-cooled

fields.name: Condenser Fan Power Ratio
fields.memo: Use for air-cooled or evaporatively-cooled condensers. Ratio of condenser fan power to reference chiller capacity

fields.name: Fraction of Compressor Electric Consumption Rejected by Condenser
fields.memo: Fraction of compressor electrical energy that must be rejected by the condenser. Enter a value of 1.0 when modeling hermetic chillers. For open chillers, enter the compressor motor efficiency. This value should be greater than 0.6 for practical applications.

fields.name: Leaving Chilled Water Lower Temperature Limit
Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered. Heat recovery is only available with Condenser Type = WaterCooled.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the chiller is not operating.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Condenser Heat Recovery Relative Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This optional field is the fraction of total rejected heat that can be recovered at full load

fields.name: Heat Recovery Inlet High Temperature Limit Schedule Name
fields.memo: This optional schedule of temperatures will turn off heat recovery if inlet exceeds the value

fields.name: Heat Recovery Leaving Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: This optional field provides control over the heat recovery Using this triggers a model more suited to series bundle and chillers with higher temperature heat recovery If this field is not used, the bundles are modeled as being in parallel

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

generator:microchp:nonnormalizedparamete.name: Generator:MicroCHP:NonNormalizedParameters
generator:microchp:nonnormalizedparamete.memo: This object is referenced by a Generator:MicroCHP object and provides the non-normalized parameters for the MicroCHP generator model.

fields.name: Electrical Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: TriQuadratic

fields.name: Thermal Efficiency Curve Name
fields.memo: TriQuadratic

fields.name: Cooling Water Flow Rate Curve Name
Maximum Net Electrical Power Rate of Change
Maximum Fuel Flow Rate of Change
Heat Exchanger U-Factor Times Area Value
Skin Loss U-Factor Times Area Value
Aggregated Thermal Mass of Energy Conversion Portion of Generator
Aggregated Thermal Mass of Heat Recovery Portion of Generator
Warm Up Mode
fields.memo: Stirling engines use Nominal Engine Temperature Internal combustion engines use Time Delay

fields.name: Warm Up Fuel Flow Rate Coefficient
Warm Up Fuel Flow Rate Limit Ratio

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitExport:To:Actuator
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.memo: Hardware portion of EMS used to set up actuators in the model that are dynamically updated from the FMU.

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during the first call of EnergyPlus.

wall:detailed.name: Wall:Detailed
wall:detailed.memo: Allows for detailed entry of wall heat transfer surfaces.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Non-blank only if the field Outside Boundary Condition is Surface, Zone, OtherSideCoefficients or OtherSideConditionsModel If Surface, specify name of corresponding surface in adjacent zone or specify current surface name for internal partition separating like zones If Zone, specify the name of the corresponding zone and the program will generate the corresponding interzone surface If Foundation, specify the name of the corresponding Foundation object and If OtherSideCoefficients, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideCoefficients If OtherSideConditionsModel, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel

fields.name: View Factor to Ground
fields.memo: From the exterior of the surface Unused if one uses the "reflections" options in Solar Distribution in Building input unless a DaylightingDevice:Shelf or DaylightingDevice:Tubular object has been specified. autocalculate will automatically calculate this value from the tilt of the surface

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 10 vertex coordinates -- extensible object "extensible" -- duplicate last set of x,y,z coordinates, renumbering please (and changing z terminator to a comma "," for all but last one which needs a semi-colon ";") vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- if relative, all surface coordinates are "relative" to the Zone Origin.  If world, then building and zone origins are used for some internal calculations, but all coordinates are given in an "absolute" system.

output:illuminancemap.name: Output:IlluminanceMap
output:illuminancemap.memo: reference points are given in coordinates specified in the GlobalGeometryRules object Daylighting Reference Point CoordinateSystem field

fields.name: Number of X Grid Points
fields.memo: Maximum number of total grid points must be <= 2500 (X*Y)

fields.name: Number of Y Grid Points
fields.memo: Maximum number of total grid points must be <= 2500 (X*Y)

outputcontrol:reportingtolerances.name: OutputControl:ReportingTolerances
outputcontrol:reportingtolerances.memo: Calculations of the time that setpoints are not met use a tolerance of 0.2C. This object allows changing the tolerance used to determine when setpoints are being met.

fields.name: Tolerance for Time Heating Setpoint Not Met
fields.memo: If the zone temperature is below the heating setpoint by more than this value, the following output variables will increment as appropriate Zone Heating Setpoint Not Met Time Zone Heating Setpoint Not Met While Occupied Time This also impacts table report "Annual Building Utility Performance Summary" subtable "Comfort and Setpoint Not Met Summary"

fields.name: Tolerance for Time Cooling Setpoint Not Met
fields.memo: If the zone temperature is above the cooling setpoint by more than this value, the following output variables will increment as appropriate Zone Cooling Setpoint Not Met Time Zone Cooling Setpoint Not Met While Occupied Time This also impacts table report "Annual Building Utility Performance Summary" subtable "Comfort and Setpoint Not Met Summary"

plantequipmentoperation:userdefined.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:UserDefined
plantequipmentoperation:userdefined.memo: Defines a generic plant operation scheme for custom supervisory control using Energy Management System or External Interface to dispatch loads

fields.name: Main Model Program Calling Manager Name

groundheatexchanger:slinky.name: GroundHeatExchanger:Slinky
groundheatexchanger:slinky.memo: This models a slinky horizontal heat exchanger placed in a series of trenches The model uses the model developed by: Xiong, Z., D.E. Fisher, and J.D. Spitler. 2015. Development and Validation of a Slinky Ground Heat Exchanger Model. Applied Energy 141: 57-69.

fields.name: Heat Exchanger Configuration
fields.memo: This is the orientation of the heat exchanger

fields.name: Coil Diameter
fields.memo: This is the diameter of the heat exchanger coil

fields.name: Coil Pitch
fields.memo: This is the center-to-center distance between coils

fields.name: Trench Depth
fields.memo: This is the distance from the ground surface to the trench bottom

fields.name: Trench Length
fields.memo: This is the total length of a single trench This assumes the heat exchanger runs the full length of the trench

fields.name: Number of Trenches
fields.memo: This is the number of parallel trenches that has a heat exchanger, one per trench

fields.name: Horizontal Spacing Between Pipes
fields.memo: This represents the average horizontal spacing between any two trenches for heat exchangers that have multiple trenches

fenestrationsurface:detailed.name: FenestrationSurface:Detailed
fenestrationsurface:detailed.memo: Allows for detailed entry of subsurfaces (windows, doors, glass doors, tubular daylighting devices).

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Non-blank only if base surface field Outside Boundary Condition is Surface or OtherSideCoefficients If Base Surface's Surface, specify name of corresponding subsurface in adjacent zone or specify current subsurface name for internal partition separating like zones If OtherSideCoefficients, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideCoefficients or leave blank to inherit Base Surface's OtherSide Coefficients

fields.name: View Factor to Ground
fields.memo: From the exterior of the surface Unused if one uses the "reflections" options in Solar Distribution in Building input unless a DaylightingDevice:Shelf or DaylightingDevice:Tubular object has been specified. autocalculate will automatically calculate this value from the tilt of the surface

fields.name: Shading Control Name
fields.memo: enter the name of a WindowProperty:ShadingControl object used for windows and glass doors only If not specified, window or glass door has no shading (blind, roller shade, etc.)

fields.name: Frame and Divider Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a WindowProperty:FrameAndDivider object Used only for exterior windows (rectangular) and glass doors. Unused for triangular windows. If not specified (blank), window or glass door has no frame or divider and no beam solar reflection from reveal surfaces.

fields.name: Multiplier
fields.memo: Used only for Surface Type = WINDOW, GLASSDOOR or DOOR Non-integer values will be truncated to integer

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- if relative, all surface coordinates are "relative" to the Zone Origin.  If world, then building and zone origins are used for some internal calculations, but all coordinates are given in an "absolute" system.

fields.name: Vertex 4 X-coordinate
fields.memo: Not used for triangles

fields.name: Vertex 4 Y-coordinate
fields.memo: Not used for triangles

fields.name: Vertex 4 Z-coordinate
fields.memo: Not used for triangles

airflownetwork:distribution:component:te.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:TerminalUnit
airflownetwork:distribution:component:te.memo: This object defines the name of a terminal unit in an air loop.

fields.name: Terminal Unit Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a terminal unit in the AirLoopHVAC.

fields.name: Terminal Unit Object Type
fields.memo: Select the type of terminal unit corresponding to the name entered in the field above.

fields.name: Air Path Length
fields.memo: Enter the air path length (depth) for the terminal unit.

fields.name: Air Path Hydraulic Diameter
fields.memo: Enter the hydraulic diameter of this terminal unit. The hydraulic diameter is defined as 4 multiplied by the cross section area divided by perimeter.

refrigeration:compressorrack.name: Refrigeration:CompressorRack
refrigeration:compressorrack.memo: Works in conjunction with the refrigeration case and walk-in objects to simulate the performance of a refrigerated case system. This object models the electric consumption of the rack compressors and the condenser fans. Heat can be rejected either outdoors or to a zone. Compressor rack waste heat can also be reclaimed for use by an optional air- or water-heating coil (Coil:Heating:Desuperheater and Coil:WaterHeating:Desuperheater).

fields.name: Design Compressor Rack COP
fields.memo: It is important that this COP correspond to the lowest saturated suction temperature needed to serve all refrigeration loads

fields.name: Compressor Rack COP Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: It is important that this COP curve correspond to the lowest saturated suction temperature needed to serve all refrigeration loads

fields.name: Design Condenser Fan Power
fields.memo: Design power for condenser fan(s).

fields.name: Condenser Fan Power Function of Temperature Curve Name
Condenser Type
fields.memo: Applicable only when Heat Rejection Location is Outdoors.

fields.name: Water-Cooled Loop Flow Type
fields.memo: Applicable only when Condenser Type is WaterCooled.

fields.name: Water-Cooled Condenser Outlet Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Applicable only when loop Flow type is VariableFlow.

fields.name: Water-Cooled Condenser Design Flow Rate
fields.memo: Applicable only when loop flow type is ConstantFlow.

fields.name: Water-Cooled Condenser Maximum Water Outlet Temperature
Water-Cooled Condenser Minimum Water Inlet Temperature
Evaporative Condenser Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 indicate that evaporative cooling of the condenser is available. This schedule allows the user to define seasonal shutdown/draining of the water cooling system in cold climate applications. For periods with schedule values of 0, the condenser operates as AirCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Effectiveness
fields.memo: Applicable only for Condenser Type = EvaporativlyCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Applicable only for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the evaporatively cooled condenser is available (field Evaporative Condenser Availability Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater heats the basin water when the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature falls below the setpoint temperature, but only when the condenser fans are off (i.e., no refrigerated case load).

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature at which the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Design Evaporative Condenser Water Pump Power
fields.memo: Design recirc water pump power for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Applicable only for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Water Supply Tank Name
fields.memo: If blank, water supply is from Mains. Applicable only for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Applicable only when Heat Rejection Location is Outdoors and Condenser Type is not WaterCooled; otherwise, leave field blank. If field is left blank with Heat Rejection Location = Outdoors, then the model assumes that the Inlet Air conditions are the outdoor air conditions for the current timestep (e.g., no adjustment for height above ground).

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory

fields.memo: This must be a controlled zone and appear in a ZoneHVAC:EquipmentConnections object. Required only if walk-in[s] are connected to this rack AND the heat rejection location is "Zone"

zonehvac:ventilatedslab.name: ZoneHVAC:VentilatedSlab
zonehvac:ventilatedslab.memo: Ventilated slab system where outdoor air flows through hollow cores in a building surface (wall, ceiling, or floor).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: (name of zone system is serving)

fields.name: Surface Name or Radiant Surface Group Name
fields.memo: (name of surface system is embedded in) or list of surfaces

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: schedule values multiply the minimum outdoor air flow rate

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Fraction or Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Note that this depends on the control type as to whether schedule values are a fraction or temperature

fields.name: Hollow Core Length
fields.memo: (length of core cavity embedded in surface)

fields.name: Number of Cores
fields.memo: flow will be divided evenly among the cores

fields.name: Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: (temperature on which unit is controlled)

fields.name: Heating High Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Air and control temperatures for heating work together to provide a linear function that determines the air temperature sent to the radiant system. The current control temperature (see A14) is compared to the high and low control temperatures at the current time. If the control temperature is above the high temperature, then the inlet air temperature is set to the low air temperature. If the control temperature is below the low temperature, then the inlet air temperature is set to the high air temperature. If the control temperature is between the high and low value, then the inlet air temperature is linearly interpolated between the low and high air temperature values.

fields.name: Heating Low Air Temperature Schedule Name
Heating High Control Temperature Schedule Name
Heating Low Control Temperature Schedule Name
Cooling High Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: See note for heating high air temperature schedule above for interpretation information (or see the Input/Output Reference).

fields.name: Cooling Low Air Temperature Schedule Name

Cooling Low Control Temperature Schedule Name
Return Air Node Name
fields.memo: This is the zone return air inlet to the ventilated slab system outdoor air mixer. This node is typically a zone exhaust node (do not connect to "Zone Return Air Node").

fields.name: Slab In Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node entering the slab or series of slabs after the fan and coil(s).

fields.name: Zone Supply Air Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node name exiting the slab. This node is typically a zone inlet node. Leave blank when the system configuration is SlabOnly or SeriesSlabs.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: This node is the outdoor air inlet to the ventilated slab oa mixer. This node should also be specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Relief Air Node Name
fields.memo: This node is the relief air node from the ventilated slab outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node name leaving the outdoor air mixer and entering the fan and coil(s).

fields.name: Fan Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node name of the fan outlet.

fields.name: Fan Name
fields.memo: Allowable fan types are Fan:SystemModel and Fan:ConstantVolume

fields.name: Hot Water or Steam Inlet Node Name
Availability Manager List Name

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

outdoorair:node.name: OutdoorAir:Node
outdoorair:node.memo: This object sets the temperature and humidity conditions for an outdoor air node.  It allows the height above ground to be specified.  This object may be used more than once. The same node name may not appear in both an OutdoorAir:Node object and an OutdoorAir:NodeList object. This object defines local outdoor air environmental conditions.

fields.name: Height Above Ground
fields.memo: A value less than zero indicates that the height will be ignored and the weather file conditions will be used.

fields.name: Drybulb Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are real numbers, -100.0 to 100.0, units C

fields.name: Wetbulb Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are real numbers, -100.0 to 100.0, units C

fields.name: Wind Speed Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are real numbers, 0.0 to 40.0, units m/s

fields.name: Wind Direction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values are real numbers, 0.0 to 360.0, units degree

fields.name: Wind Pressure Coefficient Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of the AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientValues, curve, or table object specifying the wind pressure coefficient.

fields.name: Symmetric Wind Pressure Coefficient Curve
fields.memo: Specify whether the pressure curve is symmetric or not. Specify Yes for curves that should be evaluated from 0 to 180 degrees Specify No for curves that should be evaluated from 0 to 360 degrees

fields.name: Wind Angle Type
fields.memo: Specify whether the angle used to compute the wind pressure coefficient is absolute or relative Specify Relative to compute the angle between the wind direction and the surface azimuth Specify Absolute to use the wind direction angle directly

zonehvac:refrigerationchillerset.name: ZoneHVAC:RefrigerationChillerSet
zonehvac:refrigerationchillerset.memo: Works in conjunction with one or multiple air chillers, compressor racks, refrigeration systems, or refrigeration secondary system objects to simulate the performance of a group of air chillers cooling a single zone. The chiller set model passes information about the zone conditions to determine the performance of individual chiller coils within the set, thus providing the sensible and latent heat exchange with the zone environment.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: This must be a controlled zone and appear in a ZoneHVAC:EquipmentConnections object.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Not used - reserved for future use Name of the zone exhaust node (see Node) from which the refrigeration chiller draws its indoor air. This should be one of the zone exhaust nodes for the zone cooled by the chiller set.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Not used - reserved for future use The name of the node where the chiller coil sends its outlet air, which must be one of the inlet air nodes for the zone which is being cooled.

internalmass.name: InternalMass
internalmass.memo: Used to describe internal zone surface area that does not need to be part of geometric representation. This should be the total surface area exposed to the zone air.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of used to be Interior Environment

waterheater:stratified.name: WaterHeater:Stratified
waterheater:stratified.memo: Water heater with stratified, multi-node water tank. May be used to model a tankless water heater (small tank volume), a hot water storage tank (zero heater capacity), or a heat pump water heater (see WaterHeater:HeatPump:*.)

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.memo: Only used if use side node connections are blank Defaults to water temperatures calculated by Site:WaterMainsTemperature object

fields.name: Use Side Effectiveness
fields.memo: The use side effectiveness in the stratified tank model is a simplified analogy of a heat exchanger's effectiveness. This effectiveness is equal to the fraction of use mass flow rate that directly mixes with the tank fluid. And one minus the effectiveness is the fraction that bypasses the tank. The use side mass flow rate that bypasses the tank is mixed with the fluid or water leaving the stratified tank.

fields.name: Use Side Inlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to bottom of tank

fields.name: Use Side Outlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to top of tank

fields.name: Source Side Effectiveness
fields.memo: The source side effectiveness in the stratified tank model is a simplified analogy of a heat exchanger's effectiveness. This effectiveness is equal to the fraction of source mass flow rate that directly mixes with the tank fluid. And one minus the effectiveness is the fraction that bypasses the tank. The source side mass flow rate that bypasses the tank is mixed with the fluid or water leaving the stratified tank.

fields.name: Source Side Inlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to top of tank

fields.name: Source Side Outlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to bottom of tank

fields.name: Indirect Water Heating Recovery Time
fields.memo: Parameter for autosizing design flow rates for indirectly heated water tanks time required to raise temperature of entire tank from 14.4C to 57.2C

fields.name: Source Side Flow Control Mode
fields.memo: StorageTank mode always requests flow unless tank is at its Maximum Temperature Limit IndirectHeatPrimarySetpoint mode requests flow whenever primary setpoint for heater 1 calls for heat IndirectHeatAlternateSetpoint mode requests flow whenever alternate indirect setpoint calls for heat
