availabilitymanager:lowtemperatureturnof.name: AvailabilityManager:LowTemperatureTurnOff
availabilitymanager:lowtemperatureturnof.memo: Overrides fan/pump schedules depending on temperature at sensor node.

fields.name: Applicability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, defaults to always active

curve:cubic.name: Curve:Cubic
curve:cubic.memo: Cubic curve with one independent variable. Input for a cubic curve consists of the curve name, the 4 coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2 + C4*x**3

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

evaporativecooler:indirect:wetcoil.name: EvaporativeCooler:Indirect:WetCoil
evaporativecooler:indirect:wetcoil.memo: Indirect evaporative cooler with wetted coil, recirculating water pump, and secondary air fan. This model has no controls other than its availability schedule.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: This field is not currently used and can be left blank

fields.name: Secondary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

daylightingdevice:lightwell.name: DaylightingDevice:LightWell
daylightingdevice:lightwell.memo: Applies only to exterior windows in daylighting-controlled zones or in zones that share an interior window with a daylighting-controlled  zone. Generally used with skylights.

fields.name: Height of Well
fields.memo: Distance from Bottom of Window to Bottom of Well

zonecrossmixing.name: ZoneCrossMixing
zonecrossmixing.memo: ZoneCrossMixing exchanges an equal amount of air between two zones. Note that this statement affects the energy balance of both zones.

fields.name: Design Flow Rate Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of ventilation for this set of attributes Choices: Flow/Zone => Design Flow Rate -- simply enter Design Flow Rate Flow/Area => Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area - Value * Floor Area (zone) = Design Flow Rate Flow/Person => Flow Rate per Person - Value * #people = Design Flow Rate AirChanges/Hour => Air Changes per Hour - Value * Floor Volume (zone) adjusted for m3/s = Design Volume Flow Rate "Vdesign" in Equation is the result.

fields.name: Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
Delta Temperature
fields.memo: This field contains the constant temperature differential between source and receiving zones below which cross mixing is shutoff. This value must be greater than or equal to zero.

fields.name: Delta Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the temperature differential between source and receiving zones versus time below which cross mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the indoor temperature versus time below which cross mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the indoor temperature versus time above which cross mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Source Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the source zone dry-bulb temperature versus time below which cross mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Source Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the source zone dry-bulb temperature versus time above which cross mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time below which cross mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time above which cross mixing is shutoff.

surfacecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:.name: SurfaceContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:PressureDriven
surfacecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:.memo: Simulate generic contaminant source driven by the pressure difference across a surface.

fields.name: Generation Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Design Generation Rate Coefficient

photovoltaicperformance:simple.name: PhotovoltaicPerformance:Simple
photovoltaicperformance:simple.memo: Describes a simple model of photovoltaics that may be useful for early phase design analysis. In this model the user has direct access to the efficiency with which surfaces convert incident solar radiation to electricity and need not specify arrays of specific modules.

fields.name: Fraction of Surface Area with Active Solar Cells
Value for Cell Efficiency if Fixed
fields.memo: Efficiency = (power generated [W])/(incident solar[W])

geometrytransform.name: GeometryTransform
geometrytransform.memo: Provides a simple method of altering the footprint geometry of a model. The intent is to provide a single parameter that can be used to reshape the building description contained in the rest of the input file.

fields.name: Plane of Transform
fields.memo: only current allowed value is "XY"

fields.name: Current Aspect Ratio
fields.memo: Aspect ratio of building as described in idf

fields.name: New Aspect Ratio
fields.memo: Aspect ratio to transform to during run

windowmaterial:drape:equivalentlayer.name: WindowMaterial:Drape:EquivalentLayer
windowmaterial:drape:equivalentlayer.memo: Specifies the properties of equivalent layer drape fabric materials. Shades are considered to be perfect diffusers (all transmitted and reflected radiation is hemispherically-diffuse) independent of angle of incidence. unpleated drape fabric is treated as thin and flat layer.

fields.name: Drape Beam-Beam Solar Transmittance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: The beam-beam solar transmittance at normal incidence. This value is the same as the openness area fraction of the drape fabric. Assumed to be same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Front Side Drape Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Back Side Drape Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Front Side Drape Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar reflectance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Drape Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar reflectance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Drape Beam-Beam Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-beam visible transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum of solar radiation. Assumed same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Drape Beam-Diffuse Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse visible transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Drape Beam-Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse visible reflectance at normal incidence average over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Drape Material Infrared Transmittance
fields.memo: Long-wave transmittance of the drape fabric at zero openness fraction. Assumed same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Front Side Drape Material Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: Front side long-wave emissivity of the drape fabric at zero shade openness. Openness fraction specified above is used to calculate the effective emissivity value.

fields.name: Back Side Drape Material Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: Back side long-wave emissivity of the drape fabric at zero shade openness. Openness fraction specified above is used to calculate the effective emissivity value.

fields.name: Width of Pleated Fabric
fields.memo: Width of the pleated section of the draped fabric. If the drape fabric is unpleated or is flat, then the pleated section width is set to zero.

fields.name: Length of Pleated Fabric
fields.memo: Length of the pleated section of the draped fabric. If the drape fabric is unpleated or is flat, then the pleated section length is set to zero.

roomairsettings:underfloorairdistributio.name: RoomAirSettings:UnderFloorAirDistributionInterior
roomairsettings:underfloorairdistributio.memo: This Room Air Model is applicable to interior spaces that are served by an underfloor air distribution system. The dominant sources of heat gain should be from people, equipment, and other localized sources located in the occupied part of the room. The model should be used with caution in zones which have large heat gains or losses through exterior walls or windows or which have considerable direct solar gain. Used with RoomAirModelType = UnderFloorAirDistributionInterior.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of Zone with underfloor air distribution

fields.name: Number of Diffusers
fields.memo: Total number of diffusers in this zone

fields.name: Thermostat Height
fields.memo: Height of thermostat/temperature control sensor above floor

fields.name: Comfort Height
fields.memo: Height at which air temperature is calculated for comfort purposes

fields.name: Temperature Difference Threshold for Reporting
fields.memo: Minimum temperature difference between predicted upper and lower layer temperatures above which UFAD auxiliary outputs are calculated. These outputs are 'UF Transition Height' and 'UF Average Temp Gradient'.  They are set to zero values when the temperature difference is less than the threshold and the output 'UF Zone Is Mixed' is set to 1

fields.name: Transition Height
fields.memo: user-specified height above floor of boundary between occupied and upper subzones

fields.name: Coefficient A
fields.memo: Coefficient A in Formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2 Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient B
fields.memo: Coefficient B in Formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2 Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient C
fields.memo: Coefficient C in Formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2 Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient D
fields.memo: Coefficient D in Formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2 Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient E
fields.memo: Coefficient E in Formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2 Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

zoneinfiltration:effectiveleakagearea.name: ZoneInfiltration:EffectiveLeakageArea
zoneinfiltration:effectiveleakagearea.memo: Infiltration is specified as effective leakage area at 4 Pa, schedule fraction, stack and wind coefficients, and is a function of temperature difference and wind speed: Infiltration=FSchedule * (AL /1000) SQRT(Cs*|(Tzone-Todb)| +  Cw*WindSpd**2 )

fields.name: Effective Air Leakage Area
fields.memo: "AL" in Equation units are cm2 (square centimeters)

fields.name: Stack Coefficient
fields.memo: "Cs" in Equation

fields.name: Wind Coefficient
fields.memo: "Cw" in Equation

floor:adiabatic.name: Floor:Adiabatic
floor:adiabatic.memo: Allows for simplified entry of exterior floors ignoring ground contact or interior floors. View Factor to Ground is automatically calculated.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Floors are usually tilted 180 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: if not flat, should be lower left corner (from outside)

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: Along X Axis

fields.name: Width
fields.memo: Along Y Axis

swimmingpool:indoor.name: SwimmingPool:Indoor
swimmingpool:indoor.memo: Specifies an indoor swimming pools linked to a floor surface. The pool is assumed to cover the entire floor to which it is linked.

fields.name: Surface Name
fields.memo: Name of the floor surface where the pool is located.

fields.name: Pool Heating System Maximum Water Flow Rate
Pool Miscellaneous Equipment Power
fields.memo: Power input per pool water flow rate

airloophvac:outdoorairsystem.name: AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem
airloophvac:outdoorairsystem.memo: Outdoor air subsystem for an AirLoopHVAC. Includes an outdoor air mixing box and optional outdoor air conditioning equipment such as heat recovery, preheat, and precool coils. From the perspective of the primary air loop the outdoor air system is treated as a single component.

fields.name: Controller List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC:ControllerList object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Equipment List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem:EquipmentList object.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

meter:customdecrement.name: Meter:CustomDecrement
meter:customdecrement.memo: Used to allow users to combine specific variables and/or meters into "custom" meter configurations. To access these meters by name, one must first run a simulation to generate the RDD/MDD files and names.

chillerheater:absorption:directfired.name: ChillerHeater:Absorption:DirectFired
chillerheater:absorption:directfired.memo: Direct fired gas absorption chiller-heater using performance curves similar to DOE-2

fields.name: Heating to Cooling Capacity Ratio
fields.memo: A positive fraction that represents the ratio of the heating capacity divided by the cooling capacity at rated conditions.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Cooling Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous fuel used divided by the cooling capacity at rated conditions.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Heating Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous fuel used divided by the nominal heating capacity.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous electricity used divided by the cooling capacity at rated conditions. If the chiller is both heating and cooling only the cooling electricity is used.

fields.name: Electric Input to Heating Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous electricity used divided by the nominal heating capacity. If the chiller is both heating and cooling only the cooling electricity is used.

fields.name: Condenser Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Not required if air-cooled

fields.name: Minimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the minimum cooling output possible when operated continually at rated temperature conditions divided by the nominal cooling capacity at those same conditions.  If the load on the chiller is below this fraction the chiller will cycle.

fields.name: Maximum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the maximum cooling output possible at rated temperature conditions divided by the nominal cooling capacity at those same conditions.  If greater than 1.0, the chiller is typically thought of as capable of being overloaded.

fields.name: Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the optimal cooling output at rated temperature conditions divided by the nominal cooling capacity at those same conditions.  It represents the most desirable operating point for the chiller.

fields.name: Design Entering Condenser Water Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature of the water entering the condenser of the chiller when operating at design conditions.  This is usually based on the temperature delivered by the cooling tower in a water cooled application.

fields.name: Design Leaving Chilled Water Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature of the water leaving the evaporator of the chiller when operating at design conditions also called the chilled water supply temperature or leaving chilled water temperature.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the max flow & for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: The water flow rate at design conditions through the condenser. This field is not used for Condenser Type = AirCooled

fields.name: Design Hot Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: The water flow rate at design conditions through the heater side.

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The CoolCapFT curve represents the fraction of the cooling capacity of the chiller as it varies by temperature.  The curve is normalized so that at design conditions the value of the curve should be 1.0.  This is a biquadratic curve with the input variables being the leaving chilled water temperature and either the entering or leaving condenser water temperature.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the fuel input to the chiller at full load as it varies by temperature.  The curve is normalized so that at design conditions the value of the curve should be 1.0.  This is a biquadratic curve with the input variables being the leaving chilled water temperature and either the entering or leaving condenser water temperature.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the fuel input to the chiller as the load on the chiller varies but the operating temperatures remain at the design values. The curve is normalized so that at full load the value of the curve should be 1.0. The curve is usually linear or quadratic.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the electricity to the chiller at full load as it varies by temperature.  The curve is normalized so that at design conditions the value of the curve should be 1.0.  This is a biquadratic curve with the input variables being the leaving chilled water temperature and either the entering or leaving condenser water temperature.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the electricity to the chiller as the load on the chiller varies but the operating temperatures remain at the design values. The curve is normalized so that at full load the value of the curve should be 1.0. The curve is usually linear or quadratic.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Cooling Capacity Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents how the heating capacity of the chiller varies with cooling capacity when the chiller is simultaneous heating and cooling.  The curve is normalized so an input of 1.0 represents the nominal cooling capacity and an output of 1.0 represents the full heating capacity (see the Heating to cooling capacity ratio input) The curve is usually linear or quadratic.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Heat Output Ratio During Heating Only Operation Curve Name
fields.memo: When the chiller is operating as only a heater, this curve is used to represent the fraction of fuel used as the heating load varies.  It is normalized so that a value of 1.0 is the full heating capacity.  The curve is usually linear or quadratic and will probably be similar to a boiler curve for most chillers.

fields.name: Temperature Curve Input Variable
fields.memo: Sets the second independent variable in the three temperature dependent performance curves to either the leaving or entering condenser water temperature.  Manufacturers express the performance of their chillers using either the leaving condenser water temperature (to the tower) or the entering condenser water temperature (from the tower).

fields.name: Condenser Type
fields.memo: The condenser can either be air cooled or connected to a cooling tower.

fields.name: Chilled Water Temperature Lower Limit
fields.memo: The chilled water supply temperature below which the chiller will shut off.

fields.name: Fuel Higher Heating Value
fields.memo: Not currently used.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

groundheattransfer:basement:combldg.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:ComBldg
groundheattransfer:basement:combldg.memo: ComBldg contains the monthly average temperatures (C) and possibility of daily variation amplitude

fields.name: Daily variation sine wave amplitude
fields.memo: (Normally zero, just for checking)

output:meter:cumulative:meterfileonly.name: Output:Meter:Cumulative:MeterFileOnly
output:meter:cumulative:meterfileonly.memo: Each Output:Meter:Cumulative:MeterFileOnly command picks meters to be reported cumulatively onto the standard output file (.eso) and meter file (.mtr). Not all meters are reported in every simulation. a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Key Name
fields.memo: Form is EnergyUseType:..., e.g. Electricity:* for all Electricity meters or EndUse:..., e.g. GeneralLights:* for all General Lights Output:Meter:Cumulative:MeterFileOnly puts results on the eplusout.mtr file only

fields.name: Reporting Frequency
fields.memo: Timestep refers to the zone Timestep/Number of Timesteps in hour value RunPeriod and Environment are the same

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Rotor Type
fields.memo: allowed values are: Horizontal Axis Wind Turbine or Vertical Axis Wind Turbine

fields.name: Power Control
fields.memo: Constant power output is obtained in the last three control types when the wind speed exceeds the rated wind speed. allowed values are: Fixed Speed Fixed Pitch, Fixed Speed Variable Pitch, Variable Speed Fixed Pitch or Variable Speed Variable Pitch

fields.name: Rotor Diameter
fields.memo: This field is the diameter of the perpendicular circle of the Vertical Axis Wind Turbine system from the upright pole on the ground.

fields.name: Overall Height
fields.memo: This field is the height of the hub for the Horizontal Axis Wind Turbines and of the pole for the Vertical Axis Wind Turbines.

fields.name: Rated Power
fields.memo: This field is the nominal power at the rated wind speed. Users should input maximum power in case of Fixed Speed Fixed Pitch control type.

fields.name: Maximum Power Coefficient
fields.memo: This field should be input if the rotor type is Horizontal Axis Wind Turbine

fields.name: Height for Local Average Wind Speed
Blade Drag Coefficient
fields.memo: This field is only for Vertical Axis Wind Turbine.. The user must input this field if the rotor type is Vertical Axis Wind Turbine.

fields.name: Blade Lift Coefficient
fields.memo: This field is only for Vertical Axis Wind Turbine.. The user must input this field if the rotor type is Vertical Axis Wind Turbine.

fields.name: Power Coefficient C1
fields.memo: This field is only available for Horizontal Axis Wind Turbine. The user should input all six parameters so that the analytic approximation is assumed. The simple approximation will be assumed, if any field C1 through C6 is not input. Leave this field blank, if the manufacturer's data is unavailable so that the simple approximation will be assumed.

coilsystem:heating:dx.name: CoilSystem:Heating:DX
coilsystem:heating:dx.memo: Virtual container component that consists of a DX heating coil (heat pump) and its associated controls. This control object supports two different types of DX heating coils and may be placed directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

coolingtower:variablespeed:merkel.name: CoolingTower:VariableSpeed:Merkel
coolingtower:variablespeed:merkel.memo: This tower model is based on Merkel's theory, which is also the basis for the tower model in ASHRAE's HVAC1 Toolkit. The open wet cooling tower is modeled as a counter flow heat exchanger with a variable-speed fan drawing air through the tower (induced-draft configuration). For a multi-cell tower, the capacity and air/water flow rate inputs are for the entire tower.

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower water outlet node

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define tower thermal performance by specifying the tower UA, the Design Air Flow Rate and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the tower nominal capacity

fields.name: Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio
Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal tower capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature, with the tower fan operating at Design Air Flow Rate (full speed). Design water flow rate is as set in Design Water Flow Rate per Unit of Nominal Capacity. Nominal tower capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Free Convection Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: required field when performance method is NominalCapacity Tower capacity in free convection regime with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate is as set in Design Water Flow Rate per Unit of Nominal Capacity. Tower free convection capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25)  gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions

fields.name: Free Convection Nominal Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: Design Water Flow Rate per Unit of Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous is set to autocalculate and performance input method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This is the air flow rate at full fan speed

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate Per Unit of Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous is set to autocalculate When field is left blank the default scaling factor is adjusted for elevation to increase volume flow at altitude When field has a value the scaling factor is used without adjusting for elevation

fields.name: Minimum Air Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the minimum air flow rate ratio. This is typically determined by the variable speed drive that controls the fan motor speed. Valid entries are from 0.1 to 0.5.

fields.name: Design Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power at high speed

fields.name: Design Fan Power Per Unit of Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous is set to autocalculate [W/W] Watts of fan power per Watt of tower nominal capacity

fields.name: Fan Power Modifier Function of Air Flow Rate Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used cubic curve = a + b*AFR + c*AFR**2 + d*AFR**3 quartic curve = a + b*AFR + c*AFR**2 + d*AFR**3 + e*AFR**4 x = AFR = Ratio of current operating air flow rate to Design Air Flow Rate

fields.name: Free Convection Regime Air Flow Rate
Free Convection Regime Air Flow Rate Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: required field when performance method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate when performance method is NominalCapacity the program will solve for this UA

fields.name: Free Convection Regime U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: required field when performance input method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate Leave field blank if performance input method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Free Convection U-Factor Times Area Value Sizing Factor
fields.memo: required field when performance input method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the performance input method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate

fields.name: U-Factor Times Area Modifier Function of Air Flow Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: This curve describes how tower's design UA changes with variable air flow rate Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used cubic curve = a + b*AFR + c*AFR**2 + d*AFR**3 quartic curve = a + b*AFR + c*AFR**2 + d*AFR**3 + e*AFR**4 x = AFR = Ratio of current operating air flow rate to Design Air Flow Rate

fields.name: U-Factor Times Area Modifier Function of Wetbulb Temperature Difference Curve Name
fields.memo: curve describes how tower UA changes with outdoor air wet-bulb temperature difference from design wet-bulb Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used cubic curve = a + b*DeltaWB + c*DeltaWB**2 + d*DeltaWB**3 quartic curve = a + b*DeltaWB + c*DeltaWB**2 + d*DeltaWB**3 + e*DeltaWB**4 x = DeltaWB = (design wet-bulb temperature in C - current wet-bulb temperature in C) where design wet-bulb temperature of entering air is 25.56C (78F)

fields.name: U-Factor Times Area Modifier Function of Water Flow Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: curve describes how tower UA changes with the flow rate of condenser water through the tower Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used cubic curve = a + b*WFR + c*WFR**2 + d*WFR**3 quartic curve = a + b*WFR + c*WFR**2 + d*WFR**3 + e*WFR**4 x = WFR = Ratio of current operating water flow rate to Design Water Flow Rate

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air dry-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air wet-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the approach temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design range temperature. Design approach temp = outlet water temperature minus inlet air wet-bulb temperature at design conditions. Autosized to 3.9 deltaC.

fields.name: Design Range Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the range temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design approach temperature. Design range = inlet water temperature minus outlet water temperature at design conditions. Autosized to 5.5 deltaC.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when water is not flowing through the tower.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Evaporation Loss Factor
fields.memo: Rate of water evaporated from the cooling tower and lost to the outdoor air [%/K] Evaporation loss is calculated as percentage of the circulating condenser water rate Value entered here is percent-per-degree K of temperature drop in the condenser water Typical values are from 0.15 to 0.27 [%/K].

fields.name: Drift Loss Percent
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a percentage of circulating condenser water flow rate Typical values are between 0.002 and 0.2% The default value is 0.008%

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the cooling tower. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the tower in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. Typical values for tower operation are 3 to 5.  The default value is 3.

fields.name: Blowdown Makeup Water Usage Schedule Name
fields.memo: Makeup water usage due to blowdown results from occasionally draining some amount of water in the tower basin to purge scale or other contaminants to reduce their concentration in order to maintain an acceptable level of water quality. Schedule values should reflect water usage in m3/s.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

fields.name: Cell Minimum  Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable minimal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Cell Maximum Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable maximal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

roomair:temperaturepattern:surfacemappin.name: RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:SurfaceMapping
roomair:temperaturepattern:surfacemappin.memo: Defines a distribution pattern for the air temperatures adjacent to individual surfaces. This allows controlling the adjacent air temperature on a surface-by-surface basis rather than by height. This allows modeling different adjacent air temperatures on the opposite sides of the zone. Used in combination with RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:UserDefined.

fields.name: Control Integer for Pattern Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: reference this entry in schedule

fields.name: Thermostat Offset
fields.memo: = (Temp at thermostat- Mean Air Temp)

fields.name: Return Air Offset
fields.memo: = (Tleaving - Mean Air Temp ) deg C

fields.name: Exhaust Air Offset
fields.memo: = (Texhaust - Mean Air Temp) deg C

generator:fuelcell:inverter.name: Generator:FuelCell:Inverter
generator:fuelcell:inverter.memo: Used to describe the power condition unit subsystem of a fuel cell power generator. This object models an inverter system contained within a fuel cell system that converts from direct current (DC) to alternating current (AC).

fields.name: Efficiency Function of DC Power Curve Name

coil:heating:desuperheater.name: Coil:Heating:Desuperheater
coil:heating:desuperheater.memo: Desuperheater air heating coil. The heating energy provided by this coil is reclaimed from the superheated refrigerant gas leaving a compressor and does not impact the performance of the compressor. If the coil is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list, then it is controlled on leaving air temperature and the Temperature Setpoint Node Name must be specified. If the coil is contained within another component such as a unitary system, then the coil is controlled by the parent component and the setpoint node name is not entered.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: Required if coil is temperature controlled. Temperature-based control requires the use of a SetpointManager object

fields.name: Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: parasitic electric load associated with the desuperheater coil operation such as solenoid valves, etc.

photovoltaicperformance:equivalentone-di.name: PhotovoltaicPerformance:EquivalentOne-Diode
photovoltaicperformance:equivalentone-di.memo: Describes the performance characteristics of Photovoltaic (PV) modules to be modeled using an equivalent one-diode circuit.  This model is also known as the 4- or 5-parameter TRNSYS model for photovoltaics.

fields.name: Active Area
fields.memo: The total power output of the array is determined by the number of modules (see above).  The Active Area is only used to calculate the PV Array Efficiency output variable.

fields.name: Module Current at Maximum Power
fields.memo: Single module current at the maximum power point and reference conditions.  Module Current, Module Voltage, Number of Modules in Parallel and Number of Modules in Series determine the maximum power output of the array.

fields.name: Module Voltage at Maximum Power
fields.memo: Single module voltage at the maximum power point and reference conditions.  Module Current, Module Voltage, Number of Modules in Parallel and Number of Modules in Series determine the maximum power output of the array.

fields.name: Temperature Coefficient of Short Circuit Current
Temperature Coefficient of Open Circuit Voltage
Nominal Operating Cell Temperature Test Ambient Temperature
Nominal Operating Cell Temperature Test Cell Temperature
Nominal Operating Cell Temperature Test Insolation

surfaceproperty:solarincidentinside.name: SurfaceProperty:SolarIncidentInside
surfaceproperty:solarincidentinside.memo: Used to provide incident solar radiation on the inside of the surface. Reference surface-construction pair and if that pair is used in a simulation, then program will use value provided in schedule instead of calculating it.

fields.name: Inside Surface Incident Sun Solar Radiation Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in schedule are expected to be in W/m2

groundheatexchanger:responsefactors.name: GroundHeatExchanger:ResponseFactors
groundheatexchanger:responsefactors.memo: Response factor definitions from third-party tool, commonly referred to a "g-functions"

connector:splitter.name: Connector:Splitter
connector:splitter.memo: Split one air/water stream into N outlet streams.  Branch names cannot be duplicated within a single Splitter list.

roomairsettings:airflownetwork.name: RoomAirSettings:AirflowNetwork
roomairsettings:airflownetwork.memo: RoomAir modeling using Airflow pressure network solver

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of Zone being described. Any existing zone name

electricloadcenter:transformer.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Transformer
electricloadcenter:transformer.memo: a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Transformer Usage
fields.memo: A transformer can be used to transfer electric energy from utility grid to building (PowerInFromGrid)or from building on-site generation to the grid (PowerOutToGrid) or within a load center to match generation to the facility service main panel (LoadCenterPowerConditioning)

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter name of zone to receive transformer losses as heat if blank then transformer losses are dissipated to outdoors

fields.name: Rated Capacity
fields.memo: the unit is VA, instead of kVA as usually shown on transformer nameplates.

fields.name: Phase
fields.memo: Must be single or three phase transformer. NOT used in the current model.

fields.name: Conductor Material
fields.memo: Winding material used by the transformer.

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define transformer performance by specifying load and no load losses at rated conditions or nameplate efficiency and maximum efficiency

fields.name: Rated No Load Loss
fields.memo: Only required when RatedLosses is the performance input method

fields.name: Rated Load Loss
fields.memo: Only required when RatedLosses is the performance input method

fields.name: Nameplate Efficiency
fields.memo: Only required when NominalEfficiency is the performance input method

fields.name: Per Unit Load for Nameplate Efficiency
fields.memo: Percentage of the rated capacity at which the nameplate efficiency is defined Only required when NominalEfficiency is the performance input method

fields.name: Reference Temperature for Nameplate Efficiency
fields.memo: Conductor operating temperature at which the nameplate efficiency is defined Only required when NominalEfficiency is the performance input method

fields.name: Per Unit Load for Maximum Efficiency
fields.memo: Percentage of the rate capacity at which the maximum efficiency is obtained Only required when NominalEfficiency is the performance input method

fields.name: Consider Transformer Loss for Utility Cost
fields.memo: Only required when the transformer is used for power in from the utility grid

curve:quadlinear.name: Curve:QuadLinear
curve:quadlinear.memo: Linear curve with four independent variables. Input for the linear curve consists of a curve name, the two coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*w + C3*x + C4*y + C5*z

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

door:interzone.name: Door:Interzone
door:interzone.memo: Allows for simplified entry of interzone (opaque interior) doors (adjacent to other zones).

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Building Surface Name
fields.memo: Name of Surface (Wall, usually) the Door is on (i.e., Base Surface) Door assumes the azimuth and tilt angles of the surface it is on.

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Specify a surface name in an adjacent zone for known interior doors. Specify a zone name of an adjacent zone to automatically generate the interior door in the adjacent zone. a blank field will set up a Window in an adjacent zone (same zone as adjacent to base surface)

fields.name: Multiplier
fields.memo: Used only for Surface Type = WINDOW, GLASSDOOR or DOOR Non-integer values will be truncated to integer

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Door starting coordinate is specified relative to the Base Surface origin.

fields.name: Starting Z Coordinate
fields.memo: How far up the wall the Door starts. (in 2-d, this would be a Y Coordinate)

airloophvac:unitaryheatpump:airtoair.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatPump:AirToAir
airloophvac:unitaryheatpump:airtoair.memo: Unitary heat pump system, heating and cooling, single-speed with supply fan, direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, DX heating coil (air-to-air heat pump), and supplemental heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. A schedule value greater than zero (usually 1 is used) indicates that the unit is available to operate as needed. A value less than or equal to zero (usually zero is used) denotes that the unit must be off.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to the fan's maximum flow rate. Only used when fan operating mode is continuous (disregarded for cycling fan mode). This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required (i.e., the DX coil compressor and supplemental heating coil are off). If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works with continuous fan operating mode (i.e. fan operating mode schedule values are greater than 0 or the fan operating mode schedule name field is left blank).

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the fan object

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with Coil:Heating:DX:SingleSpeed or Coil:Heating:DX:VariableSpeed or CoilSystem:IntegratedHeatPump:AirSource

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the DX heating coil object

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with Coil:Cooling:DX:SingleSpeed or CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted or Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableSpeed or CoilSystem:IntegratedHeatPump:AirSource

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the DX cooling coil object

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the supplemental heating coil object

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature from Supplemental Heater
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Supplemental Heater Operation
Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: A fan operating mode schedule value of 0 indicates cycling fan mode (supply air fan cycles on and off in tandem with the cooling or heating coil). Any other schedule value indicates continuous fan mode (supply air fan operates continuously regardless of cooling or heating coil operation). Leaving this schedule name blank will default to cycling fan mode for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load.  Valid only with cooling coil type CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted. This control mode allows the heat exchanger to be turned on and off based on the zone dehumidification requirements. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required. CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint. as required to meet the humidity setpoint.  Valid with all cooling coil types. When a heat exchanger assisted Cooling coil is used, the heat exchanger is locked on at all times. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required.

wall:interzone.name: Wall:Interzone
wall:interzone.memo: Allows for simplified entry of interzone walls (walls between zones).

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone for the inside of the surface

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Specify a surface name in an adjacent zone for known interior walls. Specify a zone name of an adjacent zone to automatically generate the interior wall in the adjacent zone.

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of wall (S=180,N=0,E=90,W=270)

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Walls are usually tilted 90 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Starting (x,y,z) coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Wall

hvactemplate:system:constantvolume.name: HVACTemplate:System:ConstantVolume
hvactemplate:system:constantvolume.memo: Constant Air Volume air loop with optional chilled water cooling coil, optional heating coil and optional preheat.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on;  Schedule is used in availability manager and fan scheduling. Also see "Night Cycle Control" field.

fields.name: Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Control Zone name
fields.memo: name of the HVACTemplate:ZoneConstantVolume object that contains the cooling thermostat when Cooling Coil Setpoint Control Type = ControlZone

fields.name: Cooling Coil Design Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control. Defaults are 15.6C (60F) at 15.6C (60F) to 12.8C (55F) at 23.3C (74F)

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Coil Control Zone name
fields.memo: name of the HVACTemplate:ZoneConstantVolume object that contains the heating thermostat

fields.name: Heating Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control. Defaults are 15.6C (60F) at 15.6C (60F) to 12.8C (55F) at 23.3C (74F)

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Preheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Preheat Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Preheat Coil Setpoint Schedule Name specified.

fields.name: Preheat Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Gas Preheat Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the Minimum Outdoor Air Flow Rate If blank, multiplier is always one

fields.name: Economizer Upper Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Lower Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature below which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Upper Enthalpy Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor enthalpy above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Night Cycle Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Applicable only if Night Cycle Control is Cycle On Control Zone.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100) Ignored if Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint above. Schedule values must be in percent relative humidity (0 to 100).

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100). Ignored if Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint above.Schedule values must be in percent relative humidity (0 to 100).

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction

evaporativecooler:indirect:researchspeci.name: EvaporativeCooler:Indirect:ResearchSpecial
evaporativecooler:indirect:researchspeci.memo: Indirect evaporative cooler with user-specified effectiveness (can represent rigid pad or wetted coil), recirculating water pump, and secondary air fan. This model is controlled to meet the primary air outlet temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Cooler Wetbulb Design Effectiveness
fields.memo: wet operation effectiveness with respect to wetbulb depression this is the nominal design wetbulb effectiveness at design air flow rates and water rate

fields.name: Wetbulb Effectiveness Flow Ratio Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: this curve modifies the wetbulb effectiveness in the previous field (eff_wb_design) by multiplying the value by the result of this curve, eff_wb = eff_wb_design * func(HXFlowRatio) x = HXFlowRatio = sum of the primary and secondary flow rates divided by the sum of the design flow rates. If this input field is left blank, constant cooler wetbulb effectiveness is assumed. Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used: Curve:Linear, Curve:Quadratic, Curve:Cubic, Curve:Quartic, Curve:Exponent, Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal, Curve:Sigmoid, Curve:RectuangularHyperbola1, Curve:RectangularHyperbola2, Curve:ExponentialDecay, Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay, Table:OneIndependentVariable

fields.name: Cooler Drybulb Design Effectiveness
fields.memo: dry operation effectiveness with respect to drybulb temperature difference this is the nominal design dryblub effectiveness at design air flow rates, no evaporation water active

fields.name: Drybulb Effectiveness Flow Ratio Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: this curve modifies the drybulb effectiveness in the previous field (eff_db_design) by multiplying the value by the result of this curve, eff_db = eff_db_design * f(HXFlowRatio) x = HXFlowRatio = sum of the primary and secondary flow rates divided by the sum of the design flow rates. If this input field is left blank, constant cooler drybulb effectiveness is assumed. Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used: Curve:Linear, Curve:Quadratic, Curve:Cubic, Curve:Quartic, Curve:Exponent, Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal, Curve:Sigmoid, Curve:RectuangularHyperbola1, Curve:RectangularHyperbola2, Curve:ExponentialDecay, Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay, Table:OneIndependentVariable

fields.name: Recirculating Water Pump Design Power
fields.memo: This is the nominal design pump power of water recirculation and spray for evaporation at design air flow rates and cooler design effectiveness

fields.name: Water Pump Power Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is used when the previous field is set to autosize. The pump power is scaled with Secondary Air Design Air Flow Rate. This value was backed out from inputs in energy plus example files. Average Pump Power sizing factor was estimated from pump power and secondary air design flow rates inputs from energyplus example files is about 90.0 [W/(m3/s)] (=90.0 ~ Pump Power / Secondary Air Design Flow Rate). The factor ranges from 55.0 to 150.0 [W/(m3/s)] were noted. The pump power can be sized to zero by setting this factor to zero.

fields.name: Water Pump Power Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: this curve modifies the pump power in the previous field by multiplying the design power by the result of this curve. x = ff = flow fraction on the secondary side, secondary air flow rate during operation divided by Secondary Air Design Air Flow Rate. If this input field is left blank, pump power is assumed to be proportional to part load ratio. Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used: Curve:Linear, Curve:Quadratic, Curve:Cubic, Curve:Quartic, Curve:Exponent, Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal, Curve:Sigmoid, Curve:RectuangularHyperbola1, Curve:RectangularHyperbola2, Curve:ExponentialDecay, Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay, Table:OneIndependentVariable

fields.name: Secondary Air Flow Scaling Factor
fields.memo: This field is used when the previous field is set to autoize.  The Primary Design Air Flow Rate is scaled using this factor to calculate the secondary design air flow rate.

fields.name: Secondary Air Fan Design Power
fields.memo: This is the fan design power at Secondary Design Air Flow Rate. This is the nominal design power at full speed.

fields.name: Secondary Air Fan Sizing Specific Power
fields.memo: This field is used when the previous field is set to autosize. The fan power is scaled with Secondary Air Design Flow Rate. The default value is estimated from 125 Pa fan total pressure and fan total efficiency of 50.0% (250.0 = 125/0.5).

fields.name: Secondary Air Fan Power Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: this curve modifies the design fan power in the previous field by multiplying the value by the result of this curve.  It should have a value of 1.0 at a x = 1.0. x = ff = flow fraction on the secondary side, secondary air flow rate during operation divided by Secondary Air Design Air Flow Rate. If this input field is left blank, the secondary fan power is assumed to be proportional to part load ratio. Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used: Curve:Linear, Curve:Quadratic, Curve:Cubic, Curve:Quartic, Curve:Exponent, Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal, Curve:Sigmoid, Curve:RectuangularHyperbola1, Curve:RectangularHyperbola2, Curve:ExponentialDecay, Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay, Table:OneIndependentVariable

fields.name: Drift Loss Fraction
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a fraction of evaporated water flow rate. If this input field is left blank, then zero drift loss is assumed.

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the evaporative cooler. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the cooler in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. A typical value is 3.  If left blank then there is no blowdown.

fields.name: Evaporative Operation Minimum Limit Secondary Air Drybulb Temperature
fields.memo: This input field value defines the secondary air inlet node drybulb temperature limits in degreeCelsius. When the secondary side entering air dry bulb temperature drops below this limit, then the evaporative cooler operation mode changes to dry heat exchanger. Users specify their own limits. If this field is left blank, then there is no drybulb temperature lower limit for evaporative cooler operation. If operating range control is desired then this input field and the next two input fields should be specified or all the three should be left blank or left out. If no minimum drybulb temperature limit is desired while there are maximum drybulb and wetbulb temperature limits then specify very low minimum temperature limit value (e.g. -99.0C).

fields.name: Evaporative Operation Maximum Limit Outdoor Wetbulb Temperature
fields.memo: This input field value defines the secondary air inlet node wetbulb temperature limits in degree Celsius. When the secondary side entering air wet bulb temperature exceeds this limit, then the evaporative cooler urns off and does not attempt to do any cooling. If this field is left blank, then there is no wetbulb temperature upper limit for evaporative cooler wet operation mode. If this input field is left blank then, the previous and the next input fields should also be left blank. If no maximum wetbulb temperature limits is desired while there are minimum drybulb and maximum drybulb upper temperature limits then specify very high maximum wetbulb temperature limit value (e.g. 99.0 C).

fields.name: Dry Operation Maximum Limit Outdoor Drybulb Temperature
fields.memo: This input field value defines the secondary air inlet node drybulb temperature limits in degree Celsius. When the secondary side entering air drybulb temperature exceeds this limit, then the evaporative cooler will not run in dry operation mode or may be turned off depending on its wetbulb temperature. If this field is left blank, then there is no drybulb temperature maximum limit for evaporative cooler operation. If this input field is left blank then, the previous and the next input fields should also be left blank. If no maximum drybulb temperature limit is desired while there are minimum drybulb and maximum wetbulb upper temperature limits then specify very high maximum drybulb temperature limit value (e.g. 99.0 C).

faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:outdo.name: FaultModel:TemperatureSensorOffset:OutdoorAir
faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:outdo.memo: This object describes outdoor air temperature sensor offset

coilsystem:cooling:dx.name: CoilSystem:Cooling:DX
coilsystem:cooling:dx.memo: Virtual container component that consists of a DX cooling coil and its associated controls. This control object supports several different types of DX cooling coils and may be placed directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil System Inlet Node Name
DX Cooling Coil System Outlet Node Name
DX Cooling Coil System Sensor Node Name
Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load. If no sensible load exists, and Run on Latent Load = Yes, and a latent load exists, the unit will operate to meet the latent load. Valid only with Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoStageWithHumidityControlMode or CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted. CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint. as required to meet the humidity setpoint. Valid for all coil types. For all dehumidification controls, the max humidity setpoint on the Sensor Node is used. SetpointManager:SingleZone:Humidity:Maximum, SetpointManager:MultiZone:Humidity:Maximum, or SetpointManager:MultiZone:MaximumHumidity:Average, and SetpointManager:OutdoorAirPretreat (optional) objects.

fields.name: Run on Sensible Load
fields.memo: If Yes, unit will run if there is a sensible load. If No, unit will not run if there is only a sensible load. Dehumidification controls will be active if specified.

fields.name: Run on Latent Load
fields.memo: If Yes, unit will run if there is a latent load. even if there is no sensible load. If No, unit will not run only if there is a latent load. Dehumidification controls will be active if specified.

fields.name: Use Outdoor Air DX Cooling Coil
fields.memo: This input field is designed for use with DX cooling coils with low air flow to capacity ratio range (100 - 300 cfm/ton). Typical application is 100% dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Other air loop or zone HVAC systems with low flow to capacity ratio range may also use this input field.  If Yes, the DX cooling coil runs as 100% DOAS DX coil or low flow to capacity ratio range. If No, the DX cooling coil runs as a regular DX coil. If left blank the default is regular DX coil.

fields.name: Outdoor Air DX Cooling Coil Leaving Minimum Air Temperature
fields.memo: DX cooling coil leaving minimum air temperature defines the minimum DX cooling coil leaving air temperature that should be maintained to avoid frost formation. This input field is optional and only used along with the input field above.

coil:waterheating:airtowaterheatpump:var.name: Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:VariableSpeed
coil:waterheating:airtowaterheatpump:var.memo: vairlable-speed Heat pump water heater (VSHPWH) heating coil, air-to-water direct-expansion (DX) system which includes a variable-speed water heating coil, evaporator air coil, evaporator fan, electric compressor, and water pump. Part of a WaterHeater:HeatPump system.

fields.name: Nominal Speed Level
fields.memo: must be lower than or equal to the highest speed number

fields.name: Rated Water Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Water Heating capacity at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump heat.

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Inlet Air Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Evaporator inlet air dry-bulb temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Evaporator inlet air wet-bulb temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Condenser Inlet Water Temperature
fields.memo: Condenser inlet water temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Evaporator air flow rate corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR). Default is 5.035E-5 m3/s/W (31.25 cfm/MBH) of rated heating capacity when autocalculated.

fields.name: Rated Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Condenser water flow rate corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR). Default is 4.487E-8 m3/s/W (0.208 gpm/MBH) of rated heating capacity when autocalculated. A warning message will be issued if the ratio of Rated Condenser Water Flow Rate to Heating Capacity is less than 1.79405E-8 m3/s/W (0.083 gpm/MBH) or greater than 8.97024E-8 m3/s/W (0.417 gpm/MBH), but the simulation will continue.

fields.name: Evaporator Fan Power Included in Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the evaporator fan power is included in the rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of compressor electric power.

fields.name: Condenser Pump Power Included in Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the condenser pump power is included in the rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of compressor electric power.

fields.name: Condenser Pump Heat Included in Rated Heating Capacity and Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the condenser pump heat is included in the rated heating capacity and rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of water heating capacity.

fields.name: Fraction of Condenser Pump Heat to Water
fields.memo: Fraction of pump heat transferred to the condenser water. The pump is assumed to be located downstream of the condenser.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node from which the DX coil draws its inlet air.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node to which the DX coil sends its outlet air.

fields.name: Condenser Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node from which the DX coil condenser draws its inlet water. This name should match the source side outlet node name in the associated water heater tank object.

fields.name: Condenser Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node to which the DX coil condenser sends its outlet water. This name should match the source side inlet node name in the associated water heater tank object.

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Capacity
fields.memo: The compressor crankcase heater only operates when the dry-bulb temperature of air surrounding the compressor is below the Maximum Ambient Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation and the DX coil is off.  The ambient temperature surrounding the compressor is set by the WaterHeater:HeatPump parent object (field Compressor Location).

fields.name: Maximum Ambient Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
fields.memo: The compressor crankcase heater only operates when the dry-bulb temperature of air surrounding the compressor is below the Maximum Outdoor Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation and the unit is off. The ambient temperature surrounding the compressor is set by the WaterHeater:HeatPump parent object (field Compressor Location).

fields.name: Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects
fields.memo: Determines temperature type for heating capacity curves and heating COP curves. This input determines whether the inlet air dry-bulb or wet-bulb temperature is used to evaluate these curves.

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: Table:OneIndependentVariable object can also be used Part Load Fraction Correlation (function of part load ratio) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(PLR) + c(PLR)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(PLR) + c(PLR)^2 + d(PLR)^3. PLR = part load ratio (heating delivered/steady state heating capacity). Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in part load ratio.

fields.name: Rated Water Heating Capacity at Speed 1
fields.memo: Heating capacity at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump heat.

fields.name: Rated Water Heating COP at Speed 1
fields.memo: Heating coefficient of performance at the rated inlet air and water temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump power and evaporator fan power (see fields below).

fields.name: Rated Sensible Heat Ratio at Speed 1
fields.memo: Gross air-side sensible heat ratio at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Sensible heat ratio equals gross sensible cooling capacity divided by gross total cooling capacity. Rated SHR (gross) should not include evaporator fan heat, only sensible cooling and dehumidification by the coil alone.

fields.name: Speed 1 Reference Unit Rated Air Flow Rate
Speed 1 Reference Unit Rated Water Flow Rate
Speed 1 Reference Unit Water Pump Input Power At Rated Conditions
Speed 1 Total WH Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Table:TwoIndependentVariables object can also be used curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*ewt + e*ewt**2 + f*wb*ewt wb = entering wet-bulb temperature or dry bulb temperature upon selection (C) ewt = water entering temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Speed 1 Total WH Capacity Function of Air Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Table:OneIndependentVariable object can also be used quadratic curve = a + b*ffa + c*ffa**2 cubic curve = a + b*ffa + c*ffa**2 + d*ffa**3 ffa = Fraction of the full load Air Flow
