surfaceproperty:localenvironment.name: SurfaceProperty:LocalEnvironment
surfaceproperty:localenvironment.memo: This object defines the local environment properties of an exterior surface. One or more environment properties have to be defined and linked to the exterior surface.

fields.name: Exterior Surface Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an exterior surface object

fields.name: External Shading Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Schedule object

fields.name: Surrounding Surfaces Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a SurfaceProperty:SurroundingSurfaces object

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an OutdoorAir:Node object

curve:rectangularhyperbola2.name: Curve:RectangularHyperbola2
curve:rectangularhyperbola2.memo: Rectangular hyperbola type 2 curve with one independent variable. Input consists of the curve name, the three coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = ((C1*x)/(C2+x))+(C3*x)

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

airterminal:singleduct:uncontrolled.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Uncontrolled
airterminal:singleduct:uncontrolled.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, constant volume, no controls other than on/off schedule.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will adjust flow to meet this outdoor air requirement and no more. Load is still "Uncontrolled." If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone, as for demand controlled ventilation. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow.

fields.name: Per Person Ventilation Rate Mode
fields.memo: CurrentOccupancy models demand controlled ventilation using the current number of people DesignOccupancy uses the total Number of People in the zone and is constant

fields.name: Design Specification Air Terminal Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: This optional field is the name of a DesignSpecification:AirTerminal:Sizing object which specifies sizing adjustments to be made for this terminal unit.

zonecontrol:thermostat:stageddualsetpoin.name: ZoneControl:Thermostat:StagedDualSetpoint
zonecontrol:thermostat:stageddualsetpoin.memo: Define the Thermostat StagedDualSetpoint settings for a zone or list of zones. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Number of Heating Stages
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for heating temperature offset

fields.name: Stage 1 Heating Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The heating temperature offset is used to determine heating stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the heating setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is less than Stage 1 value and greater than Stage 2 value, the stage number is 1.

fields.name: Stage 2 Heating Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The heating temperature offset is used to determine heating stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the heating setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is less than Stage 2 value and greater than Stage 3 value, the stage number is 2. The value of this field has to be less the value at the previous field.

fields.name: Stage 3 Heating Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The heating temperature offset is used to determine heating stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the heating setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is less than Stage 3 value and greater than Stage 4 value, the stage number is 3. The value of this field has to be less the value at the previous field.

fields.name: Stage 4 Heating Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The heating temperature offset is used to determine heating stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the heating setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is less than Stage 4 value, the stage number is 4. The value of this field has to be less the value at the previous field.

fields.name: Number of Cooling Stages
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for cooling temperature offset

fields.name: Cooling Temperature Setpoint Base Schedule Name
Stage 1 Cooling Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The cooling temperature offset is used to determine cooling stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the cooling setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is greater than Stage 1 value and less than Stage 2 value, the stage number is 1.

fields.name: Stage 2 Cooling Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The cooling temperature offset is used to determine cooling stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the cooling setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is greater than Stage 2 value and less than Stage 3 value, the stage number is 2. The value of this field has to be greater than the value at the previous field.

fields.name: Stage 3 Cooling Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The cooling temperature offset is used to determine cooling stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the cooling setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is greater than Stage 3 value and less than Stage 4 value, the stage number is 3. The value of this field has to be greater than the value at the previous field.

fields.name: Stage 4 Cooling Temperature Offset
fields.memo: The cooling temperature offset is used to determine cooling stage number for multi stage equipment. When the temperature difference of the cooling setpoint and the controlled zone temperature at previous time step is greater than Stage 4 value, the stage number is 4. The value of this field has to be greater than the value at the previous field.

shading:overhang:projection.name: Shading:Overhang:Projection
shading:overhang:projection.memo: Overhangs are typically flat shading surfaces that reference a window or door.

fields.name: Right extension from Window/Door Width
fields.memo: N3 + N4 + Window/Door Width is Overhang Length

fields.name: Depth as Fraction of Window/Door Height

surfacecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:.name: SurfaceContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:BoundaryLayerDiffusion
surfacecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:.memo: Simulate generic contaminant source driven by the boundary layer diffusion controlled model.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Initial Emission Rate. When the value is equal to 1.0, the time will be reset to zero.

fields.name: Henry Adsorption Constant or Partition Coefficient

electricequipment.name: ElectricEquipment
electricequipment.memo: Sets internal gains for electric equipment in the zone. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in schedule should be fraction applied to design level of electric equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Design Level Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of electric equipment for this set of attributes Choices: EquipmentLevel => Equipment Level -- simply enter watts of equipment Watts/Area => Watts per Zone Floor Area -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Floor Area = Equipment Level Watts/Person => Watts per Person -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Occupants = Equipment Level

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

coil:userdefined.name: Coil:UserDefined
coil:userdefined.memo: Defines a generic air system component for custom modeling using Energy Management System or External Interface

fields.name: Overall Model Simulation Program Calling Manager Name
Model Setup and Sizing Program Calling Manager Name
Air Connection 1 Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Inlet air for primary air stream

fields.name: Air Connection 1 Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Outlet air for primary air stream

fields.name: Air Connection 2 Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Inlet air for secondary air stream

fields.name: Air Connection 2 Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Outlet air for secondary air stream

fields.name: Supply Inlet Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: Water use storage tank for alternate source of water consumed by device

fields.name: Collection Outlet Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: Water use storage tank for collection of condensate by device

fields.name: Ambient Zone Name
fields.memo: Used for modeling device losses to surrounding zone

airflownetwork:multizone:component:horiz.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:HorizontalOpening
airflownetwork:multizone:component:horiz.memo: This object specifies the properties of air flow through a horizontal opening

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient When Opening is Closed
fields.memo: Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference. Enter the coefficient used in the following equation: Mass flow rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when opening is closed.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent When Opening is Closed
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the following equation: Mass flow rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when opening is closed.

fields.name: Sloping Plane Angle
fields.memo: Sloping plane angle = 90 is equivalent to fully open.

fields.name: Discharge Coefficient
fields.memo: The Discharge Coefficient indicates the fractional effectiveness for air flow through the opening at that Opening Factor.

hvactemplate:zone:fancoil.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:FanCoil
hvactemplate:zone:fancoil.memo: 4 pipe fan coil unit with optional outdoor air.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Dedicated Outdoor Air System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:DedicatedOutdoorAir object if this zone is served by a separate dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Leave field blank if no DOAS serves this zone.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Cooling Coil Design Setpoint (above) TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Heating Coil Design Setpoint (above) TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Capacity Control Method
fields.memo: If this field is left blank, it will default to CyclingFan if a Dedicated Outdoor Air System is specified (see above), otherwise it will default to ConstantFanVariableFlow.

fields.name: Low Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio
Medium Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Medium Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio should be greater than Low Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio

fields.name: Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value of schedule multiplies maximum outdoor air flow rate This schedule is ignored if this zone is served by an HVACTemplate dedicated outdoor air system.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

availabilitymanager:hightemperatureturno.name: AvailabilityManager:HighTemperatureTurnOn
availabilitymanager:hightemperatureturno.memo: Overrides fan/pump schedules depending on temperature at sensor node.

output:sqlite.name: Output:SQLite
output:sqlite.memo: Output from EnergyPlus can be written to an SQLite format file.

electricloadcenter:generators.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Generators
electricloadcenter:generators.memo: List of electric power generators to include in the simulation including the name and type of each generators along with availability schedule, rated power output, and thermal-to-electrical power ratio.

site:spectrumdata.name: Site:SpectrumData
site:spectrumdata.memo: Spectrum Data Type is followed by up to 107 sets of normal-incidence measured values of [wavelength, spectrum] for wavelengths covering the solar (0.25 to 2.5 microns) or visible spectrum (0.38 to 0.78 microns)

surfaceproperty:exposedfoundationperimet.name: SurfaceProperty:ExposedFoundationPerimeter
surfaceproperty:exposedfoundationperimet.memo: Defines the perimeter of a foundation floor that is exposed to the exterior environment through the floor. User may either define the total exposed perimeter, fraction of perimeter exposed or individually define which segments of the floor surface perimeter are exposed.

fields.name: Exposed Perimeter Calculation Method
fields.memo: Choices: TotalExposedPerimeter => total exposed perimeter in meters ExposedPerimeterFraction => fraction of total perimeter that is exposed. Value * Fraction = Total exposed perimeter BySegment => define whether the segment between each set of consecutive vertices of the floor surface is exposed. SUM(exposed segement lengths) = Total exposed perimeter

faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:chill.name: FaultModel:TemperatureSensorOffset:ChillerSupplyWater
faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:chill.memo: This object describes fault of chiller supply water temperature sensor offset

fields.name: Chiller Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of a chiller object

fields.name: Chiller Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a chiller object

evaporativefluidcooler:singlespeed.name: EvaporativeFluidCooler:SingleSpeed
evaporativefluidcooler:singlespeed.memo: This model is based on Merkel's theory, which is also the basis for the cooling tower model in EnergyPlus. The Evaporative fluid cooler is modeled as a counter flow heat exchanger.

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Fluid Cooler water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Fluid Cooler water outlet node

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define fluid cooler thermal performance by specifying the fluid cooler UA and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the fluid cooler Standard Design Capacity or by specifying Design Capacity for Non standard conditions.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

fields.name: Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio
Standard Design Capacity
fields.memo: Standard design capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt (3 gpm/ton). Standard design capacity times the Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio (e.g. 1.25) gives the actual fluid cooler heat rejection at these operating conditions. Only used for Performance Input Method = StandardDesignCapacity; for other input methods, this field is ignored. The standard conditions mentioned above for Standard design capacity are already specified in the EnergyPlus. So the input fields such as design entering water temp., design entering air wet-bulb and dry-bulb temp. and design water flow rate, if provided in the input, will be ignored for the StandardDesignCapacity performance input method. Also, the standard conditions are for water as a fluid type so this performance input method can only be used with water as a fluid type (as specified in CondenserLoop object).

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate U-factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored.

fields.name: Design Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Input value is ignored if fluid cooler Performance Input Method= StandardDesignCapacity.

fields.name: User Specified Design Capacity
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored.

fields.name: Design Entering Water Temperature
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored. Design Entering Water Temperature must be greater than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Temperature
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored. Design Entering Air Temperature must be greater than Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Only used for Performance Input Method = UserSpecifiedDesignCapacity; for other Performance Input Methods, this field is ignored. Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature must be less than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Evaporation Loss Factor
fields.memo: Rate of water evaporation from the Fluid Cooler and lost to the outdoor air [%/K] Empirical correlation is used to calculate default loss factor if it not explicitly provided.

fields.name: Drift Loss Percent
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a percentage of circulating spray water flow rate Default value for this field in under investigation. For now Cooling tower's drift loss percent default value is taken here.

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the Evaporative Fluid Cooler. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the basin in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. Default value for this field in under investigation. For now Cooling tower's Blowdown Concentration Ratio percent default value is taken here.

fields.name: Blowdown Makeup Water Usage Schedule Name
fields.memo: Makeup water usage due to blowdown results from occasionally draining a small amount of water in the Fluid Cooler basin to purge scale or other contaminants to reduce their concentration in order to maintain an acceptable level of water quality. Schedule values should reflect water usage in m3/s.

zoneterminalunitlist.name: ZoneTerminalUnitList
zoneterminalunitlist.memo: List of variable refrigerant flow (VRF) terminal units served by a given VRF condensing unit. See ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow and AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow.

airterminal:singleduct:mixer.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer
airterminal:singleduct:mixer.memo: The mixer air terminal unit provides a means of supplying central system air to the air inlet or outlet side of a zoneHVAC equipment such as a four pipe fan coil unit. Normally the central air would be ventilation air from a dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS).

fields.name: ZoneHVAC Unit Object Type
fields.memo: The type of ZoneHVAC equipment to which this terminal mixer will be connected.

fields.name: ZoneHVAC Unit Object Name
fields.memo: The name of ZoneHVAC equipment to which this terminal mixer will be connected.

fields.name: Mixer Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is the outlet air node name of the mixer. This will be the inlet air node name of the ZoneHVAC equipment if the connection type in the input field Mixer Connection Type below is InletSide, else this will be an inlet air node name of the conditioned zone if the connection type in the input field Mixer Connection Type below is SupplySide.

fields.name: Mixer Primary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The primary air (treated outdoor air) inlet node name of the mixer. This will be an outlet air node name of an AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter or AirLoopHVAC:SupplyPlenum providing the connection to the DOA system.

fields.name: Mixer Secondary Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The secondary air (recirculating air) inlet node name of the mixer. This will be the outlet air node name of the ZoneHVAC equipment if the connection type in the input field mixer Connection Type below is SupplySide, or else this will be an exhaust air node name of the conditioned zone if the connection type in the input field Mixer Connection Type below is InletSide.

fields.name: Mixer Connection Type
fields.memo: This input field allows user to specify the mixer connection type. Valid choices are InletSide or SupplySide. This is a required input field. If the mixer connection type selected is InletSide, then the mixer is connected on the inlet side of the ZoneHVAC equipment, or else if the mixer connection type selected is SupplySide, then the mixer is connected at the outlet side of the ZoneHVAC equipment.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will adjust flow to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone, as for demand controlled ventilation. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will be controlled using the DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir objec referenced in the Sizing:Zone object.

fields.name: Per Person Ventilation Rate Mode
fields.memo: CurrentOccupancy models demand controlled ventilation using the current number of people DesignOccupancy uses the total Number of People in the zone and is constant

condenserequipmentoperationschemes.name: CondenserEquipmentOperationSchemes
condenserequipmentoperationschemes.memo: Operation schemes are listed in "priority" order.  Note that each scheme must address the entire load and/or condition ranges for the simulation. The actual one selected for use will be the first that is "Scheduled" on.  That is, if control scheme 1 is not "on" and control scheme 2 is -- then control scheme 2 is selected. Only condenser equipment should be listed on a Control Scheme for this item.

airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:re.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:ConstantVolume:Reheat
airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:re.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, constant volume, with reheat coil (hot water, electric, gas, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Maximum Reheat Air Temperature
fields.memo: Specifies the maximum allowable supply air temperature leaving the reheat coil. If left blank, there is no limit and no default. If unknown, 35C (95F) is recommended.

energymanagementsystem:sensor.name: EnergyManagementSystem:Sensor
energymanagementsystem:sensor.memo: Declares EMS variable as a sensor a list of output variables and meters that can be reported are available after a run on the report (.rdd) or meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Output:Variable or Output:Meter Index Key Name

generator:microturbine.name: Generator:MicroTurbine
generator:microturbine.memo: MicroTurbine generators are small combustion turbines (e.g., 25kW to 500kW). The model calculates electrical power output, fuel use, standby and ancillary power. Energy recovery from exhaust air can be used to heat water.

fields.name: Minimum Full Load Electrical Power Output
Maximum Full Load Electrical Power Output
fields.memo: If left blank, Maximum Full Load Electrical Power Output will be set equal to the Reference Electrical Power Output.

fields.name: Reference Electrical Efficiency Using Lower Heating Value
fields.memo: Electric power output divided by fuel energy input (LHV basis) at reference conditions.

fields.name: Reference Combustion Air Inlet Humidity Ratio
Electrical Power Function of Temperature and Elevation Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*Elev + e*Elev**2 + f*T*Elev T = combustion air inlet temperature (C) Elev = elevation (m)

fields.name: Electrical Efficiency Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 Cubic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*T**3 T = combustion air inlet temperature (C)

fields.name: Electrical Efficiency Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 Cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = ratio of Generator Load to steady state Electrical Power Output at current operating conditions

fields.name: Standby Power
fields.memo: Electric power consumed when the generator is available but not being called by the Electric Load Center.

fields.name: Ancillary Power
fields.memo: Electric power consumed by ancillary equipment (e.g., external fuel pressurization pump). Set to zero if Reference Electrical Power Output is the 'net' value (ancillary power already deducted). Input value is positive, but indicates negative electric generation.

fields.name: Ancillary Power Function of Fuel Input Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*mdot + c*mdot**2 mdot = fuel mass flow rate (kg/s) If left blank, model assumes ancillary power defined in previous field is constant whenever the generator is operating.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Inlet Node Name
Heat Recovery Water Outlet Node Name
Reference Thermal Efficiency Using Lower Heat Value
fields.memo: Reference thermal efficiency (heat recovery to water) based on the Lower Heating Value (LHV) of the fuel.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Flow Operating Mode
fields.memo: PlantControl means the heat recovery water flow rate is determined by the plant, but the user needs to supply a heat recovery water flow rate. InternalControl means the heat recovery water flow rate is controlled by this generator. If 'InternalControl' is selected, then the user needs to supply a reference heat recovery water flow rate and optionally the name of a heat recovery flow rate modifier curve.

fields.name: Reference Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate Function of Temperature and Power Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*Pnet + e*Pnet + f*T*Pnet T = heat recovery inlet water temperature Pnet = net power output = electric power output - ancillary power If left blank, model assumes the heat recovery water flow rate is constant whenever the generator is operating, at the Reference HR Water Flow Rate defined in the previous field.

fields.name: Thermal Efficiency Function of Temperature and Elevation Curve Name
fields.memo: Bicubic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*Elev + e*Elev**2 + f*T*Elev + g*T**3 + h*Elev**3 + i*T**2*Elev + j*T*Elev**2 Biquadratic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*Elev + e*Elev**2 + f*T*Elev T = combustion air inlet temperature (C) Elev = elevation (m) If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Rate Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 Cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = ratio of Generator Load to steady state Electrical Power Output at current operating conditions If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Rate Function of Inlet Water Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 T = inlet water temperature (C) If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Rate Function of Water Flow Rate Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*Flow + c*Flow**2 Flow = flow rate of water through the heat exchanger (m3/s) If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Minimum Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
Maximum Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
Combustion Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Must be an outdoor air node.

fields.name: Reference Exhaust Air Mass Flow Rate
Exhaust Air Flow Rate Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 Cubic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*T**3 T = combustion air inlet temperature (C) If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Exhaust Air Flow Rate Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 Cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = ratio of Generator Load to steady state Electrical Power Output at current operating conditions. If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Nominal Exhaust Air Outlet Temperature
fields.memo: Exhaust air outlet temperature at reference conditions.

fields.name: Exhaust Air Temperature Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 Cubic curve = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*T**3 T = combustion air inlet temperature (C) If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

fields.name: Exhaust Air Temperature Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 Cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = ratio of Generator Load to steady state Electrical Power Output at current operating conditions. If field is left blank, model assumes this modifier equals 1 for entire simulation.

airterminal:singleduct:parallelpiu:rehea.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:ParallelPIU:Reheat
airterminal:singleduct:parallelpiu:rehea.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume, parallel powered induction unit (PIU), with reheat coil (hot water, electric, gas, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Fan On Flow Fraction
fields.memo: the fraction of the primary air flow at which fan turns on

fields.name: Reheat Coil Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: mixer outlet node

fields.name: Fan Name
fields.memo: Fan type must be Fan:SystemModel or Fan:ConstantVolume

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

coil:cooling:dx:variablerefrigerantflow.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow
coil:cooling:dx:variablerefrigerantflow.memo: Variable refrigerant flow (VRF) direct expansion (DX) cooling coil. Used with ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow. Condensing unit is modeled separately, see AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Cooling capacity excluding supply air fan heat

fields.name: Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Sensible heat ratio excluding supply air fan heat

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Volume flow rate corresponding to rated total cooling capacity should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total cooling capacity

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
Cooling Capacity Modifier Curve Function of Flow Fraction Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Name of Water Storage Tank for Condensate Collection

thermalstorage:ice:simple.name: ThermalStorage:Ice:Simple
thermalstorage:ice:simple.memo: This ice storage model is a simplified model It requires a setpoint placed on the Chilled Water Side Outlet Node It should be placed in the chilled water supply side outlet branch followed by a pipe. Use the PlantEquipmentOperation:ComponentSetpoint plant operation scheme.

fields.name: Ice Storage Type
fields.memo: IceOnCoilInternal = Ice-on-Coil, internal melt IceOnCoilExternal = Ice-on-Coil, external melt

refrigeration:system.name: Refrigeration:System
refrigeration:system.memo: Simulates the performance of a supermarket refrigeration system when used along with other objects to define the refrigeration load(s), the compressor(s), and the condenser.

fields.name: Refrigerated Case or Walkin or CaseAndWalkInList Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Refrigeration:Case or Refrigeration:WalkIn object. If there is more than one refrigerated case or walk-in served by this system, enter the name of a Refrigeration:CaseAndWalkInList object. Only cases and walkins served directly by the system should be included in this list. Any cases served indirectly via a secondary chiller should NOT be included in this list

fields.name: Refrigeration Transfer Load or TransferLoad List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Refrigeration:SecondarySystem object OR a Refrigeration:Condenser:Cascade object OR, a Refrigeration:TransferLoadList object. A transfer load is identified as one which moves the load from one system to another. So if you have more than one such load (including cascade condensers and secondary loops) served by the same system, use a TransferLoadList object.

fields.name: Minimum Condensing Temperature
fields.memo: related to the proper operation of the thermal expansion valves and compressors

fields.name: Refrigeration System Working Fluid Type
fields.memo: Fluid property data for the refrigerant must be entered. The fluid property data, including the objects: FluidProperties:Name, FluidProperties:Temperatures, FluidProperties:Saturated and FluidProperties:Superheated can be copied from the FluidPropertiesRefData.idf dataset

fields.name: Mechanical Subcooler Name
fields.memo: Optional Field Recipient of refrigeration capacity, that is receives cool liquid from another refrigeration system to help meet aggregate case loads

fields.name: Liquid Suction Heat Exchanger Subcooler Name
fields.memo: Optional Field Liquid Suction Heat Exchanger Name, or leave blank

fields.name: Sum UA Suction Piping
fields.memo: Use only if you want to include suction piping heat gain in refrigeration load

fields.name: Suction Piping Zone Name
fields.memo: This will be used to determine the temperature used for distribution piping heat gain and the pipe heat gains  as cooling credit for the zone. Required only if Sum UA Distribution Piping >0.0

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

output:daylightfactors.name: Output:DaylightFactors
output:daylightfactors.memo: Reports hourly daylight factors for each exterior window for four sky types (clear, turbid clear, intermediate, and overcast).

groundheatexchanger:system.name: GroundHeatExchanger:System
groundheatexchanger:system.memo: Models vertical ground heat exchangers systems using the response factor approach developed by Eskilson. Response factors are calculated using a finite line source model assuming uniform heat flux at the borehole wall.

dehumidifier:desiccant:nofans.name: Dehumidifier:Desiccant:NoFans
dehumidifier:desiccant:nofans.memo: This object models a solid desiccant dehumidifier. The process air stream is the air which is dehumidified. The regeneration air stream is the air which is heated to regenerate the desiccant. This object determines the process air outlet conditions, the load on the regeneration heating coil, the electric power consumption for the wheel rotor motor, and the regeneration air fan mass flow rate. All other heat exchangers are modeled as separate objects connected to the inlet and outlet nodes of the dehumidifier. The solid desiccant dehumidifier is typically used in an AirLoopHVAC:OutdoorAirSystem, but can also be specified in any AirLoopHVAC.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Process Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node entering the process side of the desiccant wheel.

fields.name: Process Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node leaving the process side of the desiccant wheel.

fields.name: Regeneration Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: This is the node entering the regeneration side of the desiccant wheel after the regeneration coil.

fields.name: Regeneration Fan Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Node for air entering the regeneration fan, mass flow is set by the desiccant dehumidifier module.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: Type of setpoint control: LeavingMaximumHumidityRatioSetpoint means that the unit is controlled to deliver air at the Leaving Max Humidity Ratio Setpoint (see below), SystemNodeMaximumHumidityRatioSetpoint means that the leaving humidity ratio setpoint is the System Node Humidity Ratio Max property of the Process Air Outlet Node.  A Setpoint object must be used to control this setpoint. Both control types use bypass dampers to prevent over drying.

fields.name: Leaving Maximum Humidity Ratio Setpoint
fields.memo: Fixed setpoint for maximum process air leaving humidity ratio Applicable only when Control Type = LeavingMaximumHumidityRatioSetpoint.

fields.name: Nominal Process Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Process air flow rate at nominal conditions

fields.name: Nominal Process Air Velocity
fields.memo: Process air velocity at nominal flow When using Performance Model Type of Default, must be 2.032 to 4.064 m/s (400 to 800 fpm)

fields.name: Rotor Power
fields.memo: Power input to wheel rotor motor

fields.name: Regeneration Coil Object Type
fields.memo: heating coil type works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Regeneration Coil Name
fields.memo: Name of heating coil object for regeneration air

fields.name: Regeneration Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Type of fan object for regeneration air.  When using the Default Performance Model Type (see below), only Fan:VariableVolume or Fan:SystemModel are valid.

fields.name: Regeneration Fan Name
fields.memo: Name of fan object for regeneration air

fields.name: Performance Model Type
fields.memo: Specifies whether the default performance model or user-specified curves should be used to model the performance.  The default model is a generic solid desiccant wheel using performance curves of the form: curve = C1 + C2*edb + C3*edb**2 + C4*ew + C5*ew**2 + C6*vel + C7*vel**2 + C8*edb*ew + C9*edb**2*ew**2 + C10*edb*vel + C11*edb**2*vel**2 + C12*ew*vel + C13*ew**2*vel**2 + C14*ALOG(edb) + C15*ALOG(ew) + C16*ALOG(vel) edb = process entering dry-bulb temperature [C] ew  = process entering humidity ratio [kgWater/kgDryAir] vel = process air velocity [m/s] If UserCurves are specified, then performance is calculated as follows: Leaving Dry-Bulb = (Leaving Dry-Bulb fTW Curve) * (Leaving Dry-Bulb fV Curve) Leaving Humidity Ratio = (Leaving Humidity Ratio fTW Curve) * (Leaving Humidity Ratio fV Curve) Regen Energy = (Regen Energy fTW Curve) * (Regen Energy fV Curve) Regen Velocity = (Regen Velocity fTW Curve) * (Regen Velocity fV Curve)

fields.name: Leaving Dry-Bulb Function of Entering Dry-Bulb and Humidity Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Leaving dry-bulb of process air as a function of entering dry-bulb and entering humidity ratio, biquadratic curve curve = C1 + C2*edb + C3*edb**2 + C4*ew + C5*ew**2 + C6*edb*ew edb = process entering dry-bulb temperature [C] ew  = process entering humidity ratio [kgWater/kgDryAir]

fields.name: Leaving Dry-Bulb Function of Air Velocity Curve Name
fields.memo: Leaving dry-bulb of process air as a function of air velocity, quadratic curve. curve = C1 + C2*v + C3*v**2 v = process air velocity [m/s]

fields.name: Leaving Humidity Ratio Function of Entering Dry-Bulb and Humidity Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Leaving humidity ratio of process air as a function of entering dry-bulb and entering humidity ratio, biquadratic curve curve = C1 + C2*edb + C3*edb**2 + C4*ew + C5*ew**2 + C6*edb*ew edb = process entering dry-bulb temperature [C] ew  = process entering humidity ratio [kgWater/kgDryAir]

fields.name: Leaving Humidity Ratio Function of Air Velocity Curve Name
fields.memo: Leaving humidity ratio of process air as a function of process air velocity, quadratic curve. curve = C1 + C2*v + C3*v**2 v = process air velocity [m/s]

fields.name: Regeneration Energy Function of Entering Dry-Bulb and Humidity Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Regeneration energy [J/kg of water removed] as a function of entering dry-bulb and entering humidity ratio, biquadratic curve curve = C1 + C2*edb + C3*edb**2 + C4*ew + C5*ew**2 + C6*edb*ew edb = process entering dry-bulb temperature [C] ew  = process entering humidity ratio [kgWater/kgDryAir]

fields.name: Regeneration Energy Function of Air Velocity Curve Name
fields.memo: Regeneration energy [J/kg of water removed] as a function of process air velocity, quadratic curve. curve = C1 + C2*v + C3*v**2 v = process air velocity [m/s]

fields.name: Regeneration Velocity Function of Entering Dry-Bulb and Humidity Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Regeneration velocity [m/s] as a function of entering dry-bulb and entering humidity ratio, biquadratic curve curve = C1 + C2*edb + C3*edb**2 + C4*ew + C5*ew**2 + C6*edb*ew edb = process entering dry-bulb temperature [C] ew  = process entering humidity ratio [kgWater/kgDryAir]

fields.name: Regeneration Velocity Function of Air Velocity Curve Name
fields.memo: Regeneration velocity [m/s] as a function of process air velocity, quadratic curve. curve = C1 + C2*v + C3*v**2 v = process air velocity [m/s]

fields.name: Nominal Regeneration Temperature
fields.memo: Nominal regen temperature upon which the regen energy modifier curve is based.  Not used if Default if chosen for the field Performance Mode Type. 121 C is a commonly used value.

site:heightvariation.name: Site:HeightVariation
site:heightvariation.memo: This object is used if the user requires advanced control over height-dependent variations in wind speed and temperature.  When this object is not present, the default model for temperature dependence on height is used, and the wind speed is modeled according to the Terrain field of the BUILDING object.

fields.name: Wind Speed Profile Exponent
fields.memo: Set to zero for no wind speed dependence on height.

fields.name: Wind Speed Profile Boundary Layer Thickness
Air Temperature Gradient Coefficient
fields.memo: Set to zero for no air temperature dependence on height.

zonehvac:hightemperatureradiant.name: ZoneHVAC:HighTemperatureRadiant
zonehvac:hightemperatureradiant.memo: The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 100, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of zone system is serving

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the maximum heating power input capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Fuel Type
fields.memo: Natural gas or electricity

fields.name: Combustion Efficiency
fields.memo: Not used for non-gas radiant heaters

fields.name: Fraction of Input Converted to Radiant Energy
fields.memo: Radiant+latent+lost fractions must sum to 1 or less, remainder is considered convective heat

fields.name: Fraction of Input Converted to Latent Energy
Fraction of Input that Is Lost
fields.memo: Fraction of input vented to outdoor environment

fields.name: Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: Temperature type used to control unit

fields.name: Heating Setpoint Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This setpoint is an "operative temperature" setpoint

fields.name: Fraction of Radiant Energy Incident on People
fields.memo: This will affect thermal comfort but from an energy balance standpoint this value gets added to the convective gains from the radiant heater

wateruse:storage.name: WaterUse:Storage
wateruse:storage.memo: A water storage tank. If the building model is to include any on-site water collection, wells, or storing and reuse of graywater, then a WaterUse:Storage object is needed. Each WaterUse:Storage can serve as a central node and make connections to numerous sources of supply or numerous components with demand. If a maximum capacity is not specified, the tank is assumed to have unlimited capacity.

fields.name: Maximum Capacity
fields.memo: Defaults to unlimited capacity.

fields.name: Design In Flow Rate
fields.memo: Defaults to unlimited flow.

fields.name: Design Out Flow Rate
fields.memo: Defaults to unlimited flow.

fields.name: Overflow Destination
fields.memo: If blank, overflow is discarded

fields.name: Type of Supply Controlled by Float Valve
Float Valve On Capacity
fields.memo: Lower range of target storage level e.g. float valve kicks on

fields.name: Float Valve Off Capacity
fields.memo: Upper range of target storage level e.g. float valve kicks off

fields.name: Backup Mains Capacity
fields.memo: Lower range of secondary target storage level used to keep tanks at a minimum level using mains water if well can't keep up

roomairsettings:onenodedisplacementventi.name: RoomAirSettings:OneNodeDisplacementVentilation
roomairsettings:onenodedisplacementventi.memo: The Mundt model for displacement ventilation

fields.name: Fraction of Convective Internal Loads Added to Floor Air
Fraction of Infiltration Internal Loads Added to Floor Air

lifecyclecost:recurringcosts.name: LifeCycleCost:RecurringCosts
lifecyclecost:recurringcosts.memo: Recurring costs are costs that repeat over time on a regular schedule during the study period. If costs associated with equipment do repeat but not on a regular schedule, use LifeCycleCost:NonrecurringCost objects instead.

fields.name: Cost
fields.memo: Enter the cost in dollars (or the appropriate monetary unit) for the recurring costs. Enter the cost for each time it occurs. For example if the annual maintenance cost is 500 dollars enter 500 here.

fields.name: Start of Costs
fields.memo: Enter when the costs start. The First Year of Cost is based on the number of years past the Start of Costs. For most maintenance costs the Start of Costs should be Service Period.

fields.name: Years from Start
fields.memo: This field and the Months From Start field together represent the time from either the start of the Service Period on the service month and year or start of the Base Period on the base month and year (depending on the Start of Costs field) that the costs start to occur. Only integers should be entered representing whole years.

fields.name: Months from Start
fields.memo: This field and the Years From Start field together represent the time from either the start of the Service Period on the service month and year or start of the Base Period on the base month and year (depending on the Start of Costs field) that the costs start to occur. Only integers should be entered representing whole months. The Years From Start (times 12) and Months From Start are added together.

fields.name: Repeat Period Years
fields.memo: This field and the Repeat Period Months field indicate how much time elapses between re-occurrences of the cost. For costs that occur every year such the Repeat Period Years should be 1 and Repeat Period Months should be 0. Only integers should be entered representing whole years.

fields.name: Repeat Period Months
fields.memo: This field and the Repeat Period Years field indicate how much time elapses between re-occurrences of the cost. Only integers should be entered representing whole years. The Repeat Period Years (times 12) and Repeat Period Months are added together.

fields.name: Annual escalation rate
fields.memo: Enter the annual escalation rate as a decimal. For a 1% rate enter the value 0.01. This input is used when the Inflation Approach is CurrentDollar. When Inflation Approach is set to ConstantDollar this input is ignored.

roomair:temperaturepattern:twogradient.name: RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:TwoGradient
roomair:temperaturepattern:twogradient.memo: Used to model room air with two temperature gradients in the vertical direction. Used in combination with RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:UserDefined.

fields.name: Room Air Temperature Pattern Two Gradient Name
Control Integer for Pattern Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: reference this entry in Schedule Name

fields.name: Thermostat Height
fields.memo: = Distance from floor of zone

fields.name: Return Air Height
fields.memo: = Distance from floor of zone

fields.name: Exhaust Air Height
fields.memo: = Distance from floor of zone

fields.name: Temperature Gradient Lower Bound
fields.memo: Slope of temperature change in vertical direction

fields.name: Temperature Gradient Upper  Bound
fields.memo: Slope of temperature change in vertical direction

zoneaircontaminantbalance.name: ZoneAirContaminantBalance
zoneaircontaminantbalance.memo: Determines which contaminant concentration will be simulates.

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Concentration
fields.memo: If Yes, CO2 simulation will be performed.

fields.name: Outdoor Carbon Dioxide Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be in parts per million (ppm)

fields.name: Generic Contaminant Concentration
fields.memo: If Yes, generic contaminant simulation will be performed.

fields.name: Outdoor Generic Contaminant Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be generic contaminant concentration in parts per million (ppm)

zonemixing.name: ZoneMixing
zonemixing.memo: ZoneMixing is a simple air exchange from one zone to another. Note that this statement only affects the energy balance of the "receiving" zone and will not produce any effect on the "source" zone. Mixing statements can be complementary and include multiple zones, but the balancing of flows between zones is left to the user's discretion.

fields.name: Design Flow Rate Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of ventilation for this set of attributes Choices: Flow/Zone => Design Flow Rate -- simply enter Design Flow Rate Flow/Area => Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area - Value * Floor Area (zone) = Design Flow Rate Flow/Person => Flow Rate per Person - Value * #people = Design Flow Rate AirChanges/Hour => Air Changes per Hour - Value * Floor Volume (zone) adjusted for m3/s = Design Volume Flow Rate "Vdesign" in Equation is the result.

fields.name: Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
Delta Temperature
fields.memo: This field contains the constant temperature differential between source and receiving zones below which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Delta Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the temperature differential between source and receiving zones versus time below which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the zone dry-bulb temperature versus time below which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the zone dry-bulb temperature versus time above which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Source Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the source zone dry-bulb temperature versus time below which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Source Zone Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the source zone dry-bulb temperature versus time above which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time below which mixing is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time above which mixing is shutoff.

airflownetwork:multizone:surface.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface
airflownetwork:multizone:surface.memo: This object specifies the properties of a surface linkage through which air flows. Airflow Report: Node 1 as an inside face zone; Node 2 as an outside face zone or external node.

fields.name: Surface Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a heat transfer surface.

fields.name: Leakage Component Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an Airflow Network leakage component. A leakage component is one of the following AirflowNetwork:Multizone objects: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:DetailedOpening, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:SimpleOpening, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface:Crack, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface:EffectiveLeakageArea, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:HorizontalOpening, or AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:ZoneExhaustFan. When the zone exhaust fan name is entered, any surface control fields below A3 are ignored when the zone exhaust fan turns on.

fields.name: External Node Name
fields.memo: Used if Wind Pressure Coefficient Type = Input in the AirflowNetwork:SimulationControl object, otherwise this field may be left blank.

fields.name: Window/Door Opening Factor, or Crack Factor
fields.memo: This field specifies a multiplier for a crack, window, or door.

fields.name: Ventilation Control Mode
fields.memo: When Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature or Enthalpy, the following fields are used to modulate the Ventilation Open Factor for a window or door opening according to the parent zone's indoor-outdoor temperature or enthalpy difference. When Ventilation Control Mode = AdjacentTemperature or AdjacentEnthalpy, the following fields are used to modulate the Ventilation Open Factor for an interior window or door opening according to temperature or enthalpy difference between the parent zone and the adjacent zone. Constant: controlled by field Venting Schedule Name. NoVent: control will not open window or door during simulation (Ventilation Open Factor = 0). ZoneLevel: control will be controlled by AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Zone Mode.

fields.name: Ventilation Control Zone Temperature Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature or Enthalpy.

fields.name: Minimum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Used only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature or Enthalpy.

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Temperature Difference Lower Limit For Maximum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Temperature Difference Upper Limit for Minimum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature. This value must be greater than the corresponding lower value (previous field).

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Enthalpy Difference Lower Limit For Maximum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Enthalpy. This value must be less than the corresponding upper value (next field).

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Enthalpy Difference Upper Limit for Minimum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Enthalpy. This value must be greater than the corresponding lower value (previous field).

fields.name: Venting Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Non-zero schedule value means venting is allowed if other venting control conditions are satisfied. A zero (or negative) schedule value means venting is not allowed under any circumstances. The schedule values should be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 1. If this schedule is not specified then venting is allowed if other venting control conditions are satisfied. Not used if Ventilation Control Mode = NoVent or ZoneLevel.

fields.name: Occupant Ventilation Control Name
fields.memo: Enter the name where Occupancy Ventilation Control is required.

fields.name: Equivalent Rectangle Method
fields.memo: This field is applied to a non-rectangular window or door. The equivalent shape has the same area as a polygonal window or door.

fields.name: Equivalent Rectangle Aspect Ratio
fields.memo: This field is used when UserDefinedAspectRatio is entered in the Equivalent Rectangle Method field.

coilperformance:dx:cooling.name: CoilPerformance:DX:Cooling
coilperformance:dx:cooling.memo: Used to specify DX cooling coil performance for one mode of operation for a Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoStageWithHumidityControlMode object which may reference one to four CoilPerformance:DX:Cooling objects depending on the specified number of stages and dehumidification modes. In nearly all cases, the Rated Air Flow Rate will be the same for all performance objects associated with a given coil. If bypass is specified, the Rated Air Flow Rate includes both the bypassed flow and the flow through the active part of the coil.

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to Rated total Cooling capacity, Rated SHR and Rated COP

fields.name: Fraction of Air Flow Bypassed Around Coil
fields.memo: Fraction of Rated Air Flow Rate which bypasses the cooling coil in this performance mode.  The remaining portion of the flow should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total cooling capacity. This is used to model face-split coils on multi-stage units or bypass dampers. If total flow rate varies during simulation, the same fraction is bypassed.

fields.name: Total Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Total Cooling Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Nominal Time for Condensate Removal to Begin
fields.memo: The nominal time for condensate to begin leaving the coil's condensate drain line at the coil's rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Nominal time is equal to the ratio of the energy of the coil's maximum condensate holding capacity (J) to the coil's steady state latent capacity (W). Suggested value is 1000; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Ratio of Initial Moisture Evaporation Rate and Steady State Latent Capacity
fields.memo: Ratio of the initial moisture evaporation rate from the cooling coil (when the compressor first turns off) and the coil's steady state latent capacity at rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Suggested value is 1.5; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: The maximum on-off cycling rate for the compressor, which occurs at 50% run time fraction. Suggested value is 3; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Latent Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: Time constant for the cooling coil's latent capacity to reach steady state after startup. Suggested value is 45; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*wb*db wb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) db = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the DX cooling coil (C) entering temperature can be outside air or pretreated air.

fields.name: Sensible Heat Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

coil:heating:dx:multispeed.name: Coil:Heating:DX:MultiSpeed
coil:heating:dx:multispeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) heating coil (air-to-air heat pump) and compressor unit (includes electric or engine-driven compressor and outdoor fan), multi-speed (or variable-speed), with defrost controls. Requires two to four sets of performance data and will interpolate between speeds.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature to Turn On Compressor
fields.memo: The outdoor temperature when the compressor is automatically turned back on following an automatic shut off because of low outdoor dry-bulb temperature. This field is only used for the calculation of HSPF. If this field is not provided, then outdoor bin temperature used in the HSPF calculation is always considered to be greater than this temperature and 'Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation' field described above. This assumption is based on AHRI standard 210/240 (2008) and can introduce significant error in the final value of HSPF.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Defrost Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: biquadratic curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*wb*oat wb = wet-bulb temperature (C) of air entering the indoor coil oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) only required if ReverseCycle defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode only applicable if timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Apply Part Load Fraction to Speeds Greater than 1
Region number for Calculating HSPF
fields.memo: Standard Region number for which HSPF and other standard ratings are calculated

fields.name: Number of Speeds
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for coil capacity, COP, flow rate, and associated curves.

fields.name: Speed 1 Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Speed 1 Gross Rated Heating COP
fields.memo: Rated heating capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total capacity should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total heating capacity

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Supply Air Fan Power Per Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air fan power per air volume flow rate at the rated speed 1 test conditions. The test conditions vary external static pressure based on heating capacity. This value is only used to calculate Heating Seasonal Performance Factor(HSPF). This value is not used for modeling the supply air fan during simulations.

fields.name: Speed 1 Heating Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 cubic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 + d*oat**3 biquadratic curve = a + b*iat + c*iat**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*iat*oat oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) iat = indoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) biquadratic curve is recommended if sufficient manufacturer data is available for the heating capacity to be sensitive to both iat and oat.

fields.name: Speed 1 Heating Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Speed 1 Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 cubic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 + d*oat**3 biquadratic curve = a + b*iat + c*iat**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*iat*oat oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) iat = indoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) biquadratic curve is recommended if sufficient manufacturer data is available for the energy input ratio to be sensitive to both iat and oat.

fields.name: Speed 1 Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Speed 1 Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (sensible heating load/steady state heating capacity)

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Waste Heat Fraction of Power Input
fields.memo: recoverable waste heat at full load and rated conditions

fields.name: Speed 1 Waste Heat Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*odb + c*odb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*odb*db odb = Outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) db = entering coil dry-bulb temperature (C)

fields.name: Speed 2 Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Speed 2 Gross Rated Heating COP
fields.memo: Rated heating capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy

fields.name: Speed 2 Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total capacity should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total heating capacity

fields.name: Speed 2 Rated Supply Air Fan Power Per Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air fan power per air volume flow rate at the rated speed 2 test conditions. The test conditions vary external static pressure based on heating capacity. This value is only used to calculate Heating Seasonal Performance Factor(HSPF). This value is not used for modeling the supply air fan during simulations.

fields.name: Speed 2 Heating Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 cubic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 + d*oat**3 biquadratic curve = a + b*iat + c*iat**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*iat*oat oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) iat = indoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) biquadratic curve is recommended if sufficient manufacturer data is available for the heating capacity to be sensitive to both iat and oat.

fields.name: Speed 2 Heating Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Speed 2 Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 cubic curve = a + b*oat + c*oat**2 + d*oat**3 biquadratic curve = a + b*iat + c*iat**2 + d*oat + e*oat**2 + f*iat*oat oat = outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) iat = indoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) biquadratic curve is recommended if sufficient manufacturer data is available for the energy input ratio to be sensitive to both iat and oat.

fields.name: Speed 2 Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Speed 2 Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (sensible heating load/steady state heating capacity)

fields.name: Speed 2 Rated Waste Heat Fraction of Power Input
fields.memo: recoverable waste heat at full load and rated conditions

fields.name: Speed 2 Waste Heat Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*odb + c*odb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*odb*db odb = Outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) db = entering coil dry-bulb temperature (C)

fields.name: Speed 3 Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat capacity excluding supply air fan heat rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Speed 3 Gross Rated Heating COP
fields.memo: Rated heating capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy

fields.name: Speed 3 Rated Air Flow Rate

fields.name: Zone Name for Evaporator Placement
fields.memo: This input field is name of a conditioned or unconditioned zone where the secondary coil (evaporator) of a heat pump is to be placed.  This is an optional input field specified only when user desires to extract heat from the zone.  The heat extracted is modeled as internal heat gain of the zone. If the primary DX system is a heat pump, then the zone name should be the same as the zone name specified for placing the secondary cooling DX coil.

fields.name: Speed 1 Secondary Coil Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This input value is the secondary coil (evaporator) air flow rate when the heat pump is working in heating mode or the secondary DX coil (condenser) air flow rate when the heat pump is working in cooling mode.

fields.name: Speed 1 Secondary Coil Fan Flow Scaling Factor
fields.memo: This input field is scaling factor for autosizing the secondary DX coil fan flow rate. The secondary air flow rate is determined by multiplying the primary DX coil rated air flow rate by the fan flow scaling factor. Default value is 1.25. If the secondary coil fan flow rate is not autosized, then the secondary coil fan flow scaling factor is set to 1.0.

fields.name: Speed 1 Nominal Sensible Heat Ratio of Secondary Coil
fields.memo: This input value is the nominal sensible heat ratio used to split the heat extracted by a secondary DX coil (evaporator) of a heat pump into sensible and latent components. This is an optional input field.  If this input field is left blank, then pure sensible internal heat gain is assumed, i.e., sensible heat ratio of 1.0.

fields.name: Speed 1 Sensible Heat Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*wb*db wb = entering wet-bulb temperature seen by the secondary DX coil (C) db = entering dry-bulb temperature seen by the primary DX coil (C) This input field is name of sensible heat ratio modifier biquadratic curve.  The value of this curve modifies the nominal sensible heat ratio for current time step depending on the secondary zone air node wet-bulb temperature and the heating DX coil entering air dry-bulb temperature.  This is an optional input field.  If this input field is left blank, then the nominal sensible heat ratio specified in the field above will be used.

fields.name: Speed 1 Sensible Heat Ratio Modifier Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = secondary air flow fraction of the full load flow This input field is name of sensible heat ratio modifier curve.  The value of this curve modifies the nominal sensible heat ratio for current time step depending on the secondary coil air flow fraction. This is an optional input field.  If this input field is left blank, then the nominal sensible heat ratio specified will be used.
