zoneventilation:designflowrate.name: ZoneVentilation:DesignFlowRate
zoneventilation:designflowrate.memo: Ventilation is specified as a design level which is modified by a schedule fraction, temperature difference and wind speed: Ventilation=Vdesign * Fschedule * (A + B*|(Tzone-Todb)| + C*WindSpd + D * WindSpd**2) If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Design Flow Rate Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of ventilation for this set of attributes Choices: Flow/Zone => Design Flow Rate -- simply enter Design Flow Rate Flow/Area => Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area - Value * Floor Area (zone) = Design Flow Rate Flow/Person => Flow Rate per Person - Value * #people = Design Flow Rate AirChanges/Hour => Air Changes per Hour - Value * Floor Volume (zone) adjusted for m3/s = Design Volume Flow Rate "Vdesign" in Equation is the result.

fields.name: Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
Fan Pressure Rise
fields.memo: pressure rise across the fan

fields.name: Constant Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "A" in Equation

fields.name: Temperature Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "B" in Equation

fields.name: Velocity Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "C" in Equation

fields.name: Velocity Squared Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "D" in Equation

fields.name: Minimum Indoor Temperature
fields.memo: this is the indoor temperature below which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Minimum Indoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the indoor temperature versus time below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Indoor Temperature
fields.memo: this is the indoor temperature above which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Maximum Indoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the indoor temperature versus time above which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Delta Temperature
fields.memo: This is the temperature differential between indoor and outdoor below which ventilation is shutoff. If ((IndoorTemp - OutdoorTemp) < DeltaTemperature) then ventilation is not allowed. For example, if delta temperature is 2C, ventilation is assumed to be available if the outside air temperature is at least 2C cooler than the zone air temperature. The values for this field can include negative numbers. This allows ventilation to occur even if the outdoor temperature is above the indoor temperature.

fields.name: Delta Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the temperature differential between indoor and outdoor versus time below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature
fields.memo: this is the outdoor temperature below which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time below which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature
fields.memo: this is the outdoor temperature above which ventilation is shutoff

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: This schedule contains the outdoor temperature versus time above which ventilation is shutoff.

fields.name: Maximum Wind Speed
fields.memo: this is the outdoor wind speed above which ventilation is shutoff

windowproperty:stormwindow.name: WindowProperty:StormWindow
windowproperty:stormwindow.memo: This is a movable exterior glass layer that is usually applied in the winter and removed in the summer.

fields.name: Window Name
fields.memo: Must be the name of a FenestrationSurface:Detailed object with Surface Type = WINDOW. The WindowProperty:StormWindow object can only be used with exterior windows.

fields.name: Storm Glass Layer Name
fields.memo: Must be a WindowMaterial:Glazing or WindowMaterial:Glazing:RefractionExtinctionMethod Gap between storm glass layer and adjacent glass layer is assumed to be filled with Air

fields.name: Distance Between Storm Glass Layer and Adjacent Glass
Month that Storm Glass Layer is Put On

ALBEDO: Surface albedo for snow conditions
VEGHT: Surface roughness No snow conditions
PET: Flag, Potential evapotranspiration on?

site:watermainstemperature.name: Site:WaterMainsTemperature
site:watermainstemperature.memo: Used to calculate water mains temperatures delivered by underground water main pipes. Water mains temperatures are a function of outdoor climate conditions and vary with time of year.

condenserloop.name: CondenserLoop
condenserloop.memo: Defines a central plant condenser loop. CondenserLoop and PlantLoop are nearly identical except some components and operation schemes are applicable to only one loop type or the other.

fields.name: User Defined Fluid Type
fields.memo: This field is only required when Fluid Type is UserDefinedFluidType

fields.name: Condenser Loop Temperature Setpoint Node Name
Condenser Demand Side Branch List Name
Condenser Demand Side Connector List Name
Loop Circulation Time
fields.memo: This field is only used to autocalulate the Condenser Loop Volume. Loop Volume = Loop Circulation Time * Maximum Loop Flow Rate

availabilitymanager:nightcycle.name: AvailabilityManager:NightCycle
availabilitymanager:nightcycle.memo: Determines the availability of a loop or system: whether it is on or off. Depending on zone temperatures, overrides Schedules and forces system Fans on.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: When AvailabilityManager:NightCycle is used in the zone component availability manager assignment list, the key choices for Control Type would only be StayOff and CycleOnControlZone

fields.name: Control Zone or Zone List Name
fields.memo: When AvailabilityManager:NightCycle is used in the zone component availability manager assignment list, the Control Zone Name should be the name of the zone in which the zone component is.

Heating Control Zone or Zone List Name
Heating Zone Fans Only Zone or Zone List Name

plantequipmentoperation:uncontrolled.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:Uncontrolled
plantequipmentoperation:uncontrolled.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for uncontrolled operation. Specifies a group of equipment that runs if the loop is active, unless turned off by the loop flow resolver to maintain continuity in the fluid loop.

schedule:constant.name: Schedule:Constant
schedule:constant.memo: Constant hourly value for entire year.

materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.name: MaterialProperty:HeatAndMoistureTransfer:Suction
materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.memo: HeatBalanceAlgorithm = CombinedHeatAndMoistureFiniteElement solution algorithm only. Relationship between liquid suction transport coefficient and moisture content Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms

fields.name: Material Name
fields.memo: Material Name that the moisture properties will be added to.

fields.name: Number of Suction points
fields.memo: Number of Suction Liquid Transport Coefficient coordinates

output:diagnostics.name: Output:Diagnostics
output:diagnostics.memo: Special keys to produce certain warning messages or effect certain simulation characteristics.

pipingsystem:underground:pipecircuit.name: PipingSystem:Underground:PipeCircuit
pipingsystem:underground:pipecircuit.memo: The pipe circuit object in an underground piping system. This object is simulated within an underground piping domain object and connected on a branch on a plant loop.

fields.name: Convergence Criterion for the Inner Radial Iteration Loop
Maximum Iterations in the Inner Radial Iteration Loop
Number of Soil Nodes in the Inner Radial Near Pipe Mesh Region
Radial Thickness of Inner Radial Near Pipe Mesh Region

fields.name: Number of Pipe Segments Entered for this Pipe Circuit

site:groundreflectance:snowmodifier.name: Site:GroundReflectance:SnowModifier
site:groundreflectance:snowmodifier.memo: Specifies ground reflectance multipliers when snow resident on the ground. These multipliers are applied to the "normal" ground reflectances specified in Site:GroundReflectance.

fields.name: Ground Reflected Solar Modifier
fields.memo: Value for modifying the "normal" ground reflectance when Snow is on ground when calculating the "Ground Reflected Solar Radiation Value" a value of 1.0 here uses the "normal" ground reflectance Ground Reflected Solar = (BeamSolar*CosSunZenith + DiffuseSolar)*GroundReflectance This would be further modified by the Snow Ground Reflectance Modifier when Snow was on the ground When Snow on ground, effective GroundReflectance is normal GroundReflectance*"Ground Reflectance Snow Modifier" Ground Reflectance achieved in this manner will be restricted to [0.0,1.0]

fields.name: Daylighting Ground Reflected Solar Modifier
fields.memo: Value for modifying the "normal" daylighting ground reflectance when Snow is on ground when calculating the "Ground Reflected Solar Radiation Value" a value of 1.0 here uses the "normal" ground reflectance Ground Reflected Solar = (BeamSolar*CosSunZenith + DiffuseSolar)*GroundReflectance This would be further modified by the Snow Ground Reflectance Modifier when Snow was on the ground When Snow on ground, effective GroundReflectance is normal GroundReflectance*"Daylighting Ground Reflectance Snow Modifier" Ground Reflectance achieved in this manner will be restricted to [0.0,1.0]

chiller:absorption:indirect.name: Chiller:Absorption:Indirect
chiller:absorption:indirect.memo: This indirect absorption chiller model is an enhanced model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Chiller performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to third order polynomial equations. The chiller capacity is a function of condenser, chilled water, and generator temperatures. The heat input is a function of part-load ratio, condenser temperature, and chilled water temperature.

fields.name: Design Condenser Inlet Temperature
fields.memo: Used only when condenser flow rate is autosized.

fields.name: Condenser Inlet Temperature Lower Limit
fields.memo: Provides warnings when entering condenser temperature is below minimum. Capacity is not adjusted when entering condenser temperature is below minimum.

fields.name: Chilled Water Outlet Temperature Lower Limit
fields.memo: Capacity is adjusted when leaving chilled water temperature is below minimum.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable flow this is the max flow & for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Generator Heat Input Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
Pump Electric Input Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
Generator Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the generator inlet node name which connects this chiller to a steam or hot water plant, otherwise leave this field blank. Generator nodes are used to model heat input to the chiller.

fields.name: Generator Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the generator outlet node name which connects this chiller to a steam or hot water plant, otherwise leave this field blank. Generator nodes are used to model heat input to the chiller.

fields.name: Capacity Correction Function of Condenser Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve which shows the change in normalized capacity to changes in condenser temperature.

fields.name: Capacity Correction Function of Chilled Water Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve which shows the change in normalized capacity to changes in leaving chilled water temperature.

fields.name: Capacity Correction Function of Generator Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Used when generator fluid type is hot water Curve which shows the change in normalized capacity to changes in generator temperature.

fields.name: Generator Heat Input Correction Function of Condenser Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve which shows the change in normalized heat input to changes in condenser temperature.

fields.name: Generator Heat Input Correction Function of Chilled Water Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve which shows the change in normalized heat input to changes in leaving chilled water temperature.

fields.name: Generator Heat Source Type
fields.memo: The Generator side of the chiller can be connected to a hot water or steam plant where the generator inlet and outlet nodes are connected to a plant loop. If the generator is not connected to a plant loop, and the generator inlet/outlet nodes are not used, this field should be specified as steam or left blank. When a plant is not used, the model assumes steam as the heat source.

fields.name: Design Generator Fluid Flow Rate

fields.name: Temperature Lower Limit Generator Inlet
fields.memo: Provides warnings when entering generator temperature is below minimum. Capacity is not adjusted when entering generator temperature is below minimum.

fields.name: Degree of Subcooling in Steam Generator
fields.memo: This field is not used when the generator inlet/outlet nodes are not specified or the generator is connected to a hot water loop.

fields.name: Degree of Subcooling in Steam Condensate Loop
fields.memo: This field is not used when the generator inlet/outlet nodes are not specified or the generator is connected to a hot water loop.

fields.name: Sizing Factor

fields.name: Starting Vertex Position
fields.memo: Specified as entry for a 4 sided surface/rectangle Surfaces are specified as viewed from outside the surface Shading surfaces as viewed from behind.  (towards what they are shading)

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control. Defaults are 15.6C (60F) at 15.6C (60F) to 12.8C (55F) at 23.3C (74F)

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross SHR

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Control Type
fields.memo: When selecting OutdoorAirTemperatureReset, the Heating Coil Design Setpoint may need to be changed

fields.name: Heating Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control. Defaults 15.0C (59F) at 7.8C (46F) to 12.2C (54F) at 12.2C (54F)

fields.name: Heating Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb Low
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint at Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Heating Coil Reset Outdoor Dry-Bulb High
fields.memo: Applicable only for OutdoorAirTemperatureReset control.

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheatHeatingCoil = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint, reheat with heating coil Valid for all cooling coil types.  If no heating coil specified, cold supply temps may occur. CoolReheatDesuperheater = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint, reheat with desuperheater coil. Valid only for Cooling Coil Type = TwoSpeedDX, TwoStageDX, TwoStageHumidityControlDX, or HeatExchangerAssistedDX. Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load. Valid only for Cooling Coil Type = TwoStageHumidityControlDX or HeatExchangerAssistedDX

fields.name: Dehumidification Setpoint
fields.memo: The supply air humidity ratio for dehumidification control. Default of 0.00924 kgWater/kgDryAir is equivalent to 12.8C (55F) dewpoint. Ignored if Dehumidification Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Constant Setpoint
fields.memo: The supply air humidity ratio for humidification control. Ignored if Humidifier Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Dehumidification Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Dehumidification Setpoint above. Schedule values must be in units of humidity ratio (kgWater/kgDryAir or lbWater/lbDryAir)

fields.name: Humidifier Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Humidifier Constant Setpoint above. Schedule values must be in units of humidity ratio (kgWater/kgDryAir or lbWater/lbDryAir)

materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.name: MaterialProperty:HeatAndMoistureTransfer:Settings
materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.memo: HeatBalanceAlgorithm = CombinedHeatAndMoistureFiniteElement solution algorithm only. Additional material properties for surfaces. Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms

fields.name: Material Name
fields.memo: Material Name that the moisture properties will be added to. This augments material properties needed for combined heat and moisture transfer for surfaces.

fields.name: Initial Water Content Ratio
fields.memo: units are the water/material density ratio at the beginning of each run period.

solarcollectorperformance:integralcollec.name: SolarCollectorPerformance:IntegralCollectorStorage
solarcollectorperformance:integralcollec.memo: Thermal and optical performance parameters for a single glazed solar collector with integral storage unit.

fields.name: ICS Collector Type
fields.memo: Currently only RectangularTank ICS collector type is available.

fields.name: Bottom Heat Loss Conductance
fields.memo: Heat loss conductance of the collector bottom insulation

fields.name: Side Heat Loss Conductance
fields.memo: heat loss conductance of the collector side insulation

fields.name: Aspect Ratio
fields.memo: This value is ratio of the width (short side) to length (long side of) of the collector.  Used to calculate the perimeter of the collector

fields.name: Collector Side Height
fields.memo: This value is used to estimate collector side area for the heat loss calculation through the collector side

fields.name: Thermal Mass of Absorber Plate
fields.memo: Calculated from the specific heat, density and thickness of the absorber plate.

fields.name: Number of Covers
fields.memo: Number of transparent covers. Common practice is to use low-iron glass as the outer cover and very thin transparent sheet such as Teflon as the inner cover.

fields.name: Cover Spacing
fields.memo: The gap between the transparent covers and between the inner cover and the absorber plate

fields.name: Refractive Index of Outer Cover
fields.memo: Refractive index of outer cover. Typically low-iron glass is used as the outer cover material, and used as the default outer cover with a value of 1.526.

fields.name: Extinction Coefficient Times Thickness of Outer Cover
fields.memo: Clear glass has extinction coefficient of about 15 [1/m] and with thickness of 3.0mm, the product of the extinction coefficient and thickness becomes 0.045 (=15 * 0.003)

fields.name: Emissivity of Outer Cover
fields.memo: Thermal emissivity of the outer cover, commonly glass is used as the out collector cover material.

fields.name: Refractive Index of Inner Cover
fields.memo: Typical material is very thin sheet of Teflon (PTFE). The default value is refractive index of Teflon.

fields.name: Extinction Coefficient Times Thickness of the inner Cover
fields.memo: Default inner cover is very thin sheet of Teflon with extinction coefficient of approximately 40.0 and a thickness 0.2mm yields a default value of 0.008.

fields.name: Emissivity of Inner Cover
fields.memo: Thermal emissivity of the inner cover material

fields.name: Absorptance of Absorber Plate
fields.memo: The absorber plate solar absorptance.  Copper is assumed as the default absorber plate.

fields.name: Emissivity of Absorber Plate
fields.memo: Thermal emissivity of the absorber plate

site:grounddomain:slab.name: Site:GroundDomain:Slab
site:grounddomain:slab.memo: Ground-coupled slab model for on-grade and in-grade cases with or without insulation.

fields.name: Soil Moisture Content Volume Fraction at Saturation
Evapotranspiration Ground Cover Parameter
fields.memo: This specifies the ground cover effects during evapotranspiration calculations.  The value roughly represents the following cases: = 0   : concrete or other solid, non-permeable ground surface material = 0.5 : short grass, much like a manicured lawn = 1   : standard reference state (12 cm grass) = 1.5 : wild growth

fields.name: Slab Location
fields.memo: This field specifies whether the slab is located "in-grade" or "on-grade"

fields.name: Slab Material Name
fields.memo: Only applicable for the in-grade case

fields.name: Horizontal Insulation
fields.memo: This field specifies the presence of insulation beneath the slab. Only required for in-grade case.

fields.name: Horizontal Insulation Material Name
fields.memo: This field specifies the horizontal insulation material.

fields.name: Horizontal Insulation Extents
fields.memo: This field specifies whether the horizontal insulation fully insulates the surface or is perimeter only insulation

fields.name: Perimeter Insulation Width
fields.memo: This field specifies the width of the underfloor perimeter insulation

fields.name: Vertical Insulation
fields.memo: This field specifies the presence of vertical insulation at the slab edge.

fields.name: Vertical Insulation Material Name
fields.memo: This field specifies the vertical insulation material.

fields.name: Vertical Insulation Depth
fields.memo: Only used when including vertical insulation This field specifies the depth of the vertical insulation

fields.name: Simulation Timestep
fields.memo: This field specifies the ground domain simulation timestep.

groundheattransfer:slab:manualgrid.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:ManualGrid
groundheattransfer:slab:manualgrid.memo: Manual Grid only necessary when using manual gridding (not recommended) Used only in special cases when previous two objects are not used. User must input complete gridding information.

fields.name: NX: Number of cells in the X direction
NY: Number of cells in the Y direction
NZ: Number of cells in the Z direction
IBOX: X direction cell indicator of slab edge
fields.memo: typical values= 1-10

fields.name: JBOX: Y direction cell indicator of slab edge
fields.memo: typical values= 1-10

daylighting:delight:complexfenestration.name: Daylighting:DELight:ComplexFenestration
daylighting:delight:complexfenestration.memo: Used for DElight Complex Fenestration of all types

fields.name: Complex Fenestration Type
fields.memo: Used to select the appropriate Complex Fenestration BTDF data

fields.name: Building Surface Name
fields.memo: This is a reference to a valid surface object (such as BuildingSurface:Detailed) hosting this complex fenestration, analogous to the base surface Name field for subsurfaces such as Windows.

fields.name: Window Name
fields.memo: This is a reference to a valid FenestrationSurface:Detailed window object used to account for the geometry, and the solar and thermal gains/losses, of the Complex Fenestration

fields.name: Fenestration Rotation
fields.memo: In-plane counter-clockwise rotation angle of the Complex Fenestration optical reference direction and the base edge of the Complex Fenestration. The Rotation will typically be zero when the host and CFS surfaces are rectangular and height and width edges are aligned.

condenserequipmentlist.name: CondenserEquipmentList
condenserequipmentlist.memo: List condenser equipment in order of operating priority, 1st in list will be used 1st, etc Use only condenser equipment in this list. If no equipment object types and equipment names are specified, then the corresponding PlantEquipmentOperation:* object will assume all available condenser equipment for the loop should be OFF (not operate) within the specified lower/upper limit.

airflownetwork:multizone:component:zonee.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:ZoneExhaustFan
airflownetwork:multizone:component:zonee.memo: This object specifies the additional properties for a zone exhaust fan to perform multizone airflow calculations.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient When the Zone Exhaust Fan is Off at Reference Conditions
fields.memo: Enter the air mass flow coefficient at the conditions defined in the Reference Crack Conditions object. Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference. Enter the coefficient used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when the fan is off.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent When the Zone Exhaust Fan is Off
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when the fan is off.

fields.name: Reference Crack Conditions
fields.memo: Select a AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ReferenceCrackConditions name associated with the air mass flow coefficient entered above.

complexfenestrationproperty:solarabsorbe.name: ComplexFenestrationProperty:SolarAbsorbedLayers
complexfenestrationproperty:solarabsorbe.memo: Used to provide solar radiation absorbed in fenestration layers. References surface-construction pair and if that pair is used in a simulation, then program will use value provided in schedules instead of calculating it.

fields.name: Layer 1 Solar Radiation Absorbed Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in schedule are expected to be in W/m2

fields.name: Layer 2 Solar Radiation Absorbed Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in schedule are expected to be in W/m2

fields.name: Layer 3 Solar Radiation Absorbed Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in schedule are expected to be in W/m2

fields.name: Layer 4 Solar Radiation Absorbed Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in schedule are expected to be in W/m2

fields.name: Layer 5 Solar Radiation Absorbed Schedule Name
fields.memo: Values in schedule are expected to be in W/m2

thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.name: ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:SingleHeating
thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.memo: Used for heating only thermal comfort control. The PMV setpoint can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation but only heating is allowed with this control type.

fields.name: Fanger Thermal Comfort Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be Predicted Mean Vote (PMV)

setpointmanager:outdoorairpretreat.name: SetpointManager:OutdoorAirPretreat
setpointmanager:outdoorairpretreat.memo: This setpoint manager determines the required conditions at the outdoor air stream node which will produce the reference setpoint condition at the mixed air node when mixed with the return air stream

fields.name: Minimum Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Applicable only if Control variable is Temperature

fields.name: Maximum Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Applicable only if Control variable is Temperature

fields.name: Minimum Setpoint Humidity Ratio
fields.memo: Applicable only if Control variable is MaximumHumidityRatio, MinimumHumidityRatio, or HumidityRatio - then minimum is 0.00001

fields.name: Maximum Setpoint Humidity Ratio
fields.memo: Applicable only if Control variable is MaximumHumidityRatio, MinimumHumidityRatio, or HumidityRatio - then minimum is 0.00001

fields.name: Reference Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: The current setpoint at this node is the desired condition for the Mixed Air Node This node must have a valid setpoint which has been set by another setpoint manager

fields.name: Mixed Air Stream Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Mixed Air Node

fields.name: Outdoor Air Stream Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Outdoor Air Stream Node

fields.name: Return Air Stream Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Return Air Stream Node

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature or humidity ratio will be set

generator:fuelcell:electricalstorage.name: Generator:FuelCell:ElectricalStorage
generator:fuelcell:electricalstorage.memo: Used to describe the electrical storage subsystem for a fuel cell power generator. The electrical storage model is a very simple "constrained bucket" model. Note that this electrical storage is embedded within the FC device.

hvactemplate:plant:tower:objectreference.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:Tower:ObjectReference
hvactemplate:plant:tower:objectreference.memo: This object references a detailed cooling tower object and adds it to an HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop or MixedWaterLoop. The user must create a complete detailed cooling tower object with all required curve or performance objects.

fields.name: Cooling Tower Name
fields.memo: The name of the detailed cooling tower object.

fields.name: Priority
fields.memo: If Condenser Plant Operation Scheme Type=Default in HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop or MixedWaterLoop, then equipment operates in Priority order, 1, 2, 3, etc.

fields.name: Template Plant Loop Type
fields.memo: Specifies if this tower serves a template chilled water loop or mixed water loop If left blank, will serve a chilled water loop if present, or a mixed water loop (if no chilled water loop is present).

zoneinfiltration:flowcoefficient.name: ZoneInfiltration:FlowCoefficient
zoneinfiltration:flowcoefficient.memo: Infiltration is specified as flow coefficient, schedule fraction, stack and wind coefficients, and is a function of temperature difference and wind speed: Infiltration=FSchedule * SQRT( (c * Cs*|(Tzone-Todb)|**n)**2 + (c* Cw*(s * WindSpd)**2n)**2 )

fields.name: Flow Coefficient
fields.memo: "c" in Equation

fields.name: Stack Coefficient
fields.memo: "Cs" in Equation

fields.name: Pressure Exponent
fields.memo: "n" in Equation

fields.name: Wind Coefficient
fields.memo: "Cw" in Equation

fields.name: Shelter Factor
fields.memo: "s" in Equation

windowmaterial:complexshade.name: WindowMaterial:ComplexShade
windowmaterial:complexshade.memo: Complex window shading layer thermal properties

fields.name: Slat Spacing
fields.memo: Distance between adjacent slat faces

fields.name: Slat Thickness
fields.memo: Distance between top and bottom surfaces of slat Slat is assumed to be rectangular in cross section and flat

fields.name: Slat Curve
fields.memo: this value represents curvature radius of the slat. if the slat is flat use zero. if this value is not zero, then it must be > SlatWidth/2.

lights.name: Lights
lights.memo: Sets internal gains for lights in the zone. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in schedule should be fraction applied to design level of lights, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Design Level Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of lights for this set of attributes Choices: LightingLevel => Lighting Level -- simply enter watts of lights Watts/Area => Watts per Zone Floor Area -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Floor Area = Lights Watts/Person => Watts per Person -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Occupants = Lights

fields.name: Return Air Fraction
fields.memo: Used only for sizing calculation if return-air-fraction coefficients are specified.

fields.name: Fraction Replaceable
fields.memo: For Daylighting:Controls must be 0 or 1:  0 = no dimming control, 1 = full dimming control

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Return Air Fraction Calculated from Plenum Temperature
Return Air Fraction Function of Plenum Temperature Coefficient 1
fields.memo: Used only if Return Air Fraction Is Calculated from Plenum Temperature = Yes Equation is Return Air Fraction = Coefficient#1 - Coefficient#2 X PlenumTemp(degC)

fields.name: Return Air Fraction Function of Plenum Temperature Coefficient 2
fields.memo: Used only if Return Air Fraction Is Calculated from Plenum Temperature = Yes Equation is Return Air Fraction = Coefficient#1 - Coefficient#2 X PlenumTemp(degC)

fields.name: Return Air Heat Gain Node Name
fields.memo: Name of the return air node for this heat gain. If left blank, defaults to the first return air node for the zone. Leave this field blank when using a ZoneList name.

setpointmanager:warmesttemperatureflow.name: SetpointManager:WarmestTemperatureFlow
setpointmanager:warmesttemperatureflow.memo: This setpoint manager sets both the supply air temperature and the supply air flow rate.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object.

fields.name: Strategy
fields.memo: For TemperatureFirst the manager tries to find the highest setpoint temperature that will satisfy all the zone cooling loads at minimum supply air flow rate. If this setpoint temperature is less than the minimum, the setpoint temperature is set to the minimum, and the supply air flow rate is increased to meet the loads. For FlowFirst the manager tries to find the lowest supply air flow rate that will satisfy all the zone cooling loads at the maximum setpoint temperature. If this flow is greater than the maximum, the flow is set to the maximum and the setpoint temperature is reduced to satisfy the cooling loads.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

fields.name: Minimum Turndown Ratio
fields.memo: Fraction of the maximum supply air flow rate. Used to define the minimum supply flow for the TemperatureFirst strategy.

headeredpumps:variablespeed.name: HeaderedPumps:VariableSpeed
headeredpumps:variablespeed.memo: This Headered pump object describes a pump bank with more than 1 pump in parallel

fields.name: Total Design Flow Rate
fields.memo: If the field is not autosized set to the flow rate to the total flow when all pumps are running at full load

fields.name: Design Pump Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet

fields.name: Design Power Consumption
fields.memo: If the field is not autosized set to the power consumed by the pump bank when all the pumps are running at nominal flow When autosized the type of scaling factor is chosen in the input field Design Power Sizing Method

fields.name: Motor Efficiency
fields.memo: This is the motor efficiency only. When the Design Power Consumption is autosized using PowerPerFlowPerPressure, the Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used in addition to the motor efficiency.

fields.name: Fraction of Motor Inefficiencies to Fluid Stream
Coefficient 1 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 2 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 3 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 4 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Minimum Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: This value can be zero and will be defaulted to that if not specified.

fields.name: Pump Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the rated flow rate of the pump on a time basis. Default is that the pump is on and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: optional, if used pump losses transfered to zone as internal gains

fields.name: Skin Loss Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: optional. If zone identified in previous field then this determines the split between convection and radiation for the skin losses

fields.name: Design Power Sizing Method
fields.memo: Used to indicate which sizing factor is used to calculate Design Power Consumption. PowerPerFlow indicates that Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * scaling factor PowerPerFlowPerPressure indicates that Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * Design Pump Head * scaling factor / Motor Efficiency

fields.name: Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate

fields.name: Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate for head and motor efficiency

coil:heating:electric.name: Coil:Heating:Electric
coil:heating:electric.memo: Electric heating coil. If the coil is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list, then it is controlled on leaving air temperature and the Temperature Setpoint Node Name must be specified. If the coil is contained within another component such as an air terminal unit, zone HVAC equipment, or unitary system, then the coil is controlled by the parent component and the setpoint node name is not entered.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: Required if coil is temperature controlled.

zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:surfacegr.name: ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:SurfaceGroup
zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:surfacegr.memo: This is used to allow the coordinate control of several radiant system surfaces. Note that the following flow fractions must sum up to 1.0 The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 100, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

zonehvac:packagedterminalairconditioner.name: ZoneHVAC:PackagedTerminalAirConditioner
zonehvac:packagedterminalairconditioner.memo: Packaged terminal air conditioner (PTAC).  Forced-convection heating-cooling unit with supply fan, direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam) and fixed-position outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air inlet node for the PTAC must be a zone air exhaust Node.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air outlet node for the PTAC must be a zone air inlet node.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: Currently only one OutdoorAir:Mixer object type is available. This field should be left blank if the PTAC is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the OutdoorAir:Mixer is not used. This optional field specifies the name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. When used, this name needs to match name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. This field should be left blank if the PTAC is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size. Only used when supply air fan operating mode schedule values specify continuous fan (schedule values greater than 0 specify continuous fan operation). This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the cooling or heating coil is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Cooling Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to supply air flow rate during cooling operation. This field is set to zero flow when the PTAC is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Heating Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to supply air flow rate during heating operation. This field is set to zero flow when the PTAC is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: No Load Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when supply air fan operating mode schedule values specify continuous fan (schedule values greater than 0 specify continuous fan operation). This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the cooling or heating coil is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the outdoor air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. This field is set to zero flow when the PTAC is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works when continuous fan operation is used the entire simulation (all supply air fan operating mode schedule values are greater than 0). If any fan operating mode schedule values are 0 a Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff object must be used.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the fan object.

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Select the type of heating coil.

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the heating coil object.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Select the type of Cooling Coil. Only works with Coil:Cooling:DX:SingleSpeed or CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted or Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableSpeed.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match a DX cooling coil object.

fields.name: Fan Placement
fields.memo: Select fan placement as either blow through or draw through.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule Name values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling or heating coil). Schedule Name values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation).

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Air Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: For Capacity Control Method = SingleZoneVAV, enter the minimum air temperature limit for reduced fan speed.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: For Capacity Control Method = SingleZoneVAV, enter the maximum air temperature limit for reduced fan speed.

curve:bicubic.name: Curve:Bicubic
curve:bicubic.memo: Cubic curve with two independent variables. Input consists of the curve name, the ten coefficients, and the minimum and maximum values for each of the independent variables. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2 + C4*y + C5*y**2 + C6*x*y + C7*x**3 + C8*y**3 + C9*x**2*y + C10*x*y**2

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

windowthermalmodel:params.name: WindowThermalModel:Params
windowthermalmodel:params.memo: object is used to select which thermal model should be used in tarcog simulations

fields.name: Initial temperature
fields.memo: This is temperature in time of window fabrication

fields.name: Initial pressure
fields.memo: This is pressure in time of window fabrication

branchlist.name: BranchList
branchlist.memo: Branches MUST be listed in Flow order: Inlet branch, then parallel branches, then Outlet branch. Branches are simulated in the order listed.  Branch names cannot be duplicated within a single branch list.

faultmodel:enthalpysensoroffset:outdoora.name: FaultModel:EnthalpySensorOffset:OutdoorAir
faultmodel:enthalpysensoroffset:outdoora.memo: This object describes outdoor air enthalpy sensor offset

surfacecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:.name: SurfaceContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:DepositionVelocitySink
surfacecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:.memo: Simulate generic contaminant source driven by the boundary layer diffusion controlled model.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Initial Emission Rate. When the value is equal to 1.0, the time will be reset to zero.

sizingperiod:designday.name: SizingPeriod:DesignDay
sizingperiod:designday.memo: The design day object creates the parameters for the program to create the 24 hour weather profile that can be used for sizing as well as running to test the other simulation parameters. Parameters in this include a date (month and day), a day type (which uses the appropriate schedules for either sizing or simple tests), min/max temperatures, wind speeds, and solar radiation values.

fields.name: Day of Month
fields.memo: must be valid for Month field

fields.name: Day Type
fields.memo: Day Type selects the schedules appropriate for this design day

fields.name: Maximum Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: This field is required when field "Dry-Bulb Temperature Range Modifier Type" is not "TemperatureProfileSchedule".

fields.name: Daily Dry-Bulb Temperature Range
fields.memo: Must still produce appropriate maximum dry-bulb (within range) This field is not needed if Dry-Bulb Temperature Range Modifier Type is "delta".

fields.name: Dry-Bulb Temperature Range Modifier Type
fields.memo: Type of modifier to the dry-bulb temperature calculated for the timestep

fields.name: Dry-Bulb Temperature Range Modifier Day Schedule Name
fields.memo: Only used when previous field is "MultiplierSchedule", "DifferenceSchedule" or "TemperatureProfileSchedule". For type "MultiplierSchedule"  the hour/time interval values should specify the fraction (0-1) of the dry-bulb temperature range to be subtracted from the maximum dry-bulb temperature for each timestep in the day For type "DifferenceSchedule" the values should specify a number to be subtracted from the maximum dry-bulb temperature for each timestep in the day. Note that numbers in the difference schedule cannot be negative as that would result in a higher maximum than the maximum previously specified. For type "TemperatureProfileSchedule" the values should specify the actual dry-bulb temperature for each timestep in the day.

fields.name: Humidity Condition Type
fields.memo: values/schedules indicated here and in subsequent fields create the humidity values in the 24 hour design day conditions profile.

fields.name: Wetbulb or DewPoint at Maximum Dry-Bulb
fields.memo: Wetbulb or dewpoint temperature coincident with the maximum temperature. Required only if field Humidity Condition Type is "Wetbulb", "Dewpoint", "WetBulbProfileMultiplierSchedule", "WetBulbProfileDifferenceSchedule", or "WetBulbProfileDefaultMultipliers"

fields.name: Humidity Condition Day Schedule Name
fields.memo: Only used when Humidity Condition Type is "RelativeHumiditySchedule", "WetBulbProfileMultiplierSchedule", or "WetBulbProfileDifferenceSchedule" For type "RelativeHumiditySchedule", the hour/time interval values should specify relative humidity (percent) from 0.0 to 100.0. For type "WetBulbProfileMultiplierSchedule" the hour/time interval values should specify the fraction (0-1) of the wet-bulb temperature range to be subtracted from the maximum wet-bulb temperature for each timestep in the day (units = Fraction) For type "WetBulbProfileDifferenceSchedule" the values should specify a number to be subtracted from the maximum wet-bulb temperature for each timestep in the day. (units = deltaC)

fields.name: Humidity Ratio at Maximum Dry-Bulb
fields.memo: Humidity ratio coincident with the maximum temperature (constant humidity ratio throughout day). Required only if field Humidity Condition Type is "HumidityRatio".

fields.name: Enthalpy at Maximum Dry-Bulb
fields.memo: Enthalpy coincident with the maximum temperature. Required only if field Humidity Condition Type is "Enthalpy".

fields.name: Daily Wet-Bulb Temperature Range
fields.memo: Required only if Humidity Condition Type = "WetbulbProfileMultiplierSchedule" or "WetBulbProfileDefaultMultipliers"

fields.name: Barometric Pressure
fields.memo: This field's value is also checked against the calculated "standard barometric pressure" for the location.  If out of range (>10%) or blank, then is replaced by standard value.

fields.name: Wind Direction
fields.memo: North=0.0 East=90.0 0 and 360 are the same direction.

fields.name: Rain Indicator
fields.memo: Yes is raining (all day), No is not raining

fields.name: Snow Indicator
fields.memo: Yes is Snow on Ground, No is no Snow on Ground

fields.name: Daylight Saving Time Indicator
fields.memo: Yes -- use schedules modified for Daylight Saving Time Schedules. No - do not use schedules modified for Daylight Saving Time Schedules

fields.name: Beam Solar Day Schedule Name
fields.memo: if Solar Model Indicator = Schedule, then beam schedule name (for day)

fields.name: Diffuse Solar Day Schedule Name
fields.memo: if Solar Model Indicator = Schedule, then diffuse schedule name (for day)

fields.name: ASHRAE Clear Sky Optical Depth for Beam Irradiance (taub)
fields.memo: Required if Solar Model Indicator = ASHRAETau

fields.name: ASHRAE Clear Sky Optical Depth for Diffuse Irradiance (taud)
fields.memo: Required if Solar Model Indicator = ASHRAETau

fields.name: Sky Clearness
fields.memo: Used if Sky Model Indicator = ASHRAEClearSky or ZhangHuang 0.0 is totally unclear, 1.0 is totally clear

fluidcooler:singlespeed.name: FluidCooler:SingleSpeed
fluidcooler:singlespeed.memo: The fluid cooler is modeled as a cross flow heat exchanger (both streams unmixed) with single-speed fans (induced draft configuration).

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of fluid cooler water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of fluid cooler water outlet node

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define fluid cooler thermal performance by specifying the fluid cooler UA and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the fluid cooler nominal capacity

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate U-factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if fluid cooler Performance Input Method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal fluid cooler capacity

fields.name: Design Entering Water Temperature
fields.memo: Design Entering Water Temperature must be specified for both the performance input methods and its value must be greater than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Temperature
fields.memo: Design Entering Air Temperature must be specified for both the performance input methods and its value must be greater than Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature.

fields.name: Design Entering Air Wetbulb Temperature
fields.memo: Design Entering Air Wet-bulb Temperature must be specified for both the performance input methods and its value must be less than Design Entering Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

surfaceconvectionalgorithm:outside:adapt.name: SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:AdaptiveModelSelections
surfaceconvectionalgorithm:outside:adapt.memo: Options to change the individual convection model equations for dynamic selection when using AdaptiveConvectiongAlgorithm This object is only needed to make changes to the default model selections for any or all of the surface categories. This object is for the outside face, the side of the surface facing away from the thermal zone.

fields.name: Wind Convection Windward Vertical Wall Equation Source
Wind Convection Windward Equation Vertical Wall User Curve Name
fields.memo: The SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve named in this field is used when the previous field is set to UserCurve

fields.name: Wind Convection Leeward Vertical Wall Equation Source
Wind Convection Leeward Vertical Wall Equation User Curve Name
fields.memo: The SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve named in this field is used when the previous field is set to UserCurve

fields.name: Wind Convection Horizontal Roof Equation Source
Wind Convection Horizontal Roof User Curve Name
fields.memo: The SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve named in this field is used when the previous field is set to UserCurve

fields.name: Natural Convection Vertical Wall Equation Source
fields.memo: This is for vertical walls

fields.name: Natural Convection Vertical Wall Equation User Curve Name
fields.memo: The SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve named in this field is used when the previous field is set to UserCurve

fields.name: Natural Convection Stable Horizontal Equation Source
fields.memo: This is for horizontal surfaces with heat flow directed for stable thermal stratification

fields.name: Natural Convection Stable Horizontal Equation User Curve Name
fields.memo: The SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve named in this field is used when the previous field is set to UserCurve

fields.name: Natural Convection Unstable Horizontal Equation Source
Natural Convection Unstable Horizontal Equation User Curve Name
fields.memo: The SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside:UserCurve named in this field is used when the previous field is set to UserCurve

groundheattransfer:control.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Control
groundheattransfer:control.memo: Object determines if the Slab and Basement preprocessors are going to be executed.

generator:fuelsupply.name: Generator:FuelSupply
generator:fuelsupply.memo: Used only with Generator:FuelCell and Generator:MicroCHP

fields.name: Compressor Power Multiplier Function of Fuel Rate Curve Name
Liquid Generic Fuel Lower Heating Value
Liquid Generic Fuel Higher Heating Value
Liquid Generic Fuel CO2 Emission Factor
Number of Constituents in Gaseous Constituent Fuel Supply

pipingsystem:underground:pipesegment.name: PipingSystem:Underground:PipeSegment
pipingsystem:underground:pipesegment.memo: The pipe segment to be used in an underground piping system This object represents a single pipe leg positioned axially in the local z-direction, at a given x, y location in the domain

fields.name: X Position
fields.memo: This segment will be centered at this distance from the x=0 domain surface or the basement wall surface, based on whether a basement exists in this domain and the selection of the shift input field found in the domain object.

fields.name: Y Position
fields.memo: This segment will be centered at this distance away from the ground surface; thus this value represents the burial depth of this pipe segment.

fields.name: Flow Direction
fields.memo: This segment will be simulated such that the flow is in the selected direction.  This can allow for detailed analysis of circuiting effects in a single domain.

output:schedules.name: Output:Schedules
output:schedules.memo: Produces a condensed reporting that illustrates the full range of schedule values in the eio output file. In the style of input: DaySchedule,  WeekSchedule, and Annual Schedule.

coil:cooling:watertoairheatpump:equation.name: Coil:Cooling:WaterToAirHeatPump:EquationFit
coil:cooling:watertoairheatpump:equation.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil for water-to-air heat pump (includes electric compressor), single-speed, equation-fit model. Optional inputs for moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation. Equation-fit model uses normalized curves to describe the heat pump performance.

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Nominal Time for Condensate Removal to Begin
fields.memo: The nominal time for condensate to begin leaving the coil's condensate drain line at the coil's rated air flow and temperature conditions. Nominal time is equal to the ratio of the energy of the coil's maximum condensate holding capacity (J) to the coil's steady state latent capacity (W). Suggested value is 1000; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Ratio of Initial Moisture Evaporation Rate and Steady State Latent Capacity
fields.memo: Ratio of the initial moisture evaporation rate from the cooling coil (when the compressor first turns off) and the coil's steady state latent capacity at rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Suggested value is 1.5; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

zonehvac:baseboard:radiantconvective:wat.name: ZoneHVAC:Baseboard:RadiantConvective:Water
zonehvac:baseboard:radiantconvective:wat.memo: The number of surfaces can be expanded beyond 100, if necessary, by adding more groups to the end of the list

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Rated Average Water Temperature
fields.memo: Rated average water temperature is the average of the inlet and outlet water temperatures at rated conditions.

fields.name: Rated Water Mass Flow Rate
fields.memo: Standard is I=B=R Rating document where all baseboards are rated at either 0.063 kg/s (1 gpm) or 0.252 kg/s (4 gpm).  It is recommended that users find data for the baseboard heater that corresponds to performance at 0.063 kg/s unless the flow rate is expected to be above 0.252 kg/s. If the flow rate is expected to be above 0.252 kg/s, this field should be 0.252 kg/s.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity. Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity. This input field is rated heating capacity. Users must multiply the actual finned length published in the literature to determine the rated capacity. Rated Capacity is for an inlet air dry-bulb temperature of 18.0C, the Rated Water Mass Flow Rate of 0.063kg/s or 0.252kg/s, and the Rated Average Water Temperature between 32.2C and 115.6C.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Fraction of Radiant Energy Incident on People

hvactemplate:zone:unitary.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:Unitary
hvactemplate:zone:unitary.memo: Zone terminal unit, constant volume, no controls.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Unitary System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:Unitary, HVACTemplate:System:UnitaryHeatPump:AirTtoAir, or HVACTemplate:System:UnitarySystem object serving this zone.

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum runs through only this zone. Blank if none.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:Unitary or HVACTemplate:System:UnitaryHeatPump:AirToAir Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference SystemSupplyAirTemperature = use the value from HVACTemplate:System:Unitary or HVACTemplate:System:UnitaryHeatPump:AirToAir Heating Design Supply Air Temperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

airloophvac:supplypath.name: AirLoopHVAC:SupplyPath
airloophvac:supplypath.memo: A supply path can only contain AirLoopHVAC:ZoneSplitter and AirLoopHVAC:SupplyPlenum objects which may be in series or parallel.

fields.name: Supply Air Path Inlet Node Name

faultmodel:fouling:airfilter.name: FaultModel:Fouling:AirFilter
faultmodel:fouling:airfilter.memo: This object describes fault of dirty air filters

fields.name: Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Choose the type of the fan

fields.name: Fan Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a fan object

fields.name: Pressure Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule describing the variations of the fan pressure rise in terms of multipliers to the fan design pressure rise

fields.name: Fan Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve describes the relationship between the fan pressure rise and air flow rate

refrigeration:compressorlist.name: Refrigeration:CompressorList
refrigeration:compressorlist.memo: List of all the compressors included within a single refrigeration system (Refrigeration:System). Each list must contain at least one compressor. The order in which the individual compressors are listed here will be the order in which the compressors are dispatched to meet the system load. IMPORTANT: List compressor names in the order in which the compressors will be loaded Data is available for many compressors in the RefrigerationCompressor.idf dataset

zoneinfiltration:designflowrate.name: ZoneInfiltration:DesignFlowRate
zoneinfiltration:designflowrate.memo: Infiltration is specified as a design level which is modified by a Schedule fraction, temperature difference and wind speed: Infiltration=Idesign * FSchedule * (A + B*|(Tzone-Todb)| + C*WindSpd + D * WindSpd**2) If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Design Flow Rate Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of infiltration for this set of attributes Choices: Flow/Zone => Design Flow Rate -- simply enter Design Flow Rate Flow/Area => Flow per Zone Floor Area - Value * Floor Area (zone) = Design Flow Rate Flow/ExteriorArea => Flow per Exterior Surface Area - Value * Exterior Surface Area (zone) = Design Flow Rate Flow/ExteriorWallArea => Flow per Exterior Surface Area - Value * Exterior Wall Surface Area (zone) = Design Flow Rate AirChanges/Hour => Air Changes per Hour - Value * Floor Volume (zone) adjusted for m3/s = Design Volume Flow Rate "Idesign" in Equation is the result.

fields.name: Flow per Exterior Surface Area
fields.memo: use key Flow/ExteriorArea for all exterior surface area use key Flow/ExteriorWallArea to include only exterior wall area

fields.name: Constant Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "A" in Equation

fields.name: Temperature Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "B" in Equation

fields.name: Velocity Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "C" in Equation

fields.name: Velocity Squared Term Coefficient
fields.memo: "D" in Equation

generator:pvwatts.name: Generator:PVWatts
generator:pvwatts.memo: Describes a simple set of inputs for an array of photovoltaic (PV) modules as described in the PVWatts software. A series of different PVWatts arrays can be connected to a single electric load center (preferably through an ElectricLoadCenter:Inverter:PVWatts). Array tilt and azimuth can be either specified on this object or taken from a referenced building surface or shading surface. If a surface is specified, the array participates normally in all shading calculations.

fields.name: DC System Capacity
fields.memo: Nameplate rated DC system capacity in watts

fields.name: Array Geometry Type
fields.memo: TiltAzimuth - The tilt and azimuth angles are specified in the next two fields. An unshaded array is assumed. Surface - The array geometry (tilt and azimuth) as well as shading is determined from surface referenced.

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: The tilt angle is the angle from horizontal of the photovoltaic modules in the array.

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: For a fixed array, the azimuth angle is the angle clockwise from true north describing the direction that the array faces. For an array with one-axis tracking, the azimuth angle is the angle clockwise from true north of the axis of rotation.

fields.name: Ground Coverage Ratio
fields.memo: Applies only to arrays with one-axis tracking and is the ratio of module surface area to area of the ground or roof occupied by the array.

demandmanager:electricequipment.name: DemandManager:ElectricEquipment
demandmanager:electricequipment.memo: used for demand limiting ElectricEquipment objects.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Limit Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

fields.name: Limit Step Change
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Rotation Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

windowmaterial:glazing.name: WindowMaterial:Glazing
windowmaterial:glazing.memo: Glass material properties for Windows or Glass Doors Transmittance/Reflectance input method.

fields.name: Window Glass Spectral Data Set Name
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = Spectral

fields.name: Solar Transmittance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Front Side Solar Reflectance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Front Side is side closest to outdoor air

fields.name: Back Side Solar Reflectance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage Back Side is side closest to zone air

fields.name: Visible Transmittance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Front Side Visible Reflectance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Back Side Visible Reflectance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAverage

fields.name: Dirt Correction Factor for Solar and Visible Transmittance
Young's modulus
fields.memo: coefficient used for deflection calculations. Used only with complex fenestration when deflection model is set to TemperatureAndPressureInput

fields.name: Poisson's ratio
fields.memo: coefficient used for deflection calculations. Used only with complex fenestration when deflection model is set to TemperatureAndPressureInput

fields.name: Window Glass Spectral and Incident Angle Transmittance Data Set Table Name
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAndAngle

fields.name: Window Glass Spectral and Incident Angle Front Reflectance Data Set Table Name
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAndAngle

fields.name: Window Glass Spectral and Incident Angle Back Reflectance Data Set Table Name
fields.memo: Used only when Optical Data Type = SpectralAndAngle

coolingtower:variablespeed.name: CoolingTower:VariableSpeed
coolingtower:variablespeed.memo: This open wet tower model is based on purely empirical algorithms derived from manufacturer's performance data or field measurements. The user can select from two existing algorithms (CoolTools or YorkCalc), or they can enter their own correlation for approach temperature by using a variable speed tower model coefficient object. For a multi-cell tower, the capacity and air/water flow rate inputs are for the entire tower.

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower water outlet node

fields.name: Model Type
fields.memo: Determines the coefficients and form of the equation for calculating approach temperature

fields.name: Model Coefficient Name
fields.memo: Name of the tower model coefficient object. Used only when tower Model Type is either CoolToolsUserDefined or YorkCalcUserDefined.

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air wet-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the approach temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design range temperature. Design approach temp = outlet water temperature minus inlet air wet-bulb temperature at design conditions.

fields.name: Design Range Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the range temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design approach temperature. Design range = inlet water temperature minus outlet water temperature at design conditions.

fields.name: Design Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Water flow rate through the tower at design conditions

fields.name: Design Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Design (maximum) air flow rate through the tower

fields.name: Design Fan Power
fields.memo: Enter the fan motor electric input power at design (max) air flow through the tower Standard conversion for horsepower is 1 HP = 745.7 W

fields.name: Fan Power Ratio Function of Air Flow Rate Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: FPR = a + b*AFR + c*AFR**2 + d*AFR**3 FPR = fraction of the design fan power AFR = fraction of the design air flow rate If left blank, then fan power is assumed to be proportional to (air flow rate ratio)^3

fields.name: Minimum Air Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the minimum air flow rate ratio. This is typically determined by the variable speed drive that controls the fan motor speed. Valid entries are from 0.2 to 0.5.

fields.name: Fraction of Tower Capacity in Free Convection Regime
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of tower capacity in the free convection regime. This is the fraction of the tower capacity, at the current inlet air wet-bulb temperature, that is available when the tower fan is off. Manufacturers typically estimate the free convection capacity at approximately 10-15%. Values are entered as a fraction and can range from 0 to 0.2.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when water is not flowing through the tower.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Evaporation Loss Factor
fields.memo: Rate of water evaporated from the cooling tower and lost to the outdoor air [%/K] Evaporation loss is calculated as percentage of the circulating condenser water rate Value entered here is percent-per-degree K of temperature drop in the condenser water Typical values are from 0.15 to 0.27 [percent/K].

fields.name: Drift Loss Percent
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a percentage of circulating condenser water flow rate Typical values are between 0.002 and 0.2% The default value is 0.008%

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the cooling tower. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the tower in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. Typical values for tower operation are 3 to 5.  The default value is 3.

fields.name: Blowdown Makeup Water Usage Schedule Name
fields.memo: Makeup water usage due to blowdown results from occasionally draining a small amount of water in the tower basin to purge scale or other contaminants to reduce their concentration in order to maintain an acceptable level of water quality. Schedule values should reflect water usage in m3/s.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

fields.name: Cell Minimum  Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable minimal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Cell Maximum Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable maximal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

exterior:waterequipment.name: Exterior:WaterEquipment
exterior:waterequipment.memo: only used for Meter type reporting, does not affect building loads

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in Schedule should be fraction applied to capacity of the exterior water equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

zoneearthtube.name: ZoneEarthtube
zoneearthtube.memo: Earth Tube is specified as a design level which is modified by a Schedule fraction, temperature difference and wind speed: Earthtube=Edesign * Fschedule * (A + B*|(Tzone-Todb)| + C*WindSpd + D * WindSpd**2)

fields.name: Design Flow Rate
fields.memo: "Edesign" in Equation

fields.name: Minimum Zone Temperature when Cooling
fields.memo: this is the indoor temperature below which the earth tube is shut off

fields.name: Maximum Zone Temperature when Heating
fields.memo: this is the indoor temperature above which the earth tube is shut off

fields.name: Delta Temperature
fields.memo: This is the temperature difference between indoor and outdoor below which the earth tube is shut off

fields.name: Fan Pressure Rise
fields.memo: pressure rise across the fan
