fields.name: Phase Constant of Soil Surface Temperature
Constant Term Flow Coefficient
fields.memo: "A" in Equation

fields.name: Temperature Term Flow Coefficient
fields.memo: "B" in Equation

fields.name: Velocity Term Flow Coefficient
fields.memo: "C" in Equation

fields.name: Velocity Squared Term Flow Coefficient
fields.memo: "D" in Equation

zonehvac:dehumidifier:dx.name: ZoneHVAC:Dehumidifier:DX
zonehvac:dehumidifier:dx.memo: This object calculates the performance of zone (room) air dehumidifiers. Meant to model conventional direct expansion (DX) cooling-based room air dehumidifiers (reject 100% of condenser heat to the zone air), but this object might be able to be used to model other room air dehumidifier types.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off. Schedule values >0.0 (usually 1.0) indicate that the dehumidifier is available to operate.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air inlet node for the dehumidifier must be a zone air exhaust node.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air outlet node for the dehumidifier must be a zone air inlet node.

fields.name: Rated Water Removal
fields.memo: Rating point: air entering dehumidifier at 26.7 C (80 F) dry-bulb and 60% relative humidity.

fields.name: Rated Energy Factor
fields.memo: Rating point: air entering dehumidifier at 26.7 C (80 F) dry-bulb and 60% relative humidity.

fields.name: Water Removal Curve Name
fields.memo: Name of a curve that describes the water removal rate (normalized to rated conditions) as a function of the dry-bulb temperature and relative humidity of the air entering the dehumidifier. Curve output = (actual water removal/rated water removal) = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*RH + e*RH**2 + f*T*RH T = inlet air dry-bulb temperature (C) RH = inlet air RH (%)

fields.name: Energy Factor Curve Name
fields.memo: Name of a curve that describes the energy factor (normalized to rated conditions) as a function of the dry-bulb temperature and relative humidity of the air entering the dehumidifier. Curve output = (actual energy factor/rated energy factor) = a + b*T + c*T**2 + d*RH + e*RH**2 + f*T*RH T = inlet air dry-bulb temperature (C) RH = inlet air RH (%)

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: Name of a curve that describes the part load fraction (PLF) of the system as a function of the part load ratio. Used to calculate dehumidifier run time fraction and electric power. quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (dehumidification load/steady state water removal capacity)

fields.name: Minimum Dry-Bulb Temperature for Dehumidifier Operation
fields.memo: Dehumidifier shut off if inlet air (zone) temperature is below this value. This value must be less than the Maximum Dry-Bulb Temperature for Dehumidifier Operation.

fields.name: Maximum Dry-Bulb Temperature for Dehumidifier Operation
fields.memo: Dehumidifier shut off if inlet air (zone) temperature is above this value. This value must be greater than the Minimum Dry-Bulb Temperature for Dehumidifier Operation.

fields.name: Off-Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power consumed when the dehumidifier is available to operate, but does not operate (i.e., no high humidity load to be met). Off cycle parasitic power is 0 when the availability schedule is 0. This electric load is considered as a heat gain to the zone air.

fields.name: Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
fields.memo: Name of storage tank used to collect water removed by the dehumidifier.

setpointmanager:returntemperature:hotwat.name: SetpointManager:ReturnTemperature:HotWater
setpointmanager:returntemperature:hotwat.memo: This setpoint manager is used to place a temperature setpoint on a plant supply outlet node based on a target return water setpoint. The setpoint manager attempts to achieve the desired return water temperature by adjusting the supply temperature setpoint based on the plant conditions at each system time step.

fields.name: Plant Loop Supply Outlet Node
fields.memo: This is the name of the supply outlet node for the plant being controlled by this setpoint manager.  Typically this is where the setpoint will be actuated for supply equipment to control to, but not necessarily.  This setpoint manager will mine that information from the internal plant data structures.

fields.name: Plant Loop Supply Inlet Node
fields.memo: This is the name of the supply inlet node for the plant being controlled with this setpoint manager. The temperature on this node is controlled by actuating the supply setpoint.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: This is the minimum reset temperature for the hot water supply.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Temperature Setpoint
fields.memo: This is the maximum hot water supply temperature setpoint.  This is also used as the default setpoint during no-load or negative-load conditions and during initialization.

fields.name: Return Temperature Setpoint Input Type
fields.memo: This defines whether the hot water return temperature target is constant, scheduled, or specified on the supply inlet node by a separate setpoint manager.

fields.name: Return Temperature Setpoint Constant Value
fields.memo: This is the desired return temperature target, which is met by adjusting the supply temperature setpoint. This constant value is only used if the Design Hot Water Return Temperature Input Type is Constant

fields.name: Return Temperature Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: This is the desired return temperature target, which is met by adjusting the supply temperature setpoint. This is a schedule name to allow the return temperature target value to be scheduled.  This field is only used if the Design Hot Water Return Temperature Input Type is Scheduled

zonecontrol:thermostat:thermalcomfort.name: ZoneControl:Thermostat:ThermalComfort
zonecontrol:thermostat:thermalcomfort.memo: If you use a ZoneList in the Zone or ZoneList name field then this definition applies to all the zones in the ZoneList.

fields.name: Averaging Method
fields.memo: The method used to calculate thermal comfort dry-bulb temperature setpoint for multiple people objects in a zone

fields.name: Specific People Name
fields.memo: Used only when Averaging Method = SpecificObject in the previous field.

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Control Type Schedule Name
fields.memo: The Thermal Comfort Control Type Schedule contains values that are appropriate control types. Thermal Comfort Control types are integers: 0 - Uncontrolled (floating), 1 = ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:SingleHeating 2 = ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:SingleCooling 3 = ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:SingleHeatingOrCooling 4 = ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:DualSetpoint

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Control 1 Name
fields.memo: Control type names are names for individual control type objects. Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Control 2 Name
fields.memo: Control Type names are names for individual control type objects. Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Control 3 Name
fields.memo: Control type names are names for individual control type objects. Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

fields.name: Thermal Comfort Control 4 Name
fields.memo: Control type names are names for individual control type objects. Schedule values in these objects list actual setpoint temperatures for the control types

curve:rectangularhyperbola1.name: Curve:RectangularHyperbola1
curve:rectangularhyperbola1.memo: Rectangular hyperbola type 1 curve with one independent variable. Input consists of the curve name, the three coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = ((C1*x)/(C2+x))+C3

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

outdoorair:mixer.name: OutdoorAir:Mixer
outdoorair:mixer.memo: Outdoor air mixer. Node names cannot be duplicated within a single OutdoorAir:Mixer object or across all outdoor air mixers.

fields.name: Mixed Air Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Mixed Air Node

fields.name: Outdoor Air Stream Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Outdoor Air Stream Node

fields.name: Relief Air Stream Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Relief Air Stream Node

fields.name: Return Air Stream Node Name
fields.memo: Name of Return Air Stream Node

site:groundtemperature:deep.name: Site:GroundTemperature:Deep
site:groundtemperature:deep.memo: These temperatures are specifically for the ground heat exchangers that would use "deep" (3-4 m depth) ground temperatures for their heat source. They are not used in other models.

hotwaterequipment.name: HotWaterEquipment
hotwaterequipment.memo: Sets internal gains for hot water equipment in the zone. If you use a ZoneList in the Zone name field then this definition applies to all those zones.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in Schedule should be fraction applied to design level of hot water equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Design Level Calculation Method
fields.memo: The entered calculation method is used to create the maximum amount of hot water equipment for this set of attributes Choices: EquipmentLevel => Design Level -- simply enter power input of equipment Watts/Area or Power/Area => Power per Zone Floor Area -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Floor Area = Equipment Level Watts/Person or Power/Person => Power per Person -- enter the number to apply.  Value * Occupants = Equipment Level

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

coil:heating:steam.name: Coil:Heating:Steam
coil:heating:steam.memo: Steam heating coil. Condenses and sub-cools steam at loop pressure and discharges condensate through steam traps to low pressure condensate line.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Coil Control Type
fields.memo: Use ZoneLoadControl if the coil is contained within another component such as an air terminal unit, zone HVAC equipment, or unitary system. Use TemperatureSetpointControl if the coil is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list.

fields.name: Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: Required if Coil Control Type is TemperatureSetpointControl

pipingsystem:underground:domain.name: PipingSystem:Underground:Domain
pipingsystem:underground:domain.memo: The ground domain object for underground piping system simulation.

fields.name: Xmax
fields.memo: Domain extent in the local 'X' direction

fields.name: Ymax
fields.memo: Domain extent in the local 'Y' direction

fields.name: Zmax
fields.memo: Domain extent in the local 'Y' direction

fields.name: X-Direction Mesh Density Parameter
fields.memo: If mesh type is symmetric geometric, this should be an even number.

fields.name: X-Direction Geometric Coefficient
fields.memo: optional Only used if mesh type is symmetric geometric

fields.name: Y-Direction Mesh Density Parameter
fields.memo: If mesh type is symmetric geometric, this should be an even number.

fields.name: Y-Direction Geometric Coefficient
fields.memo: optional Only used if mesh type is symmetric geometric

fields.name: Z-Direction Mesh Density Parameter
fields.memo: If mesh type is symmetric geometric, this should be an even number.

fields.name: Z-Direction Geometric Coefficient
fields.memo: optional Only used if mesh type is symmetric geometric

fields.name: Soil Specific Heat
fields.memo: This is a dry soil property, which is adjusted for freezing effects by the simulation algorithm.

fields.name: Soil Moisture Content Volume Fraction at Saturation
This Domain Includes Basement Surface Interaction
fields.memo: if Yes, then the following basement inputs are used if No, then the following basement inputs are *ignored*

fields.name: Width of Basement Floor in Ground Domain
fields.memo: Required only if Domain Has Basement Interaction

fields.name: Depth of Basement Wall In Ground Domain
fields.memo: Required only if Domain Has Basement Interaction

fields.name: Shift Pipe X Coordinates By Basement Width
fields.memo: Required only if Domain Has Basement Interaction

fields.name: Name of Basement Wall Boundary Condition Model
fields.memo: Required only if Domain Has Basement Interaction

fields.name: Name of Basement Floor Boundary Condition Model
fields.memo: Required only if Domain Has Basement Interaction

fields.name: Convergence Criterion for the Outer Cartesian Domain Iteration Loop
Maximum Iterations in the Outer Cartesian Domain Iteration Loop
Evapotranspiration Ground Cover Parameter
fields.memo: This specifies the ground cover effects during evapotranspiration calculations.  The value roughly represents the following cases: = 0   : concrete or other solid, non-permeable ground surface material = 0.5 : short grass, much like a manicured lawn = 1   : standard reference state (12 cm grass) = 1.5 : wild growth

fields.name: Number of Pipe Circuits Entered for this Domain

refrigeration:caseandwalkinlist.name: Refrigeration:CaseAndWalkInList
refrigeration:caseandwalkinlist.memo: Provides a list of all the refrigerated cases, walk in coolers, or air chillers cooled by a single refrigeration system.  Note that the names of all cases, walk-ins ,air chillers, and CaseAndWalkInLists must be unique.  That is, you cannot give a list the same name as one of list items. This list may contain a combination of case and walk-in names OR a list of air chiller names.  Air chillers may not be included in any list that also includes cases or walk-ins.

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitImport:To:Variable
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.memo: Declares Erl variable as having global scope No spaces allowed in names used for Erl variables

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during the first call of EnergyPlus.

zonehvac:packagedterminalheatpump.name: ZoneHVAC:PackagedTerminalHeatPump
zonehvac:packagedterminalheatpump.memo: Packaged terminal heat pump (PTHP). Forced-convection heating-cooling unit with supply fan, direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, DX heating coil (air-to-air heat pump), supplemental heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam), and fixed-position outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air inlet node for the PTHP must be a zone air exhaust node.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Air outlet node for the PTHP must be a zone air inlet node.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: Currently only one OutdoorAir:Mixer object type is available. This field should be left blank if the PTHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the OutdoorAir:Mixer is not used. This optional field specifies the name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. When used, this name needs to match name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. This field should be left blank if the PTHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size. Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Cooling Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to supply air flow rate during cooling operation. This field is set to zero flow when the PTHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Heating Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to supply air flow rate during heating operation. This field is set to zero flow when the PTHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: No Load Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when heat pump Fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the outdoor air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. This field is set to zero flow when the PTHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works with fan operating mode is continuous.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match a fan object.

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with Coil:Heating:DX:SingleSpeed or Coil:Heating:DX:VariableSpeed.

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the DX Heating Coil object.

fields.name: Heating Convergence Tolerance
fields.memo: Defines Heating convergence tolerance as a fraction of Heating load to be met.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with Coil:Cooling:DX:SingleSpeed or CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted or Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableSpeed.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the DX Cooling Coil object.

fields.name: Cooling Convergence Tolerance
fields.memo: Defines Cooling convergence tolerance as a fraction of the Cooling load to be met.

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coil.

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the supplemental heating coil object.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature from Supplemental Heater
fields.memo: Supply air temperature from the supplemental heater will not exceed this value.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Supplemental Heater Operation
fields.memo: Supplemental heater will not operate when outdoor temperature exceeds this value.

fields.name: Fan Placement
fields.memo: Select fan placement as either blow through or draw through.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling or heating coil). Schedule Name values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this field is left blank.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Air Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: For Capacity Control Method = SingleZoneVAV, enter the minimum air temperature limit for reduced fan speed.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: For Capacity Control Method = SingleZoneVAV, enter the maximum air temperature limit for reduced fan speed.

coil:heating:dx:variablerefrigerantflow:.name: Coil:Heating:DX:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl
coil:heating:dx:variablerefrigerantflow:.memo: This is a key object in the new physics based VRF model applicable for Fluid Temperature Control. It describes the the indoor unit coil of the system at heating mode. Used with ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow. Outdoor unit is modeled separately, see AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl or AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl:HR

fields.name: Availability Schedule
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that defines the availability of the coil Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off. All other values denote the unit is available If this field is left blank, the unit is available the entire simulation

fields.name: Coil Air Inlet Node
fields.memo: the inlet node to the coil

fields.name: Coil Air Outlet Node
fields.memo: the outlet node to the coil

fields.name: Rated Total Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Supply air fan heat is not included

fields.name: Indoor Unit Condensing Temperature Function of Subcooling Curve Name

setpointmanager:singlezone:heating.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:Heating
setpointmanager:singlezone:heating.memo: This setpoint manager detects the control zone load to meet the current heating setpoint, zone inlet node flow rate, and zone node temperature, and calculates a setpoint temperature for the supply air that will satisfy the zone heating load for the control zone.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

airterminal:singleduct:vav:heatandcool:r.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:HeatAndCool:Reheat
airterminal:singleduct:vav:heatandcool:r.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume for both cooling and heating, with reheat coil (hot water, electric, gas, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Damper Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: the outlet node of the damper and the inlet node of the reheat coil this is an internal node to the terminal unit and connects the damper and reheat coil

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: the inlet node to the terminal unit and the damper

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: fraction of maximum air flow

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The outlet node of the terminal unit and the reheat coil. This is also the zone inlet node.

fields.name: Maximum Reheat Air Temperature
fields.memo: Specifies the maximum allowable supply air temperature leaving the reheat coil. If left blank, there is no limit and no default. If unknown, 35C (95F) is recommended.

controller:mechanicalventilation.name: Controller:MechanicalVentilation
controller:mechanicalventilation.memo: This object is used in conjunction with Controller:OutdoorAir to specify outdoor ventilation air based on outdoor air specified in the DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object The Controller:OutdoorAir object is associated with a specific air loop, so the outdoor air flow rates specified in Controller:MechanicalVentilation correspond to the zones attached to that specific air loop. Duplicate groups of Zone name, Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name, and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name to increase allowable number of entries

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the controller uses the values from the associated Controller:OutdoorAir. Schedule values greater than 0 indicate mechanical ventilation is enabled

hvactemplate:system:vav.name: HVACTemplate:System:VAV
hvactemplate:system:vav.memo: Variable Air Volume (VAV) air loop with optional heating coil and optional preheat.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on; VAV System always on.  Schedule is used in availability manager and fan scheduling. Also see "Night Cycle Control" field.

fields.name: Supply Fan Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Supply Fan Minimum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is only used to set a minimum part load on the VAV fan power curve. Autosize or zero is recommended.

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Cooling Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Heating Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Preheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Preheat Coil Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: Preheat Coil Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Preheat Coil Setpoint Schedule Name specified.

fields.name: Gas Preheat Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the Minimum Outdoor Air Flow Rate If blank, multiplier is always one

fields.name: Economizer Upper Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Lower Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor temperature below which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Upper Enthalpy Limit
fields.memo: Outdoor enthalpy above which economizer is disabled and heat recovery is enabled (if available). Blank means no limit.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Supply Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

fields.name: Night Cycle Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Applicable only if Night Cycle Control is Cycle On Control Zone.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Setpoint Reset Type
fields.memo: Overrides Cooling Coil Setpoint Schedule Name None = no reset, control to Cooling Coil Design Setpoint Temperature or Schedule Warmest = reset as warm as possible yet meet all zone cooling loads at max supply air flow rate OutdoorAirTemperatureReset = reset based on outdoor air temperature (18.0C at 15.6C ODB, to the Cooling Design Setpoint at 26.7C) WarmestTemperatureFirst = reset as warm as possible yet meet all zone cooling loads at min supply air flow rate

fields.name: Heating Coil Setpoint Reset Type
fields.memo: Overrides Heating Coil Setpoint Schedule Name None = no reset, control to Heating Coil Design Setpoint Temperature or Schedule OutdoorAirTemperatureReset = reset based on outdoor air temperature (Heating Design Setpoint at -6.7C ODB to Heating Design Setpoint minus 5.2C at 10C ODB) min supply air flow rate

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint as required to meet the humidity setpoint.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Dehumidification Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Sizing Option
fields.memo: Select whether autosized system supply flow rate is the sum of Coincident or NonCoincident zone air flow rates.

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Return Fan Part-Load Power Coefficients
fields.memo: This field selects a predefined set of fan power coefficients. The ASHRAE 90.1-2004 Appendix G coefficients are from TABLE G3.1.3.15, Method 2. The other sets of coefficients are from the EnergyPlus Input Output Reference, Fan Coefficient Values table.

heatexchanger:airtoair:flatplate.name: HeatExchanger:AirToAir:FlatPlate
heatexchanger:airtoair:flatplate.memo: Flat plate air-to-air heat exchanger, typically used for exhaust or relief air heat recovery.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Economizer Lockout
fields.memo: Yes means that the heat exchanger will be locked out (off) when the economizer is operating or high humidity control is active

fields.name: Ratio of Supply to Secondary hA Values
fields.memo: Ratio of h*A for supply side to h*A for exhaust side

output:constructions.name: Output:Constructions
output:constructions.memo: Adds a report to the eio output file which shows details for each construction, including overall properties, a list of material layers, and calculated results related to conduction transfer functions.

designspecification:zonehvac:sizing.name: DesignSpecification:ZoneHVAC:Sizing
designspecification:zonehvac:sizing.memo: This object is used to describe general scalable zone HVAC equipment sizing which are referenced by other objects.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the cooling supply air volume flow rate. None is used when a cooling coil is not included in the Zone HVAC Equip or this field may be blank. SupplyAirFlowRate => selected when the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate is specified. FlowPerFloorArea => selected when the supply air volume flow rate is determined from total floor area served by the Zone HVAC unit and Flow Per Floor Area value specified. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingAirflow => is selected when the supply air volume is determined from a user specified fraction and the autosized cooling supply air flow rate value determined by the simulation. FlowPerCoolingCapacity => is selected when the supply air volume is determined from user specified flow per Cooling Capacity and Cooling Capacity determined by the simulation.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the magnitude of supply air volume flow rate during cooling operation. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is SupplyAirFlowRate. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the cooling supply air volume flow rate per total conditioned floor area. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Cooling Fraction of Autosized Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling supply air flow rate. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingAirflow. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the cooling supply air volume flow rate unit cooling capacity. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerCoolingCapacity. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the supply air volume flow rate When No Cooling or Heating is Required. None is used when a cooling or heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC Equipment or this field may be blank. SupplyAirFlowRate => selected when the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate is specified. FlowPerFloorArea => selected when the supply air volume flow rate is determined from total floor area served by the Zone HVAC unit and Flow Per Floor Area is specified. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingAirflow => is selected when the supply air volume is determined from a user specified fraction and the Autosized cooling supply air flow rate value determined by the simulation. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingAirflow => is selected when the supply air volume is determined from a user specified fraction and the Autosized heating supply air flow rate value determined by the simulation.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate during when no cooling or heating is required. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is SupplyAirFlowRate.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate per total floor area. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea.

fields.name: No Load Fraction of Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling supply air flow rate. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingAirflow.

fields.name: No Load Fraction of Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating supply air flow rate. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingAirflow.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating supply air volume flow rate. None is used when a heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC Equipment or this field may be blank. SupplyAirFlowRate => selected when the magnitude of the heating supply air volume flow rate is specified.  FlowPerFloorArea => selected when the supply air volume flow rate is determined from total floor area served by a Zone HVAC unit and user specified value of Flow Per Floor Area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingAirflow => is selected when the supply air volume is determined from a user specified fraction and the Autosized heating supply air flow rate value determined by the simulation. FlowPerHeatingCapacity => is selected when the supply air volume is determined from user specified flow per Heating Capacity and Heating Capacity determined by the simulation.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate during heating operation. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is SupplyAirFlowRate. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating supply air volume flow rate per total conditioned floor area. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Heating Fraction of Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating supply air flow rate. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingAirflow. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate per unit heating capacity. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerHeatingCapacity. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC equipment.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the cooling design capacity for scalable sizing. None is used when a cooling coils is not included in the Zone HVAC Equipment or this field may be blank. If this input field is left blank, then the design cooling capacity is set to zero. CoolingDesignCapacity => selected when the design cooling capacity value is specified or auto-sized. CapacityPerFloorArea => selected when the design cooling capacity is determine from user specified cooling capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity => is selected when the design cooling capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design cooling capacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design cooling capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method CoolingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Cooling Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the cooling design capacity per zone floor area. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Cooling Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto-sized cooling design capacity. Required field when the cooling design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity for scalable sizing. None is used when a heating coil is not included in the Zone HVAC Equipment or this field may be blank. If this input field is left blank, then the design heating capacity is set to zero. HeatingDesignCapacity => selected when the design heating capacity value is specified or auto-sized. CapacityPerFloorArea => selected when the design cooling capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per flow area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity => is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity. Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area. Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto-sized heating design capacity. Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

lifecyclecost:nonrecurringcost.name: LifeCycleCost:NonrecurringCost
lifecyclecost:nonrecurringcost.memo: A non-recurring cost happens only once during the study period. For costs that occur more than once during the study period on a regular schedule, use the LifeCycleCost:RecurringCost object.

fields.name: Cost
fields.memo: Enter the non-recurring cost value. For construction and other capital costs the value entered is typically a positive value. For salvage costs the value entered is typically a negative value which represents the money paid to the investor for the equipment at the end of the study period.

fields.name: Start of Costs
fields.memo: Enter when the costs start. The First Year of Cost is based on the number of years past the Start of Costs. For most non-recurring costs the Start of Costs should be Base Period which begins at the base month and year.

fields.name: Years from Start
fields.memo: This field and the Months From Start field together represent the time from either the start of the Service Period on the service month and year or start of the Base Period on the base month and year (depending on the Start of Cost field) that the costs start to occur. Only integers should be entered representing whole years.

fields.name: Months from Start
fields.memo: This field and the Years From Start field together represent the time from either the start of the Service Period on the service month and year or start of the Base Period on the base month and year (depending on the Start of Cost field) that the costs start to occur. Only integers should be entered representing whole months. The Years From Start (times 12) and Months From Start are added together.

zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:con.name: ZoneContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:Constant
zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:con.memo: Sets internal generic contaminant gains and sinks in a zone with constant values.

fields.name: Design Generation Rate
fields.memo: The values represent source.

fields.name: Generation Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Design Generation Rate

fields.name: Design Removal Coefficient
fields.memo: The value represent sink.

fields.name: Removal Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Design removal Coefficient

daylightingdevice:tubular.name: DaylightingDevice:Tubular
daylightingdevice:tubular.memo: Defines a tubular daylighting device (TDD) consisting of three components: a dome, a pipe, and a diffuser. The dome and diffuser are defined separately using the FenestrationSurface:Detailed object.

fields.name: Dome Name
fields.memo: This must refer to a subsurface object of type TubularDaylightDome

fields.name: Diffuser Name
fields.memo: This must refer to a subsurface object of type TubularDaylightDiffuser Delivery zone is specified in the diffuser object

fields.name: Total Length
fields.memo: The exterior exposed length is the difference between total and sum of zone lengths

fields.name: Effective Thermal Resistance
fields.memo: R value between TubularDaylightDome and TubularDaylightDiffuser

plantequipmentoperationschemes.name: PlantEquipmentOperationSchemes
plantequipmentoperationschemes.memo: Operation schemes are listed in "priority" order.  Note that each scheme must address the entire load and/or condition ranges for the simulation. The actual one selected for use will be the first that is "Scheduled" on.  That is, if control scheme 1 is not "on" and control scheme 2 is -- then control scheme 2 is selected. Only plant equipment should be listed on a Control Scheme for this item.

airconditioner:variablerefrigerantflow:f.name: AirConditioner:VariableRefrigerantFlow:FluidTemperatureControl:HR
airconditioner:variablerefrigerantflow:f.memo: This is a key object in the new physics based VRF Heat Recovery (HR) model applicable for Fluid Temperature Control. It describes the VRF HR system excluding the performance of indoor units. Indoor units are modeled separately in the ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow object

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that defines the availability of the unit Schedule values of 0 denote the unit is off. All other values denote the unit is available If this field is left blank, the unit is available the entire simulation

fields.name: Zone Terminal Unit List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneTerminalUnitList. This list connects zone terminal units to this heat pump

fields.name: Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the total evaporative capacity in watts at rated conditions This is the capacity corresponding to the max compressor speed at rated conditions The actual evaporative capacity is obtained by multiplying the rated capacity with the modification factor calculated by Evaporative Capacity Multiplier Function of Temperature Curve

fields.name: Rated Compressor Power Per Unit of Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the rated compressor power per Watt of rated evaporative capacity [W/W] Rated compressor power corresponds to the max compressor speed at rated conditions The actual compressor power is obtained by multiplying the rated power with the modification factor calculated by Compressor Power Multiplier Function of Temperature Curve

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Temperature in Cooling Only Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation Cooling is disabled below this temperature

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Temperature in Cooling Only Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation Cooling is disabled above this temperature

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Temperature in Heating Only Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation Heating is disabled below this temperature

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Air Temperature in Heating Only Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation Heating is disabled below this temperature

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
fields.memo: The minimum outdoor temperature below which heat recovery mode will not operate.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
fields.memo: The maximum outdoor temperature above which heat recovery mode will not operate.

fields.name: Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm for Indoor Unit
Reference Evaporating Temperature for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is ConstantTemp Evaporating temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Reference Condensing Temperature for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is ConstantTemp Condensing temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Evaporating Temperature Minimum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Evaporating temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Evaporating Temperature Maximum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Evaporating temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Condensing Temperature Minimum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Condensing temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Variable Condensing Temperature Maximum for Indoor Unit
fields.memo: This field is used if Refrigerant Temperature Control Algorithm is VariableTemp Condensing temperature is the refrigerant temperature, not air temperature

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Evaporator Rated Bypass Factor
Outdoor Unit Condenser Rated Bypass Factor
Difference between Outdoor Unit Evaporating Temperature and Outdoor Air Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
Outdoor Unit Heat Exchanger Capacity Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the rated capacity ratio between the main and supplementary outdoor unit heat exchangers [W/W]

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Fan Power Per Unit of Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor unit fan power per Watt of rated evaporative capacity [W/W]

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Fan Flow Rate Per Unit of Rated Evaporative Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor unit fan flow rate per Watt of rated evaporative capacity [W/W]

fields.name: Outdoor Unit Evaporating Temperature Function of Superheating Curve Name
Outdoor Unit Condensing Temperature Function of Subcooling Curve Name
Diameter of Main Pipe for Suction Gas
fields.memo: used to calculate the piping loss

fields.name: Diameter of Main Pipe for Discharge Gas
fields.memo: used to calculate the piping loss

fields.name: Length of Main Pipe Connecting Outdoor Unit to the First Branch Joint
fields.memo: used to calculate the heat loss of the main pipe

fields.name: Equivalent Length of Main Pipe Connecting Outdoor Unit to the First Branch Joint
fields.memo: used to calculate the refrigerant pressure drop of the main pipe

fields.name: Height Difference Between Outdoor Unit and Indoor Units
fields.memo: Difference between outdoor unit height and indoor unit height Positive means outdoor unit is higher than indoor unit Negative means outdoor unit is lower than indoor unit

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Power per Compressor
fields.memo: Enter the value of the resistive heater located in the compressor(s). This heater is used to warm the refrigerant and oil when the compressor is off

fields.name: Number of Compressors
fields.memo: Enter the total number of compressor. This input is used only for crankcase heater calculations.

fields.name: Ratio of Compressor Size to Total Compressor Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the ratio of the first stage compressor to total compressor capacity All other compressors are assumed to be equally sized. This inputs is used only for crankcase heater calculations

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which the crankcase heaters are disabled

fields.name: Defrost Strategy
fields.memo: Select a defrost strategy. Reverse cycle reverses the operating mode from heating to cooling to melt frost formation on the condenser coil The resistive strategy uses a resistive heater to melt the frost.

fields.name: Defrost Control
fields.memo: Choose a defrost control type Either use a fixed Timed defrost period or select OnDemand to defrost only when necessary

fields.name: Defrost Energy Input Ratio Modifier Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: A valid performance curve must be used if ReverseCycle defrost strategy is selected

fields.name: Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode Only applicable if timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the size of the resistive defrost heating element Only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which the defrost operation is disabled

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Cooling Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the fractional capacity available at the start of heat recovery mode. The capacity exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Modifier and Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Cooling Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Cooling Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Fraction
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Cooling Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the fractional electric consumption rate at the start of heat recovery mode. The electric consumption rate exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Modifier and Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Time Constant
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Cooling Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Heating Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the fractional capacity available at the start of heat recovery mode. The capacity exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Modifier and Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Heating Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Heating Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Initial Heat Recovery Heating Energy Fraction
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Heating Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the fractional electric consumption rate at the start of heat recovery mode. The electric consumption rate exponentially approaches the steady-state value according to the inputs for Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Modifier and Heat Recovery Cooling Energy Time Constant

fields.name: Heat Recovery Heating Energy Time Constant
fields.memo: This is used to describe the transition from Heating Only mode to Heat Recovery mode Enter the time constant used to model the transition from cooling only mode to heat recovery mode

fields.name: Compressor Inverter Efficiency
fields.memo: Efficiency of the compressor inverter

fields.name: Compressor Evaporative Capacity Correction Factor
fields.memo: Describe the evaporative capacity difference because of system configuration difference between test bed and real system.

fields.name: Number of Compressor Loading Index Entries
fields.memo: Load index describe the compressor operational state, either a single compressor or multiple compressors, at different load levels. First index represents minimal capacity operation Last index represents full capacity operation

airflownetwork:multizone:windpressurecoe.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientArray
airflownetwork:multizone:windpressurecoe.memo: Used only if Wind Pressure Coefficient (WPC) Type = Input in the AirflowNetwork:SimulationControl object. Number of WPC Values in the corresponding AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientValues object must be the same as the number of wind directions specified for this AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientArray object.

fields.name: Wind Direction 1
fields.memo: Enter the wind direction corresponding to the 1st WPC Array value.

fields.name: Wind Direction 2

fields.memo: Enter the wind direction corresponding to the 23rd WPC Array value.
