setpointmanager:multizone:heating:averag.name: SetpointManager:MultiZone:Heating:Average
setpointmanager:multizone:heating:averag.memo: This setpoint manager sets the average supply air temperature based on the heating load requirements of all controlled zones in an air loop served by a central air-conditioner.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

groundheattransfer:slab:matlprops.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:MatlProps
groundheattransfer:slab:matlprops.memo: This object contains the material properties for the materials used in the model. The fields are mostly self explanatory.

fields.name: RHO: Slab Material density
fields.memo: Density of Slab Material typical value= 2300.0

fields.name: RHO: Soil Density
fields.memo: Density of Soil Material typical value= 1200.0

fields.name: CP: Slab CP
fields.memo: Specific Heat of Slab Material typical value=650.0

fields.name: CP: Soil CP
fields.memo: Specific Heat of Soil Material typical value= 1200.0

fields.name: TCON: Slab k
fields.memo: Conductivity of Slab Material typical value= .9

fields.name: TCON: Soil k
fields.memo: Conductivity of Soil Material typical value= 1.0

airloophvac:unitaryheatonly.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatOnly
airloophvac:unitaryheatonly.memo: Unitary system, heating-only with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling) and heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam). Identical to AirLoopHVAC:Unitary:Furnace:HeatOnly.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Unitary System Air Inlet Node Name
Unitary System Air Outlet Node Name
Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: A fan operating mode schedule value of 0 indicates cycling fan mode (supply air fan cycles on and off in tandem with the heating coil). Any other schedule value indicates continuous fan mode (supply air fan operates continuously regardless of heating coil operation). Leaving this schedule name blank will default to cycling fan mode for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This value should be > 0 and <= than the fan air flow rate.

fields.name: Supply Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works with continuous fan operating mode (i.e. fan operating mode schedule values are greater than 0).

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

energymanagementsystem:meteredoutputvari.name: EnergyManagementSystem:MeteredOutputVariable
energymanagementsystem:meteredoutputvari.memo: This object sets up an EnergyPlus output variable from an Erl variable

fields.name: EMS Variable Name
fields.memo: must be an acceptable EMS variable, no spaces

fields.name: EMS Program or Subroutine Name
fields.memo: optional for global scope variables, required for local scope variables

fields.name: Resource Type
fields.memo: choose the type of fuel, water, electricity, pollution or heat rate that should be metered.

fields.name: Group Type
fields.memo: choose a general classification, building (internal services), HVAC (air systems), or plant (hydronic systems), or system

fields.name: End-Use Category
fields.memo: choose how the metered output should be classified for end-use category

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table. enter a user-defined subcategory for this metered output

fields.name: Units
fields.memo: optional but will result in dimensionless units for blank EnergyPlus units are standard SI units

construction:cfactorundergroundwall.name: Construction:CfactorUndergroundWall
construction:cfactorundergroundwall.memo: Alternate method of describing underground wall constructions

fields.name: C-Factor
fields.memo: Enter C-Factor without film coefficients or soil

fields.name: Height
fields.memo: Enter height of the underground wall

table:oneindependentvariable.name: Table:OneIndependentVariable
table:oneindependentvariable.memo: Allows entry of tabular data pairs as alternate input for performance curve objects. Performance curve objects can be created using these inputs. Linear Table Equation: Output = a + bX Linear solution requires a minimum of 2 data pairs Quadratic Table Equation: Output = a + b*X + c*X**2 Quadratic solution requires a minimum of 3 data pairs Cubic Table Equation: Output = a + b*X + c* X**2 + d*X**3 Cubic solution requires a minimum of 4 data pairs Quartic Table Equation: Output = a + b*X + c* X**2 + d*X**3 + e*X**4 Quartic solution requires a minimum of 5 data pairs Exponent Table Equation: Output = a + b*X**c Exponent solution requires a minimum of 4 data pairs

fields.name: Minimum Value of X
fields.memo: used only when Interpolation Type is Evaluate Curve to Limits

fields.name: Maximum Value of X
fields.memo: used only when Interpolation Type is Evaluate Curve to Limits

fields.name: Minimum Table Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this table lookup object used only when Interpolation Type is Evaluate Curve to Limits

fields.name: Maximum Table Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this table lookup object used only when Interpolation Type is Evaluate Curve to Limits

fields.name: Normalization Reference
fields.memo: This field is used to normalize the following ouput data. The minimum and maximum table output fields are also normalized. If this field is blank or 1, the table data presented in the following fields will be used with normalization reference set to 1.

chiller:electric.name: Chiller:Electric
chiller:electric.memo: This chiller model is the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Chiller performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to third order polynomial equations.  Three sets of coefficients are required.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the maximum flow & for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Fluid Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = AirCooled or EvaporativelyCooled when Heat Recovery is specified

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 2 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 3 of Full Load Ratio Curve
Chilled Water Outlet Temperature Lower Limit
Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered. Heat recovery is only available with Condenser Type = WaterCooled.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the chiller is not operating.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Condenser Heat Recovery Relative Capacity Fraction
fields.memo: This optional field is the fraction of total rejected heat that can be recovered at full load

fields.name: Heat Recovery Inlet High Temperature Limit Schedule Name
fields.memo: This optional schedule of temperatures will turn off heat recovery if inlet exceeds the value

fields.name: Heat Recovery Leaving Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: This optional field provides control over the heat recovery Using this triggers a model more suited to series bundle and chillers with higher temperature heat recovery If this field is not used, the bundles are modeled as being in parallel

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

zonecapacitancemultiplier:researchspecia.name: ZoneCapacitanceMultiplier:ResearchSpecial
zonecapacitancemultiplier:researchspecia.memo: Multiplier altering the relative capacitance of the air compared to an empty zone

fields.name: Zone or ZoneList Name
fields.memo: If this field is left blank, the multipliers are applied to all the zones not specified

fields.name: Temperature Capacity Multiplier
fields.memo: Used to alter the capacitance of zone air with respect to heat or temperature

fields.name: Humidity Capacity Multiplier
fields.memo: Used to alter the capacitance of zone air with respect to moisture or humidity ratio

fields.name: Carbon Dioxide Capacity Multiplier
fields.memo: Used to alter the capacitance of zone air with respect to zone air carbon dioxide concentration

fields.name: Generic Contaminant Capacity Multiplier
fields.memo: Used to alter the capacitance of zone air with respect to zone air generic contaminant concentration

coolingtower:singlespeed.name: CoolingTower:SingleSpeed
coolingtower:singlespeed.memo: This tower model is based on Merkel's theory, which is also the basis for the tower model in ASHRAE's HVAC1 Toolkit. The open wet cooling tower is modeled as a counter flow heat exchanger with a single-speed fan drawing air through the tower (induced-draft configuration). Added fluid bypass as an additional capacity control. 8/2008. For a multi-cell tower, the capacity and air/water flow rate inputs are for the entire tower.

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower water inlet node

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of tower water outlet node

fields.name: Design Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Leave field blank if tower performance input method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Design Fan Power
fields.memo: This is the fan motor electric input power

fields.name: Design U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: Leave field blank if tower performance input method is NominalCapacity

fields.name: Free Convection Air Flow Rate Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate.

fields.name: Free Convection U-Factor Times Area Value
Free Convection U-Factor Times Area Value Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate and the Performance Input Method is UFactorTimesAreaAndDesignWaterFlowRate

fields.name: Performance Input Method
fields.memo: User can define tower thermal performance by specifying the tower UA, the Design Air Flow Rate and the Design Water Flow Rate, or by specifying the tower nominal capacity

fields.name: Heat Rejection Capacity and Nominal Capacity Sizing Ratio
Nominal Capacity
fields.memo: Nominal tower capacity with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt (3 gpm/ton). Nominal tower capacity times (1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Free Convection Capacity
fields.memo: Tower capacity in free convection regime with entering water at 35C (95F), leaving water at 29.44C (85F), entering air at 25.56C (78F) wet-bulb temperature and 35C (95F) dry-bulb temperature. Design water flow rate assumed to be 5.382E-8 m3/s per watt of nominal tower capacity (3 gpm/ton). Tower free convection capacity times (1.25) gives the actual tower heat rejection at these operating conditions.

fields.name: Free Convection Nominal Capacity Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is only used if the previous field is set to autocalculate

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air dry-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the tower's design inlet air wet-bulb temperature

fields.name: Design Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the approach temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design range temperature. Design approach temp = outlet water temperature minus inlet air wet-bulb temperature at design conditions. Autosized to 3.9 deltaC.

fields.name: Design Range Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the range temperature corresponding to the design inlet air wet-bulb temperature and design approach temperature. Design range = inlet water temperature minus outlet water temperature at design conditions. Autosized to 5.5 deltaC.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when water is not flowing through the tower.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Evaporation Loss Factor
fields.memo: Rate of water evaporation from the cooling tower and lost to the outdoor air [%/K] Evaporation loss is calculated as percentage of the circulating condenser water rate Value entered here is percent-per-degree K of temperature drop in the condenser water Typical values are from 0.15 to 0.27 [%/K].

fields.name: Drift Loss Percent
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a percentage of circulating condenser water flow rate Typical values are between 0.002 and 0.2% The default value is 0.008%

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the cooling tower. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the tower in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. Typical values for tower operation are 3 to 5.  The default value is 3.

fields.name: Blowdown Makeup Water Usage Schedule Name
fields.memo: Makeup water usage due to blowdown results from occasionally draining a small amount of water in the tower basin to purge scale or other contaminants to reduce their concentration in order to maintain an acceptable level of water quality. Schedule values should reflect water usage in m3/s.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

fields.name: Cell Minimum  Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable minimal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Cell Maximum Water Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: The allowable maximal fraction of the nominal flow rate per cell

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

roof.name: Roof
roof.memo: Allows for simplified entry of roofs (exterior). View Factor to Ground is automatically calculated.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of Roof

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Flat Roofs are tilted 0 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: If not Flat, Starting coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Roof

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: Along X Axis

fields.name: Width
fields.memo: Along Y Axis

output:debuggingdata.name: Output:DebuggingData
output:debuggingdata.memo: switch eplusout.dbg file on or off

fields.name: Report Debugging Data
fields.memo: value=1 then yes all others no

fields.name: Report During Warmup
fields.memo: value=1 then always even during warmup  all others no

generator:combustionturbine.name: Generator:CombustionTurbine
generator:combustionturbine.memo: This generator model is the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Generator performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to second order polynomial equations.  Three sets of coefficients are required.

fields.name: Part Load Based Fuel Input Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output this curve is multiplied to the Temperature Based Fuel Input Curve to determine Fuel Energy In

fields.name: Temperature Based Fuel Input Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*AT + c*AT**2 AT = Ambient Delta T this curve is multiplied to the Part Load Based Fuel Input Curve to determine Fuel Energy In

fields.name: Exhaust Flow Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*AT + c*AT**2 AT = Ambient Delta T

fields.name: Part Load Based Exhaust Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output this curve is multiplied to the Temperature Based Exhaust Temperature Curve to determine Exhaust Temperature

fields.name: Temperature Based Exhaust Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*AT + c*AT**2 AT = Ambient Delta T this curve is multiplied to the Part Load Based Exhaust Temperature Curve to determine Exhaust Temperature

fields.name: Heat Recovery Lube Energy Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = Ratio of Generator Load to Rated Power Output

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: curve = C1 * Rated Power Output**C2

fields.name: Coefficient 2 of U-Factor Times Area Curve
fields.memo: curve = C1 * Rated Power Output**C2 typical value .9

fields.name: Maximum Exhaust Flow per Unit of Power Output
Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: if non-zero, then inlet, outlet nodes must be entered.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node

pump:variablespeed.name: Pump:VariableSpeed
pump:variablespeed.memo: This pump model is described in the ASHRAE secondary HVAC toolkit.

fields.name: Design Pump Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet

fields.name: Design Power Consumption
fields.memo: When autosized the type of scaling factor is chosen in the input field Design Power Sizing Method

fields.name: Motor Efficiency
fields.memo: This is the motor efficiency only. When the Design Power Consumption is autosized using PowerPerFlowPerPressure, the Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used in addition to the motor efficiency.

fields.name: Fraction of Motor Inefficiencies to Fluid Stream
Coefficient 1 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 2 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 3 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Coefficient 4 of the Part Load Performance Curve
Design Minimum Flow Rate
fields.memo: When autosized the scaling factor is the input field Design Minimum Flow Rate Fraction

fields.name: Pump Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the rated flow rate of the pump on a time basis. Default is that the pump is on and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations.

fields.name: Pump Curve Name
fields.memo: This references any single independent variable polynomial curve in order to do pressure vs. flow calculations for this pump.  The available types are then: Linear, Quadratic, Cubic, and Quartic The non-dimensional pump pressure relationship is of the following form: (psi = C4*phi^4 + C3*phi^3 + C2*phi^2 + C1*phi + C0) Where the non-dimensional variables are defined as: delP = rho * ((N/60)^2) * (D^2) * psi mdot = rho * (N/60) * (D^3) * phi

fields.name: Impeller Diameter
fields.memo: "D" in above expression in field A6

fields.name: Pump rpm Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the rpm of the pump on a time basis. Default is that the pump is on and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: optional, if used pump losses transfered to zone as internal gains

fields.name: Skin Loss Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: optional. If zone identified in previous field then this determines the split between convection and radiation for the skin losses

fields.name: Design Power Sizing Method
fields.memo: Used to indicate which sizing factor is used to calculate Design Power Consumption. PowerPerFlow indicates that Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * scaling factor PowerPerFlowPerPressure indicates that Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head is used as scaling factor. Design Power Consumption = Design Maximum Flow Rate * Design Pump Head * scaling factor / Motor Efficiency

fields.name: Design Electric Power per Unit Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate

fields.name: Design Shaft Power per Unit Flow Rate per Unit Head
fields.memo: Used to size Design Power Consumption from design flow rate for head and motor efficiency

fields.name: Design Minimum Flow Rate Fraction
fields.memo: Used to size Design Minimum Flow Rate

setpointmanager:multizone:humidity:minim.name: SetpointManager:MultiZone:Humidity:Minimum
setpointmanager:multizone:humidity:minim.memo: This setpoint manager sets the minimum supply air humidity ratio based on humidification requirements of a controlled zone with critical humidity ratio setpoint (i.e., a zone with the highest humidity ratio setpoint) in an air loop served by a central air-conditioner.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the humidity ratio will be set

schedule:week:daily.name: Schedule:Week:Daily
schedule:week:daily.memo: A Schedule:Week:Daily contains 12 Schedule:Day:Hourly objects, one for each day type.

temperingvalve.name: TemperingValve
temperingvalve.memo: Temperature-controlled diversion valve used to divert flow around one or more plant components such as a hot water heater. It can only be used on one of two branches between a Splitter and a Mixer.

fields.name: Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of a Node

fields.name: Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of a Node

fields.memo: Name of a Node

componentcost:adjustments.name: ComponentCost:Adjustments
componentcost:adjustments.memo: Used to perform various modifications to the construction costs to arrive at an estimate for total project costs. This object allows extending the line item model so that the overall costs of the project will reflect various profit and fees.

fields.name: Miscellaneous Cost per Conditioned Area
fields.memo: based on conditioned floor area for cost not accounted for in current line item cost model

fields.name: Regional Adjustment Factor
fields.memo: for use with average data in line item and Misc cost models

coil:heating:gas:multistage.name: Coil:Heating:Gas:MultiStage
coil:heating:gas:multistage.memo: Gas heating coil, multi-stage. If the coil is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list, then it is controlled on leaving air temperature and the Temperature Setpoint Node Name must be specified. If the coil is contained within another component such as an air terminal unit, zone HVAC equipment, or unitary system, then the coil is controlled by the parent component and the setpoint node name is not entered.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: optional, used if coil is temperature control and not load-base controlled.

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve, PLF = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve, PLF = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLF = part load fraction PLR = part load ratio (sensible heating load/steady state heating capacity) Coil runtime fraction = Part Load Ratio / PLF This part load degradation is for coil performance & will increase the gas consumption of the coil due to transient coil operation.

fields.name: Parasitic Gas Load
fields.memo: parasitic gas load associated with the gas coil operation (i.e., standing pilot)

fields.name: Number of Stages
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for coil capacity and Gas Burner Efficiency.

fields.name: Stage 1 Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Stage 1 parasitic electric load associated with the gas coil operation such as an inducer fan, etc.  This will be modified by the part load ratio to reflect the time of operation in a timestep.

fields.name: Stage 2 Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Stage 2 parasitic electric load associated with the gas coil operation such as an inducer fan, etc.  This will be modified by the part load ratio to reflect the time of operation in a timestep.

fields.name: Stage 3 Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Stage 3 parasitic electric load associated with the gas coil operation such as an inducer fan, etc.  This will be modified by the part load ratio to reflect the time of operation in a timestep.

fields.name: Stage 4 Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Stage 4 parasitic electric load associated with the gas coil operation such as an inducer fan, etc.  This will be modified by the part load ratio to reflect the time of operation in a timestep.

plantequipmentoperation:outdoordrybulbdi.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorDryBulbDifference
plantequipmentoperation:outdoordrybulbdi.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor dry-bulb temperature difference operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive ranges based the difference between a reference node temperature and the outdoor dry-bulb temperature.

airflownetwork:intrazone:node.memo: This object represents a node in a zone in the combination of RoomAir and AirflowNetwork model.

airterminal:singleduct:vav:reheat:variab.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:Reheat:VariableSpeedFan
airterminal:singleduct:vav:reheat:variab.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume, with reheat coil (hot water, electric, gas, or steam) and variable-speed fan. These units are usually employed in underfloor air distribution (UFAD) systems where the air is supplied at low static pressure through an underfloor plenum. The fan is used to control the flow of conditioned air that enters the space.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name

fields.memo: The name of the HVAC system node that is the air inlet node for the terminal unit. This is also the air inlet node for the unit's fan.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name

site:groundreflectance.name: Site:GroundReflectance
site:groundreflectance.memo: Specifies the ground reflectance values used to calculate ground reflected solar. The ground reflectance can be further modified when snow is on the ground by Site:GroundReflectance:SnowModifier.

airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:co.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:ConstantVolume:CooledBeam
airterminal:singleduct:constantvolume:co.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, constant volume, with cooled beam (active or passive).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Maximum Total Chilled Water Volumetric Flow Rate
Number of Beams
fields.memo: Number of individual beam units in the zone

fields.name: Beam Length
fields.memo: Length of an individual beam unit

fields.name: Coil Surface Area per Coil Length
Model Parameter a0
fields.memo: Free area of the coil in plan view per unit beam length

convergencelimits.name: ConvergenceLimits
convergencelimits.memo: Specifies limits on HVAC system simulation timesteps and iterations. This item is an advanced feature that should be used only with caution.

fields.name: Minimum System Timestep
fields.memo: 0 sets the minimum to the zone timestep (ref: Timestep) 1 is normal (ratchet down to 1 minute) setting greater than zone timestep (in minutes) will effectively set to zone timestep

fields.name: Minimum Plant Iterations
fields.memo: Controls the minimum number of plant system solver iterations within a single HVAC iteration Larger values will increase runtime but might improve solution accuracy for complicated plant systems Complex plants include: several interconnected loops, heat recovery, thermal load following generators, etc.

fields.name: Maximum Plant Iterations
fields.memo: Controls the maximum number of plant system solver iterations within a single HVAC iteration Smaller values might decrease runtime but could decrease solution accuracy for complicated plant systems

zonehvac:airdistributionunit.name: ZoneHVAC:AirDistributionUnit
zonehvac:airdistributionunit.memo: Central air system air distribution unit, serves as a wrapper for a specific type of air terminal unit. This object is referenced in a ZoneHVAC:EquipmentList.

fields.name: Air Distribution Unit Outlet Node Name
Nominal Upstream Leakage Fraction
fields.memo: fraction at system design Flow; leakage Flow constant, leakage fraction varies with variable system Flow Rate.

fields.name: Design Specification Air Terminal Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: This optional field is the name of a DesignSpecification:AirTerminal:Sizing object which specifies sizing adjustments to be made for this terminal unit.

generator:fuelcell:stackcooler.name: Generator:FuelCell:StackCooler
generator:fuelcell:stackcooler.memo: This object is optional and is used to define details needed to model the stack cooler on PEMFC.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Inlet Node Name
Heat Recovery Water Outlet Node Name
Stack Cooler U-Factor Times Area Value
Stack Cogeneration Exchanger Nominal Flow Rate
Stack Cogeneration Exchanger Nominal Heat Transfer Coefficient
Stack Cogeneration Exchanger Nominal Heat Transfer Coefficient Exponent
Stack Cooler Pump Heat Loss Fraction
Stack Air Cooler Fan Coefficient f0
Stack Air Cooler Fan Coefficient f1
Stack Air Cooler Fan Coefficient f2

setpointmanager:multizone:cooling:averag.name: SetpointManager:MultiZone:Cooling:Average
setpointmanager:multizone:cooling:averag.memo: This setpoint manager sets the average supply air temperature based on the cooling load requirements of all controlled zones in an air loop served by a central air-conditioner.

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

chiller:absorption.name: Chiller:Absorption
chiller:absorption.memo: This indirect absorption chiller model is the empirical model from the Building Loads and System Thermodynamics (BLAST) program.  Chiller performance curves are generated by fitting catalog data to third order polynomial equations.  Two sets of coefficients are required.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the max flow & for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: The steam use coefficients below specify the steam use as a fraction of chiller operating capacity

fields.name: Coefficient 1 of the Hot Water or Steam Use Part Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 2 of the Hot Water or Steam Use Part Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 3 of the Hot Water or Steam Use Part Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 1 of the Pump Electric Use Part Load Ratio Curve
fields.memo: The pump electric use coefficients specify the pumping power as a Fraction of Nominal pumping power

fields.name: Coefficient 2 of the Pump Electric Use Part Load Ratio Curve
Coefficient 3 of the Pump Electric Use Part Load Ratio Curve
Chilled Water Outlet Temperature Lower Limit
Chiller Flow Mode
fields.memo: Select operating mode for fluid flow through the chiller. "NotModulated" is for either variable or constant pumping with flow controlled by the external plant system. "ConstantFlow" is for constant pumping with flow controlled by chiller to operate at full design flow rate.  "LeavingSetpointModulated" is for variable pumping with flow controlled by chiller to vary flow to target a leaving temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Generator Heat Source Type
fields.memo: The Generator side of the chiller can be connected to a hot water or steam plant where the generator inlet and outlet nodes are connected to a plant loop. If the generator is not connected to a plant loop, and the generator inlet/outlet nodes are not used, this field should be specified as steam or left blank. When a plant is not used, the model assumes steam as the heat source.

fields.name: Degree of Subcooling in Steam Generator
fields.memo: This field is not used when the generator inlet/outlet nodes are not specified or the generator is connected to a hot water loop.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

windowproperty:shadingcontrol.name: WindowProperty:ShadingControl
windowproperty:shadingcontrol.memo: Specifies the type, location, and controls for window shades, window blinds, and switchable glazing. Referenced by the surface objects for exterior windows and glass doors (ref: FenestrationSurface:Detailed, Window, and GlazedDoor).

fields.name: Construction with Shading Name
fields.memo: Required if Shading Type = SwitchableGlazing Required if Shading Type = interior or exterior shade or blind, or exterior screen, and "Shading Device Material Name" is not specified. If both "Construction with Shading Name" and "Shading Device Material Name" are entered, the former takes precedence.

fields.name: Shading Control Type
fields.memo: OnIfScheduleAllows requires that Schedule Name be specified and Shading Control Is Scheduled = Yes. AlwaysOn, AlwaysOff and OnIfScheduleAllows are the only valid control types for ExteriorScreen. The following six control types are used primarily to reduce zone cooling load due to window solar gain Following entry should be used only if Shading Type = SwitchableGlazing and window is in a daylit zone The following three control types are used to reduce zone Heating load. They can be used with any Shading Type but are most appropriate for opaque interior or exterior shades with high insulating value ("opaque movable insulation") The following two control types are used to reduce zone heating and cooling load. They can be used with any Shading Type but are most appropriate for translucent interior or exterior shades with high insulating value ("translucent movable insulation") The following two control types are used to reduce zone Cooling load. They can be used with any Shading Type but are most appropriate for interior or exterior blinds,interior or exterior shades with low insulating value, or switchable glazing The following four control types require that both Setpoint and Setpoint2 be specified Setpoint will correspond to outdoor air temp or zone air temp (deg C) Setpoint2 will correspond to solar on window or horizontal solar (W/m2)

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Required if Shading Control Is Scheduled = Yes. If schedule value = 1, shading control is active, i.e., shading can take place only if the control test passes. If schedule value = 0, shading is off whether or not the control test passes. Schedule Name is required if Shading Control Is Scheduled = Yes. If Schedule Name is not specified, shading control is assumed to be active at all times.

fields.name: Setpoint
fields.memo: W/m2 for solar-based controls, W for cooling- or heating-based controls, deg C for temperature-based controls. Unused for Shading Control Type = AlwaysOn, AlwaysOff, OnIfScheduleAllows, OnIfHighGlare, Glare, and DaylightIlluminance

fields.name: Shading Control Is Scheduled
fields.memo: If Yes, Schedule Name is required; if No, Schedule Name is not used. Shading Control Is Scheduled = Yes is required if Shading Control Type = OnIfScheduleAllows.

fields.name: Glare Control Is Active
fields.memo: If Yes and window is in a daylit zone, shading is on if zone's discomfort glare index exceeds the maximum discomfort glare index specified in the Daylighting object referenced by the zone. The glare test is OR'ed with the test specified by Shading Control Type. Glare Control Is Active = Yes is required if Shading Control Type = OnIfHighGlare.

fields.name: Shading Device Material Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a WindowMaterial:Shade, WindowMaterial:Screen or WindowMaterial:Blind object. Required if "Construction with Shading Name" is not specified. Not used if Shading Control Type = SwitchableGlazing, BetweenGlassShade, or BetweenGlassBlind. If both "Construction with Shading Name" and "Shading Device Material Name" are entered, the former takes precedence.

fields.name: Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds
fields.memo: Used only if Shading Type = InteriorBlind, ExteriorBlind or BetweenGlassBlind. If choice is ScheduledSlatAngle then Slat Angle Schedule Name is required.

fields.name: Slat Angle Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Shading Type = InteriorBlind, ExteriorBlind or BetweenGlassBlind. Required if Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds = ScheduledSlatAngle Schedule values should be degrees (0 minimum, 180 maximum)

fields.name: Setpoint 2
fields.memo: W/m2 for solar-based controls, deg C for temperature-based controls. Used only as the second setpoint for the following two-setpoint control types: OnIfHighOutdoorAirTempAndHighSolarOnWindow, OnIfHighOutdoorAirTempAndHighHorizontalSolar, OnIfHighZoneAirTempAndHighSolarOnWindow, and OnIfHighZoneAirTempAndHighHorizontalSolar

setpointmanager:singlezone:onestageheati.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:OneStageHeating
setpointmanager:singlezone:onestageheati.memo: This object can be used with CoilSystem:Heating:DX, Coil:Heating:Fuel, Coil:Heating:Electric to model on/off cycling control of single stage air systems. Setpoints are modulated to run coil full on or full off depending on zone conditions. Intended for use with ZoneControl:Thermostat:StagedDualSetpoint.

fields.name: Heating Stage On Supply Air Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This is the setpoint value applied when heating device is to cycle ON

fields.name: Heating Stage Off Supply Air Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This is the setpoint value applied when heating device is to cycle OFF

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

branch.name: Branch
branch.memo: List components on the branch in simulation and connection order Note: this should NOT include splitters or mixers which define endpoints of branches

fields.name: Pressure Drop Curve Name
fields.memo: Optional field to include this branch in plant pressure drop calculations This field is only relevant for branches in PlantLoops and CondenserLoops Air loops do not account for pressure drop using this field Valid curve types are: Curve:Functional:PressureDrop or one of Curve:{Linear,Quadratic,Cubic,Exponent}')

plantequipmentoperation:outdoorrelativeh.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorRelativeHumidity
plantequipmentoperation:outdoorrelativeh.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor relative humidity range operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive outdoor relative humidity ranges.

schedule:day:list.name: Schedule:Day:List
schedule:day:list.memo: Schedule:Day:List will allow the user to list 24 hours worth of values, which can be sub-hourly in nature.

fields.name: Interpolate to Timestep
fields.memo: when the interval does not match the user specified timestep a "Average" choice will average between the intervals request (to timestep resolution.  A "No" choice will use the interval value at the simulation timestep without regard to if it matches the boundary or not. A "Linear" choice will interpolate linearly between successive values.

fields.name: Minutes per Item
fields.memo: Must be evenly divisible into 60

fields.name: Compressor Suction and Discharge Pressure Drop
Constant Part of Electromechanical Power Losses
Loss Factor
fields.memo: Used to define electromechanical loss that is proportional to the theoretical power %

groundheattransfer:basement:interior.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:Interior
groundheattransfer:basement:interior.memo: Provides the information needed to simulate the inside boundary conditions for the Basement preprocessor ground heat transfer simulation.

fields.name: COND: Flag: Is the basement conditioned?
fields.memo: for EnergyPlus this should be TRUE

fields.name: HIN: Downward convection only heat transfer coefficient
HIN: Upward convection only heat transfer coefficient
HIN: Horizontal convection only heat transfer coefficient
HIN: Downward combined (convection and radiation) heat transfer coefficient
HIN: Upward combined (convection and radiation) heat transfer coefficient
HIN: Horizontal combined (convection and radiation) heat transfer coefficient

setpointmanager:mixedair.name: SetpointManager:MixedAir
setpointmanager:mixedair.memo: The Mixed Air Setpoint Manager is meant to be used in conjunction with a Controller:OutdoorAir object. This setpoint manager is used to establish a temperature setpoint at the mixed air node.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

fields.name: Cooling Coil Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Optional field used to limit economizer operation to prevent freezing of DX cooling coil.

fields.name: Cooling coil Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Optional field used to limit economizer operation to prevent freezing of DX cooling coil.

fields.name: Minimum Temperature at Cooling Coil Outlet Node
fields.memo: Optional field used to limit economizer operation to prevent freezing of DX cooling coil.

plantequipmentlist.name: PlantEquipmentList
plantequipmentlist.memo: List plant equipment in order of operating priority, 1st in list will be used 1st, etc Use only plant equipment in this list. If no equipment object types and equipment names are specified, then the corresponding PlantEquipmentOperation:* object will assume all available plant equipment for the loop should be OFF (not operate) within the specified lower/upper limit.

coil:heating:water.name: Coil:Heating:Water
coil:heating:water.memo: Hot water heating coil, NTU-effectiveness model, assumes a cross-flow heat exchanger. Two options for capacity inputs: UA and water flow rate or capacity and design temperatures.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: U-Factor Times Area Value
fields.memo: UA value under rating conditions

fields.name: Rated Ratio for Air and Water Convection
Design Water Temperature Difference
fields.memo: This input field is optional. If specified, it is used for sizing the Design Water Flow Rate. If blank or omitted, the Loop Design Temperature Difference value specified in Sizing:Plant object is used for sizing the Design Water Flow Rate.

window:interzone.name: Window:Interzone
window:interzone.memo: Allows for simplified entry of interzone windows (adjacent to other zones).

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Building Surface Name
fields.memo: Name of Surface (Wall, usually) the Window is on (i.e., Base Surface) Window assumes the azimuth and tilt angles of the surface it is on.

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Specify a surface name in an adjacent zone for known interior windows. Specify a zone name of an adjacent zone to automatically generate the interior window in the adjacent zone. a blank field will set up a Window in an adjacent zone (same zone as adjacent to base surface)

fields.name: Multiplier
fields.memo: Used only for Surface Type = WINDOW, GLASSDOOR or DOOR Non-integer values will be truncated to integer

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Window starting coordinate is specified relative to the Base Surface origin.

fields.name: Starting Z Coordinate
fields.memo: How far up the wall the Window starts. (in 2-d, this would be a Y Coordinate)

refrigeration:gascooler:aircooled.name: Refrigeration:GasCooler:AirCooled
refrigeration:gascooler:aircooled.memo: The transcritical refrigeration system requires a single gas cooler to reject the system heat.

fields.name: Rated Total Heat Rejection Rate Curve Name
fields.memo: Be sure the rating corresponds to the correct refrigerant (R744) HeatRejection(W)=C1 +C2(Gas Cooler Outlet Temp - Entering Air Temp, deg C) Will be adjusted for elevation automatically

fields.name: Gas Cooler Fan Speed Control Type
Rated Fan Power
fields.memo: Power for gas cooler fan(s) corresponding to rated total heat rejection effect.

fields.name: Minimum Fan Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Minimum air flow fraction through gas cooler fan

fields.name: Transition Temperature
fields.memo: Temperature at which system transitions between subcritical and transcritical operation.

fields.name: Transcritical Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Temperature difference between the CO2 exiting the gas cooler and the air entering the gas cooler during transcritical operation.

fields.name: Subcritical Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Temperature difference between the saturated condensing temperature and the air temperature during subcritical operation.

fields.name: Minimum Condensing Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum saturated condensing temperature during subcritical operation.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: If field is left blank, then the model assumes that the inlet air conditions are the outdoor air conditions for the current timestep (e.g., no adjustment for height above ground).

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Gas Cooler Refrigerant Operating Charge Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Gas Cooler Receiver Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Gas Cooler Outlet Piping Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

roomairsettings:underfloorairdistributio.name: RoomAirSettings:UnderFloorAirDistributionExterior
roomairsettings:underfloorairdistributio.memo: Applicable to exterior spaces that are served by an underfloor air distribution system. The dominant sources of heat gain should be from people, equipment, and other localized sources located in the occupied part of the room, as well as convective gain coming from a warm window. Used with RoomAirModelType = CrossVentilation.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of Zone being described. Any existing zone name

fields.name: Thermostat Height
fields.memo: Height of thermostat/temperature control sensor above floor

fields.name: Comfort Height
fields.memo: Height at which Air temperature is calculated for comfort purposes

fields.name: Temperature Difference Threshold for Reporting
fields.memo: Minimum temperature difference between upper and lower layer temperatures above which UFAD auxiliary outputs are calculated. These outputs are 'UF Transition Height' and 'UF Average Temp Gradient'.  They are set to zero values when the temperature difference is less than the threshold and the output 'UF Zone Is Mixed' is set to 1

fields.name: Transition Height
fields.memo: User-specified height above floor of boundary between occupied and upper subzones

fields.name: Coefficient A in formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2
fields.memo: Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient B in formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2
fields.memo: Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient C in formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2
fields.memo: Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient D in formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2
fields.memo: Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

fields.name: Coefficient E in formula Kc = A*Gamma**B + C + D*Gamma + E*Gamma**2
fields.memo: Kc is the fraction of the total zone load attributable to the lower subzone

airterminal:singleduct:vav:heatandcool:n.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:HeatAndCool:NoReheat
airterminal:singleduct:vav:heatandcool:n.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume for both cooling and heating, with no reheat coil.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The outlet node of the terminal unit. This is also the zone inlet node.

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: fraction of maximum air flow

hybridmodel:zone.name: HybridModel:Zone
hybridmodel:zone.memo: Zones with measured air temperature data and a range of dates. If the range of temperature measurement dates includes a leap day, the weather data should include a leap day.

fields.name: Calculate Zone Internal Thermal Mass
fields.memo: Use measured temperature data to calculate zone temperature capacity multiplier Zone Air Infiltration Rate and Zone Internal Thermal Mass calculations cannot be performed simultaneously

fields.name: Calculate Zone Air Infiltration Rate
fields.memo: Use measured temperature data to calculate zone air infiltration air flow rate Zone Air Infiltration Rate and Zone Internal Thermal Mass calculations cannot be performed simultaneously

fields.name: Zone Measured Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: from Schedule:File

curve:sigmoid.name: Curve:Sigmoid
curve:sigmoid.memo: Sigmoid curve with one independent variable. Input consists of the curve name, the five coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1+C2/[1+exp((C3-x)/C4)]**C5

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

coil:waterheating:desuperheater.name: Coil:WaterHeating:Desuperheater
coil:waterheating:desuperheater.memo: Desuperheater air heating coil. The heating energy provided by this coil is reclaimed from the superheated refrigerant gas leaving a compressor and does not impact the performance of the compressor. This coil must be used with a water heater tank, see Water Heater:Mixed.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Schedule values of 0 denote the desuperheater heating coil is off and the parasitic electric energy is also off.

fields.name: Setpoint Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defines the cut-out temperature where the desuperheater water heating coil turns off. The desuperheater heating coil setpoint temperature should always be greater than the water tank's heater (element or burner) setpoint temperature. Temperature schedule values should be in degrees C.

fields.name: Dead Band Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Setpoint temperature minus the dead band temperature difference defines the cut-in temperature where the desuperheater water heating coil turns on. The water tank's heater (element or burner) setpoint temperature should always be less than the desuperheater heating coil cut-in temperature.

fields.name: Rated Heat Reclaim Recovery Efficiency
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of waste heat reclaimed by the desuperheater water heating coil.

fields.name: Rated Inlet Water Temperature
fields.memo: The inlet water temperature corresponding to the rated heat reclaim recovery efficiency.

fields.name: Rated Outdoor Air Temperature
fields.memo: The outdoor air dry-bulb temperature corresponding to the rated heat reclaim recovery efficiency.

fields.name: Maximum Inlet Water Temperature for Heat Reclaim
fields.memo: The desuperheater water heating coil is off when the inlet water temperature is above the maximum inlet water temperature for heat reclaim.

fields.name: Heat Reclaim Efficiency Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: A biquadratic curve defining the performance of the desuperheater heating coil. Performance can be specified as a function of inlet water temperature, outdoor air dry-bulb temperature, or both. Curve = a + b*Tw + c*Tw**2 + d*odb + e*odb**2 + f*Tw*odb. Tw = desuperheater heating coil entering water temperature (C). Odb = outdoor dry-bulb temperature at DX system condenser (C).

fields.name: Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node from which the desuperheater heating coil draws its inlet water. This name should match the source side outlet node name in the associated water heater tank object.

fields.name: Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node to which the desuperheater heating coil sends its outlet water. This name should match the source side inlet node name in the associated water heater tank object.

fields.name: Tank Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of water heater tank used by this desuperheater water heating coil.

fields.name: Tank Name
fields.memo: The name of the water heater tank used by this desuperheater water heating coil. Needs to match the name used in the corresponding water heater object.

fields.name: Heating Source Object Type
fields.memo: The type of DX system that is providing waste heat for reclaim.

fields.name: Heating Source Name
fields.memo: The name of the DX system used for heat reclaim.

fields.name: Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: The operating water flow rate.

fields.name: Water Pump Power
fields.memo: The water circulation pump electric power.

fields.name: Fraction of Pump Heat to Water
fields.memo: The fraction of pump heat transferred to the water. The pump is assumed to be downstream of the desuperheater water heating coil.

fields.name: On-Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power consumed when the desuperheater water heating coil operates. Parasitic electric load does not contribute to water heating or the zone air heat balance.

fields.name: Off-Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric load consumed when the desuperheater water heating coil is off. Parasitic electric load does not contribute to water heating or the zone air heat balance. Off-cycle parasitic power is 0 when the availability schedule is 0.

airterminal:singleduct:seriespiu:reheat.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:SeriesPIU:Reheat
airterminal:singleduct:seriespiu:reheat.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume, series powered induction unit (PIU), with reheat coil (hot water, electric, gas, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Reheat Coil Air Inlet Node Name
Fan Name
fields.memo: Fan type must be Fan:SystemModel or Fan:ConstantVolume

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

airflownetwork:intrazone:linkage.name: AirflowNetwork:IntraZone:Linkage
airflownetwork:intrazone:linkage.memo: This object defines the connection between two nodes and a component used in the combination of RoomAir and AirflowNetwork model.

fields.name: Node 1 Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of zone or AirflowNetwork Node.

fields.name: Node 2 Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of zone or AirflowNetwork Node.

fields.name: Component Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirflowNetwork component. A component is one of the following AirflowNetwork:Multizone:Component objects: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface:Crack, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface:EffectiveLeakageArea, If the next field is specified, this field can be either blank or ignored.

fields.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface Name
fields.memo: Only used when one of two nodes defined above are not located in the same zone, and the input of the Component Name field in this object is ignored

heatpump:watertowater:equationfit:coolin.name: HeatPump:WaterToWater:EquationFit:Cooling
heatpump:watertowater:equationfit:coolin.memo: simple water-water heat pump curve-fit model

fields.name: Reference Coefficient of Performance
fields.memo: This optional field is used to autosize Reference Cooling Power Consumption COP = Rated Cooling Capacity / Rated Cooling Power Consumption

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Companion Heating Heat Pump Name
fields.memo: This optional field is used to coordinate sizing calculations between heating and cooling modes.

fan:constantvolume.name: Fan:ConstantVolume
fan:constantvolume.memo: Constant volume fan that is intended to operate continuously based on a time schedule. This fan will not cycle on and off based on cooling/heating load or other control signals.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Motor In Airstream Fraction
fields.memo: 0.0 means fan motor outside of air stream, 1.0 means motor inside of air stream

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

building.name: Building
building.memo: Describes parameters that are used during the simulation of the building. There are necessary correlations between the entries for this object and some entries in the Site:WeatherStation and Site:HeightVariation objects, specifically the Terrain field.

fields.name: North Axis
fields.memo: degrees from true North

fields.name: Terrain
fields.memo: Country=FlatOpenCountry | Suburbs=CountryTownsSuburbs | City=CityCenter | Ocean=body of water (5km) | Urban=Urban-Industrial-Forest

fields.name: Loads Convergence Tolerance Value
fields.memo: Loads Convergence Tolerance Value is a fraction of load

fields.name: Solar Distribution
fields.memo: MinimalShadowing | FullExterior | FullInteriorAndExterior | FullExteriorWithReflections | FullInteriorAndExteriorWithReflections

fields.name: Maximum Number of Warmup Days
fields.memo: EnergyPlus will only use as many warmup days as needed to reach convergence tolerance. This field's value should NOT be set less than 25.

fields.name: Minimum Number of Warmup Days
fields.memo: The minimum number of warmup days that produce enough temperature and flux history to start EnergyPlus simulation for all reference buildings was suggested to be 6. When this field is greater than the maximum warmup days defined previous field the maximum number of warmup days will be reset to the minimum value entered here. Warmup days will be set to be the value you entered when it is less than the default 6.

generator:microchp.name: Generator:MicroCHP
generator:microchp.memo: Small-scale combined heat and power (micro CHP) electric generator using the model developed by IEA/ECBCS Annex 42 see www.cogen-sim.net. The model was developed for both internal combustion and Stirling cycle engines, but might be used for other types of residential CHP devices.

fields.name: Performance Parameters Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:MicroCHP:NonNormalizedParameters object.

fields.name: Generator Fuel Supply Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Generator:FuelSupply object.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fluidproperties:superheated.name: FluidProperties:Superheated
fluidproperties:superheated.memo: fluid properties for the superheated region

fields.name: Fluid Property Type
fields.memo: Enthalpy Units are J/kg Density Units are kg/m3

fields.name: Temperature Values Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a FluidProperties:Temperatures object.

fields.name: Pressure
fields.memo: pressure for this list of properties

externalinterface:actuator.name: ExternalInterface:Actuator
externalinterface:actuator.memo: Hardware portion of EMS used to set up actuators in the model

fields.name: Optional Initial Value
fields.memo: If specified, it is used during warm-up and system sizing. If not specified, then the actuator only overwrites the actuated component after the warm-up and system sizing.

setpointmanager:singlezone:cooling.name: SetpointManager:SingleZone:Cooling
setpointmanager:singlezone:cooling.memo: This setpoint manager detects the control zone load to meet the current cooling setpoint, zone inlet node flow rate, and zone node temperature, and calculates a setpoint temperature for the supply air that will satisfy the zone cooling load for the control zone.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which the temperature will be set

refrigeration:condenser:watercooled.name: Refrigeration:Condenser:WaterCooled
refrigeration:condenser:watercooled.memo: Water cooled condenser for a refrigeration system (Refrigeration:System).

fields.name: Rated Effective Total Heat Rejection Rate
fields.memo: Rating as per ARI 450 Be sure the rating corresponds to the correct refrigerant not used in calculations, only for identification and output

fields.name: Rated Condensing Temperature
fields.memo: must correspond to rating given for total heat rejection effect

fields.name: Rated Subcooling Temperature Difference
fields.memo: must correspond to rating given for total heat rejection effect

fields.name: Rated Water Inlet Temperature
fields.memo: must correspond to rating given for total heat rejection effect

fields.name: Water Outlet Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Applicable only when loop flow type is Variable Flow.

fields.name: Water Design Flow Rate
fields.memo: note required units must be converted from L/s as specified in ARI 450-2007 Applicable only when loop flow type is Constant Flow.

fields.name: Water Minimum Water Inlet Temperature
fields.memo: related to the minimum allowed refrigeration system condensing temperature

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Condenser Refrigerant Operating Charge Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Receiver Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Piping Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Slat Separation
fields.memo: Distance between adjacent slat faces

fields.name: Slat Thickness
fields.memo: Distance between top and bottom surfaces of slat Slat is assumed to be rectangular in cross section and flat

fields.name: Slat Angle
fields.memo: If WindowProperty:ShadingControl for the window that incorporates this blind has Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds = FixedSlatAngle, then this is the fixed value of the slat angle; If WindowProperty:ShadingControl for the window that incorporates this blind has Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds = BlockBeamSolar, then this is the slat angle when slat angle control is not in effect (e.g., when there is no beam solar on the blind); Not used if WindowProperty:ShadingControl for the window that incorporates this blind has Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds = ScheduledSlatAngle.

fields.name: Slat Conductivity
fields.memo: default is for aluminum

fields.name: Front Side Slat Beam Solar Reflectance
Back Side Slat Beam Solar Reflectance
Slat Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: Must equal "Slat beam solar transmittance"

fields.name: Front Side Slat Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Must equal "Front Side Slat Beam Solar Reflectance"

fields.name: Back Side Slat Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Must equal "Back Side Slat Beam Solar Reflectance"

fields.name: Slat Beam Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: Required for detailed daylighting calculation

fields.name: Front Side Slat Beam Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Required for detailed daylighting calculation

fields.name: Back Side Slat Beam Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Required for detailed daylighting calculation

fields.name: Slat Diffuse Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: Used only for detailed daylighting calculation Must equal "Slat Beam Visible Transmittance"

fields.name: Front Side Slat Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Required for detailed daylighting calculation Must equal "Front Side Slat Beam Visible Reflectance"

fields.name: Back Side Slat Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Required for detailed daylighting calculation Must equal "Back Side Slat Beam Visible Reflectance"

fields.name: Front Side Slat Infrared Hemispherical Emissivity
Back Side Slat Infrared Hemispherical Emissivity
Minimum Slat Angle
fields.memo: Used only if WindowProperty:ShadingControl for the window that incorporates this blind varies the slat angle (i.e., WindowProperty:ShadingControl with Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds = ScheduledSlatAngle or BlockBeamSolar)

fields.name: Maximum Slat Angle
fields.memo: Used only if WindowProperty:ShadingControl for the window that incorporates this blind varies the slat angle (i.e., WindowProperty:ShadingControl with Type of Slat Angle Control for Blinds = ScheduledSlatAngle or BlockBeamSolar)

centralheatpumpsystem.name: CentralHeatPumpSystem
centralheatpumpsystem.memo: This chiller bank can contain multiple chiller heaters and heat pump performance objects. Its function is to encapsulate the extra controls needed to turn individual modules on/off and whether they are to operate in cooling-only, heating-only or simultaneous cooling/heating mode and whether to connect the source water to the evaporator or condenser side.

fields.name: Ancillary Power
fields.memo: Power as demanded from any auxiliary controls

fields.name: Ancillary Operation Schedule Name
fields.memo: This value from this schedule is multiplied times the Ancillary Power

fields.name: Chiller Heater Modules Performance Component Object Type 1
Chiller Heater Modules Performance Component Name 1
Chiller Heater Modules Control Schedule Name 1

Chiller Heater Modules Performance Component Name 2

Chiller Heater Modules Performance Component Object Type 5

Chiller Heater Modules Control Schedule Name 7

faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:conde.memo: This object describes fault of condenser supply water temperature sensor offset

fields.name: Cooling Tower Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of the cooling tower affected

fields.memo: Enter the name of the cooling tower affected

airflownetwork:zonecontrol:pressurecontr.name: AirflowNetwork:ZoneControl:PressureController
airflownetwork:zonecontrol:pressurecontr.memo: This object is used to control a zone to a specified indoor pressure using the AirflowNetwork model. The specified pressure setpoint is used to control the zone exhaust fan flow rate in a controlled zone or the relief air flow rate in an air loop.

fields.name: Control Object Type
fields.memo: The current selection is AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Component:ZoneExhaustFan or AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:ReliefAirFlow.

fields.name: Control Object Name
fields.memo: Control names are names of individual control objects

fields.name: Pressure Control Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for pressure controller. Schedule value > 0 means the pressure controller is enabled. If this field is blank, then pressure controller is always enabled.

refrigeration:condenser:cascade.name: Refrigeration:Condenser:Cascade
refrigeration:condenser:cascade.memo: Cascade condenser for a refrigeration system (Refrigeration:System). The cascade condenser is unlike the other condenser options because it rejects heat to another, higher-temperature, refrigeration system. That is, the cascade condenser acts as a heat rejection object for one system, but acts as a refrigeration load for another system.

fields.name: Rated Condensing Temperature
fields.memo: This is the condensing temperature for the lower temperature secondary loop

fields.name: Rated Approach Temperature Difference
fields.memo: This is the difference between the condensing and evaporating temperatures

fields.name: Rated Effective Total Heat Rejection Rate
fields.memo: used for identification and rough system size error checking

fields.name: Condensing Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: Fixed keeps condensing temperature constant Float sets the condensing temperature according to the other loads on the higher temperature system

fields.name: Condenser Refrigerant Operating Charge Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Receiver Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Piping Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:dep.name: ZoneContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:DepositionRateSink
zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:dep.memo: Simulate generic contaminant source driven by the boundary layer diffusion controlled model.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Initial Emission Rate. When the value is equal to 1.0, the time will be reset to zero.

zonehvac:equipmentlist.name: ZoneHVAC:EquipmentList
zonehvac:equipmentlist.memo: List equipment in simulation order.  Note that an ZoneHVAC:AirDistributionUnit or AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Uncontrolled object must be listed in this statement if there is a forced air system serving the zone from the air loop. Equipment is simulated in the order specified by Zone Equipment Cooling Sequence and Zone Equipment Heating or No-Load Sequence, depending on the thermostat request. For equipment of similar type, assign sequence 1 to the first system intended to serve that type of load.  For situations where one or more equipment types has limited capacity or limited control, order the sequence so that the most controllable piece of equipment runs last. For example, with a dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS), the air terminal for the DOAS should be assigned Heating Sequence = 1 and Cooling Sequence = 1.  Any other equipment should be assigned sequence 2 or higher so that it will see the net load after the DOAS air is added to the zone.

windowproperty:frameanddivider.name: WindowProperty:FrameAndDivider
windowproperty:frameanddivider.memo: Specifies the dimensions of a window frame, dividers, and inside reveal surfaces. Referenced by the surface objects for exterior windows and glass doors (ref: FenestrationSurface:Detailed, Window, and GlazedDoor).

fields.name: Frame Width
fields.memo: Width of frame in plane of window Frame width assumed the same on all sides of window

fields.name: Frame Outside Projection
fields.memo: Amount that frame projects outward from the outside face of the glazing

fields.name: Frame Inside Projection
fields.memo: Amount that frame projects inward from the inside face of the glazing

fields.name: Frame Conductance
fields.memo: Effective conductance of frame Excludes air films Obtained from WINDOW 5 or other 2-D calculation

fields.name: Ratio of Frame-Edge Glass Conductance to Center-Of-Glass Conductance
fields.memo: Excludes air films; applies only to multipane windows Obtained from WINDOW 5 or other 2-D calculation

fields.name: Frame Solar Absorptance
fields.memo: Assumed same on outside and inside of frame

fields.name: Frame Visible Absorptance
fields.memo: Assumed same on outside and inside of frame

fields.name: Frame Thermal Hemispherical Emissivity
fields.memo: Assumed same on outside and inside of frame

fields.name: Divider Width
fields.memo: Width of dividers in plane of window Width assumed the same for all dividers

fields.name: Number of Horizontal Dividers
fields.memo: "Horizontal" means parallel to local window X-axis

fields.name: Number of Vertical Dividers
fields.memo: "Vertical" means parallel to local window Y-axis

fields.name: Divider Outside Projection
fields.memo: Amount that divider projects outward from the outside face of the glazing Outside projection assumed the same for all divider elements

fields.name: Divider Inside Projection
fields.memo: Amount that divider projects inward from the inside face of the glazing Inside projection assumed the same for all divider elements

fields.name: Divider Conductance
fields.memo: Effective conductance of divider Excludes air films Obtained from WINDOW 5 or other 2-D calculation

fields.name: Ratio of Divider-Edge Glass Conductance to Center-Of-Glass Conductance
fields.memo: Excludes air films Obtained from WINDOW 5 or other 2-D calculation

fields.name: Divider Solar Absorptance
fields.memo: Assumed same on outside and inside of divider

fields.name: Divider Visible Absorptance
fields.memo: Assumed same on outside and inside of divider

fields.name: Divider Thermal Hemispherical Emissivity
fields.memo: Assumed same on outside and inside of divider

fields.name: Inside Reveal Depth
fields.memo: Distance from plane of inside surface of glazing to plane of inside surface of wall. Outside reveal depth is determined from the geometry of the window and the wall it is on; it is non-zero if the plane of the outside surface of the glazing is set back from the plane of the outside surface of the wall.

coil:cooling:dx:variablespeed.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:VariableSpeed
coil:cooling:dx:variablespeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and condensing unit (includes electric compressor and condenser fan), variable-speed. Optional inputs for moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation. Requires two to ten sets of performance data and will interpolate between speeds. Modeled as a single coil with variable-speed compressor.

fields.name: Nominal Speed Level
fields.memo: must be lower than or equal to the highest speed number

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity At Selected Nominal Speed Level
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate At Selected Nominal Speed Level
Nominal Time for Condensate to Begin Leaving the Coil
Initial Moisture Evaporation Rate Divided by Steady-State AC Latent Capacity
Energy Part Load Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.
