groundheatexchanger:pond.name: GroundHeatExchanger:Pond
groundheatexchanger:pond.memo: A model of a shallow pond with immersed pipe loops. Typically used in hybrid geothermal systems and included in the condenser loop. This component may also be used as a simple solar collector.

table:multivariablelookup.name: Table:MultiVariableLookup
table:multivariablelookup.memo: The multi-variable lookup table can represent from 1 to 6 independent variables and can interpolate these independent variables up to a 4th order polynomial. The polynomial order is assumed to be the number of interpolation points (n) minus 1. When any independent variable value is outside the table limits, linear extrapolation is used to predict the table result and is based on the two nearest data points in the table for that particular independent variable.

fields.name: Curve Type
fields.memo: The curve types BiCubic and TriQuadratic may not be used with Interpolation Method = EvaluateCurveToLimits

fields.name: Normalization Reference
fields.memo: This field is used to normalize the table output data. The minimum and maximum table output fields are also normalized. If this field is blank or 1, the table data will be directly used. This field is not allowed to be set equal to 0.

fields.name: Minimum Table Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Table Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Number of Values for Independent Variable X1
Field 1 Determined by the Number of Independent Variables
Field 2 Determined by the Number of Independent Variables

plantcomponent:temperaturesource.name: PlantComponent:TemperatureSource
plantcomponent:temperaturesource.memo: Simulates an object of pre-determined (constant or scheduled) source temperature The object introduces fluid into the plant loop at the specified temperature and at the same flow rate as the fluid enters the component Fluid entering the component vanishes equivalent to the relief air in an air system

fields.name: Inlet Node
fields.memo: Name of the source inlet node

fields.name: Outlet Node
fields.memo: Name of the source outlet node

fields.name: Design Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: The design volumetric flow rate for this source

fields.name: Source Temperature
fields.memo: Used if Temperature Specification Type = Constant

fields.name: Source Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used if Temperature Specification Type = Scheduled

outputcontrol:illuminancemap:style.name: OutputControl:IlluminanceMap:Style
outputcontrol:illuminancemap:style.memo: default style for the Daylighting Illuminance Map is comma -- this works well for importing into spreadsheet programs such as Excel(tm) but not so well for word processing programs -- there tab may be a better choice.  fixed puts spaces between the "columns"

thermostatsetpoint:singleheatingorcoolin.name: ThermostatSetpoint:SingleHeatingOrCooling
thermostatsetpoint:singleheatingorcoolin.memo: Used for a heating and cooling thermostat with a single setpoint. The setpoint can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation for both heating and cooling.

windowmaterial:screen.name: WindowMaterial:Screen
windowmaterial:screen.memo: Window screen physical properties. Can only be located on the exterior side of a window construction.

fields.name: Reflected Beam Transmittance Accounting Method
fields.memo: Select the method used to account for the beam solar reflected off the material surface.

fields.name: Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: Diffuse reflectance of the screen material over the entire solar radiation spectrum. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Diffuse Visible Reflectance
fields.memo: Diffuse visible reflectance of the screen material averaged over the solar spectrum and weighted by the response of the human eye. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Thermal Hemispherical Emissivity
fields.memo: Long-wave emissivity of the screen material. Assumed to be the same for both sides of the screen.

fields.name: Conductivity
fields.memo: Thermal conductivity of the screen material. Default is for aluminum.

fields.name: Screen Material Spacing
fields.memo: Spacing assumed to be the same in both directions.

fields.name: Screen Material Diameter
fields.memo: Diameter assumed to be the same in both directions.

fields.name: Screen to Glass Distance
fields.memo: Distance from the window screen to the adjacent glass surface.

fields.name: Top Opening Multiplier
fields.memo: Effective area for air flow at the top of the screen divided by the perpendicular area between the glass and the top of the screen.

fields.name: Bottom Opening Multiplier
fields.memo: Effective area for air flow at the bottom of the screen divided by the perpendicular area between the glass and the bottom of the screen.

fields.name: Left Side Opening Multiplier
fields.memo: Effective area for air flow at the left side of the screen divided by the perpendicular area between the glass and the left side of the screen.

fields.name: Right Side Opening Multiplier
fields.memo: Effective area for air flow at the right side of the screen divided by the perpendicular area between the glass and the right side of the screen.

fields.name: Angle of Resolution for Screen Transmittance Output Map
fields.memo: Select the resolution of azimuth and altitude angles for the screen transmittance map. A value of 0 means no transmittance map will be generated. Valid values for this field are 0, 1, 2, 3 and 5.

zonehvac:watertoairheatpump.name: ZoneHVAC:WaterToAirHeatPump
zonehvac:watertoairheatpump.memo: Water-to-air heat pump. Forced-convection heating-cooling unit with supply fan, water-to-air cooling and heating coils, supplemental heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam), and fixed-position outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: Currently only one OutdoorAir:Mixer object type is available. This field should be left blank if the WSHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the OutdoorAir:Mixer is not used. This optional field specifies the name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. When used, this name needs to match name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. This field should be left blank if the WSHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to fan size. Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Cooling Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to supply air flow rate during cooling operation. This field is set to zero flow when the WSHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Heating Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Must be less than or equal to supply air flow rate during heating operation. This field is set to zero flow when the WSHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: No Load Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when heat pump Fan operating mode is continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the outdoor air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. This field is set to zero flow when the PTHP is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through air terminal single duct mixer object.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff object

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the water-to-air heat pump heating coil object

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the water-to-air heat pump cooling coil object

fields.name: Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: The maximum on-off cycling rate for the compressor Suggested value is 2.5 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Heat Pump Time Constant
fields.memo: Time constant for the cooling coil's capacity to reach steady state after startup Suggested value is 60 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Fraction of On-Cycle Power Use
fields.memo: The fraction of on-cycle power use to adjust the part load fraction based on the off-cycle power consumption due to crankcase heaters, controls, fans, and etc. Suggested value is 0.01 for a typical heat pump

fields.name: Heat Pump Fan Delay Time
fields.memo: Programmed time delay for heat pump fan to shut off after compressor cycle off. Only required when fan operating mode is cycling Enter 0 when fan operating mode is continuous

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the supplemental heating coil object

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature from Supplemental Heater
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Supplemental Heater Operation
Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature Sensor Node Name
Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling or heating coil). Schedule values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this field is left blank.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Heat Pump Coil Water Flow Mode
fields.memo: used only when the heat pump coils are of the type WaterToAirHeatPump:EquationFit Constant results in 100% water flow regardless of compressor PLR Cycling results in water flow that matches compressor PLR ConstantOnDemand results in 100% water flow whenever the coil is on, but is 0% whenever the coil has no load

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

zonehvac:energyrecoveryventilator:contro.name: ZoneHVAC:EnergyRecoveryVentilator:Controller
zonehvac:energyrecoveryventilator:contro.memo: This controller is used exclusively by the ZoneHVAC:EnergyRecoveryVentilator object to allow economizer (free cooling) operation when possible.

fields.name: Temperature High Limit
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for economizer operation. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative

fields.name: Temperature Low Limit
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for economizer operation. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative

fields.name: Enthalpy High Limit
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor enthalpy limit for economizer operation. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative

fields.name: Dewpoint Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dew point temperature limit for economizer operation. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative

fields.name: Electronic Enthalpy Limit Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a quadratic or cubic curve which defines the maximum outdoor humidity ratio (function of outdoor dry-bulb temperature) for economizer operation. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative

fields.name: Time of Day Economizer Flow Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values greater than 0 indicate economizer operation is active. This schedule may be used with or without the High Humidity Control option. When used together, high humidity control has priority over economizer control.

fields.name: High Humidity Control Flag
fields.memo: Select Yes to modify air flow rates based on a zone humidistat. Select No to disable this feature.

fields.name: Humidistat Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the zone where the humidistat is located.

fields.name: High Humidity Outdoor Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the ratio of supply (outdoor) air to the maximum supply air flow rate when modified air flow rates are active based on high indoor humidity.

fields.name: Control High Indoor Humidity Based on Outdoor Humidity Ratio
fields.memo: If NO is selected, the air flow rate is modified any time indoor relative humidity is above humidistat setpoint. If YES is selected, outdoor air flow rate is modified any time indoor relative humidity is above the humidistat setpoint AND the outdoor humidity ratio is less than the indoor humidity ratio.

floor:detailed.name: Floor:Detailed
floor:detailed.memo: Allows for detailed entry of floor heat transfer surfaces.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Non-blank only if the field Outside Boundary Condition is Surface, Zone, OtherSideCoefficients or OtherSideConditionsModel If Surface, specify name of corresponding surface in adjacent zone or specify current surface name for internal partition separating like zones If Zone, specify the name of the corresponding zone and the program will generate the corresponding interzone surface If Foundation, specify the name of the corresponding Foundation object and If OtherSideCoefficients, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideCoefficients If OtherSideConditionsModel, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel

fields.name: View Factor to Ground
fields.memo: From the exterior of the surface Unused if one uses the "reflections" options in Solar Distribution in Building input unless a DaylightingDevice:Shelf or DaylightingDevice:Tubular object has been specified. autocalculate will automatically calculate this value from the tilt of the surface

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 10 vertex coordinates -- extensible object "extensible" -- duplicate last set of x,y,z coordinates, renumbering please (and changing z terminator to a comma "," for all but last one which needs a semi-colon ";") vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- if relative, all surface coordinates are "relative" to the Zone Origin.  If world, then building and zone origins are used for some internal calculations, but all coordinates are given in an "absolute" system.

surfaceproperties:vaporcoefficients.name: SurfaceProperties:VaporCoefficients
surfaceproperties:vaporcoefficients.memo: The interior and external vapor transfer coefficients. Normally these value are calculated using the heat convection coefficient values. Use this object to used fixed constant values. Units are kg/Pa.s.m2 This will only work with the CombinedHeatAndMoistureFiniteElement algorithm for surfaces. Other algorithms will ignore these coefficients

heatexchanger:fluidtofluid.name: HeatExchanger:FluidToFluid
heatexchanger:fluidtofluid.memo: A fluid/fluid heat exchanger designed to couple the supply side of one loop to the demand side of another loop Loops can be either plant or condenser loops but no air side connections are allowed

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. default is that heat exchanger is on

fields.name: Loop Demand Side Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: This connection is to the demand side of a loop and is the inlet to the heat exchanger

fields.name: Loop Demand Side Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: This connection is to the demand side of a loop

fields.name: Loop Demand Side Design Flow Rate
Loop Supply Side Inlet Node Name
Loop Supply Side Outlet Node Name
Loop Supply Side Design Flow Rate
Heat Exchanger U-Factor Times Area Value
Heat Exchanger Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: Setpoint node is needed with any Control Type that is "*Setpoint*"

fields.name: Minimum Temperature Difference to Activate Heat Exchanger
fields.memo: Tolerance between control temperatures used to determine if heat exchanger should run.

fields.name: Heat Transfer Metering End Use Type
fields.memo: This field controls end use reporting for heat transfer meters

fields.name: Component Override Loop Supply Side Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: This field is only used if Control Type is set to CoolingSetpointOnOffWithComponentOverride

fields.name: Component Override Loop Demand Side Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: This field is only used if Control Type is set to CoolingSetpointOnOffWithComponentOverride

fields.name: Component Override Cooling Control Temperature Mode
fields.memo: This field is only used if Control Type is set to CoolingSetpointOnOffWithComponentOverride

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized flow rates for this device

fields.name: Operation Minimum Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Lower limit on inlet temperatures, heat exchanger will not operate if either inlet is below this limit

fields.name: Operation Maximum Temperature Limit
fields.memo: Upper limit on inlet temperatures, heat exchanger will not operate if either inlet is above this limit

airloophvac:unitarysystem.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitarySystem
airloophvac:unitarysystem.memo: AirloopHVAC:UnitarySystem is a generic HVAC system type that allows any configuration of coils and/or fan. This object is a replacement of other AirloopHVAC objects. This object can be used in outdoor air systems, outdoor air units, air loops, and as zone equipment if desired.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: Load control requires a Controlling Zone name. SetPoint control requires set points at coil outlet node. SingleZoneVAV also requires a Controlling Zone name and allows load control at low speed fan until the load exceeds capacity or outlet air temperature limits. The fan speed is then increased.

fields.name: Controlling Zone or Thermostat Location
fields.memo: Used only for Load based control Zone name where thermostat is located. Required when Control Type = Load.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only. Required when Control Type = SingleZoneVAV. Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load.  Valid only with cooling coil type Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoStageWithHumidityControlMode or CoilSystem:Cooling:DX:HeatExchangerAssisted. This control mode either switches the coil mode or allows the heat exchanger to be turned on and off based on the zone dehumidification requirements. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required. CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint. as required to meet the humidity setpoint.  Valid with all cooling coil types. When a heat exchanger assisted cooling coil is used, the heat exchanger is locked on at all times. A ZoneControl:Humidistat object is also required.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. A schedule value greater than zero (usually 1 is used) indicates that the unit is available to operate as needed. A value less than or equal to zero (usually zero is used) denotes that the unit must be off.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the node name used as the inlet air node for the unitary system.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the node name used as the outlet air node for the unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of supply air fan if included in the unitary system. Fan:ConstantVolume only works with continuous fan operating mode (i.e. supply air fan operating mode schedule values greater than 0). Specify a Fan:SystemModel or a Fan:OnOff object when the Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name input field above is left blank. Specify a Fan:SystemModel or a Fan:VariableVolume when modeling VAV systems which used setpoint based control if the fan is included in the unitary system object. The ComponentModel fan type may be substituted for the ConstantVolume or VariableVolume fan types when more detailed fan modeling is required. The variable or constant volume fan may be specified on the branch instead of contained within the unitary system object (i.e., this field may be blank for certain configurations).

fields.name: Supply Fan Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the supply air fan if included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Fan Placement
fields.memo: Enter the type of supply air fan if included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: A fan operating mode schedule value of 0 indicates cycling fan mode (supply air fan cycles on and off in tandem with the cooling or heating coil). Any other schedule value indicates continuous fan mode (supply air fan operates continuously regardless of cooling or heating coil operation). Provide a schedule with non-zero values when high humidity control is specified. Leaving this schedule name blank will default to constant fan mode for the entire simulation period. This field is not used when set point based control is used where a set point controls the coil. SingleZoneVAV control type is only active when constant fan operating mode is active.

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of heating coil if included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the heating coil if included in the unitary system.

fields.name: DX Heating Coil Sizing Ratio
fields.memo: Used to adjust heat pump heating capacity with respect to DX cooling capacity used only for heat pump configurations (i.e., a DX cooling and DX heating coil is used).

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of cooling coil if included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the cooling coil if included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Use DOAS DX Cooling Coil
fields.memo: If Yes, the DX cooling coil runs as 100% DOAS DX coil. If No, the DX cooling coil runs as a regular DX coil. If left blank the default is regular dx coil.

fields.name: Minimum Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: When Use DOAS DX Cooling Coil is specified as Yes, Minimum Supply Air Temperature defines the minimum DOAS DX cooling coil leaving air temperature that should be maintained to avoid frost formation. This field is not autosizable when the input for Use DOAS DX Cooling Coil = Yes. When Control Type = SingleZoneVAV, enter the minimum air temperature limit for reduced fan speed.

fields.name: Latent Load Control
fields.memo: SensibleOnlyLoadControl is selected when thermostat or SingleZoneVAV control is used. LatentOnlyLoadControl is selected when humidistat control is used. LatentWithSensibleLoadControl is selected when thermostat control is used and dehumidification is required only when a sensible load exists. LatentOrSensibleLoadControl is selected when thermostat control is used and dehumidification is required any time the humidistat set point is exceeded.

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of supplemental heating or reheat coil if included in the unitary system. Only required if dehumidification control type is "CoolReheat". This coil supplements heating mode operation or reheats the supply air during dehumidification mode operation. If set point based control is used the coils operate to meet their respective supply air temperature set point.

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the supplemental heating coil if included in the unitary system. Only required if dehumidification control type is "CoolReheat".

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the cooling supply air volume flow rate. None is used when a cooling coil is not included in the unitary system or this field may be blank. SupplyAirFlowRate is selected when the magnitude of the supply air volume is used. FlowPerFloorArea is selected when the supply air volume flow rate is based on total floor area served by the unitary system. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingValue is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the value determined by the simulation. FlowPerCoolingCapacity is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the cooling capacity as determined by the simulation.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate during cooling operation. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is SupplyAirFlowRate. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate per total floor area fraction. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Cooling Fraction of Autosized Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling supply air flow rate. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingValue. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit of Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling capacity. Required field when Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerCoolingCapacity. This field may be blank if a cooling coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating supply air volume flow rate. None is used when a heating coil is not included in the unitary system or this field may be blank. SupplyAirFlowRate is selected when the magnitude of the supply air volume is used. FlowPerFloorArea is selected when the supply air volume flow rate is based on total floor area served by the unitary system. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingValue is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the value determined by the simulation. FlowPerHeatingCapacity is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the heating capacity as determined by the simulation.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate during heating operation. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is SupplyAirFlowRate. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate per total floor area fraction. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Fraction of Autosized Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating supply air flow rate. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingValue. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit of Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating capacity. Required field when Heating Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerHeatingCapacity. This field may be blank if a heating coil is not included in the unitary system.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the supply air volume flow rate when no cooling or heating is required. None is used when a cooling and heating coil is not included in the unitary system or this field may be blank. SupplyAirFlowRate is selected when the magnitude of the supply air volume is used. FlowPerFloorArea is selected when the supply air volume flow rate is based on total floor area served by the unitary system. FractionOfAutosizedCoolingValue is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the cooling value determined by the simulation. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingValue is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the heating value determined by the simulation. FlowPerCoolingCapacity is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the cooling capacity as determined by the simulation. FlowPerHeatingCapacity is selected when the supply air volume is a fraction of the heating capacity as determined by the simulation.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the magnitude of the supply air volume flow rate during when no cooling or heating is required. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is SupplyAirFlowRate.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate per total floor area fraction. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerFloorArea.

fields.name: No Load Fraction of Autosized Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling supply air flow rate. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedCoolingValue.

fields.name: No Load Fraction of Autosized Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating supply air flow rate. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingValue.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit of Capacity During Cooling Operation
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the cooling capacity. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerCoolingCapacity.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Per Unit of Capacity During Heating Operation
fields.memo: Enter the supply air volume flow rate as a fraction of the heating capacity. Required field when No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Method is FlowPerHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum supply air temperature leaving the heating coil. When Control Type = SingleZoneVAV, enter the maximum air temperature limit for reduced fan speed.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Supplemental Heater Operation
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature for supplemental heater operation.

fields.name: Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature Sensor Node Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, outdoor temperature from the weather file is used. If this field is not blank, the node name specified determines the outdoor temperature used for controlling supplemental heater operation.

fields.name: Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: Used only for water source heat pump. The maximum on-off cycling rate for the compressor. Suggested value is 2.5 for a typical heat pump.

fields.name: Heat Pump Time Constant
fields.memo: Used only for water source heat pump. Time constant for the cooling coil's capacity to reach steady state after startup. Suggested value is 60 for a typical heat pump.

fields.name: Fraction of On-Cycle Power Use
fields.memo: Used only for water source heat pump. The fraction of on-cycle power use to adjust the part load fraction based on the off-cycle power consumption due to crankcase heaters, controls, fans, and etc. Suggested value is 0.01 for a typical heat pump.

fields.name: Heat Pump Fan Delay Time
fields.memo: Used only for water source heat pump. Programmed time delay for heat pump fan to shut off after compressor cycle off. Only required when fan operating mode is cycling. Enter 0 when fan operating mode is continuous.

fields.name: Ancillary On-Cycle Electric Power
fields.memo: Enter the value of ancillary electric power for controls or other devices consumed during the on cycle.

fields.name: Ancillary Off-Cycle Electric Power
fields.memo: Enter the value of ancillary electric power for controls or other devices consumed during the off cycle.

fields.name: Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered. Used for heat recovery to an EnergyPlus plant loop.

fields.name: Maximum Temperature for Heat Recovery
fields.memo: Enter the maximum heat recovery inlet temperature allowed for heat recovery.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the heat recovery water inlet node if plant water loop connections are present.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the heat recovery water outlet node if plant water loop connections are present.

fields.name: Design Specification Multispeed Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of performance specification object used to describe the multispeed coil.

fields.name: Design Specification Multispeed Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the performance specification object used to describe the multispeed coil.

energymanagementsystem:trendvariable.name: EnergyManagementSystem:TrendVariable
energymanagementsystem:trendvariable.memo: This object sets up an EMS trend variable from an Erl variable A trend variable logs values across timesteps

fields.name: EMS Variable Name
fields.memo: must be a global scope EMS variable

fields.name: Number of Timesteps to be Logged

hvactemplate:system:unitarysystem.name: HVACTemplate:System:UnitarySystem
hvactemplate:system:unitarysystem.memo: Unitary HVAC system with optional cooling and heating. Supports DX and chilled water, cooling, gas, electric, and hot water heating, air-to-air and water-to-air heat pumps.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available. Also see Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name field.

fields.name: Control Type
fields.memo: Load control requires a Controlling Zone name. SetPoint control requires set points at coil outlet nodes. The user must add appropriate SetpointManager objects to the idf file.

fields.name: Control Zone or Thermostat Location Name
fields.memo: This field is required if Control Type is Load.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during cooling operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during heating operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate when no cooling or heating is needed Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is Continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Number of Speeds for Cooling
fields.memo: Used only for Cooling Coil Type = MultiSpeedDX.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing.

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include effect of supply fan heat

fields.name: DX Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electric power input

fields.name: Number of Speeds or Stages for Heating
fields.memo: Used only for Heating Coil Type = MultiSpeedDXHeatPumpAirSource), MultiStageElectric, or MultiStageGas.

fields.name: Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing.

fields.name: Heating Coil Gross Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Rated heating capacity excluding the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Heating Coil Rated Capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy. Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C Applies only to DX coils

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
Heat Pump Defrost Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
Heat Pump Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode only applicable if Timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Supplemental Heating or Reheat Coil Type
Supplemental Heating or Reheat Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supplemental Heating or Reheat Coil Capacity
Supplemental Heating or Reheat Coil Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Supplemental heater will not operate when outdoor temperature exceeds this value.

fields.name: Supplemental Gas Heating or Reheat Coil Efficiency
fields.memo: Applies only if Supplemental Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Supplemental Gas Heating or Reheat Coil Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Applies only if Supplemental Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the minimum outdoor air flow rate If blank, multiplier is always one

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for FixedDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Enthalpy
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor enthalpy limit for FixedEnthalpy economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Minimum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for economizer control. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Latent Heat Recovery Effectiveness
fields.memo: Applicable only if Heat Recovery Type is Enthalpy.

fields.name: Dehumidification Control Type
fields.memo: None = meet sensible load only CoolReheat = cool beyond the dry-bulb setpoint, reheat with reheat coil If no reheat coil specified, cold supply temps may occur. Multimode = activate enhanced dehumidification mode as needed and meet sensible load. Valid only for Cooling Coil Type = TwoStageHumidityControlDX or HeatExchangerAssistedDX

fields.name: Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100) Ignored if Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Dehumidification Relative Humidity Setpoint above. Schedule values must be in percent relative humidity (0 to 100).

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100). Ignored if Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule specified below

fields.name: Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank to use constant setpoint specified in Humidifier Relative Humidity Setpoint above.Schedule values must be in percent relative humidity (0 to 100).

fields.name: Sizing Option
fields.memo: Select whether autosized system supply flow rate is the sum of Coincident or NonCoincident zone air flow rates.

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction

fluidproperties:temperatures.name: FluidProperties:Temperatures
fluidproperties:temperatures.memo: property values for fluid properties list of up to 250 temperatures, note that number of property values must match the number of properties in other words, there must be a one-to-one correspondence between the property values in this list and the actual properties list in other syntax degrees C (for all temperature inputs)

coil:cooling:dx:multispeed.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:MultiSpeed
coil:cooling:dx:multispeed.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and condensing unit (includes electric or engine-driven compressor and condenser fan), multi-speed (or variable-speed). Optional moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation. Requires two to four sets of performance data and will interpolate between speeds. Modeled as a single coil (multi-speed compressor or multiple compressors with row split or intertwined coil).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Condenser Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an outdoor air node. This node name is also specified in an OutdoorAir:Node or OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Apply Part Load Fraction to Speeds Greater than 1
Apply Latent Degradation to Speeds Greater than 1
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Number of Speeds
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for coil capacity, SHR, COP, flow rate, and associated curves.

fields.name: Speed 1 Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Gross capacity excluding supply air fan heat Rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb Speed 1 is defined as low speed

fields.name: Speed 1 Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include supply fan heat

fields.name: Speed 1 Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Flow rate corresponding to rated total cooling capacity, rated SHR and rated COP should be between 0.00004027 m3/s and .00006041 m3/s per watt of rated total cooling capacity

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Evaporator Fan Power Per Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the evaporator fan power per air volume flow rate at the rated test conditions. The test conditions vary external static pressure based on total cooling capacity. This value is only used to calculate Seasonal Energy Efficiency Ratio (SEER), and the Standard Rating (Net) Cooling Capacity which will be outputs in the EnergyPlus eio file. This value is not used for modeling the evaporator fan during simulations.

fields.name: Speed 1 Total Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Speed 1 Total Cooling Capacity Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = Fraction of the full load Flow

fields.name: Speed 1 Energy Input Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*wb + c*wb**2 + d*edb + e*edb**2 + f*wb*edb wb = entering wet-bulb temperature (C) edb = dry-bulb temperature seen by the condenser (C)

fields.name: Speed 1 Energy Input Ratio Function of Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 cubic curve = a + b*ff + c*ff**2 + d*ff**3 ff = fraction of the full load flow

fields.name: Speed 1 Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity)

fields.name: Speed 1 Nominal Time for Condensate Removal to Begin
fields.memo: The nominal time for condensate to begin leaving the coil's condensate drain line at the coil's rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Nominal time is equal to the ratio of the energy of the coil's maximum condensate holding capacity (J) to the coil's steady state latent capacity (W). Suggested value is 1000; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Speed 1 Ratio of Initial Moisture Evaporation Rate and Steady State Latent Capacity
fields.memo: Ratio of the initial moisture evaporation Rate from the Cooling Coil (when the compressor first turns off) and the Coil's steady state latent capacity at rated air flow rate and temperature conditions. Suggested value is 1.5; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Speed 1 Maximum Cycling Rate
fields.memo: The maximum on-off cycling rate for the compressor, which occurs at 50% run time fraction. Suggested value is 3; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Speed 1 Latent Capacity Time Constant
fields.memo: Time constant for the cooling coil's latent capacity to reach steady state after startup. Suggested value is 45; zero value means latent degradation model is disabled.

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Waste Heat Fraction of Power Input
fields.memo: Recoverable waste heat at full load and rated conditions

fields.name: Speed 1 Waste Heat Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: curve = a + b*odb + c*odb**2 + d*db + e*db**2 + f*odb*db odb = Outdoor air dry-bulb temperature (C) db = entering coil dry-bulb temperature (C)

fields.name: Speed 1 Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use

fields.name: Speed 1 Rated Evaporative Condenser Pump Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump at high speed

windowmaterial:gap.name: WindowMaterial:Gap
windowmaterial:gap.memo: Used to define the gap between two layers in a complex fenestration system, where the Construction:ComplexFenestrationState object is used. It is referenced as a layer in the Construction:ComplexFenestrationState object. It cannot be referenced as a layer from the Construction object.

fields.name: Gas (or Gas Mixture)
fields.memo: This field should reference only WindowMaterial:Gas or WindowMaterial:GasMixture objects

fields.name: Deflection State
fields.memo: If left blank, it will be considered that gap is not deflected

fields.name: Support Pillar
fields.memo: If left blank, it will be considered that gap does not have support pillars

faultmodel:humidistatoffset.name: FaultModel:HumidistatOffset
faultmodel:humidistatoffset.memo: This object describes fault of humidistat offset

fields.name: Humidistat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a ZoneControl:Humidistat object.

fields.name: Humidistat Offset Type
fields.memo: Two types are available: Type ThermostatOffsetIndependent Type ThermostatOffsetDependent

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is applicable for Type ThermostatOffsetIndependent

fields.name: Severity Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is applicable for Type ThermostatOffsetIndependent

fields.name: Reference Humidistat Offset
fields.memo: Required field for Type ThermostatOffsetIndependent

fields.name: Related Thermostat Offset Fault Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a FaultModel:ThermostatOffset object Required field for Type ThermostatOffsetDependent

curve:cubiclinear.name: Curve:CubicLinear
curve:cubiclinear.memo: Cubic-linear curve with two independent variables. Input consists of the curve name, the six coefficients, and min and max values for each of the independent variables. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = (C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2 + C4*x**3) + (C5 + C6*x)*y

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

demandmanagerassignmentlist.name: DemandManagerAssignmentList
demandmanagerassignmentlist.memo: a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Billing Period Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field should reference the same schedule as the month schedule name field of the UtilityCost:Tariff object, if used. If blank, defaults to regular divisions between months.

fields.name: Peak Period Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field should reference the same schedule as the period schedule name field of the UtilityCost:Tariff object, if used. If blank, defaults to always on peak.

chillerheaterperformance:electric:eir.name: ChillerHeaterPerformance:Electric:EIR
chillerheaterperformance:electric:eir.memo: This chiller model is a generic chiller-heater where the cooling mode performance is a function of condenser entering or leaving fluid temperature and the heating mode performance is typically a function of condenser leaving fluid temperature. Performance at off-reference conditions is modeled using three polynomial equations per mode. Six curve objects are required.

fields.name: Reference Cooling Mode COP
fields.memo: Efficiency of the chiller compressor (cooling output/compressor energy input).

fields.name: Reference Cooling Mode Leaving Chilled Water Temperature
Reference Cooling Mode Entering Condenser Fluid Temperature
Reference Cooling Mode Leaving Condenser Water Temperature
Reference Heating Mode Cooling Capacity Ratio
fields.memo: During simultaneous cooling-heating mode, this ratio is relative to the Reference Cooling Mode Cooling Capacity (Evaporator capacity at simul clg-htg mode ref condition)/ (Evaporator capacity at cooling mode ref condition)

fields.name: Reference Heating Mode Cooling Power Input Ratio
fields.memo: During simultaneous cooling-heating mode, this ratio is relative to the Reference Cooling Mode COP (Power at simultaneous clg-htg mode reference condition)/ (Power at cooling mode reference condition)

fields.name: Reference Heating Mode Leaving Chilled Water Temperature
fields.memo: During simultaneous cooling-heating mode

fields.name: Reference Heating Mode Leaving Condenser Water Temperature
fields.memo: During simultaneous cooling-heating mode

fields.name: Reference Heating Mode Entering Condenser Fluid Temperature
Heating Mode Entering Chilled Water Temperature Low Limit
fields.memo: During simultaneous cooling-heating mode

fields.name: Chilled Water Flow Mode Type
fields.memo: Sets chilled water flow rate to either constant or variable.

fields.name: Compressor Motor Efficiency
fields.memo: Fraction of compressor electrical energy that must be rejected by the condenser. Enter 1.0 or leave this field blank for a hermetic compressor.

fields.name: Cooling Mode Temperature Curve Condenser Water Independent Variable
fields.memo: Sets the second independent variable in the three temperature dependent performance curves to either the leaving or entering condenser water temperature. Manufacturers express the performance of their chillers using either the leaving condenser water temperature (to the tower) or the entering condenser water temperature (from the tower). Cooling mode is generally a stronger function of Entering Condenser Fluid Temperature

fields.name: Cooling Mode Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Cooling capacity as a function of leaving chilled water temperature and either entering or leaving condenser fluid temperature curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*TCond + e*TCond**2 + f*CWS*TCond If ClgModeCondWaterCurveInputVariable = EnteringCondenser, TCond = ECT If ClgModeCondWaterCurveInputVariable = LeavingCondenser, TCond = LCT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Cooling Mode Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of supply (leaving) chilled water temperature and leaving condenser fluid temperature.   EIR = 1/COP. curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*TCond + e*TCond**2 + f*CWS*TCond If ClgModeCondWaterCurveInputVariable = EnteringCondenser, TCond = ECT If ClgModeCondWaterCurveInputVariable = LeavingCondenser, TCond = LCT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Cooling Mode Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) EIR = 1/COP Bicubic = a + b*TCond + c*TCond**2 + d*PLR + e*PLR**2 + f*TCond*PLR +g*0 + h*PLR**3+i*0+j*0 If ClgModeCondWaterCurveInputVariable = EnteringCondenser, TCond = ECT If ClgModeCondWaterCurveInputVariable = LeavingCondenser, TCond = LCT Normally, a bicubic curve here should be in terms of LCT rather than ECT Also, a bicubic curve is more applicable for variable-speed compressor motor drives or Quadratic = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady-state capacity) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Cooling Mode Cooling Capacity Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Optimum part load ratio where the chiller is most efficient. Must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio. The Min/Max PLR are taken from their associated EIR-FPLR curve references.

fields.name: Heating Mode Temperature Curve Condenser Water Independent Variable
fields.memo: Sets the second independent variable in the three temperature dependent performance curves to either the leaving or entering condenser water temperature. Manufacturers express the performance of their chillers using either the leaving condenser water temperature (to the tower) or the entering condenser water temperature (from the tower). Heating mode (or Simul Clg/Htg Load) should be a function of Leaving Condenser Fluid Temperature Only use EnteringCondenser as a last resort in case no performance data exists for LeavingCondenser

fields.name: Heating Mode Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Evaporator (cooling) capacity as a function of leaving chilled water temperature and leaving condenser fluid temperature when in heating or simultaneous cool/heat mode curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*TCond + e*TCond**2 + f*CWS*TCond If independent variable = EnteringCondenser, TCond = ECT If independent variable = LeavingCondenser, TCond = LCT CWS = supply (leaving) chilled water temperature(C) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Heating Mode Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of leaving chilled water temperature when in heating or simultaneous cool/heat mode and leaving condenser fluid temperature.   EIR = 1/COP. curve = a + b*CWS + c*CWS**2 + d*TCond + e*TCond**2 + f*CWS*TCond If independent variable = EnteringCondenser, TCond = ECT If independent variable = LeavingCondenser, TCond = LCT CWS = leaving chilled water temperature(C) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Heating Mode Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: Electric Input Ratio (EIR) as a function of Part Load Ratio (PLR) when in heating or simultaneous cool/heat mode EIR = 1/COP Bicubic = a + b*LCT + c*LCT**2 + d*PLR + e*PLR**2 + f*LCT*PLR + g*0 + h*PLR**3 + i*0 + j*0 Normally, a bicubic curve here should be in terms of LCT rather than ECT Also, a bicubic curve is more applicable for variable-speed compressor motor drives or Quadratic = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady-state capacity) LCT = leaving condenser fluid temperature(C) ECT = entering condenser fluid temperature(C)

fields.name: Heating Mode Cooling Capacity Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Optimum part load ratio where the chiller is most efficient when in heating or simultaneous cool/heat mode. Must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio. The Min/Max PLR are taken from their associated EIR-FPLR curve references.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

thermalstorage:chilledwater:stratified.name: ThermalStorage:ChilledWater:Stratified
thermalstorage:chilledwater:stratified.memo: Chilled water storage with a stratified, multi-node tank. The chilled water is "used" by drawing from the "Use Side" of the water tank.  The tank is indirectly charged by circulating cold water through the "Source Side" of the water tank.

fields.name: Tank Height
fields.memo: Height is measured in the axial direction for horizontal cylinders

fields.name: Tank Perimeter
fields.memo: Only used if Tank Shape is Other

fields.name: Ambient Temperature Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: required for Ambient Temperature Indicator=Outdoors

fields.name: Uniform Skin Loss Coefficient per Unit Area to Ambient Temperature
Use Side Heat Transfer Effectiveness
fields.memo: The use side effectiveness in the stratified tank model is a simplified analogy of a heat exchanger's effectiveness. This effectiveness is equal to the fraction of use mass flow rate that directly mixes with the tank fluid. And one minus the effectiveness is the fraction that bypasses the tank. The use side mass flow rate that bypasses the tank is mixed with the fluid or water leaving the stratified tank.

fields.name: Use Side Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for use side. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Use Side Inlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to top of tank

fields.name: Use Side Outlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to bottom of tank

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Effectiveness
fields.memo: The source side effectiveness in the stratified tank model is a simplified analogy of a heat exchanger's effectiveness. This effectiveness is equal to the fraction of source mass flow rate that directly mixes with the tank fluid. And one minus the effectiveness is the fraction that bypasses the tank. The source side mass flow rate that bypasses the tank is mixed with the fluid or water leaving the stratified tank.

fields.name: Source Side Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for use side. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Source Side Inlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to bottom of tank

fields.name: Source Side Outlet Height
fields.memo: Defaults to top of tank

fields.name: Tank Recovery Time
fields.memo: Parameter for autosizing design flow rates for indirectly cooled water tanks time required to lower temperature of entire tank from 14.4C to 9.0C

controller:outdoorair.name: Controller:OutdoorAir
controller:outdoorair.memo: Controller to set the outdoor air flow rate for an air loop. Control options include fixed, proportional, scheduled, economizer, and demand-controlled ventilation.

fields.name: Actuator Node Name
fields.memo: Outdoor air inlet node entering the first pre-treat component if any

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: If there is a Mechanical Ventilation Controller (Controller:MechanicalVentilation), note that this value times the Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule is a hard minimum that may override DCV or other advanced OA controls.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for FixedDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Enthalpy
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor enthalpy limit for FixedEnthalpy economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Electronic Enthalpy Limit Curve Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a quadratic or cubic curve which defines the maximum outdoor humidity ratio (function of outdoor dry-bulb temperature) for ElectronicEnthalpy economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Minimum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for economizer control. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the minimum outdoor air flow rate

fields.name: Minimum Fraction of Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: schedule values multiply the design/mixed air flow rate

fields.name: Maximum Fraction of Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: schedule values multiply the design/mixed air flow rate

fields.name: Mechanical Ventilation Controller Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Controller:MechanicalVentilation object. Optional field for defining outdoor ventilation air based on flow rate per unit floor area and flow rate per person. Simplified method of demand-controlled ventilation.

fields.name: Time of Day Economizer Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: Optional schedule to simulate "push-button" type economizer control. Schedule values greater than 0 indicate time-of-day economizer control is enabled. Economizer control may be used with or without the high humidity control option. When used together, high humidity control has priority over economizer control. If the field Economizer Control Type = NoEconomizer, then this option is disabled.

fields.name: High Humidity Control
fields.memo: Optional field to enable modified outdoor air flow rates based on zone relative humidity. Select Yes to modify outdoor air flow rate based on a zone humidistat. Select No to disable this feature. If the field Economizer Control Type = NoEconomizer, then this option is disabled.

fields.name: Humidistat Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the zone where the humidistat is located. This field is only used when the field High Humidity Control = Yes.

fields.name: High Humidity Outdoor Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the ratio of outdoor air to the maximum outdoor air flow rate when modified air flow rates are active based on high indoor humidity. The minimum value must be greater than 0. This field is only used when the field High Humidity Control = Yes.

fields.name: Control High Indoor Humidity Based on Outdoor Humidity Ratio
fields.memo: If No is selected, the outdoor air flow rate is modified any time indoor relative humidity is above the humidistat setpoint. If Yes is selected, the outdoor air flow rate is modified any time the indoor relative humidity is above the humidistat setpoint and the outdoor humidity ratio is less than the indoor humidity ratio. This field is only used when the field High Humidity Control = Yes.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Bypass Control Type
fields.memo: BypassWhenWithinEconomizerLimits specifies that heat recovery is active only when the economizer is off because conditions are outside the economizer control limits BypassWhenOAFlowGreaterThanMinimum specifies enhanced economizer controls to allow heat recovery when economizer is active (within limits) but the outdoor air flow rate is at the minimum.

demandmanager:lights.name: DemandManager:Lights
demandmanager:lights.memo: used for demand limiting Lights objects.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Limit Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

fields.name: Limit Step Change
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Rotation Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

construction:internalsource.name: Construction:InternalSource
construction:internalsource.memo: Start with outside layer and work your way to the inside Layer Up to 10 layers total, 8 for windows Enter the material name for each layer

fields.name: Source Present After Layer Number
fields.memo: refers to the list of materials which follows

fields.name: Temperature Calculation Requested After Layer Number
fields.memo: refers to the list of materials which follows

fields.name: Dimensions for the CTF Calculation
fields.memo: 1 = 1-dimensional calculation, 2 = 2-dimensional calculation

fields.name: Tube Spacing
fields.memo: uniform spacing between tubes or resistance wires in direction perpendicular to main intended direction of heat transfer

zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:dec.name: ZoneContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:DecaySource
zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:dec.memo: Simulate generic contaminant source driven by the cutoff concentration model.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Initial Emission Rate. When the value is equal to 1.0, the time will be reset to zero.

generator:fuelcell:exhaustgastowaterheat.name: Generator:FuelCell:ExhaustGasToWaterHeatExchanger
generator:fuelcell:exhaustgastowaterheat.memo: Describes the exhaust gas heat exchanger subsystem of a fuel cell power generator used to recovery thermal energy

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Inlet Node Name
Heat Recovery Water Outlet Node Name
Heat Recovery Water Maximum Flow Rate
Method 3 N dot Water ref Coefficient

airflownetwork:multizone:surface:crack.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface:Crack
airflownetwork:multizone:surface:crack.memo: This object specifies the properties of airflow through a crack.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient at Reference Conditions
fields.memo: Enter the air mass flow coefficient at the conditions defined in the Reference Crack Conditions object. Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference across this crack.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent
fields.memo: Enter the air mass flow exponent for the surface crack.

fields.name: Reference Crack Conditions
fields.memo: Select a AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ReferenceCrackConditions name associated with the air mass flow coefficient entered above.

hvactemplate:zone:vrf.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:VRF
hvactemplate:zone:vrf.memo: Zone terminal unit with variable refrigerant flow (VRF) DX cooling and heating coils (air-to-air or water-to-air heat pump). The VRF terminal units are served by an HVACTemplate:System:VRF system.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template VRF System Name
fields.memo: Name of a HVACTemplate:System:VRF object serving this zone

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Rated Total Heating Capacity Sizing Ratio
fields.memo: If this terminal unit's heating coil is autosized, the heating capacity is sized to be equal to the cooling capacity multiplied by this sizing ratio. This input applies to the terminal unit heating coil and overrides the sizing ratio entered in the HVACTemplate:System:VRF object.

fields.name: Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: No Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This flow rate is used when the terminal is not cooling and the previous mode was cooling. This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: No Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This flow rate is used when the terminal is not heating and the previous mode was heating. This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Cooling Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: If this field is set to autosize it will be sized based on the outdoor air inputs below, unless a dedicated outdoor air system is specified for this zone and then it will be set to zero.

fields.name: Heating Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: If this field is set to autosize it will be sized based on the outdoor air inputs below, unless a dedicated outdoor air system is specified for this zone and then it will be set to zero.

fields.name: No Load Outdoor Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: If this field is set to autosize it will be sized based on the outdoor air inputs below, unless a dedicated outdoor air system is specified for this zone and then it will be set to zero.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Zone, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name
fields.memo: This field is used only when Outdoor Air Method=DetailedSpecification.

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan placement
fields.memo: Select fan placement as either blow through or draw through.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include effect of supply fan heat

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Capacity excluding supply air fan heat Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Zone Terminal Unit On Parasitic Electric Energy Use
Zone Terminal Unit Off Parasitic Electric Energy Use
Dedicated Outdoor Air System Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an HVACTemplate:System:DedicatedOutdoorAir object if this zone is served by a separate dedicated outdoor air system (DOAS). Leave field blank if no DOAS serves this zone.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be subtracted from the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method
fields.memo: SupplyAirTemperature = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature TemperatureDifference = use the value from Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = SupplyAirTemperature

fields.name: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Difference
