fields.memo: Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature is only used when Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature Input Method = TemperatureDifference The absolute value of this field will be added to the zone temperature at peak load to calculate the Zone Heating Design Supply Air Temperature.

fields.name: Baseboard Heating Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

setpointmanager:returnairbypassflow.name: SetpointManager:ReturnAirBypassFlow
setpointmanager:returnairbypassflow.memo: This setpoint manager determines the required mass flow rate through a return air bypass duct to meet the specified temperature setpoint

fields.name: HVAC Air Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC object.

zonehvac:baseboard:convective:water.name: ZoneHVAC:Baseboard:Convective:Water
zonehvac:baseboard:convective:water.memo: Hot water baseboard heater, convection-only. Natural convection hydronic heating unit.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:retur.name: FaultModel:TemperatureSensorOffset:ReturnAir
faultmodel:temperaturesensoroffset:retur.memo: This object describes return air temperature sensor offset

refrigeration:condenser:evaporativecoole.name: Refrigeration:Condenser:EvaporativeCooled
refrigeration:condenser:evaporativecoole.memo: Evaporative-cooled condenser for a refrigeration system (Refrigeration:System).

fields.name: Rated Effective Total Heat Rejection Rate
fields.memo: Rating as per ARI 490 Be sure the rating corresponds to the correct refrigerant

fields.name: Rated Subcooling Temperature Difference
fields.memo: must correspond to rating given for total heat rejection effect

fields.name: Rated Fan Power
fields.memo: Power for condenser fan(s) corresponding to rated total heat rejection effect.

fields.name: Minimum Fan Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Minimum air flow fraction through condenser fan

fields.name: Approach Temperature Constant Term
fields.memo: A1 in delta T = A1 + A2(hrcf) + A3/(hrcf) + A4(Twb)

fields.name: Approach Temperature Coefficient 2
fields.memo: A2 in delta T = A1 + A2(hrcf) +A3/(hrcf) +A4(Twb)

fields.name: Approach Temperature Coefficient 3
fields.memo: A3 in delta T = A1 + A2(hrcf) +A3/(hrcf) +A4(Twb)

fields.name: Approach Temperature Coefficient 4
fields.memo: A4 in deltaT=A1 + A2(hrcf) +A3/(hrcf) +A4(Twb)

fields.name: Minimum Capacity Factor
fields.memo: taken from manufacturer's Heat Rejection Capacity Factor Table

fields.name: Maximum Capacity Factor
fields.memo: taken from manufacturer's Heat Rejection Capacity Factor Table

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: If field is left blank, then the model assumes that the inlet air conditions are the outdoor air conditions for the current timestep (e.g., no adjustment for height above ground).

fields.name: Rated Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use and fan energy use.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for periods when the evap condenser is available (field Evaporative Condenser Availability Schedule). For this situation, the heater heats the basin water when the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature falls below the set point temperature, but only when the condenser fans are off (i.e., no refrigerated case load).

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature at which the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Rated Water Pump Power
fields.memo: Design recirculating water pump power.

fields.name: Evaporative Water Supply Tank Name
fields.memo: If blank, water supply is from Mains.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values greater than 0 indicate that evaporative cooling of the condenser is available. This schedule allows the user to define seasonal shutdown/draining of the water cooling system in cold climate applications. For periods with schedule values of 0, the condenser operates as Air Cooled.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Condenser Refrigerant Operating Charge Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Receiver Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

fields.name: Condensate Piping Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: optional input

hvactemplate:system:unitaryheatpump:airt.name: HVACTemplate:System:UnitaryHeatPump:AirToAir
hvactemplate:system:unitaryheatpump:airt.memo: Unitary furnace with electric air-to-air heat pump

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on; Unitary System always on.  Schedule is used in availability manager and fan scheduling. Also see "Night Cycle Control" field.

fields.name: Control Zone or Thermostat Location Name
Cooling Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during cooling operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate during heating operation This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Supply air flow rate when no cooling or heating is needed Only used when heat pump fan operating mode is Continuous. This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the DX coil compressor is off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used. This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will *not* be multiplied by any sizing factor or by zone multipliers.  If using zone multipliers a value entered here must be large enough to serve the multiplied zones.

fields.name: Supply Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Refers to a schedule to specify unitary supply fan operating mode. Schedule values of 0 indicate cycling fan (auto) Schedule values of 1 indicate continuous fan (on) If this field is left blank, a schedule of always zero (cycling fan) will be used.

fields.name: Supply Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction
Cooling Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Cooling Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Total Capacity
fields.memo: Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point: air entering the cooling coil at 26.7 C dry-bulb/19.4 C wet-bulb, and air entering the outdoor condenser coil at 35 C dry-bulb/23.9 C wet-bulb

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Rated sensible heat ratio (gross sensible capacity/gross total capacity) Sensible and total capacities do not include effect of supply fan heat

fields.name: Cooling Coil Gross Rated COP
fields.memo: Gross cooling capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electric power input

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Heating Design Supply Air Temperature
fields.memo: Used for sizing.

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Gross Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Rated heating capacity excluding the effect of supply air fan heat Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Coil Rated COP
fields.memo: Heat Pump Heating Coil Rated Capacity divided by power input to the compressor and outdoor fan, does not include supply air fan heat or supply air fan electrical energy. Rating point outdoor dry-bulb temp 8.33 C, outdoor wet-bulb temp 6.11 C Rating point heating coil entering air dry-bulb 21.11 C, coil entering wet-bulb 15.55 C

fields.name: Heat Pump Heating Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
Heat Pump Defrost Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
Heat Pump Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode only applicable if Timed defrost control is specified

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always on

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Supplemental heater will not operate when outdoor temperature exceeds this value.

fields.name: Supplemental Gas Heating Coil Efficiency
fields.memo: Applies only if Supplemental Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Supplemental Gas Heating Coil Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Applies only if Supplemental Heating Coil Type is Gas

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values multiply the minimum outdoor air flow rate If blank, multiplier is always one

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for FixedDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Enthalpy
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor enthalpy limit for FixedEnthalpy economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Maximum Limit Dewpoint Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor dewpoint temperature limit for FixedDewPointAndDryBulb economizer control type. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative. Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Economizer Minimum Limit Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor dry-bulb temperature limit for economizer control. No input or blank input means this limit is not operative Limit is applied regardless of economizer control type.

fields.name: Supply Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Supply plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Return Plenum Name
fields.memo: Plenum zone name.  Return plenum serves all zones on this system. Blank if none.

fields.name: Night Cycle Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Applicable only if Night Cycle Control is Cycle On Control Zone.

fields.name: Latent Heat Recovery Effectiveness
fields.memo: Applicable only if Heat Recovery Type is Enthalpy.

fields.name: Humidifier Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Capacity
fields.memo: Moisture output rate at full rated power input. The humidifier does not currently autosize, so the default is very large to allow for adequate capacity.

fields.name: Humidifier Rated Electric Power
fields.memo: Electric power input at rated capacity moisture output. Power consumption is proportional to moisture output with no part-load penalty.

fields.name: Humidifier Control Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name where humidistat is located

fields.name: Humidifier Setpoint
fields.memo: Zone relative humidity setpoint in percent (0 to 100)

fields.name: Return Fan
fields.memo: Specifies if the system has a return fan.

fields.name: Return Fan Motor in Air Stream Fraction

output:meter:meterfileonly.name: Output:Meter:MeterFileOnly
output:meter:meterfileonly.memo: Each Output:Meter:MeterFileOnly command picks meters to be put only onto meter file (.mtr). Not all meters are reported in every simulation. A list of meters that can be reported a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Key Name
fields.memo: Form is EnergyUseType:..., e.g. Electricity:* for all Electricity meters or EndUse:..., e.g. GeneralLights:* for all General Lights Output:Meter:MeterFileOnly puts results on the eplusout.mtr file only

fields.name: Reporting Frequency
fields.memo: Timestep refers to the zone Timestep/Number of Timesteps in hour value RunPeriod and Environment are the same

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitImport:From:Variable
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitim.memo: This object declares an FMU input variable

materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.name: MaterialProperty:HeatAndMoistureTransfer:Redistribution
materialproperty:heatandmoisturetransfer.memo: HeatBalanceAlgorithm = CombinedHeatAndMoistureFiniteElement solution algorithm only. Relationship between liquid transport coefficient and moisture content Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms

fields.name: Material Name
fields.memo: Moisture Material Name that the moisture properties will be added to.

fields.name: Number of Redistribution points
fields.memo: number of data points

airflownetwork:distribution:component:ou.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:OutdoorAirFlow
airflownetwork:distribution:component:ou.memo: This object includes the outdoor air flow rate set by the Controller:OutdoorAir object in the airflow network.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Coefficient When No Outdoor Air Flow at Reference Conditions
fields.memo: Enter the air mass flow coefficient at the conditions defined in the Reference Crack Conditions object. Defined at 1 Pa pressure difference. Enter the coefficient used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when no outdoor air flow rate.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent When No Outdoor Air Flow
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the following equation: Mass Flow Rate = Air Mass Flow Coefficient * (dP)^Air Mass Flow Exponent. Used only when no outdoor air flow rate.

fields.name: Reference Crack Conditions
fields.memo: Select a AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ReferenceCrackConditions name associated with the air mass flow coefficient entered above.

externalinterface:variable.name: ExternalInterface:Variable
externalinterface:variable.memo: This input object is similar to EnergyManagementSystem:GlobalVariable. However, at the beginning of each zone time step, its value is set to the value received from the external interface. During the warm-up period and the system sizing, its value is set to the value specified by the field "initial value." This object can be used to move data into Erl subroutines.

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during warm-up and system sizing.

fields.name: User Defined Fluid Type
fields.memo: This field is only required when Fluid Type is UserDefinedFluidType

fields.name: Common Pipe Simulation
fields.memo: Specifies a primary-secondary loop configuration. The plant side is the primary loop, and the demand side is the secondary loop. A secondary supply pump is required on the demand side. None = Primary-only, no secondary simulation CommonPipe = Primary-secondary with no temperature control at primary-secondary interface TwoWayCommonPipe = Primary-secondary with control of secondary supply temperature or primary return temperature (requires a setpoint be placed on the plant side or demand side inlet node).

fields.name: Loop Circulation Time
fields.memo: This field is only used to autocalulate the Plant Loop Volume. Loop Volume = Loop Circulation Time * Maximum Loop Flow Rate

groundheattransfer:basement:xface.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:XFACE
groundheattransfer:basement:xface.memo: This is only needed when using manual gridding (not recommended) XFACE: X Direction cell face coordinates: m

plantequipmentoperation:coolingload.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:CoolingLoad
plantequipmentoperation:coolingload.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for cooling load range operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive cooling load ranges.

plantequipmentoperation:outdoorwetbulb.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorWetBulb
plantequipmentoperation:outdoorwetbulb.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor wet-bulb temperature range operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive outdoor wet-bulb temperature ranges.

roofceiling:detailed.name: RoofCeiling:Detailed
roofceiling:detailed.memo: Allows for detailed entry of roof/ceiling heat transfer surfaces.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Non-blank only if the field Outside Boundary Condition is Surface, Zone, OtherSideCoefficients or OtherSideConditionsModel If Surface, specify name of corresponding surface in adjacent zone or specify current surface name for internal partition separating like zones If Zone, specify the name of the corresponding zone and the program will generate the corresponding interzone surface If OtherSideCoefficients, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideCoefficients If OtherSideConditionsModel, specify name of SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel

fields.name: View Factor to Ground
fields.memo: From the exterior of the surface Unused if one uses the "reflections" options in Solar Distribution in Building input unless a DaylightingDevice:Shelf or DaylightingDevice:Tubular object has been specified. autocalculate will automatically calculate this value from the tilt of the surface

fields.name: Number of Vertices
fields.memo: shown with 10 vertex coordinates -- extensible object "extensible" -- duplicate last set of x,y,z coordinates, renumbering please (and changing z terminator to a comma "," for all but last one which needs a semi-colon ";") vertices are given in GlobalGeometryRules coordinates -- if relative, all surface coordinates are "relative" to the Zone Origin.  If world, then building and zone origins are used for some internal calculations, but all coordinates are given in an "absolute" system.

zonehvac:fourpipefancoil.name: ZoneHVAC:FourPipeFanCoil
zonehvac:fourpipefancoil.memo: Four pipe fan coil system. Forced-convection hydronic heating-cooling unit with supply fan, hot water heating coil, chilled water cooling coil, and fixed-position outdoor air mixer.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Low Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio
Medium Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio
fields.memo: Medium Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio should be greater than Low Speed Supply Air Flow Ratio

fields.name: Outdoor Air Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value of schedule multiplies maximum outdoor air flow rate

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Object Type
fields.memo: Currently only one type OutdoorAir:Mixer object is available. This field should be left blank if the FanCoil is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Mixer Name
fields.memo: If this field is blank, the OutdoorAir:Mixer is not used. This optional field specifies the name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. When used, this name needs to match name of the OutdoorAir:Mixer object. This field should be left blank if the FanCoil is connected to central dedicated outdoor air through an AirTerminal:SingleDuct:Mixer object.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan type must be according to capacity control method (see I/O) For ConstantFanVariableFlow a Fan:OnOff or Fan:ConstantVolume is valid. For CyclingFan a Fan:OnOff is valid. For VariableFanVariableFlow or VariableFanConstantFlow a Fan:VariableVolume is valid. For ASHRAE90.1 a Fan:OnOff or Fan:VariableVolume is valid. Fan:SystemModel is valid for all capacity control methods. The fan's inlet node should be the same as the outdoor air mixer's mixed air node.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule that controls fan operation. Schedule Name values of 0 denote cycling fan operation (fan cycles with cooling coil). Schedule values greater than 0 denote constant fan operation (fan runs continually regardless of coil operation). The fan operating mode defaults to cycling fan operation if this field is left blank. This input field is currently used with MultiStageFan capacity control method

fields.name: Minimum Supply Air Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: For Capacity Control Method = ASHRAE90VariableFan, enter the minimum air temperature in cooling mode. Leave this field blank or enter 0 to control to the zone load per ASHRAE 90.1. In this case, a zone sizing simulation is required.

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: For Capacity Control Method = ASHRAE90VariableFan, enter the maximum air temperature in heating mode. Leave this field blank or enter 0 to control to the zone load per ASHRAE 90.1. In this case, a zone sizing simulation is required.

materialproperty:glazingspectraldata.name: MaterialProperty:GlazingSpectralData
materialproperty:glazingspectraldata.memo: Name is followed by up to 800 sets of normal-incidence measured values of [wavelength, transmittance, front reflectance, back reflectance] for wavelengths covering the solar spectrum (from about 0.25 to 2.5 microns)

curve:biquadratic.name: Curve:Biquadratic
curve:biquadratic.memo: Quadratic curve with two independent variables. Input consists of the curve name, the six coefficients, and min and max values for each of the independent variables. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2 + C4*y + C5*y**2 + C6*x*y

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

zonehvac:evaporativecoolerunit.name: ZoneHVAC:EvaporativeCoolerUnit
zonehvac:evaporativecoolerunit.memo: Zone evaporative cooler. Forced-convection cooling-only unit with supply fan, 100% outdoor air supply.  Optional relief exhaust node

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: this is an outdoor air node

fields.name: Cooler Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: this is a zone inlet node

fields.name: Zone Relief Air Node Name
fields.memo: this is a zone exhaust node, optional if flow is being balanced elsewhere

fields.name: Throttling Range Temperature Difference
fields.memo: used for ZoneTemperatureDeadbandOnOffCycling hystersis range for thermostatic control

fields.name: Cooling Load Control Threshold Heat Transfer Rate
fields.memo: Sign convention is that positive values indicate a cooling load

fields.name: Second Evaporative Cooler Object Type
fields.memo: optional, used for direct/indirect configurations second cooler must be immediately downstream of first cooler, if present

fields.name: Second Evaporative Cooler Name
fields.memo: optional, used for direct/indirect configurations

fields.name: Design Specification ZoneHVAC Sizing Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a DesignSpecificationZoneHVACSizing object.

groundheattransfer:basement:bldgdata.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:BldgData
groundheattransfer:basement:bldgdata.memo: Specifies the surface and gravel thicknesses used for the Basement preprocessor ground heat transfer simulation.

fields.name: DGRAVXY: Width of gravel pit beside basement wall
DGRAVZN: Gravel depth extending above the floor slab
DGRAVZP: Gravel depth below the floor slab

outdoorair:nodelist.name: OutdoorAir:NodeList
outdoorair:nodelist.memo: This object sets the temperature and humidity conditions for an outdoor air node using the weather data values. to vary outdoor air node conditions with height above ground use OutdoorAir:Node instead of this object. This object may be used more than once. The same node name may not appear in both an OutdoorAir:Node object and an OutdoorAir:NodeList object.

plantequipmentoperation:heatingload.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:HeatingLoad
plantequipmentoperation:heatingload.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for heating load range operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive heating load ranges.

curve:exponentialdecay.name: Curve:ExponentialDecay
curve:exponentialdecay.memo: Exponential decay curve with one independent variable. Input consists of the curve name, the three coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1+C2*exp(C3*x)

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

airflownetwork:distribution:component:he.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:HeatExchanger
airflownetwork:distribution:component:he.memo: This object defines the name of an air-to-air heat exchanger used in an air loop.

fields.name: HeatExchanger Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an air-to-air heat exchanger in the primary Air loop.

fields.name: HeatExchanger Object Type
fields.memo: Select the type of heat exchanger corresponding to the name entered in the field above.

fields.name: Air Path Length
fields.memo: Enter the air path length (depth) for the heat exchanger.

fields.name: Air Path Hydraulic Diameter
fields.memo: Enter the hydraulic diameter of this heat exchanger. The hydraulic diameter is defined as 4 multiplied by the cross section area divided by perimeter.

setpointmanager:followgroundtemperature.name: SetpointManager:FollowGroundTemperature
setpointmanager:followgroundtemperature.memo: This setpoint manager is used to place a temperature setpoint on a system node that is derived from a current ground temperature. The ground temperatures are specified in different Site:GroundTemperature:* objects and used during the simulation. This setpoint manager is primarily intended for condenser or plant loops using some type of ground heat exchanger.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which control variable will be set

lifecyclecost:usepriceescalation.name: LifeCycleCost:UsePriceEscalation
lifecyclecost:usepriceescalation.memo: Life cycle cost escalation factors. The values for this object may be found in the annual supplement to NIST Handbook 135 in Tables Ca-1 to Ca-5 and are included in an EnergyPlus dataset file.

fields.name: LCC Price Escalation Name
fields.memo: The identifier used for the object. The name usually identifies the location (such as the state or region or country or census area) that the escalations apply to. In addition the name should identify the building class such as residential or commercial or industrial and the use type such as electricity or natural gas or water.

fields.name: Escalation Start Year
fields.memo: This field and the Escalation Start Month define the time that corresponds to Year 1 Escalation such as 2010 when the escalation rates are applied. This field and the Escalation Start Month define the time that escalation begins.

fields.name: Escalation Start Month
fields.memo: This field and the Escalation Start Year define the time that corresponds to Year 1 Escalation such as 2010 when the escalation rates are applied. This field and the Escalation Start Year define the time that escalation begins.

energymanagementsystem:actuator.name: EnergyManagementSystem:Actuator
energymanagementsystem:actuator.memo: Hardware portion of EMS used to set up actuators in the model

windowmaterial:shade:equivalentlayer.name: WindowMaterial:Shade:EquivalentLayer
windowmaterial:shade:equivalentlayer.memo: Specifies the properties of equivalent layer window shade material Shades are considered to be perfect diffusers (all transmitted and reflected radiation is hemispherically-diffuse) independent of angle of incidence.  Shade represents roller blinds.

fields.name: Shade Beam-Beam Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The beam-beam solar transmittance at normal incidence.  This value is the same as the openness area fraction of the shade material. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides.

fields.name: Front Side Shade Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Shade Beam-Diffuse Solar Transmittance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Front Side Shade Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The front side beam-diffuse solar reflectance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Back Side Shade Beam-Diffuse Solar Reflectance
fields.memo: The back side beam-diffuse solar reflectance at normal incidence averaged over the entire spectrum of solar radiation.

fields.name: Shade Beam-Beam Visible Transmittance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: The beam-beam visible transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides of the shade.

fields.name: Shade Beam-Diffuse Visible Transmittance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse visible transmittance at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides of the shade.

fields.name: Shade Beam-Diffuse Visible Reflectance at Normal Incidence
fields.memo: The beam-diffuse visible reflectance at normal incidence averaged over the visible spectrum range of solar radiation. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides of the shade.

fields.name: Shade Material Infrared Transmittance
fields.memo: The long-wave transmittance of the shade material at zero shade openness. Assumed to be the same for front and back sides of the shade.

fields.name: Front Side Shade Material Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: The front side long-wave emissivity of the shade material at zero shade openness. Openness fraction is used to calculate the effective emissivity value.

fields.name: Back Side Shade Material Infrared Emissivity
fields.memo: The back side long-wave emissivity of the shade material at zero shade openness. Openness fraction is used to calculate the effective emissivity value.

hvactemplate:plant:chiller:objectreferen.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:Chiller:ObjectReference
hvactemplate:plant:chiller:objectreferen.memo: This object references a detailed chiller object and adds it to an HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop. The user must create a complete detailed chiller object with all required curve or performance objects.

fields.name: Chiller Name
fields.memo: The name of the detailed chiller object.

fields.name: Priority
fields.memo: If Chiller Plant Operation Scheme Type=Default in HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop, then equipment operates in Priority order, 1, 2, 3, etc.

output:surfaces:list.name: Output:Surfaces:List
output:surfaces:list.memo: Produces a report summarizing the details of surfaces in the eio output file.

fields.name: Report Specifications
fields.memo: (IDF, only for Output:Surfaces:List, Lines report -- will print transformed coordinates in IDF style)

output:preprocessormessage.name: Output:PreprocessorMessage
output:preprocessormessage.memo: This object does not come from a user input.  This is generated by a pre-processor so that various conditions can be gracefully passed on by the InputProcessor.

fields.name: Error Severity
fields.memo: Depending on type, InputProcessor may terminate the program.

coil:cooling:water:detailedgeometry.name: Coil:Cooling:Water:DetailedGeometry
coil:cooling:water:detailedgeometry.memo: Chilled water cooling coil, detailed flat fin coil model for continuous plate fins, with inputs for detailed coil geometry specifications.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Tube Outside Surface Area
fields.memo: Tube Primary Surface Area

fields.name: Total Tube Inside Area
fields.memo: Total tube inside surface area

fields.name: Fin Diameter
fields.memo: Fin diameter or the coil height

fields.name: Tube Inside Diameter
fields.memo: Inner diameter of tubes

fields.name: Tube Outside Diameter
fields.memo: Outer diameter of tubes

fields.name: Fin Spacing
fields.memo: Fin spacing or distance

fields.name: Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Design Water Temperature Difference
fields.memo: This input field is optional. If specified, it is used for sizing the Design Water Flow Rate. If blank or omitted, the Loop Design Temperature Difference value specified in Sizing:Plant object is used for sizing the Design Water Flow Rate.

heatbalancealgorithm.name: HeatBalanceAlgorithm
heatbalancealgorithm.memo: Determines which Heat Balance Algorithm will be used ie. CTF (Conduction Transfer Functions), EMPD (Effective Moisture Penetration Depth with Conduction Transfer Functions). Advanced/Research Usage: CondFD (Conduction Finite Difference) Advanced/Research Usage: ConductionFiniteDifferenceSimplified Advanced/Research Usage: HAMT (Combined Heat And Moisture Finite Element)

fields.name: Minimum Surface Convection Heat Transfer Coefficient Value
Maximum Surface Convection Heat Transfer Coefficient Value

surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm.name: SurfaceProperty:HeatTransferAlgorithm
surfaceproperty:heattransferalgorithm.memo: Determines which Heat Balance Algorithm will be used for a specific surface Allows selectively overriding the global setting in HeatBalanceAlgorithm CTF (Conduction Transfer Functions), EMPD (Effective Moisture Penetration Depth with Conduction Transfer Functions). Advanced/Research Usage: CondFD (Conduction Finite Difference) Advanced/Research Usage: HAMT (Combined Heat And Moisture Finite Element)

hvactemplate:plant:chiller.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:Chiller
hvactemplate:plant:chiller.memo: This object adds a chiller to an HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop.

fields.name: Nominal COP
fields.memo: Not applicable if Chiller Type is DistrictChilledWater Electric Reciprocating Chiller

fields.name: Condenser Type
fields.memo: Not applicable if Chiller Type is DistrictChilledWater

fields.name: Priority
fields.memo: If Chiller Plant Operation Scheme Type=Default in HVACTemplate:Plant:ChilledWaterLoop, then equipment operates in Priority order, 1, 2, 3, etc.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

fields.name: Minimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Part load ratio below which the chiller starts cycling on/off to meet the load. Must be less than or equal to Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Maximum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Maximum allowable part load ratio. Must be greater than or equal to Minimum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: Optimum part load ratio where the chiller is most efficient. Must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Minimum Unloading Ratio
fields.memo: Part load ratio where the chiller can no longer unload and false loading begins. Minimum unloading ratio must be greater than or equal to the Minimum Part Load Ratio and less than or equal to the Maximum Part Load Ratio.

fields.name: Leaving Chilled Water Lower Temperature Limit

table:twoindependentvariables.name: Table:TwoIndependentVariables
table:twoindependentvariables.memo: Allows entry of tabular data pairs as alternate input for performance curve objects. Performance curve objects can be created using these inputs. BiQuadratic Table Equation: Output = a + bX + cX**2 + dY + eY**2 + fXY BiQuadratic solution requires a minimum of 6 data pairs QuadraticLinear Table Equation: Output = a + bX + cX**2 + dY + eXY + fX**2Y QuadraticLinear solution requires a minimum of 6 data pairs

fields.name: Minimum Table Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this table lookup object

fields.name: Maximum Table Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this table lookup object

fields.name: Normalization Reference
fields.memo: This field is used to normalize the following output data. The minimum and maximum table output fields are also normalized. If this field is blank or 1, the table data presented below will be used.

hvactemplate:plant:mixedwaterloop.name: HVACTemplate:Plant:MixedWaterLoop
hvactemplate:plant:mixedwaterloop.memo: Central plant loop portion of a water source heat pump system.

fields.name: Pump Schedule Name
fields.memo: If blank, always available Applies to both chilled water and condenser loop pumps

fields.name: Pump Control Type
fields.memo: Applies to both chilled water and condenser loop pumps

fields.name: Operation Scheme Type
fields.memo: Default operation type makes all equipment available at all times operating in order of Priority specified in HVACTemplate:Plant:Boiler and HVACTemplate:Plant:Tower objects.

fields.name: Equipment Operation Schemes Name
fields.memo: Name of a PlantEquipmentOperationSchemes object Ignored if Plant Operation Scheme Type = Default

fields.name: High Temperature Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint

fields.name: High Temperature Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Setpoint Schedule Name is specified.

fields.name: Low Temperature Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Leave blank if constant setpoint May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Low Temperature Design Setpoint
fields.memo: Used for sizing and as constant setpoint if no Condenser Water Setpoint Schedule Name is specified. May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers

fields.name: Water Pump Configuration
fields.memo: VariableFlow - variable flow to boilers and coils, excess bypassed ConstantFlow - constant flow to boilers and coils, excess bypassed

fields.name: Water Pump Rated Head
fields.memo: May be left blank if not serving any water cooled chillers default head is 60 feet H2O

fields.name: Water Pump Type
fields.memo: Describes the type of pump configuration used for the mixed water loop.

fields.name: Supply Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a supply side bypass pipe is present in the hot water loop.

fields.name: Demand Side Bypass Pipe
fields.memo: Determines if a demand side bypass pipe is present in the hot water loop.

fields.name: Loop Design Delta Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature difference used in sizing the loop flow rate.

airflownetwork:multizone:zone.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Zone
airflownetwork:multizone:zone.memo: This object is used to simultaneously control a thermal zone's window and door openings, both exterior and interior.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter the zone name where ventilation control is required.

fields.name: Ventilation Control Mode
fields.memo: When Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature or Enthalpy, the following fields are used to modulate the Ventilation Open Factor for all window and door openings in the zone according to the zone's indoor-outdoor temperature or enthalpy difference. Constant: controlled by field Venting Schedule Name. NoVent: control will not open window or door during simulation (Ventilation Open Factor = 0).

fields.name: Ventilation Control Zone Temperature Setpoint Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature or Enthalpy.

fields.name: Minimum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Used only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature or Enthalpy.

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Temperature Difference Lower Limit For Maximum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature. This value must be less than the corresponding upper value (next field).

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Temperature Difference Upper Limit for Minimum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Temperature. This value must be greater than the corresponding lower value (previous field).

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Enthalpy Difference Lower Limit For Maximum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Enthalpy. This value must be less than the corresponding upper value (next field).

fields.name: Indoor and Outdoor Enthalpy Difference Upper Limit for Minimum Venting Open Factor
fields.memo: Applicable only if Ventilation Control Mode = Enthalpy. This value must be greater than the corresponding lower value (previous field).

fields.name: Venting Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Non-zero Schedule value means venting is allowed if other venting control conditions are satisfied. A zero (or negative) Schedule value means venting is not allowed under any The Schedule values should be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 1. circumstances. If this Schedule is not specified then venting is allowed if other venting control conditions are satisfied. Not used if Ventilation Control Mode = NoVent.

fields.name: Single Sided Wind Pressure Coefficient Algorithm
fields.memo: Selecting Advanced results in EnergyPlus calculating modified Wind Pressure Coefficients to account for wind direction and turbulence effects on single sided ventilation rates. Model is only valid for zones with 2 openings, both of which are on a single facade.

fields.name: Facade Width
fields.memo: This is the whole building width along the direction of the facade of this zone.

fields.name: Occupant Ventilation Control Name
fields.memo: Enter the name where Occupancy Ventilation Control is required.

wateruse:well.name: WaterUse:Well
wateruse:well.memo: Simulates on-site water supply from a well. Well water is pumped out of the ground into a WaterUse:Storage. The operation of the ground water well is controlled by the associated WaterUse:Storage which is assumed to be operated as a vented cistern with no pressure tank.

surfaceconvectionalgorithm:outside.name: SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Outside
surfaceconvectionalgorithm:outside.memo: Default outside surface heat transfer convection algorithm to be used for all zones

fields.name: Algorithm
fields.memo: SimpleCombined = Combined radiation and convection coefficient using simple ASHRAE model TARP = correlation from models developed by ASHRAE, Walton, and Sparrow et. al. MoWiTT = correlation from measurements by Klems and Yazdanian for smooth surfaces DOE-2 = correlation from measurements by Klems and Yazdanian for rough surfaces AdaptiveConvectionAlgorithm = dynamic selection of correlations based on conditions

airterminal:singleduct:vav:reheat.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:Reheat
airterminal:singleduct:vav:reheat.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume, with reheat coil (hot water, electric, gas, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Damper Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: the outlet node of the damper and the inlet node of the reheat coil this is an internal node to the terminal unit and connects the damper and reheat coil

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: the inlet node to the terminal unit and the damper

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method
fields.memo: Constant = Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction (a fraction of Maximum Air Flow Rate) FixedFlowRate = Fixed Minimum Air Flow Rate (a fixed minimum air volume flow rate) Scheduled = Scheduled Minimum Air Flow Fraction (a fraction of Maximum Air Flow

fields.name: Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Constant If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional; if a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the following field are entered, the larger result is used. The values for autosizing are picked up from the Sizing:Zone input fields "Cooling Minimum Air Flow per Zone Floor Area", "Cooling Minimum Air Flow", and "Cooling Minimum Air Flow Fraction". If there is no sizing calculation a default of 0.000762 m3/s-m2 (0.15 cfm/ft2) is used.

fields.name: Fixed Minimum Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is FixedFlowRate. If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional; if a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the previous field are entered, the larger result is used. The values for autosizing are picked up from the Sizing:Zone input fields "Cooling Minimum Air Flow per Zone Floor Area", "Cooling Minimum Air Flow", and "Cooling Minimum Air Flow Fraction". If there is no sizing calculation a default of 0.000762 m3/s-m2 (0.15 cfm/ft2) is used.

fields.name: Minimum Air Flow Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled Schedule values are fractions, 0.0 to 1.0. If the field Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction is blank, then the average of the minimum and maximum schedule values is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils.

fields.name: Maximum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Minimum Hot Water or Steam Flow Rate
fields.memo: Not used when reheat coil type is gas or electric

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The outlet node of the terminal unit and the reheat coil. This is also the zone inlet node.

fields.name: Damper Heating Action
fields.memo: Normal means the damper is fixed at the minimum position in heating mode Reverse means the damper can open fully during reheat ReverseWithLimits means the damper will open partially during reheat as specified in the following 2 fields

fields.name: Maximum Flow per Zone Floor Area During Reheat
fields.memo: Used only when Reheat Coil Object Type = Coil:Heating:Water and Damper Heating Action = ReverseWithLimits When autocalculating, the maximum flow per zone is set to 0.002032 m3/s-m2 (0.4 cfm/sqft) This optional field limits the maximum flow allowed in reheat mode. At no time will the maximum flow rate calculated here exceed the value of Maximum Air Flow Rate.

fields.name: Maximum Flow Fraction During Reheat
fields.memo: Used only when Reheat Coil Object Type = Coil:Heating:Water and Damper Heating Action = ReverseWithLimits When autocalculating, the maximum flow fraction is set to the ratio of 0.002032 m3/s-m2 (0.4 cfm/sqft) multiplied by the zone floor area and the Maximum Air Flow Rate. This optional field limits the maximum flow allowed in reheat mode. At no time will the maximum flow rate calculated here exceed the value of Maximum Air Flow Rate.

fields.name: Maximum Reheat Air Temperature
fields.memo: Specifies the maximum allowable supply air temperature leaving the reheat coil. If left blank, there is no limit and no default. If unknown, 35C (95F) is recommended.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will increase flow as needed to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow.

electricloadcenter:storage:converter.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Storage:Converter
electricloadcenter:storage:converter.memo: This model is for converting AC to DC for grid-supplied charging of DC storage

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the converter is always available.

fields.name: Power Conversion Efficiency Method
fields.memo: SimpleFixed indicates power conversion losses are based on Simple Fixed Efficiency FunctionOfPower indicates power conversion losses are a function of normalized power using a curve or table.

fields.name: Simple Fixed Efficiency
fields.memo: Constant efficiency for conversion of AC to DC at all power levels. Field is only used when Power Conversion Efficiency Method is set to SimpleFixed.

fields.name: Design Maximum Continuous Input Power
fields.memo: Required field when Power Conversion Efficiency Method is set to FunctionOfPower.

fields.name: Efficiency Function of Power Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve or table with a single independent variable that describes efficiency as a function of normalized power. The "x" input for curve or table is the ratio of current input power divided by design power in the previous field Required field when Power Conversion Efficiency Method is set to FunctionOfPower.

fields.name: Ancillary Power Consumed In Standby
fields.memo: Optional standby power consumed when converter is available but no power is being conditioned.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: enter name of zone to receive converter losses as heat if blank then converter is assumed to be outdoors

fields.name: Radiative Fraction
fields.memo: fraction of zone heat gains treated as thermal radiation

refrigeration:secondarysystem.name: Refrigeration:SecondarySystem
refrigeration:secondarysystem.memo: Works in conjunction with refrigerated cases and walkins to simulate the performance of a secondary loop supermarket refrigeration system. Heat from the refrigeration loads served by the secondary loop is absorbed by a primary refrigeration system (Refrigeration:System). The SecondarySystem object simulates a heat exchanger that is an evaporator, or refrigeration load, on the primary refrigeration system.

fields.name: Refrigerated Case or Walkin or CaseAndWalkInList Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a Refrigeration:Case or Refrigeration:WalkIn object. If there is more than one refrigerated case or walk-in served by this secondary system, enter the name of a Refrigeration:CaseAndWalkInList object.

fields.name: Circulating Fluid Type
fields.memo: If "FluidAlwaysLiquid" is selected, the fluid properties must be input using the objects: FluidProperties:Name, FluidProperties:GlycolConcentration, and, if user defined fluid type, FluidProperties:Temperatures and FluidProperties:Concentration. Many sets of fluid properties can be found in GlycolPropertiesRefData.idf. If "FluidPhaseChange" is selected, the refrigerant properties must be input using the objects: (if user defined fluid type): FluidProperties:Name, FluidProperties:Temperatures, FluidProperties:Saturated, and FluidProperties:Superheated. Many sets of refrigerant data can be found in FluidPropertiesRefData.idf.

fields.name: Circulating Fluid Name
fields.memo: This must correspond to a name in the FluidProperties:Name object.

fields.name: Evaporator Capacity
fields.memo: For "FluidAlwaysLiquid", at least one of the two, Evaporator Capacity OR Evaporator Flow Rate for Secondary Fluid, is required. For "FluidPhaseChange", the default capacity is the sum of the rated capacities of the Cases and Walk-ins served by the secondary loop.

fields.name: Evaporator Flow Rate for Secondary Fluid
fields.memo: For "FluidAlwaysLiquid", at least one of the two, Evaporator Capacity OR Evaporator Flow Rate for Secondary Fluid, is required. For "FluidPhaseChange" loops, this input is not used. (see PhaseChange Circulating Rate)

fields.name: Evaporator Evaporating Temperature
fields.memo: This is the evaporating temperature in the heat exchanger used to chill or condense the secondary loop circulating fluid. It is NOT the temperature in any cases or walk-ins served by the secondary loop.

fields.name: Evaporator Approach Temperature Difference
fields.memo: For "FluidAlwaysLiquid", this is the rated difference between the temperature of the circulating fluid leaving the heat exchanger and the heat exchanger's rated evaporating temperature. For "FluidPhaseChange", this is the difference between the temperature of the evaporating and condensing temperatures in the heat exchanger.

fields.name: Evaporator Range Temperature Difference
fields.memo: For "FluidAlwaysLiquid", this is the rated difference between the temperature of the circulating fluid entering the heat exchanger and the temperature of the circulating fluid leaving the heat exchanger, and is Required. For "FluidPhaseChange", this input is not used.

fields.name: Total Pump Flow Rate
fields.memo: For "FluidAlwaysLiquid",if not input, Evaporator Flow Rate for Secondary Fluid will be used. For "FluidPhaseChange", if not input, this will be calculated using the PhaseChange Circulating Rate.

fields.name: Total Pump Power
fields.memo: Either the Total Pump Power or the Total Pump Head is required.

fields.name: Total Pump Head
fields.memo: Either the Total Pump Power or the Total Pump Head is required.

fields.name: PhaseChange Circulating Rate
fields.memo: This is the total mass flow at the pump divided by the gaseous mass flow leaving the refrigeration load.

fields.name: Variable Speed Pump Cubic Curve Name
fields.memo: Variable Speed Pump Curve Name is applicable to variable speed pumps only.

fields.name: Pump Motor Heat to Fluid
fields.memo: This is the portion of the pump motor heat added to secondary circulating fluid and is equal to the motor efficiency for non-hermetic motor. Enter 1.0 for a semi-hermetic motor.

fields.name: Sum UA Distribution Piping
fields.memo: Use only if you want to include distribution piping heat gain in refrigeration load.

fields.name: Distribution Piping Zone Name
fields.memo: This will be used to determine the temperature used for distribution piping heat gain. The pipe heat gains are also counted as cooling credit for the zone. Required only if Sum UA Distribution Piping >0.0

fields.name: Sum UA Receiver/Separator Shell
fields.memo: Use only if you want to include Receiver/Separator Shell heat gain in refrigeration load.

fields.name: Receiver/Separator Zone Name
fields.memo: This will be used to determine the temperature used for Receiver/Separator Shell heat gain. The shell heat gains are also counted as cooling credit for the zone. Required only if Sum UA Receiver/Separator Shell >0.0

fields.name: Evaporator Refrigerant Inventory
fields.memo: This value refers to the refrigerant circulating within the primary system providing cooling to the chiller for the secondary loop, not to the fluid circulating within the secondary loop itself.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

output:surfaces:drawing.name: Output:Surfaces:Drawing
output:surfaces:drawing.memo: Produces reports/files that are capable of rendering graphically or being imported into other programs. Rendering does not alter the actual inputs/surfaces.

fields.name: Report Specifications 1
fields.memo: Triangulate3DFace (default), ThickPolyline, RegularPolyline apply to DXF This field is ignored for DXF:WireFrame and VRML

fields.name: Report Specifications 2
fields.memo: Use ColorScheme Name for DXF reports

zoneairheatbalancealgorithm.name: ZoneAirHeatBalanceAlgorithm
zoneairheatbalancealgorithm.memo: Determines which algorithm will be used to solve the zone air heat balance.

curve:exponentialskewnormal.name: Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal
curve:exponentialskewnormal.memo: Exponential-modified skew normal curve with one independent variable. Input consists of the curve name, the four coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = see Input Output Reference

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

demandmanager:ventilation.name: DemandManager:Ventilation
demandmanager:ventilation.memo: used for demand limiting Controller:OutdoorAir objects.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this demand manager. Schedule value > 0 means the demand manager is available. If this field is blank, the DR is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Limit Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

fields.name: Fixed Rate
fields.memo: Used in case when Limit strategy is set to FixedRate

fields.name: Reduction Ratio
fields.memo: Used in case when Limit Control is set to ReductionRatio

fields.name: Limit Step Change
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Rotation Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

daylightingdevice:shelf.name: DaylightingDevice:Shelf
daylightingdevice:shelf.memo: Defines a daylighting which can have an inside shelf, an outside shelf, or both. The inside shelf is defined as a building surface and the outside shelf is defined as a shading surface.

fields.name: Inside Shelf Name
fields.memo: This must refer to a BuildingSurface:Detailed or equivalent object This surface must be its own Surface for other side boundary conditions.

fields.name: Outside Shelf Name
fields.memo: This must refer to a Shading:Zone:Detailed object

fields.name: Outside Shelf Construction Name
fields.memo: Required if outside shelf is specified

surfaceconvectionalgorithm:inside:usercu.name: SurfaceConvectionAlgorithm:Inside:UserCurve
surfaceconvectionalgorithm:inside:usercu.memo: Used to describe a custom model equation for surface convection heat transfer coefficient If more than one curve is referenced they are all used and added together.

fields.name: Reference Temperature for Convection Heat Transfer
fields.memo: Controls which temperature is differenced from surface temperature when using the Hc value

fields.name: Hc Function of Temperature Difference Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is absolute value of delta-T (Surface temperature minus reference temperature, (C))

fields.name: Hc Function of Temperature Difference Divided by Height Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is absolute value of delta-T/Height (Surface temp minus Air temp)/(vertical length scale), (C/m) when used for an inside face the vertical length scale is the zone's interior height

fields.name: Hc Function of Air Change Rate Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is mechanical ACH (Air Changes per hour from mechanical air system), (1/hr)

fields.name: Hc Function of Air System Volume Flow Rate Divided by Zone Perimeter Length Curve Name
fields.memo: Curve's "x" is mechanical system air flow rate (m3/s) divided by zone's length along exterior walls (m).

connector:mixer.name: Connector:Mixer
connector:mixer.memo: Mix N inlet air/water streams into one.  Branch names cannot be duplicated within a single mixer list.

hvactemplate:system:vrf.name: HVACTemplate:System:VRF
hvactemplate:system:vrf.memo: Variable refrigerant flow (VRF) heat pump condensing unit. Serves one or more VRF zone terminal units (HVACTemplate:Zone:VRF).

fields.name: System Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Gross Rated Total Cooling Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the total cooling capacity in watts at rated conditions or set to autosize. Total cooling capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Gross Rated Cooling COP
fields.memo: Enter the coefficient of performance at rated conditions or leave blank to use default. COP includes compressor and condenser fan electrical energy input COP does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electric power input

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation. Cooling is disabled below this temperature.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for cooling operation. Cooling is disabled above this temperature.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the heating capacity in watts at rated conditions or set to autosize. Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Rated Heating Capacity Sizing Ratio
fields.memo: If the Gross Rated Heating Capacity is autosized, the heating capacity is sized to be equal to the cooling capacity multiplied by this sizing ratio. The zone terminal unit heating coils are also sized using this ratio unless the sizing ratio input in the ZoneHVAC:TerminalUnit:VariableRefrigerantFlow object is entered.

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating COP
fields.memo: COP includes compressor and condenser fan electrical energy input COP does not include supply fan heat or supply fan electrical energy input

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the minimum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature allowed for heating operation.

fields.name: Minimum Heat Pump Part-Load Ratio
fields.memo: Enter the minimum heat pump part-load ratio (PLR). When the cooling or heating PLR is below this value, the heat pump compressor will cycle to meet the cooling or heating demand.

fields.name: Zone Name for Master Thermostat Location
fields.memo: Enter the name of the zone where the master thermostat is located.

fields.name: Master Thermostat Priority Control Type
fields.memo: Choose a thermostat control logic scheme. If these control types fail to control zone temperature within a reasonable limit, consider using multiple VRF systems

fields.name: Thermostat Priority Schedule Name
fields.memo: this field is required if Master Thermostat Priority Control Type is Scheduled. Schedule values of 0 denote cooling, 1 for heating, and all other values disable the system.

fields.name: Heat Pump Waste Heat Recovery
fields.memo: This field is reserved for future use. The only valid choice is No.

fields.name: Equivalent Piping Length used for Piping Correction Factor in Cooling Mode
fields.memo: Enter the equivalent length of the farthest terminal unit from the condenser

fields.name: Vertical Height used for Piping Correction Factor
fields.memo: Enter the height difference between the highest and lowest terminal unit

fields.name: Equivalent Piping Length used for Piping Correction Factor in Heating Mode
fields.memo: Enter the equivalent length of the farthest terminal unit from the condenser

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Power per Compressor
fields.memo: Enter the value of the resistive heater located in the compressor(s). This heater is used to warm the refrigerant and oil when the compressor is off.

fields.name: Number of Compressors
fields.memo: Enter the total number of compressor. This input is used only for crankcase heater calculations.

fields.name: Ratio of Compressor Size to Total Compressor Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the ratio of the first stage compressor to total compressor capacity. All other compressors are assumed to be equally sized. This inputs is used only for crankcase heater calculations.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which the crankcase heaters are disabled.

fields.name: Defrost Strategy
fields.memo: Select a defrost strategy. Reverse cycle reverses the operating mode from heating to cooling to melt frost formation on the condenser coil. The resistive strategy uses a resistive heater to melt the frost.

fields.name: Defrost Control
fields.memo: Choose a defrost control type. Either use a fixed Timed defrost period or select OnDemand to defrost only when necessary.

fields.name: Defrost Time Period Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of time in defrost mode. Only applicable if timed defrost control is specified.

fields.name: Resistive Defrost Heater Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the size of the resistive defrost heating element. Only applicable if resistive defrost strategy is specified

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-bulb Temperature for Defrost Operation
fields.memo: Enter the maximum outdoor temperature above which defrost operation is disabled.

fields.name: Condenser Type
fields.memo: Select either an air cooled or evaporatively cooled condenser.

fields.name: Water Condenser Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when Condenser Type = WaterCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Effectiveness
fields.memo: Enter the effectiveness of the evaporatively cooled condenser. This field is only used when the Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Used to calculate evaporative condenser water use. This field is only used when the Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Evaporative Condenser Pump Rated Power Consumption
fields.memo: Rated power consumed by the evaporative condenser's water pump. This field is only used when the Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled.

fields.name: Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
fields.memo: The minimum outdoor temperature below which heat recovery mode will not operate.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Temperature in Heat Recovery Mode
fields.memo: The maximum outdoor temperature above which heat recovery mode will not operate.

solarcollector:unglazedtranspired:multis.name: SolarCollector:UnglazedTranspired:Multisystem
solarcollector:unglazedtranspired:multis.memo: quad-tuples of inlet, outlet, control, and zone nodes for multiple different outdoor air systems attached to same collector

fields.name: Solar Collector Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a SolarCollector:UnglazedTranspired object.

airloophvac:supplyplenum.name: AirLoopHVAC:SupplyPlenum
airloophvac:supplyplenum.memo: Connects 1 zone inlet air stream, through zone supply plenum, to one or more outlets. Node names cannot be duplicated within a single supply plenum list.

thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.name: ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:SingleHeatingOrCooling
thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.memo: Used for heating and cooling thermal comfort control with a single setpoint. The PMV setpoint can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation for both heating and cooling.

fields.name: Fanger Thermal Comfort Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be Predicted Mean Vote (PMV)

utilitycost:ratchet.name: UtilityCost:Ratchet
utilitycost:ratchet.memo: Allows the modeling of tariffs that include some type of seasonal ratcheting. Ratchets are most common when used with electric demand charges. A ratchet is when a utility requires that the demand charge for a month with a low demand may be increased to be more consistent with a month that set a higher demand charge.

fields.name: Tariff Name
fields.memo: The name of the UtilityCost:Tariff that is associated with this UtilityCost:Ratchet.

fields.name: Baseline Source Variable
fields.memo: When the ratcheted value exceeds the baseline value for a month the ratcheted value is used but when the baseline value is greater then the ratcheted value the baseline value is used. Usually the electric demand charge is used.  The baseline source variable can be the results of another ratchet object. This allows utility tariffs that have multiple ratchets to be modeled.

fields.name: Adjustment Source Variable
fields.memo: The variable that the ratchet is calculated from. It is often but not always the same as the baseline source variable.  The ratcheting calculations using offset and multiplier are using the values from the adjustment source variable. If left blank the adjustment source variable is the same as the baseline source variable.

fields.name: Season From
fields.memo: The name of the season that is being examined.  The maximum value for all of the months in the named season is what is used with the multiplier and offset.  This is most commonly Summer or Annual.  When Monthly is used the adjustment source variable is used directly for all months.

fields.name: Season To
fields.memo: The name of the season when the ratchet would be calculated.  This is most commonly Winter.  The ratchet only is applied to the months in the named season. The resulting variable for months not in the Season To selection will contain the values as appear in the baseline source variable.

fields.name: Multiplier Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: Often the ratchet has a clause such as "the current month demand or 90% of the summer month demand".  For this case a value of 0.9 would be entered here as the multiplier.  This value may be left blank if no multiplier is needed and a value of one will be used as a default.

fields.name: Offset Value or Variable Name
fields.memo: A less common strategy is to say that the ratchet must be all demand greater than a value in this case an offset that is added to the demand may be entered here. If entered it is common for the offset value to be negative representing that the demand be reduced.   If no value is entered it is assumed to be zero and not affect the ratchet.

electricloadcenter:storage:battery.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Storage:Battery
electricloadcenter:storage:battery.memo: Uses the kinetic battery model (KiBaM) to simulate rechargeable battery banks in an electrical load center. The battery bank is a collection of one or more individual battery modules. Given the surplus or deficit power from the electrical system and the state of charge from the previous time step, this object can model the voltage, current, and energy losses with charging and discharging during each time step. The cumulative battery damage can be also modeled and reported at the end of each simulation run.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Enter name of zone to receive electrical storage losses as heat if blank then electrical storage losses are dissipated to outdoors

fields.name: Number of Battery Modules in Parallel
fields.memo: A module usually consists of several cells. The total number of modules in the battery bank is equal to number of modules in parallel times number of modules in series.

fields.name: Number of Battery Modules in Series
fields.memo: A module usually consists of several cells. The total number of modules in the battery bank is equal to number of modules in parallel times number of modules in series.

fields.name: Maximum Module Capacity
fields.memo: The capacity is for each module. A model parameter from manufacturer's data or test data.

fields.name: Initial Fractional State of Charge
fields.memo: The state of charge is evaluated based on the maximum capacity defined in the next field.

fields.name: Fraction of Available Charge Capacity
fields.memo: A model parameter usually derived from test data by curve fitting.

fields.name: Change Rate from Bound Charge to Available Charge
fields.memo: A model parameter usually derived from test data by curve fitting.

fields.name: Fully Charged Module Open Circuit Voltage
fields.memo: The voltage is for each battery module.

fields.name: Fully Discharged Module Open Circuit Voltage
fields.memo: The voltage is for each battery module.

fields.name: Voltage Change Curve Name for Charging
fields.memo: Determines how the open circuit voltage change with state of charge relative to the fully discharged state.

fields.name: Voltage Change Curve Name for Discharging
fields.memo: Determines how the open circuit voltage change with state of charge relative to the fully charged state.

fields.name: Module Internal Electrical Resistance
fields.memo: A model parameter from manufacture or derived from test data. Internal resistance is assumed to be constant. The internal resistance is for each battery module.

fields.name: Maximum Module Discharging Current
fields.memo: The constraint on discharging current is for each battery module.

fields.name: Module Cut-off Voltage
fields.memo: The voltage constraint is for each battery module.

fields.name: Module Charge Rate Limit
fields.memo: units 1/hr Charge rate limit is the division between charging current the remaining capacity. The constraint on charging current is for each module.

fields.name: Number of Cycle Bins
fields.memo: Only required when battery life calculation is activated

fields.name: Battery Life Curve Name
fields.memo: Determines the number of cycles to failure in relation to cycle range. Only required when battery life calculation is activated.

plantequipmentoperation:outdoordewpoint.name: PlantEquipmentOperation:OutdoorDewpoint
plantequipmentoperation:outdoordewpoint.memo: Plant equipment operation scheme for outdoor dewpoint temperature range operation. Specifies one or more groups of equipment which are available to operate for successive outdoor dewpoint temperature ranges.

sizing:plant.name: Sizing:Plant
sizing:plant.memo: Specifies the input needed to autosize plant loop flow rates and equipment capacities. This information is initially used by components that use water for heating or cooling such as hot or chilled water coils to calculate their maximum water flow rates. These flow rates are then summed for use in calculating the Plant Loop flow rates.

fields.name: Plant or Condenser Loop Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a PlantLoop or a CondenserLoop object

fields.name: Sizing Option
fields.memo: if Coincident is chosen, then sizing is based on HVAC Sizing Simulations and the input field called Do HVAC Sizing Simulation for Sizing Periods in SimulationControl must be set to Yes

fields.name: Zone Timesteps in Averaging Window
fields.memo: this is used in the coincident sizing algorithm to apply a running average to peak flow rates that occur during HVAC Sizing Simulations

fields.name: Coincident Sizing Factor Mode
fields.memo: this is used to adjust the result for coincident sizing by applying a sizing factor

airterminal:singleduct:vav:noreheat.name: AirTerminal:SingleDuct:VAV:NoReheat
airterminal:singleduct:vav:noreheat.memo: Central air system terminal unit, single duct, variable volume, with no reheat coil.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method
fields.memo: Constant = Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction (a fraction of Maximum Air Flow Rate) FixedFlowRate = Fixed Minimum Air Flow Rate (a fixed minimum air volume flow rate) Scheduled = Scheduled Minimum Air Flow Fraction (a fraction of Maximum Air Flow

fields.name: Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Constant If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional; if a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the following field are entered, the larger result is used. The values for autosizing are picked up from the Sizing:Zone input fields "Cooling Minimum Air Flow per Zone Floor Area", "Cooling Minimum Air Flow", and "Cooling Minimum Air Flow Fraction". If there is no sizing calculation a default of 0.000762 m3/s-m2 (0.15 cfm/ft2) is used.

fields.name: Fixed Minimum Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is FixedFlowRate.
