If the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled, then this field is optional; if a value is entered, then it is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils. If both this field and the previous field are entered, the larger result is used. The values for autosizing are picked up from the Sizing:Zone input fields "Cooling Minimum Air Flow per Zone Floor Area", "Cooling Minimum Air Flow", and "Cooling Minimum Air Flow Fraction". If there is no sizing calculation a default of 0.000762 m3/s-m2 (0.15 cfm/ft2) is used.

fields.name: Minimum Air Flow Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is used if the field Zone Minimum Air Flow Input Method is Scheduled Schedule values are fractions, 0.0 to 1.0. If the field Constant Minimum Air Flow Fraction is blank, then the average of the minimum and maximum schedule values is used for sizing normal-action reheat coils.

fields.name: Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name
fields.memo: When the name of a DesignSpecification:OutdoorAir object is entered, the terminal unit will increase flow as needed to meet this outdoor air requirement. If Outdoor Air Flow per Person is non-zero, then the outdoor air requirement will be computed based on the current number of occupants in the zone. At no time will the supply air flow rate exceed the value for Maximum Air Flow Rate. If this field is blank, then the terminal unit will not be controlled for outdoor air flow.

airflownetwork:multizone:externalnode.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ExternalNode
airflownetwork:multizone:externalnode.memo: This object defines outdoor environmental conditions outside of the building.

fields.name: External Node Height
fields.memo: Designates the reference height used to calculate relative pressure.

fields.name: Wind Pressure Coefficient Curve Name
fields.memo: The name of the AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientValues, curve, or table object specifying the wind pressure coefficient.

fields.name: Symmetric Wind Pressure Coefficient Curve
fields.memo: Specify whether the pressure curve is symmetric or not. Specify Yes for curves that should be evaluated from 0 to 180 degrees Specify No for curves that should be evaluated from 0 to 360 degrees

fields.name: Wind Angle Type
fields.memo: Specify whether the angle used to compute the wind pressure coefficient is absolute or relative Specify Relative to compute the angle between the wind direction and the surface azimuth Specify Absolute to use the wind direction angle directly

exterior:lights.name: Exterior:Lights
exterior:lights.memo: only used for Meter type reporting, does not affect building loads

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in schedule should be fraction applied to capacity of the exterior lights equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: Control Option
fields.memo: Astronomical Clock option overrides schedule to turn lights off when sun is up

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

faultmodel:fouling:chiller.name: FaultModel:Fouling:Chiller
faultmodel:fouling:chiller.memo: This object describes the fouling fault of chillers with water-cooled condensers

fields.name: Chiller Object Type
fields.memo: Enter the type of a chiller object The fault applies to the chillers with water-cooled condensers

fields.name: Chiller Object Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a chiller object

fields.name: Fouling Factor
fields.memo: The factor indicates the decrease of the nominal capacity of the chiller It is the ratio between the nominal capacity at fouling case and that at fault free case

setpointmanager:condenserenteringreset:i.name: SetpointManager:CondenserEnteringReset:Ideal
setpointmanager:condenserenteringreset:i.memo: This setpoint manager determine the ideal optimum condenser entering water temperature setpoint for a given timestep.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which control variable will be set

airflownetwork:multizone:surface:effecti.name: AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:Surface:EffectiveLeakageArea
airflownetwork:multizone:surface:effecti.memo: This object is used to define surface air leakage.

fields.name: Effective Leakage Area
fields.memo: Enter the effective leakage area.

fields.name: Discharge Coefficient
fields.memo: Enter the coefficient used in the air mass flow equation.

fields.name: Reference Pressure Difference
fields.memo: Enter the pressure difference used to define the air mass flow coefficient and exponent.

fields.name: Air Mass Flow Exponent
fields.memo: Enter the exponent used in the air mass flow equation.

airloophvac:unitaryheatpump:airtoair:mul.name: AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatPump:AirToAir:MultiSpeed
airloophvac:unitaryheatpump:airtoair:mul.memo: Unitary system, heating and cooling, multi-speed with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling), direct expansion (DX) cooling coil, heating coil (DX air-to-air heat pump, gas, electric, hot water, or steam), and supplemental heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam).

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Select the type of supply air fan used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of the supply air fan used in this unitary system.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Placement
fields.memo: Select supply air fan placement as either BlowThrough or DrawThrough. BlowThrough means the supply air fan is located before the cooling coil. DrawThrough means the supply air fan is located after the heating coil but before the optional supplemental heating coil.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a schedule to control the supply air fan. Schedule values of zero mean that the supply air fan will cycle off if there is no cooling or heating load in the control zone. Non-zero schedule values mean that the supply air fan will operate continuously even if there is no cooling or heating load in the control zone. If this field is left blank, the supply air fan will operate continuously for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Multi Speed DX, Electric, Gas, and Single speed Water and Steam coils

fields.name: Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
fields.memo: Needs to match the corresponding minimum outdoor temperature defined in the DX heating coil object.

fields.name: Cooling Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Only works with Coil:Cooling:DX:MultiSpeed

fields.name: Cooling Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the DX Cooling Coil object

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

fields.name: Supplemental Heating Coil Name
fields.memo: Needs to match in the supplemental heating coil object

fields.name: Maximum Supply Air Temperature from Supplemental Heater
Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Supplemental Heater Operation
Design Heat Recovery Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: If non-zero, then the heat recovery inlet and outlet node names must be entered. Used for heat recovery to an EnergyPlus plant loop.

fields.name: Heat Recovery Water Inlet Node Name
Heat Recovery Water Outlet Node Name
No Load Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Only used when the supply air fan operating mode is continuous (see field Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name). This air flow rate is used when no heating or cooling is required and the coils are off. If this field is left blank or zero, the supply air flow rate from the previous on cycle (either cooling or heating) is used.

fields.name: Number of Speeds for Heating
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for air flow rates. If Heating Coil Object Type is Coil:Heating:Water or Coil:Heating:Steam, this field should be 1.

fields.name: Number of Speeds for Cooling
fields.memo: Enter the number of the following sets of data for air flow rates.

fields.name: Heating Speed 1 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during heating operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Heating Speed 2 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during heating operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Heating Speed 3 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during heating operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Heating Speed 4 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during heating operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Cooling Speed 1 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during cooling operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Cooling Speed 2 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during cooling operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Cooling Speed 3 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during cooling operation or specify autosize.

fields.name: Cooling Speed 4 Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Enter the operating supply air flow rate during cooling operation or specify autosize.

windowmaterial:glazing:refractionextinct.name: WindowMaterial:Glazing:RefractionExtinctionMethod
windowmaterial:glazing:refractionextinct.memo: Glass material properties for Windows or Glass Doors Index of Refraction/Extinction Coefficient input method Not to be used for coated glass

fields.name: Infrared Hemispherical Emissivity
fields.memo: Emissivity of front and back side assumed equal

fields.name: Dirt Correction Factor for Solar and Visible Transmittance

timestep.name: Timestep
timestep.memo: Specifies the "basic" timestep for the simulation. The value entered here is also known as the Zone Timestep.  This is used in the Zone Heat Balance Model calculation as the driving timestep for heat transfer and load calculations.

fields.name: Number of Timesteps per Hour
fields.memo: Number in hour: normal validity 4 to 60: 6 suggested Must be evenly divisible into 60 Allowable values include 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 10, 12, 15, 20, 30, and 60 Normal 6 is minimum as lower values may cause inaccuracies A minimum value of 20 is suggested for both ConductionFiniteDifference and CombinedHeatAndMoistureFiniteElement surface heat balance algorithms A minimum of 12 is suggested for simulations involving a Vegetated Roof (Material:RoofVegetation).

coil:cooling:dx:twostagewithhumiditycont.name: Coil:Cooling:DX:TwoStageWithHumidityControlMode
coil:cooling:dx:twostagewithhumiditycont.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil and condensing unit (includes electric compressor and condenser fan), two-stage with humidity control mode (e.g. sub-cool or hot gas reheat). Optional inputs for moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation. Requires two to four sets of performance data, see CoilPerformance:DX:Cooling. Stages are modeled as a face-split coil.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Maximum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
Normal Mode Stage 1 Coil Performance Object Type
Normal Mode Stage 1 Coil Performance Name
Normal Mode Stage 1+2 Coil Performance Object Type
Normal Mode Stage 1+2 Coil Performance Name
Dehumidification Mode 1 Stage 1 Coil Performance Object Type
Dehumidification Mode 1 Stage 1 Coil Performance Name
Dehumidification Mode 1 Stage 1+2 Coil Performance Object Type
Dehumidification Mode 1 Stage 1+2 Coil Performance Name
Condensate Collection Water Storage Tank Name
Minimum Outdoor Dry-Bulb Temperature for Compressor Operation
Basin Heater Capacity
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled and for periods when the basin heater is available (field Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name). For this situation, the heater maintains the basin water temperature at the basin heater setpoint temperature when the outdoor air temperature falls below the setpoint temperature. The basin heater only operates when the DX coil is off.

fields.name: Basin Heater Setpoint Temperature
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Enter the outdoor dry-bulb temperature when the basin heater turns on.

fields.name: Basin Heater Operating Schedule Name
fields.memo: This field is only used for Condenser Type = EvaporativelyCooled. Schedule values greater than 0 allow the basin heater to operate whenever the outdoor air dry-bulb temperature is below the basin heater setpoint temperature. If a schedule name is not entered, the basin heater is allowed to operate throughout the entire simulation.

floor:interzone.name: Floor:Interzone
floor:interzone.memo: Allows for simplified entry of floors using adjacent zone (interzone) heat transfer - adjacent surface should be a ceiling.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone for the inside of the surface

fields.name: Outside Boundary Condition Object
fields.memo: Specify a surface name in an adjacent zone for known interior ceilings. Specify a zone name of an adjacent zone to automatically generate the interior ceiling in the adjacent zone.

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Floors are usually tilted 180 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: If not Flat, should be Lower Left Corner (from outside)

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: Along X Axis

fields.name: Width
fields.memo: Along Y Axis

comfortviewfactorangles.name: ComfortViewFactorAngles
comfortviewfactorangles.memo: Used to specify radiant view factors for thermal comfort calculations.

wall:adiabatic.name: Wall:Adiabatic
wall:adiabatic.memo: Allows for simplified entry of interior walls.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone the surface is a part of

fields.name: Azimuth Angle
fields.memo: Facing direction of outside of wall (S=180,N=0,E=90,W=270)

fields.name: Tilt Angle
fields.memo: Walls are usually tilted 90 degrees

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Starting (x,y,z) coordinate is the Lower Left Corner of the Wall

roomair:node.name: RoomAir:Node
roomair:node.memo: Define an air node for some types of nodal room air models

fields.name: Height of Nodal Control Volume Center

externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.name: ExternalInterface:FunctionalMockupUnitExport:To:Schedule
externalinterface:functionalmockupunitex.memo: This objects contains only one value, which is used during the first call of EnergyPlus

fields.name: Initial Value
fields.memo: Used during the first call of EnergyPlus.

surfaceproperty:underwater.name: SurfaceProperty:Underwater
surfaceproperty:underwater.memo: This object sets up a convective water boundary condition for a surface The free stream temperature and velocity are scheduled. If the free stream velocity is zero, the surface will naturally convect with the surrounding water.

fields.name: Distance from Surface Centroid to Leading Edge of Boundary Layer
fields.memo: This is the distance from the leading edge of the boundary layer development to the centroid of the surface of interest.  The value of this field is used as the distance in the Reynolds number for evaluating the local convection coefficient.

airloophvac.name: AirLoopHVAC
airloophvac.memo: Defines a central forced air system.

fields.name: Controller List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AirLoopHVAC:ControllerList object.

fields.name: Availability Manager List Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of an AvailabilityManagerAssignmentList object.

fields.name: Branch List Name
fields.memo: Name of a BranchList containing all the branches in this air loop

fields.name: Connector List Name
fields.memo: Name of a ConnectorList containing all the splitters and mixers in the loop

fields.name: Supply Side Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of inlet node where air enters the supply side of the air loop. If this air loop has a return path, then this node is where return air enters the supply side. If this air loop has no return path, then this node is where outdoor air or other air enters the supply side.

fields.name: Demand Side Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Name of outlet node where return air leaves the demand side and enters the supply side. Required if this air loop has a return path. Leave this field blank if there is no return.

fields.name: Demand Side Inlet Node Names
fields.memo: Name of a Node or NodeList containing the inlet node(s) supplying air to zone equipment.

fields.name: Supply Side Outlet Node Names
fields.memo: Name of a Node or NodeList containing the outlet node(s) supplying air to the demand side.

fields.name: Design Return Air Flow Fraction of Supply Air Flow
fields.memo: The design return air flow rate as a fraction of supply air flow rate with no exhaust. This can be used to model a pressurized system or set to zero to model a DOAS with no return flow. Use ZoneAirMassFlowConservation to balance zone infiltration and mixing flows.

output:meter.name: Output:Meter
output:meter.memo: Each Output:Meter command picks meters to be put onto the standard output file (.eso) and meter file (.mtr). Not all meters are reported in every simulation. A list of a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Key Name
fields.memo: Form is EnergyUseType:..., e.g. Electricity:* for all Electricity meters or EndUse:..., e.g. GeneralLights:* for all General Lights Output:Meter puts results on both the eplusout.mtr and eplusout.eso files

fields.name: Reporting Frequency
fields.memo: Timestep refers to the zone Timestep/Number of Timesteps in hour value RunPeriod and Environment are the same

demandmanager:thermostats.name: DemandManager:Thermostats
demandmanager:thermostats.memo: used for demand limiting ZoneControl:Thermostat objects.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Minimum Reset Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

fields.name: Reset Step Change
fields.memo: Not yet implemented

fields.name: Rotation Duration
fields.memo: If blank, duration defaults to the timestep

hvactemplate:zone:constantvolume.name: HVACTemplate:Zone:ConstantVolume
hvactemplate:zone:constantvolume.memo: Zone terminal unit, constant volume, reheat optional. Referenced schedules must be defined elsewhere in the idf.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Zone name must match a building zone name

fields.name: Template Constant Volume System Name
fields.memo: Name of a HVACTemplate:System:ConstantVolume object serving this zone

fields.name: Template Thermostat Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a HVACTemplate:Thermostat object. If blank, then it is assumed that standard thermostat objects have been defined for this zone.

fields.name: Supply Air Maximum Flow Rate
fields.memo: This field may be set to "autosize".  If a value is entered, it will be multiplied by the Supply Air Sizing Factor and by zone multipliers.

fields.name: Zone Heating Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Zone Cooling Sizing Factor
fields.memo: If blank, value from Sizing:Parameters will be used.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Method
fields.memo: Flow/Person, Flow/Zone, Flow/Area, Sum, and Maximum use the values in the next three fields: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person, Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area, and Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone. DetailedSpecification ignores these three Outdoor Air Flow Rate fields and instead references design specification objects named in the fields Design Specification Outdoor Air Object Name and Design Specification Zone Air Distribution Object Name.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Person
fields.memo: Default 0.00944 is 20 cfm per person This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Person, Sum, or Maximum

fields.name: Outdoor Air Flow Rate per Zone Floor Area
fields.memo: This input is used if the field Outdoor Air Method is Flow/Area, Sum, or Maximum

coil:waterheating:airtowaterheatpump:wra.name: Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:Wrapped
coil:waterheating:airtowaterheatpump:wra.memo: Heat pump water heater (HPWH) heating coil, air-to-water direct-expansion (DX) system which includes a water heating coil, evaporator air coil, evaporator fan, electric compressor, and water pump. Part of a WaterHeater:HeatPump:WrappedCondenser system.

fields.name: Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump heat.

fields.name: Rated COP
fields.memo: Heating coefficient of performance at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump power and evaporator fan power (see fields below).

fields.name: Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross air-side sensible heat ratio at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Sensible heat ratio equals gross sensible cooling capacity divided by gross total cooling capacity. Rated SHR (gross) should not include evaporator fan heat, only sensible cooling and dehumidification by the coil alone.

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Inlet Air Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Evaporator inlet air dry-bulb temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Evaporator inlet air wet-bulb temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Condenser Water Temperature
fields.memo: Condenser inlet water temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Evaporator air flow rate corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR). Default is 5.035E-5 m3/s/W (31.25 cfm/MBH) of rated heating capacity when autocalculated.

fields.name: Evaporator Fan Power Included in Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the evaporator fan power is included in the rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of compressor electric power.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node from which the DX coil draws its inlet air.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node to which the DX coil sends its outlet air.

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Capacity
fields.memo: The compressor crankcase heater only operates when the dry-bulb temperature of air surrounding the compressor is below the Maximum Ambient Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation and the DX coil is off.  The ambient temperature surrounding the compressor is set by the WaterHeater:HeatPump:WrappedCondenser parent object (field Compressor Location).

fields.name: Maximum Ambient Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
fields.memo: The compressor crankcase heater only operates when the dry-bulb temperature of air surrounding the compressor is below the Maximum Outdoor Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation and the unit is off. The ambient temperature surrounding the compressor is set by the WaterHeater:HeatPump:WrappedCondenser parent object (field Compressor Location).

fields.name: Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects
fields.memo: Determines temperature type for heating capacity curves and heating COP curves. This input determines whether the inlet air dry-bulb or wet-bulb temperature is used to evaluate these curves.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating capacity modifier curve (function of temperature) should be biquadratic or cubic. Biquadratic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(tw) + e(tw)^2 + f(ta)(tw). Cubic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(ta)^3. ta = evaporator inlet air [dry-bulb or wet-bulb] temperature (C). tw = condenser inlet water temperature (C). The field Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects determines if dry-bulb or wet-bulb is used as the evaporator inlet air temperature (ta).

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Air Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating capacity modifier curve (function of air flow fraction) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2 + d(ff)^3. ff = fraction of the rated evaporator air flow rate. Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in air flow rate fraction.

fields.name: Heating COP Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating COP modifier curve (function of temperature) should be biquadratic or cubic. Biquadratic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(tw) + e(tw)^2 + f(ta)(tw). Cubic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(ta)^3. ta = evaporator inlet air [dry-bulb or wet-bulb] temperature (C). tw = condenser inlet water temperature (C). The field Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects determines if dry-bulb or wet-bulb is used as the evaporator inlet air temperature (ta).

fields.name: Heating COP Function of Air Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating COP modifier curve (function of air flow fraction) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2 + d(ff)^3. ff = fraction of the rated evaporator air flow rate. Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in air flow rate fraction.

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: Part Load Fraction Correlation (function of part load ratio) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(PLR) + c(PLR)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(PLR) + c(PLR)^2 + d(PLR)^3. PLR = part load ratio (heating delivered/steady state heating capacity). Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in part load ratio.

roomair:node:airflownetwork:hvacequipmen.memo: define the zone equipment associated with one particular RoomAir:Node

solarcollector:unglazedtranspired.name: SolarCollector:UnglazedTranspired
solarcollector:unglazedtranspired.memo: Unglazed transpired solar collector (UTSC) used to condition outdoor air. This type of collector is generally used to heat air drawn through perforated absorbers and also recover heat conducted out through the underlying surface. This object represents a single collector attached to one or more building or shading surfaces and to one or more outdoor air systems.

fields.name: Boundary Conditions Model Name
fields.memo: Enter the name of a SurfaceProperty:OtherSideConditionsModel object

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this collector. Schedule value > 0 means it is available. If this field is blank, the collector is always available.

fields.name: Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: required field if no SolarCollector:UnglazedTranspired:Multisystem

fields.name: Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: required field if no SolarCollector:UnglazedTranspired:Multisystem

fields.name: Setpoint Node Name

fields.name: Zone Node Name

fields.memo: if corrugated, use average depth

fields.memo: This parameter is used to help account for corrugations in the collector

fields.name: Collector Thickness
fields.memo: Collector thickness is not required for Kutscher correlation Collector thickness is required for Van Decker et al. correlation

energymanagementsystem:outputvariable.name: EnergyManagementSystem:OutputVariable
energymanagementsystem:outputvariable.memo: This object sets up an EnergyPlus output variable from an Erl variable
