fields.memo: must be an acceptable EMS variable

fields.name: EMS Program or Subroutine Name
fields.memo: optional for global scope variables, required for local scope variables

fields.name: Units
fields.memo: optional but will result in dimensionless units for blank EnergyPlus units are standard SI units

waterheater:heatpump:wrappedcondenser.name: WaterHeater:HeatPump:WrappedCondenser
waterheater:heatpump:wrappedcondenser.memo: This object models an air-source heat pump for water heating where the heating coil is wrapped around the tank, which is typical of residential HPWHs. For pumped condenser HPWHs, see WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser. WaterHeater:HeatPump:WrappedCondenser is a compound object that references other component objects - Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:Pumped, Fan:OnOff, WaterHeater:Mixed

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Schedule values of 0 denote the heat pump compressor is off and the parasitic electric energy is also off.

fields.name: Compressor Setpoint Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defines the cut-out temperature where the heat pump compressor turns off. The heat pump compressor setpoint temperature should always be greater than the water tank's heater (element or burner) setpoint temperature.

fields.name: Dead Band Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Setpoint temperature minus the dead band temperature difference defines the cut-in temperature where the heat pump compressor turns on. The water tank's heater (element or burner) setpoint temperature should always be less than the heat pump compressor cut-in temperature.

fields.name: Condenser Bottom Location
fields.memo: Distance from the bottom of the tank to the bottom of the wrapped condenser.

fields.name: Condenser Top Location
fields.memo: Distance from the bottom of the tank to the top of the wrapped condenser.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Actual air flow rate across the heat pump's air coil (evaporator). If autocalculated, the air flow rate is set equal to 5.035E-5 m3/s/W times the rated heating capacity of the heat pump's DX coil.

fields.name: Inlet Air Configuration
fields.memo: Defines the configuration of the airflow path through the air coil and fan section.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Zone air exhaust node name if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. Simply a unique Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule. Otherwise, leave field blank.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Zone Air Inlet Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. Simply a unique Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule. Otherwise, leave field blank.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: Outdoor air node name if inlet air configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir or OutdoorAirOnly, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Exhaust Air Node Name
fields.memo: Simply a unique Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir or OutdoorAirOnly, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Inlet Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule, otherwise leave blank. Schedule values should be degrees C.

fields.name: Inlet Air Humidity Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule, otherwise leave blank. Schedule values are entered as a fraction (e.g. 0.5 is equal to 50%RH)

fields.name: Inlet Air Zone Name
fields.memo: Used only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. Otherwise, leave field blank.

fields.name: Tank Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of water heater tank used by this heat pump water heater.

fields.name: Tank Name
fields.memo: Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Water Heater object. Must be a WaterHeater:Stratified tank.

fields.name: Tank Use Side Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Used only when the heat pump water heater is connected to a plant loop, otherwise leave blank. Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Water Heater object when connected to a plant loop.

fields.name: Tank Use Side Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Used only when the heat pump water heater is connected to a plant loop, otherwise leave blank. Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Water Heater object when connected to a plant loop.

fields.name: DX Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of DX coil used by this heat pump water heater. The only valid choice is Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:Wrapped

fields.name: DX Coil Name
fields.memo: Must match the name used in the corresponding Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:Wrapped object.

fields.name: Minimum Inlet Air Temperature for Compressor Operation
fields.memo: Heat pump compressor will not operate when the inlet air dry-bulb temperature is below this value.

fields.name: Maximum Inlet Air Temperature for Compressor Operation
fields.memo: Heat pump compressor will not operate when the inlet air dry-bulb temperature is above this value.

fields.name: Compressor Location
fields.memo: If Zone is selected, Inlet Air Configuration must be ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. If Schedule is selected, then you must provide a Compressor Ambient Temperature Schedule Name below.

fields.name: Compressor Ambient Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Compressor Location is Schedule, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of fan used by this heat pump water heater. The only valid choices are Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff.

fields.name: Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff object.

fields.name: Fan Placement
fields.memo: BlowThrough means the fan is located before the air coil (upstream). DrawThrough means the fan is located after the air coil (downstream).

fields.name: On Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power consumed when the heat pump compressor operates. Does not contribute to water heating but can impact the zone air heat balance.

fields.name: Off Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power consumed when the heat pump compressor is off. Does not contribute to water heating but can impact the zone air heat balance. Off-cycle parasitic power is 0 when the availability schedule is 0.

fields.name: Parasitic Heat Rejection Location
fields.memo: This field determines if the parasitic electric load impacts the zone air heat balance. If Zone is selected, Inlet Air Configuration must be ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir.

fields.name: Inlet Air Mixer Node Name
fields.memo: Required only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Outlet Air Splitter Node Name
fields.memo: Required only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Inlet Air Mixer Schedule Name
fields.memo: Required only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir, otherwise leave field blank. Schedule values define whether the heat pump draws its inlet air from the zone, outdoors or a combination of zone and outdoor air. A schedule value of 0 denotes inlet air is drawn only from the zone. A schedule value of 1 denotes inlet air is drawn only from outdoors. Schedule values between 0 and 1 denote a mixture of zone and outdoor air proportional to the schedule value.

fields.name: Tank Element Control Logic
fields.memo: MutuallyExclusive means that once the tank heating element is active the heat pump is shut down until setpoint is reached. Simultaneous (default) means that both the tank heating element and heat pump are used at the same time recover the tank temperature.

fields.name: Control Sensor 1 Height In Stratified Tank
fields.memo: Used to indicate height of control sensor if Tank Object Type is WaterHeater:Stratified If left blank, it will default to the height of Heater1

fields.name: Control Sensor 1 Weight
fields.memo: Weight to give Control Sensor 1 temperature

fields.name: Control Sensor 2 Height In Stratified Tank
fields.memo: Used to indicate height of control sensor if Tank Object Type is WaterHeater:Stratified If left blank, it will default to the height of Heater2 The weight of this control sensor will be 1 - (wt. of control sensor 1)

evaporativecooler:direct:researchspecial.name: EvaporativeCooler:Direct:ResearchSpecial
evaporativecooler:direct:researchspecial.memo: Direct evaporative cooler with user-specified effectiveness (can represent rigid pad or similar media), and recirculating water pump, and secondary air fan. This model is controlled to meet the primary air outlet temperature setpoint.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Cooler Design Effectiveness
fields.memo: effectiveness with respect to wet-bulb depression

fields.name: Effectiveness Flow Ratio Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: this curve modifies the design effectiveness in the previous field by multiplying the value by the result of this curve.  The effectiveness flow modifier curve is a function of flow fraction. Flow fraction is the ratio of current primary air flow rate to the primary air design flow rate. If this input field is left blank then, the effectiveness is assumed to be constant. Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used: Curve:Linear, Curve:Quadratic, Curve:Cubic, Curve:Quartic, Curve:Exponent, Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal, Curve:Sigmoid, Curve:RectuangularHyperbola1, Curve:RectangularHyperbola2, Curve:ExponentialDecay, Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay, Table:OneIndependentVariable

fields.name: Recirculating Water Pump Design Power
fields.memo: This is the design water pump or spray for evaporation at the primary air design air flow rates and cooler design effectiveness

fields.name: Water Pump Power Sizing Factor
fields.memo: This field is used when the previous field is set to autosize. The pump power is scaled with Secondary Air Design Air Flow Rate. This value was backed out from inputs in energy plus example files. Average Pump Power sizing factor was estimated from pump power and primary air design flow rates inputs from energyplus example files is about 90.0 [W/(m3/s)] (=90.0 ~ Pump Power / Primary Air Design Flow Rate). The factor ranges from 55.0 to 150.0 [W/(m3/s)]. The pump power can be sized to zero by setting this factor to zero.

fields.name: Water Pump Power Modifier Curve Name
fields.memo: this curve modifies the pump power in the previous field by multiplying the design power by the result of this curve. x = ff = flow fraction on the primary air. The flow fraction is the secondary air flow rate during current operation divided by Primary Air Design Flow Rate Any curve or table with one independent variable can be used: Curve:Linear, Curve:Quadratic, Curve:Cubic, Curve:Quartic, Curve:Exponent, Curve:ExponentialSkewNormal, Curve:Sigmoid, Curve:RectuangularHyperbola1, Curve:RectangularHyperbola2, Curve:ExponentialDecay, Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay, Table:OneIndependentVariable

fields.name: Drift Loss Fraction
fields.memo: Rate of drift loss as a fraction of evaporated water flow rate

fields.name: Blowdown Concentration Ratio
fields.memo: Characterizes the rate of blowdown in the evaporative cooler. Blowdown is water intentionally drained from the cooler in order to offset the build up of solids in the water that would otherwise occur because of evaporation. Ratio of solids in the blowdown water to solids in the make up water. A typical value is 3. If left blank then there is no blowdown.

fields.name: Evaporative Operation Minimum Drybulb Temperature
fields.memo: This numeric field defines the evaporative cooler air inlet node drybulb temperature minimum limit in degrees Celsius. The evaporative cooler will be turned off when the evaporator cooler air inlet node dry-bulb temperature falls below this limit. The typical minimum value is 16degC. Users are allowed to specify their own limits. If this field is left blank, then there is no drybulb lower temperature limit for evaporative cooler operation.

fields.name: Evaporative Operation Maximum Limit Wetbulb Temperature
fields.memo: when outdoor wetbulb temperature rises above this limit the cooler shuts down. This numeric field defines the evaporative cooler air inlet node wet-bulb temperature maximum limit in degrees Celsius. The evaporative cooler will be turned off when the evaporative cooler air inlet node wet-bulb temperature exceeds this limit. The typical maximum value is 24degC. Users are allowed to specify their own limits. If this field is left blank, then there is no upper wetbulb temperature limit for evaporative cooler operation.

fields.name: Evaporative Operation Maximum Limit Drybulb Temperature
fields.memo: This numeric field defines the evaporative cooler air inlet node dry-bulb temperature maximum limit in degrees Celsius. The evaporative cooler will be turned off when its air inlet node drybulb temperature exceeds this limit. The typical maximum value is 26degC. Users are allowed to specify their own limits. If this field is left blank, then there is no upper temperature limit for evaporative cooler operation.

materialproperty:phasechangehysteresis.name: MaterialProperty:PhaseChangeHysteresis
materialproperty:phasechangehysteresis.memo: Additional properties for temperature dependent thermal conductivity and enthalpy for Phase Change Materials (PCM) with separate melting and freezing curves. HeatBalanceAlgorithm = CondFD (ConductionFiniteDifference) solution algorithm only. Constructions with this should use the detailed CondFD process. Has no effect with other HeatBalanceAlgorithm solution algorithms.

fields.name: Latent Heat during the Entire Phase Change Process
fields.memo: The total latent heat absorbed or rejected during the transition from solid to liquid, or back

fields.name: Liquid State Thermal Conductivity
fields.memo: The thermal conductivity used by this material when the material is fully liquid

fields.name: Liquid State Density
fields.memo: The density used by this material when the material is fully liquid

fields.name: Liquid State Specific Heat
fields.memo: The constant specific heat used for the fully melted (liquid) state

fields.name: High Temperature Difference of Melting Curve
fields.memo: The total melting range of the material is the sum of low and high temperature difference of melting curve.

fields.name: Peak Melting Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature at which the melting curve peaks

fields.name: Low Temperature Difference of Melting Curve
fields.memo: The total melting range of the material is the sum of low and high temperature difference of melting curve.

fields.name: Solid State Thermal Conductivity
fields.memo: The thermal conductivity used by this material when the material is fully solid

fields.name: Solid State Density
fields.memo: The density used by this material when the material is fully solid

fields.name: Solid State Specific Heat
fields.memo: The constant specific heat used for the fully frozen (crystallized) state

fields.name: High Temperature Difference of Freezing Curve
fields.memo: The total freezing range of the material is the sum of low and high temperature difference of freezing curve.

fields.name: Peak Freezing Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature at which the freezing curve peaks

fields.name: Low Temperature Difference of Freezing Curve
fields.memo: The total freezing range of the material is the sum of low and high temperature difference of freezing curve.

groundheattransfer:basement:yface.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:YFACE
groundheattransfer:basement:yface.memo: This is only needed when using manual gridding (not recommended) YFACE: Y Direction cell face coordinates: m

curve:chillerpartloadwithlift.name: Curve:ChillerPartLoadWithLift
curve:chillerpartloadwithlift.memo: This chiller part-load performance curve has three independent variables. Input consists of the curve name, the twelve coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2 + C4*y + C5*y**2 + C6*x*y + C7*x**3 + C8*y**3 + C9*x**2*y + C10*x*y**2 + C11*x**2*y**2 + C12*z*y**3 x = dT* = normalized fractional Lift = dT / dTref y = PLR = part load ratio (cooling load/steady state capacity) z = Tdev* = normalized Tdev = Tdev / dTref Where: dT = Lift = Leaving Condenser Water Temperature - Leaving Chilled Water Temperature dTref = dT at the reference condition Tdev = Leaving Chilled Water Temperature - Reference Chilled Water Temperature

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

schedule:day:hourly.name: Schedule:Day:Hourly
schedule:day:hourly.memo: A Schedule:Day:Hourly contains 24 values for each hour of the day.

chillerheater:absorption:doubleeffect.name: ChillerHeater:Absorption:DoubleEffect
chillerheater:absorption:doubleeffect.memo: Exhaust fired absorption chiller-heater using performance curves similar to DOE-2

fields.name: Heating to Cooling Capacity Ratio
fields.memo: A positive fraction that represents the ratio of the heating capacity divided by the cooling capacity at rated conditions.

fields.name: Thermal Energy Input to Cooling Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous fuel used divided by the cooling capacity at rated conditions.

fields.name: Thermal Energy Input to Heating Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous fuel used divided by the nominal heating capacity.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous electricity used divided by the cooling capacity at rated conditions. If the chiller is both heating and cooling only the cooling electricity is used.

fields.name: Electric Input to Heating Output Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the ratio of the instantaneous electricity used divided by the nominal heating capacity. If the chiller is both heating and cooling only the cooling electricity is used.

fields.name: Condenser Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Not required if air-cooled

fields.name: Minimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the minimum cooling output possible when operated continually at rated temperature conditions divided by the nominal cooling capacity at those same conditions.  If the load on the chiller is below this fraction the chiller will cycle.

fields.name: Maximum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the maximum cooling output possible at rated temperature conditions divided by the nominal cooling capacity at those same conditions.  If greater than 1.0, the chiller is typically thought of as capable of being overloaded.

fields.name: Optimum Part Load Ratio
fields.memo: The positive fraction that represents the optimal cooling output at rated temperature conditions divided by the nominal cooling capacity at those same conditions.  It represents the most desirable operating point for the chiller.

fields.name: Design Entering Condenser Water Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature of the water entering the condenser of the chiller when operating at design conditions.  This is usually based on the temperature delivered by the cooling tower in a water cooled application.

fields.name: Design Leaving Chilled Water Temperature
fields.memo: The temperature of the water leaving the evaporator of the chiller when operating at design conditions also called the chilled water supply temperature or leaving chilled water temperature.

fields.name: Design Chilled Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: For variable volume this is the max flow & for constant flow this is the flow.

fields.name: Design Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: The water flow rate at design conditions through the condenser. This field is not used for Condenser Type = AirCooled

fields.name: Design Hot Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: The water flow rate at design conditions through the heater side.

fields.name: Cooling Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The CoolCapFT curve represents the fraction of the cooling capacity of the chiller as it varies by temperature.  The curve is normalized so that at design conditions the value of the curve should be 1.0.  This is a biquadratic curve with the input variables being the leaving chilled water temperature and either the entering or leaving condenser water temperature.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the fuel input to the chiller at full load as it varies by temperature.  The curve is normalized so that at design conditions the value of the curve should be 1.0.  This is a biquadratic curve with the input variables being the leaving chilled water temperature and either the entering or leaving condenser water temperature.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the fuel input to the chiller as the load on the chiller varies but the operating temperatures remain at the design values. The curve is normalized so that at full load the value of the curve should be 1.0. The curve is usually linear or quadratic.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the electricity to the chiller at full load as it varies by temperature.  The curve is normalized so that at design conditions the value of the curve should be 1.0.  This is a biquadratic curve with the input variables being the leaving chilled water temperature and either the entering or leaving condenser water temperature.

fields.name: Electric Input to Cooling Output Ratio Function of Part Load Ratio Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents the fraction of the electricity to the chiller as the load on the chiller varies but the operating temperatures remain at the design values. The curve is normalized so that at full load the value of the curve should be 1.0. The curve is usually linear or quadratic.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Cooling Capacity Curve Name
fields.memo: The curve represents how the heating capacity of the chiller varies with cooling capacity when the chiller is simultaneous heating and cooling.  The curve is normalized so an input of 1.0 represents the nominal cooling capacity and an output of 1.0 represents the full heating capacity (see the Heating to cooling capacity ratio input) The curve is usually linear or quadratic.

fields.name: Fuel Input to Heat Output Ratio During Heating Only Operation Curve Name
fields.memo: When the chiller is operating as only a heater, this curve is used to represent the fraction of fuel used as the heating load varies.  It is normalized so that a value of 1.0 is the full heating capacity.  The curve is usually linear or quadratic and will probably be similar to a boiler curve for most chillers.

fields.name: Temperature Curve Input Variable
fields.memo: Sets the second independent variable in the three temperature dependent performance curves to either the leaving or entering condenser water temperature.  Manufacturers express the performance of their chillers using either the leaving condenser water temperature (to the tower) or the entering condenser water temperature (from the tower).

fields.name: Condenser Type
fields.memo: The condenser can either be air cooled or connected to a cooling tower.

fields.name: Chilled Water Temperature Lower Limit
fields.memo: The chilled water supply temperature below which the chiller will shut off.

fields.name: Sizing Factor
fields.memo: Multiplies the autosized capacity and flow rates

electricloadcenter:distribution.name: ElectricLoadCenter:Distribution
electricloadcenter:distribution.memo: Describes a subpanel a list of meters that can be reported are available after a run on the meter dictionary file (.mdd) if the Output:VariableDictionary has been requested.

fields.name: Generator List Name
fields.memo: Name of an ElectricLoadCenter:Generators object

fields.name: Generator Operation Scheme Type
fields.memo: Determines how generators are to be controlled Required if Generator List is entered.

fields.name: Generator Demand Limit Scheme Purchased Electric Demand Limit
Generator Track Schedule Name Scheme Schedule Name
fields.memo: required when Generator Operation Scheme Type=TrackSchedule schedule values in Watts

fields.name: Generator Track Meter Scheme Meter Name
fields.memo: required when Generator Operation Scheme Type=TrackMeter

fields.name: Inverter Name
fields.memo: required when Electrical Buss Type=DirectCurrentWithInverter, DirectCurrentWithInverterDCStorage, or DirectCurrentWithInverterACStorage

fields.name: Electrical Storage Object Name
fields.memo: required when Electrical Buss Type=AlternatingCurrentWithStorage, DirectCurrentWithInverterDCStorage, or DirectCurrentWithInverterACStorage

fields.name: Transformer Object Name
fields.memo: required when power needs to be output from on-site generation or storage to the grid via transformer

fields.name: Storage Operation Scheme
fields.memo: Select method to govern how storage charge and discharge is controlled TrackFacilityElectricDemandStoreExcessOnSite indicates that storage control will follow the facility power demand while accounting for any on-site generation.  Only excess on site generation  gets stored (legacy behavior). TrackMeterDemandStoreExcessOnSite indicates that storage discharge control will follow an electric meter named in the field called Storage Control Track Meter Name.  This scheme is similiar to TrackFacilityElectricDemandStoreExcessOnSite except that instead of the main facility electric meter, the control is based off of a user-selected meter. TrackChargeDischargeSchedules indicates that control will follow the charging and discharging power and schedules defined in the fields called Maximum Storage Charge Grid Supply Power, Storage Charge Grid Supply Power Fraction Schedule Name, Design Storage Discharge Grid Export Power, and Storage Discharge Grid Export Fraction Schedule Name. FacilityDemandLeveling indicates that storage control will attempt to control the facility's power demand drawn from the utility service to a prescribed level. The target utility demand is entered in the fields called Storage Control Utility Demand Limit and Storage Control Utility Demand Limit Fraction Schedule Name This scheme first accounts for any on-site generation and during times of high use will discharge storage to reduce facility grid demand to meet the target level and during times of low use will charge storage from the grid to increase facility grid demand to meet the target level.

fields.name: Storage Control Track Meter Name
fields.memo: required when Storage Operation Scheme is set to TrackMeterDemandStoreExcessOnSite.

fields.name: Storage Converter Object Name
fields.memo: Name of an ElectricLoadCenter:Storage:Converter used to convert AC to DC when charging DC storage from grid supply. A converter is expected when using Storage Operation Schemes FacilityDemandLeveling or TrackChargeDischargeSchedules A single bidirectional device will reference both an inverter object (DC to AC) and a converter object (AC to DC).

fields.name: Maximum Storage State of Charge Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of storage capacity used as upper limit for controlling charging, for all storage operation schemes.

fields.name: Minimum Storage State of Charge Fraction
fields.memo: Fraction of storage capacity used as lower limit for controlling discharging, for all storage operation schemes.

fields.name: Design Storage Control Charge Power
fields.memo: Maximum rate that electric power can be charged into storage. Storage charging adjusted downward for conversion losses. Rate is modified by fractional values in the schedule named in the next field. Required field when using Storage Operation Schemes FacilityDemandLeveling or TrackChargeDischargeSchedules.

fields.name: Storage Charge Power Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Controls timing and magnitude of charging storage. Required field if Storage Operation Scheme is set to TrackChargeDischargeSchedules. Schedule values should be fractions from 0.0 to 1.0, inclusive.

fields.name: Design Storage Control Discharge Power
fields.memo: Maximum rate that electric power can be discharged from storage. Rate is modified by fractional values in the schedule named in the next field. Required field when using Storage Operation Schemes FacilityDemandLeveling or TrackChargeDischargeSchedules.

fields.name: Storage Discharge Power Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Controls timing and magnitude of discharging storage Required field if Storage Operation Scheme is set to TrackChargeDischargeSchedules. Schedule values should be fractions from 0.0 to 1.0, inclusive.

fields.name: Storage Control Utility Demand Target
fields.memo: Target utility service demand power for discharge control.  Storage draws are adjusted upwards for conversion losses. Required field for FacilityDemandLeveling storage operation scheme

fields.name: Storage Control Utility Demand Target Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the target utility service demand power over time. Schedule values should be fractions from -1.0 to 1.0, inclusive. if omitted a schedule value of 1.0 is used. Negative values indicate export to grid Schedule is used if Storage Operation Scheme is set to FacilityDemandLeveling.

zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:cut.name: ZoneContaminantSourceAndSink:Generic:CutoffModel
zonecontaminantsourceandsink:generic:cut.memo: Simulate generic contaminant source driven by the cutoff concentration model.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Design Generation Rate Coefficient

fields.name: Cutoff Generic Contaminant at which Emission Ceases
fields.memo: When the zone concentration level is greater than the cutoff level, emission stops, and the source level is zero.

airflownetwork:simulationcontrol.name: AirflowNetwork:SimulationControl
airflownetwork:simulationcontrol.memo: This object defines the global parameters used in an Airflow Network simulation.

fields.name: AirflowNetwork Control
fields.memo: NoMultizoneOrDistribution: Only perform Simple calculations (objects ZoneInfiltration:*, ZoneVentilation:*, ZoneMixing, ZoneCrossMixing, ZoneRefrigerationDoorMixing, ZoneAirBalance:OutdoorAir, ZoneEarthtube, ZoneThermalChimney, and ZoneCoolTower:Shower); MultizoneWithoutDistribution: Use AirflowNetwork objects to simulate multizone Airflows driven by wind during simulation time, and objects of ZoneInfiltration:*, ZoneVentilation:*, ZoneMixing, ZoneCrossMixing ZoneRefrigerationDoorMixing, ZoneAirBalance:OutdoorAir, ZoneEarthtube, ZoneThermalChimney, and ZoneCoolTower:Shower are ignored; MultizoneWithDistributionOnlyDuringFanOperation: Perform distribution system calculations during system fan on time and Simple calculations during system Fan off time; MultizoneWithDistribution: Perform distribution system calculations during system fan on time and multizone Airflow driven by wind during system fan off time.

fields.name: Wind Pressure Coefficient Type
fields.memo: Input: User must enter AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientArray, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ExternalNode, and AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientValues objects. SurfaceAverageCalculation: used only for rectangular buildings. If SurfaceAverageCalculation is selected, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientArray, AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ExternalNode, and AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:WindPressureCoefficientValues objects are not used.

fields.name: Height Selection for Local Wind Pressure Calculation
fields.memo: If ExternalNode is selected, the height given in the AirflowNetwork:MultiZone:ExternalNode object will be used. If OpeningHeight is selected, the surface opening height (centroid) will be used to calculate local wind pressure This field is ignored when the choice of the Wind Pressure Coefficient Type field is SurfaceAverageCalculation.

fields.name: Building Type
fields.memo: Used only if Wind Pressure Coefficient Type = SurfaceAverageCalculation, otherwise this field may be left blank.

fields.name: Maximum Number of Iterations
fields.memo: Determines the maximum number of iterations used to converge on a solution. If this limit is exceeded, the program terminates.

fields.name: Relative Airflow Convergence Tolerance
fields.memo: This tolerance is defined as the absolute value of the sum of the mass Flow Rates divided by the sum of the absolute value of the mass Flow Rates. The mass Flow Rates described here refer to the mass Flow Rates at all Nodes in the AirflowNetwork model. The solution converges when both this tolerance and the tolerance in the next field (Absolute Airflow Convergence Tolerance) are satisfied.

fields.name: Absolute Airflow Convergence Tolerance
fields.memo: This tolerance is defined as the absolute value of the sum of the mass flow rates. The mass flow rates described here refer to the mass flow rates at all nodes in the AirflowNetwork model. The solution converges when both this tolerance and the tolerance in the previous field (Relative Airflow Convergence Tolerance) are satisfied.

fields.name: Convergence Acceleration Limit
fields.memo: Used only for AirflowNetwork:SimulationControl

fields.name: Azimuth Angle of Long Axis of Building
fields.memo: Degrees clockwise from true North. Used only if Wind Pressure Coefficient Type = SurfaceAverageCalculation.

fields.name: Ratio of Building Width Along Short Axis to Width Along Long Axis
fields.memo: Used only if Wind Pressure Coefficient Type = SurfaceAverageCalculation.

fields.name: Height Dependence of External Node Temperature
fields.memo: If Yes, external node temperature is height dependent. If No, external node temperature is based on zero height.

fields.name: Solver
fields.memo: Select the solver to use for the pressure network solution

thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.name: ThermostatSetpoint:ThermalComfort:Fanger:SingleCooling
thermostatsetpoint:thermalcomfort:fanger.memo: Used for cooling only thermal comfort control. The PMV setpoint can be scheduled and varied throughout the simulation but only cooling is allowed with this control type.

fields.name: Fanger Thermal Comfort Schedule Name
fields.memo: Schedule values should be Predicted Mean Vote (PMV)

output:environmentalimpactfactors.name: Output:EnvironmentalImpactFactors
output:environmentalimpactfactors.memo: This is used to Automatically report the facility meters and turn on the Environmental Impact Report calculations for all of the Environmental Factors.

fields.name: Reporting Frequency
fields.memo: Timestep refers to the zone Timestep/Number of Timesteps in hour value RunPeriod and Environment are the same. Detailed is not a valid choice.

coil:waterheating:airtowaterheatpump:pum.name: Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:Pumped
coil:waterheating:airtowaterheatpump:pum.memo: Heat pump water heater (HPWH) heating coil, air-to-water direct-expansion (DX) system which includes a water heating coil, evaporator air coil, evaporator fan, electric compressor, and water pump. Part of a WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser system.

fields.name: Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump heat.

fields.name: Rated COP
fields.memo: Heating coefficient of performance at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Can optionally include condenser pump power and evaporator fan power (see fields below).

fields.name: Rated Sensible Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Gross air-side sensible heat ratio at the rated inlet air temperatures, rated condenser inlet water temperature, rated air flow rate, and rated water flow rate. Sensible heat ratio equals gross sensible cooling capacity divided by gross total cooling capacity. Rated SHR (gross) should not include evaporator fan heat, only sensible cooling and dehumidification by the coil alone.

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Inlet Air Dry-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Evaporator inlet air dry-bulb temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Evaporator inlet air wet-bulb temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Condenser Inlet Water Temperature
fields.memo: Condenser inlet water temperature corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR).

fields.name: Rated Evaporator Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Evaporator air flow rate corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR). Default is 5.035E-5 m3/s/W (31.25 cfm/MBH) of rated heating capacity when autocalculated.

fields.name: Rated Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Condenser water flow rate corresponding to rated coil performance (heating capacity, COP and SHR). Default is 4.487E-8 m3/s/W (0.208 gpm/MBH) of rated heating capacity when autocalculated. A warning message will be issued if the ratio of Rated Condenser Water Flow Rate to Heating Capacity is less than 1.79405E-8 m3/s/W (0.083 gpm/MBH) or greater than 8.97024E-8 m3/s/W (0.417 gpm/MBH), but the simulation will continue.

fields.name: Evaporator Fan Power Included in Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the evaporator fan power is included in the rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of compressor electric power.

fields.name: Condenser Pump Power Included in Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the condenser pump power is included in the rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of compressor electric power.

fields.name: Condenser Pump Heat Included in Rated Heating Capacity and Rated COP
fields.memo: Select Yes if the condenser pump heat is included in the rated heating capacity and rated COP. This choice field impacts the calculation of water heating capacity.

fields.name: Condenser Water Pump Power
fields.memo: A warning message will be issued if the ratio of Condenser Water Pump Power to Rated Heating Capacity exceeds 0.1422 W/W (41.67 Watts/MBH), but the simulation will continue.

fields.name: Fraction of Condenser Pump Heat to Water
fields.memo: Fraction of pump heat transferred to the condenser water. The pump is assumed to be located downstream of the condenser.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node from which the DX coil draws its inlet air.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node to which the DX coil sends its outlet air.

fields.name: Condenser Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node from which the DX coil condenser draws its inlet water. This name should match the source side outlet node name in the associated water heater tank object.

fields.name: Condenser Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: The node to which the DX coil condenser sends its outlet water. This name should match the source side inlet node name in the associated water heater tank object.

fields.name: Crankcase Heater Capacity
fields.memo: The compressor crankcase heater only operates when the dry-bulb temperature of air surrounding the compressor is below the Maximum Ambient Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation and the DX coil is off.  The ambient temperature surrounding the compressor is set by the WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser parent object (field Compressor Location).

fields.name: Maximum Ambient Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation
fields.memo: The compressor crankcase heater only operates when the dry-bulb temperature of air surrounding the compressor is below the Maximum Outdoor Temperature for Crankcase Heater Operation and the unit is off. The ambient temperature surrounding the compressor is set by the WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser parent object (field Compressor Location).

fields.name: Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects
fields.memo: Determines temperature type for heating capacity curves and heating COP curves. This input determines whether the inlet air dry-bulb or wet-bulb temperature is used to evaluate these curves.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating capacity modifier curve (function of temperature) should be biquadratic or cubic. Biquadratic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(tw) + e(tw)^2 + f(ta)(tw). Cubic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(ta)^3. ta = evaporator inlet air [dry-bulb or wet-bulb] temperature (C). tw = condenser inlet water temperature (C). The field Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects determines if dry-bulb or wet-bulb is used as the evaporator inlet air temperature (ta).

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Air Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating capacity modifier curve (function of air flow fraction) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2 + d(ff)^3. ff = fraction of the rated evaporator air flow rate. Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in air flow rate fraction.

fields.name: Heating Capacity Function of Water Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating capacity modifier curve (function of water flow fraction) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2 + d(ff)^3. ff = fraction of the rated condenser water flow rate. Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in water flow rate fraction.

fields.name: Heating COP Function of Temperature Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating COP modifier curve (function of temperature) should be biquadratic or cubic. Biquadratic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(tw) + e(tw)^2 + f(ta)(tw). Cubic curve = a + b(ta) + c(ta)^2 + d(ta)^3. ta = evaporator inlet air [dry-bulb or wet-bulb] temperature (C). tw = condenser inlet water temperature (C). The field Evaporator Air Temperature Type for Curve Objects determines if dry-bulb or wet-bulb is used as the evaporator inlet air temperature (ta).

fields.name: Heating COP Function of Air Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating COP modifier curve (function of air flow fraction) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2 + d(ff)^3. ff = fraction of the rated evaporator air flow rate. Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in air flow rate fraction.

fields.name: Heating COP Function of Water Flow Fraction Curve Name
fields.memo: Heating COP modifier curve (function of water flow fraction) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(ff) + c(ff)^2 + d(ff)^3. ff = fraction of the rated condenser water flow rate. Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in water flow rate fraction.

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: Part Load Fraction Correlation (function of part load ratio) should be quadratic or cubic. Quadratic curve = a + b(PLR) + c(PLR)^2. Cubic curve = a + b(PLR) + c(PLR)^2 + d(PLR)^3. PLR = part load ratio (heating delivered/steady state heating capacity). Use curve coefficients of 1,0,0 or leave this field blank when neglecting performance impacts due to variations in part load ratio.

energymanagementsystem:subroutine.name: EnergyManagementSystem:Subroutine
energymanagementsystem:subroutine.memo: This input defines an Erl program subroutine Each field after the name is a line of EMS Runtime Language

coil:heating:fuel.name: Coil:Heating:Fuel
coil:heating:fuel.memo: Gas or other fuel heating coil. If the coil is located directly in an air loop branch or outdoor air equipment list, then it is controlled on leaving air temperature and the Temperature Setpoint Node Name must be specified. If the coil is contained within another component such as an air terminal unit, zone HVAC equipment, or unitary system, then the coil is controlled by the parent component and the setpoint node name is not entered.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Temperature Setpoint Node Name
fields.memo: optional, used if coil is temperature control and not load-base controlled

fields.name: Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: parasitic electric load associated with the coil operation such as an inducer fan, etc..  This will be modified by the part load ratio to reflect the time of operation in a timestep.

fields.name: Part Load Fraction Correlation Curve Name
fields.memo: quadratic curve, PLF = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 cubic curve, PLF = a + b*PLR + c*PLR**2 + d*PLR**3 PLF = part load fraction PLR = part load ratio (sensible heating load/steady state heating capacity) Coil runtime fraction = Part Load Ratio / PLF This part load degradation is for coil performance & will increase the fuel consumption of the coil due to transient coil operation.

fields.name: Parasitic Fuel Load
fields.memo: parasitic fuel load associated with the coil operation (i.e., standing pilot)

zonebaseboard:outdoortemperaturecontroll.name: ZoneBaseboard:OutdoorTemperatureControlled
zonebaseboard:outdoortemperaturecontroll.memo: Specifies outside temperature-controlled electric baseboard heating.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: units in Schedule should be fraction applied to capacity of the baseboard heat equipment, generally (0.0 - 1.0)

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

windowmaterial:simpleglazingsystem.name: WindowMaterial:SimpleGlazingSystem
windowmaterial:simpleglazingsystem.memo: Alternate method of describing windows This window material object is used to define an entire glazing system using simple performance parameters.

fields.name: U-Factor
fields.memo: Enter U-Factor including film coefficients Note that the effective upper limit for U-factor is 5.8 W/m2-K

fields.name: Solar Heat Gain Coefficient
fields.memo: SHGC at Normal Incidence

fields.name: Visible Transmittance
fields.memo: VT at Normal Incidence optional

curve:functional:pressuredrop.name: Curve:Functional:PressureDrop
curve:functional:pressuredrop.memo: Sets up curve information for minor loss and/or friction calculations in plant pressure simulations Expression: DeltaP = {K + f*(L/D)} * (rho * V^2) / 2

fields.name: Diameter
fields.memo: "D" in above expression, used to also calculate local velocity

fields.name: Minor Loss Coefficient
fields.memo: "K" in above expression

fields.name: Length
fields.memo: "L" in above expression

fields.name: Roughness
fields.memo: This will be used to calculate "f" from Moody-chart approximations

fields.name: Fixed Friction Factor
fields.memo: Optional way to set a constant value for "f", instead of using internal Moody-chart approximations

zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:electric.name: ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:Electric
zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:electric.memo: Electric resistance low temperature radiant system

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of zone system is serving

fields.name: Surface Name or Radiant Surface Group Name
fields.memo: Identifies surfaces that radiant system is embedded in. For a system with multiple surfaces, enter the name of a ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:SurfaceGroup object.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Method
fields.memo: Enter the method used to determine the maximum electrical heating design capacity. HeatingDesignCapacity = > selected when the design heating capacity value or autosize is specified. CapacityPerFloorArea = > selected when the design heating capacity is determine from user specified heating capacity per floor area and zone floor area. FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity = > is selected when the design heating capacity is determined from a user specified fraction and the auto-sized design heating capacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the design heating capacity.Required field when the heating design capacity method HeatingDesignCapacity.

fields.name: Heating Design Capacity Per Floor Area
fields.memo: Enter the heating design capacity per zone floor area.Required field when the heating design capacity method field is CapacityPerFloorArea.

fields.name: Fraction of Autosized Heating Design Capacity
fields.memo: Enter the fraction of auto - sized heating design capacity.Required field when capacity the heating design capacity method field is FractionOfAutosizedHeatingCapacity.

fields.name: Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: Temperature used to control unit

setpointmanager:followoutdoorairtemperat.name: SetpointManager:FollowOutdoorAirTemperature
setpointmanager:followoutdoorairtemperat.memo: This setpoint manager is used to place a temperature setpoint on a system node that is derived from the current outdoor air environmental conditions. The outdoor air conditions are obtained from the weather information during the simulation.

fields.name: Setpoint Node or NodeList Name
fields.memo: Node(s) at which control variable will be set

waterheater:heatpump:pumpedcondenser.name: WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser
waterheater:heatpump:pumpedcondenser.memo: This object models an air-source heat pump for water heating where the water is pumped out of the tank, through a heating coil and returned to the tank. For wrapped condenser HPWHs, see WaterHeater:HeatPump:WrappedCondenser. WaterHeater:HeatPump:PumpedCondenser is a compound object that references other component objects - Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:*, Fan:OnOff, WaterHeater:Mixed or WaterHeater:Stratified

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available. Schedule values of 0 denote the heat pump compressor is off and the parasitic electric energy is also off.

fields.name: Compressor Setpoint Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defines the cut-out temperature where the heat pump compressor turns off. The heat pump compressor setpoint temperature should always be greater than the water tank's heater (element or burner) setpoint temperature.

fields.name: Dead Band Temperature Difference
fields.memo: Setpoint temperature minus the dead band temperature difference defines the cut-in temperature where the heat pump compressor turns on. The water tank's heater (element or burner) setpoint temperature should always be less than the heat pump compressor cut-in temperature.

fields.name: Condenser Water Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Should match the field Source Outlet Node Name in the water heater tank object. Should also match the Condenser Water Inlet Node Name in the associated DX coil object.

fields.name: Condenser Water Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Should match the field Source Inlet Node Name in water heater tank object. Should also match the Condenser Water Outlet Node Name in the associated DX Coil object.

fields.name: Condenser Water Flow Rate
fields.memo: Actual water flow rate through the heat pump's water coil (condenser). If autocalculated, the water flow rate is set equal to 4.487E-8 m3/s/W times the rated heating capacity of the heat pump's DX coil.

fields.name: Evaporator Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: Actual air flow rate across the heat pump's air coil (evaporator). If autocalculated, the air flow rate is set equal to 5.035E-5 m3/s/W times the rated heating capacity of the heat pump's DX coil.

fields.name: Inlet Air Configuration
fields.memo: Defines the configuration of the airflow path through the air coil and fan section.

fields.name: Air Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Zone air exhaust node name if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. Simply a unique Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule. Otherwise, leave field blank.

fields.name: Air Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Zone Air Inlet Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. Simply a unique Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule. Otherwise, leave field blank.

fields.name: Outdoor Air Node Name
fields.memo: Outdoor air node name if inlet air configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir or OutdoorAirOnly, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Exhaust Air Node Name
fields.memo: Simply a unique Node Name if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir or OutdoorAirOnly, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Inlet Air Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule, otherwise leave blank. Schedule values should be degrees C.

fields.name: Inlet Air Humidity Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Inlet Air Configuration is Schedule, otherwise leave blank. Schedule values are entered as a fraction (e.g. 0.5 is equal to 50%RH)

fields.name: Inlet Air Zone Name
fields.memo: Used only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. Otherwise, leave field blank.

fields.name: Tank Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of water heater tank used by this heat pump water heater.

fields.name: Tank Name
fields.memo: Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Water Heater object.

fields.name: Tank Use Side Inlet Node Name
fields.memo: Used only when the heat pump water heater is connected to a plant loop, otherwise leave blank. Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Water Heater object when connected to a plant loop.

fields.name: Tank Use Side Outlet Node Name
fields.memo: Used only when the heat pump water heater is connected to a plant loop, otherwise leave blank. Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Water Heater object when connected to a plant loop.

fields.name: DX Coil Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of DX coil used by this heat pump water heater. The only valid choice is Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:Pumped and Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:VariableSpeed, and CoilSystem:IntegratedHeatPump:AirSource

fields.name: DX Coil Name
fields.memo: Must match the name used in the corresponding Coil:WaterHeating:AirToWaterHeatPump:* object, or CoilSystem:IntegratedHeatPump:AirSource

fields.name: Minimum Inlet Air Temperature for Compressor Operation
fields.memo: Heat pump compressor will not operate when the inlet air dry-bulb temperature is below this value.

fields.name: Maximum Inlet Air Temperature for Compressor Operation
fields.memo: Heat pump compressor will not operate when the inlet air dry-bulb temperature is above this value.

fields.name: Compressor Location
fields.memo: If Zone is selected, Inlet Air Configuration must be ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir. If Schedule is selected, then you must provide a Compressor Ambient Temperature Schedule Name below.

fields.name: Compressor Ambient Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Used only if Compressor Location is Schedule, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Specify the type of fan used by this heat pump water heater. The only valid choices are Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff.

fields.name: Fan Name
fields.memo: Needs to match the name used in the corresponding Fan:SystemModel or Fan:OnOff object.

fields.name: Fan Placement
fields.memo: BlowThrough means the fan is located before the air coil (upstream). DrawThrough means the fan is located after the air coil (downstream).

fields.name: On Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power consumed when the heat pump compressor operates. Does not contribute to water heating but can impact the zone air heat balance.

fields.name: Off Cycle Parasitic Electric Load
fields.memo: Parasitic electric power consumed when the heat pump compressor is off. Does not contribute to water heating but can impact the zone air heat balance. Off-cycle parasitic power is 0 when the availability schedule is 0.

fields.name: Parasitic Heat Rejection Location
fields.memo: This field determines if the parasitic electric load impacts the zone air heat balance. If Zone is selected, Inlet Air Configuration must be ZoneAirOnly or ZoneAndOutdoorAir.

fields.name: Inlet Air Mixer Node Name
fields.memo: Required only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Outlet Air Splitter Node Name
fields.memo: Required only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir, otherwise leave field blank.

fields.name: Inlet Air Mixer Schedule Name
fields.memo: Required only if Inlet Air Configuration is ZoneAndOutdoorAir, otherwise leave field blank. Schedule values define whether the heat pump draws its inlet air from the zone, outdoors or a combination of zone and outdoor air. A schedule value of 0 denotes inlet air is drawn only from the zone. A schedule value of 1 denotes inlet air is drawn only from outdoors. Schedule values between 0 and 1 denote a mixture of zone and outdoor air proportional to the schedule value (i.e. 0.4 = 40% outdoor air, 60% zone air).

fields.name: Tank Element Control Logic
fields.memo: MutuallyExclusive means that once the tank heating element is active the heat pump is shut down until setpoint is reached. Simultaneous (default) means that both the tank heating element and heat pump are used at the same time recover the tank temperature.

fields.name: Control Sensor 1 Height In Stratified Tank
fields.memo: Used to indicate height of control sensor for Tank Object Type = WaterHeater:Stratified If left blank, it will default to the height of Heater1

fields.name: Control Sensor 1 Weight
fields.memo: Weight to give Control Sensor 1 temperature The weight of Control Sensor 2 will be 1 - (wt. of control sensor 1)

fields.name: Control Sensor 2 Height In Stratified Tank
fields.memo: Used to indicate height of control sensor for Tank Object Type = WaterHeater:Stratified If left blank, it will default to the height of Heater2

curve:quartic.name: Curve:Quartic
curve:quartic.memo: Quartic (fourth order polynomial) curve with one independent variable. Input for a Quartic curve consists of the curve name, the five coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1 + C2*x + C3*x**2 + C4*x**3 + C5*x**4

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the minimum value calculated by this curve object

fields.name: Maximum Curve Output
fields.memo: Specify the maximum value calculated by this curve object

outputcontrol:sizing:style.name: OutputControl:Sizing:Style
outputcontrol:sizing:style.memo: Default style for the Sizing output files is comma -- this works well for importing into spreadsheet programs such as Excel(tm) but not so well for word processing programs -- there tab may be a better choice.  Fixed puts spaces between the "columns"

windowmaterial:gap:equivalentlayer.name: WindowMaterial:Gap:EquivalentLayer
windowmaterial:gap:equivalentlayer.memo: Gas material properties that are used in Windows Equivalent Layer References only WindowMaterial:Gas properties

fields.name: Gap Vent Type
fields.memo: Sealed means the gap is enclosed and gas tight, i.e., no venting to indoor or outdoor environment.  VentedIndoor means the gap is vented to indoor environment, and VentedOutdoor means the gap is vented to the outdoor environment. The gap types VentedIndoor and VentedOutdoor are used with gas type "Air" only.

fields.name: Conductivity Coefficient A
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Conductivity Coefficient B
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Conductivity Coefficient C
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Viscosity Coefficient A
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Viscosity Coefficient B
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Viscosity Coefficient C
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Specific Heat Coefficient A
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Specific Heat Coefficient B
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Specific Heat Coefficient C
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Molecular Weight
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

fields.name: Specific Heat Ratio
fields.memo: Used only if Gas Type = Custom

windowgap:deflectionstate.name: WindowGap:DeflectionState
windowgap:deflectionstate.memo: Used to enter data describing deflection state of the gap. It is referenced from WindowMaterial:Gap object only and it is used only when deflection model is set to MeasuredDeflection, otherwise it is ignored.

fields.name: Deflected Thickness
fields.memo: If left blank will be considered that gap has no deflection.

coolingtowerperformance:yorkcalc.name: CoolingTowerPerformance:YorkCalc
coolingtowerperformance:yorkcalc.memo: This object is used to define coefficients for the approach temperature correlation for a variable speed cooling tower when tower Model Type is specified as YorkCalcUserDefined in the object CoolingTower:VariableSpeed.

fields.name: Minimum Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum valid inlet air wet-bulb temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Inlet Air Wet-Bulb Temperature
fields.memo: Maximum valid inlet air wet-bulb temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Minimum Range Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum valid range temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Range Temperature
fields.memo: Maximum valid range temperature for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Minimum Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Minimum valid approach temperature for this correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Approach Temperature
fields.memo: Maximum valid approach temperature for this correlation.

fields.name: Minimum Water Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Minimum valid water flow rate ratio for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Water Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Maximum valid water flow rate ratio for this approach temperature correlation.

fields.name: Maximum Liquid to Gas Ratio
fields.memo: Maximum liquid (water) to gas (air) ratio for this approach temperature correlation.

groundheattransfer:slab:autogrid.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Slab:AutoGrid
groundheattransfer:slab:autogrid.memo: AutoGrid only necessary when EquivalentSlab option not chosen. Not normally needed by EnergyPlus users. This object permits user selection of rectangular slab dimensions. NO SLAB DIMENSIONS LESS THAN 6 m.

fields.name: SLABX: X dimension of the building slab
fields.memo: typical values= 6 to 60.0

fields.name: SLABY: Y dimension of the building slab
fields.memo: typical values= 6 to 60.0

fields.name: SLABDEPTH: Thickness of slab on grade
CLEARANCE: Distance from edge of slab to domain edge
ZCLEARANCE: Distance from bottom of slab to domain bottom

door.name: Door
door.memo: Allows for simplified entry of opaque Doors.

fields.name: Construction Name
fields.memo: To be matched with a construction in this input file

fields.name: Building Surface Name
fields.memo: Name of Surface (Wall, usually) the Door is on (i.e., Base Surface) Door assumes the azimuth and tilt angles of the surface it is on.

fields.name: Multiplier
fields.memo: Used only for Surface Type = WINDOW, GLASSDOOR or DOOR Non-integer values will be truncated to integer

fields.name: Starting X Coordinate
fields.memo: Door starting coordinate is specified relative to the Base Surface origin.

fields.name: Starting Z Coordinate
fields.memo: How far up the wall the Door starts. (in 2-d, this would be a Y Coordinate)

zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:constantf.name: ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:ConstantFlow
zonehvac:lowtemperatureradiant:constantf.memo: Low temperature hydronic radiant heating and/or cooling system embedded in a building surface (wall, ceiling, or floor). Controlled by varying the hot or chilled water temperature circulating through the unit.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Zone Name
fields.memo: Name of zone system is serving

fields.name: Surface Name or Radiant Surface Group Name
fields.memo: Identifies surfaces that radiant system is embedded in. For a system with multiple surfaces, enter the name of a ZoneHVAC:LowTemperatureRadiant:SurfaceGroup object.

fields.name: Hydronic Tubing Length
fields.memo: Total length of pipe embedded in surface

fields.name: Temperature Control Type
fields.memo: Temperature used to control system

fields.name: Pump Flow Rate Schedule Name
fields.memo: Modifies the Rated Flow Rate of the pump on a time basis the default is that the pump is ON and runs according to its other operational requirements specified above.  The schedule is for special pump operations. Values here are between 0 and 1 and are multipliers on the previous field (Rated Flow Rate).

fields.name: Rated Pump Head
fields.memo: default head is 60 feet

fields.name: Fraction of Motor Inefficiencies to Fluid Stream
Heating High Water Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Water and control temperatures for heating work together to provide a linear function that determines the water temperature sent to the radiant system.  The current control temperature (see Temperature Control Type above) is compared to the high and low control temperatures at the current time. If the control temperature is above the high temperature, then the inlet water temperature is set to the low water temperature.  If the control temperature is below the low temperature, then the inlet water temperature is set to the high water temperature.  If the control temperature is between the high and low value, then the inlet water temperature is linearly interpolated between the low and high water temperature values.

fields.name: Heating Low Water Temperature Schedule Name
Heating High Control Temperature Schedule Name
Heating Low Control Temperature Schedule Name
Cooling High Water Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: See note for Heating High Water Temperature Schedule above for interpretation information (or see the Input/Output Reference).

fields.name: Cooling Low Water Temperature Schedule Name
Cooling High Control Temperature Schedule Name
Cooling Low Control Temperature Schedule Name

zonecontaminantsourceandsink:carbondioxi.name: ZoneContaminantSourceAndSink:CarbonDioxide
zonecontaminantsourceandsink:carbondioxi.memo: Represents internal CO2 gains and sinks in the zone.

fields.name: Design Generation Rate
fields.memo: Positive values represent sources and negative values represent sinks.

fields.name: Schedule Name
fields.memo: Value in this schedule should be a fraction (generally 0.0 - 1.0) applied to the Design Generation Rate

wateruse:equipment.name: WaterUse:Equipment
wateruse:equipment.memo: A generalized object for simulating all water end uses. Hot and cold water uses are included, as well as controlled mixing of hot and cold water at the tap. The WaterUse:Equipment object can be used stand-alone, or coupled into a plant loop using the WaterUse:Connections object (see below). The WaterUse:Connections object allows water uses to be linked to WaterUse:Storage objects to store and draw reclaimed water. The object can also simulate drainwater heat recovery.

fields.name: End-Use Subcategory
fields.memo: Any text may be used here to categorize the end-uses in the ABUPS End Uses by Subcategory table.

fields.name: Flow Rate Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to 1.0 at all times

fields.name: Target Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to hot water supply temperature

fields.name: Hot Water Supply Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to cold water supply temperature

fields.name: Cold Water Supply Temperature Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to water temperatures calculated by Site:WaterMainsTemperature object

fields.name: Sensible Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to 0.0 at all times

fields.name: Latent Fraction Schedule Name
fields.memo: Defaults to 0.0 at all times

meter:custom.name: Meter:Custom
meter:custom.memo: Used to allow users to combine specific variables and/or meters into "custom" meter configurations. To access these meters by name, one must first run a simulation to generate the RDD/MDD files and names. A Meter:Custom cannot reference another Meter:Custom.

airflownetwork:distribution:component:co.name: AirflowNetwork:Distribution:Component:ConstantPressureDrop
airflownetwork:distribution:component:co.memo: This object defines the characteristics of a constant pressure drop component (e.g. filter). Each node connected to this object can not be a node of mixer, splitter, a node of air primary loop, or zone equipment loop. It is recommended to connect to a duct component at both ends.

fields.name: Pressure Difference Across the Component
fields.memo: Enter the pressure drop across this component.

unitarysystemperformance:multispeed.name: UnitarySystemPerformance:Multispeed
unitarysystemperformance:multispeed.memo: The UnitarySystemPerformance object is used to specify the air flow ratio at each operating speed. This object is primarily used for multispeed DX and water coils to allow operation at alternate flow rates different from those specified in the coil object.

fields.name: Number of Speeds for Heating
fields.memo: Used only for Multi speed coils Enter the number of the following sets of data for air flow rates.

fields.name: Number of Speeds for Cooling
fields.memo: Used only for Multi speed coils Enter the number of the following sets of data for air flow rates.

fields.name: Single Mode Operation
fields.memo: Controls coil operation during each HVAC timestep. This choice does not apply to speed 1 operation. Yes = operate at the highest speed possible without exceeding the current load. No = allow operation at the average of two adjacent speeds to match the current load.

fields.name: No Load Supply Air Flow Rate Ratio
fields.memo: Used to define the no load operating air flow rate when the system fan is specified to operate continuously.

airloophvac:unitary:furnace:heatonly.name: AirLoopHVAC:Unitary:Furnace:HeatOnly
airloophvac:unitary:furnace:heatonly.memo: Unitary system, heating-only with constant volume supply fan (continuous or cycling) and heating coil (gas, electric, hot water, or steam). Identical to AirLoopHVAC:UnitaryHeatOnly.

fields.name: Availability Schedule Name
fields.memo: Availability schedule name for this system. Schedule value > 0 means the system is available. If this field is blank, the system is always available.

fields.name: Supply Air Fan Operating Mode Schedule Name
fields.memo: A fan operating mode schedule value of 0 indicates cycling fan mode (supply air fan cycles on and off in tandem with the heating coil). Any other schedule value indicates continuous fan mode (supply air fan operates continuously regardless of heating coil operation). Leaving this schedule name blank will default to cycling fan mode for the entire simulation period.

fields.name: Heating Supply Air Flow Rate
fields.memo: This value should be > 0 and <= than the fan air flow rate.

fields.name: Supply Fan Object Type
fields.memo: Fan:ConstantVolume only works with continuous fan operating mode (i.e. fan operating mode schedule values are greater than 0).

fields.name: Heating Coil Object Type
fields.memo: works with gas, electric, hot water and steam heating coils

roomair:temperaturepattern:nondimensiona.name: RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:NondimensionalHeight
roomair:temperaturepattern:nondimensiona.memo: Defines a distribution pattern for air temperatures relative to the current mean air temperature as a function of height. The height, referred to as Zeta, is nondimensional by normalizing with the zone ceiling height. Used in combination with RoomAir:TemperaturePattern:UserDefined.

fields.name: Control Integer for Pattern Control Schedule Name
fields.memo: this value should appear in as a schedule value

fields.name: Thermostat Offset
fields.memo: = (Temp at thermostat- Mean Air Temp)

fields.name: Return Air Offset
fields.memo: = (Temp leaving - Mean Air Temp ) deg C

fields.name: Exhaust Air Offset
fields.memo: = (Temp exhaust - Mean Air Temp) deg C the remaining fields have pairs that describe the relative temperature pattern in the vertical direction of a zone Zeta is the nondimensional height (in z-direction). on [0..1] DeltaTai =  (Tai - MAT) in units of deg. C relative deg C on [-10.0 .. 20.0 ]

groundheattransfer:basement:matlprops.name: GroundHeatTransfer:Basement:MatlProps
groundheattransfer:basement:matlprops.memo: Specifies the material properties for the Basement preprocessor ground heat transfer simulation. Only the Foundation Wall, Floor Slab, Soil, and Gravel properties are currently used.

fields.name: NMAT: Number of materials in this domain

coil:heating:watertoairheatpump:paramete.name: Coil:Heating:WaterToAirHeatPump:ParameterEstimation
coil:heating:watertoairheatpump:paramete.memo: Direct expansion (DX) heating coil for water-to-air heat pump (includes electric compressor), single-speed, parameter estimation model. Parameter estimation model is a deterministic model that requires a consistent set of parameters to describe the operating conditions of the heat pump components.

fields.name: Compressor Type
fields.memo: Parameters 1-4 are as named below. Parameters 5-9 depend on the type of compressor. Refer to the InputOutputReference on the parameters required

fields.name: Gross Rated Heating Capacity
fields.memo: Heating capacity not accounting for the effect of supply air fan heat

fields.name: Load Side Total Heat Transfer Coefficient
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 1

fields.name: Superheat Temperature at the Evaporator Outlet
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 2

fields.name: Compressor Power Losses
fields.memo: Accounts for the loss of work due to mechanical and electrical losses in the compressor. Previously called Parameter 3

fields.name: Compressor Efficiency
fields.memo: Previously called Parameter 4

fields.name: Compressor Piston Displacement
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Reciprocating or Rotary Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Scroll. Previously part of Parameter 5

fields.name: Compressor Suction/Discharge Pressure Drop
fields.memo: Used when Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Scroll. Previously part of Parameter 6

fields.name: Compressor Clearance Factor
fields.memo: Used when Compressor Type is Reciprocating. Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Scroll. Previously part of Parameter 7

fields.name: Refrigerant Volume Flow Rate
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Scroll Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating. Previously part of Parameter 5

fields.name: Volume Ratio
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Scroll. Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating. Previously part of Parameter 6

fields.name: Leak Rate Coefficient
fields.memo: Use when Compressor Type is Scroll. Leave this field blank for Compressor Type is Rotary or Reciprocating. Previously part of Parameter 7

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Coefficient
fields.memo: Use when Source Side Fluid Name is Water Leave this field blank when Source Side Fluid is an antifreeze Previously part of Parameter 8

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Resistance1
fields.memo: Use when Source Side Fluid Name is an antifreeze Leave this field blank for Source Side Fluid is Water Previously part of Parameter 8

fields.name: Source Side Heat Transfer Resistance2
fields.memo: Use when Source Side Fluid Name is an antifreeze Leave this field blank for Source Side Fluid is Water Previously part of Parameter 9

curve:doubleexponentialdecay.name: Curve:DoubleExponentialDecay
curve:doubleexponentialdecay.memo: Double exponential decay curve with one independent variable. Input consists of the curve name, the five coefficients, and the maximum and minimum valid independent variable values. Optional inputs for the curve minimum and maximum may be used to limit the output of the performance curve. curve = C1+C2*exp(C3*x)+C4*exp(C5*x)

fields.name: Minimum Curve Output

coil:cooling:watertoairheatpump:variable.name: Coil:Cooling:WaterToAirHeatPump:VariableSpeedEquationFit
coil:cooling:watertoairheatpump:variable.memo: Direct expansion (DX) cooling coil for water-to-air heat pump (includes electric compressor), variable-speed, equation-fit model. Optional inputs for moisture evaporation from wet coil when compressor cycles off with continuous fan operation. Equation-fit model uses normalized curves to describe the heat pump performance. Requires two to ten sets of performance data and will interpolate between speeds. Modeled as a single coil with variable-speed compressor.
